#!ctsdata
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.1#The man for wisdom's various arts renown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.2#Long exercised in woes, O Muse! resound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.3#Who, when his arms had wrought the destined fall
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.4#Of sacred Troy, and razed her heaven-built wall,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.5#Wandering from clime to clime, observant stray'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.6#Their manners noted, and their states survey'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.7#On stormy seas unnumber'd toils he bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.8#Safe with his friends to gain his natal shore:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.9#Vain toils! their impious folly dared to prey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.10#On herds devoted to the god of day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.11#The god vindictive doom'd them never more
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.12#(Ah, men unbless'd!) to touch that natal shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.13#Oh, snatch some portion of these acts from fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.1.14#Celestial Muse! and to our world relate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.1#Now at their native realms the Greeks arrived;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.2#All who the wars of ten long years survived;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.3#And 'scaped the perils of the gulfy main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.4#Ulysses, sole of all the victor train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.5#An exile from his dear paternal coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.6#Deplored his absent queen and empire lost.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.7#Calypso in her caves constrain'd his stay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.8#With sweet, reluctant, amorous delay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.9#In vain-for now the circling years disclose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.10#The day predestined to reward his woes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.11#At length his Ithaca is given by fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.12#Where yet new labours his arrival wait;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.13#At length their rage the hostile powers restrain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.14#All but the ruthless monarch of the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.15#But now the god, remote, a heavenly guest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.16#In AEthiopia graced the genial feast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.17#(A race divided, whom with sloping rays
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.18#The rising and descending sun surveys);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.19#There on the world's extremest verge revered
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.20#With hecatombs and prayer in pomp preferr'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.21#Distant he lay: while in the bright abodes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.22#Of high Olympus, Jove convened the gods:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.23#The assembly thus the sire supreme address'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.24#AEgysthus' fate revolving in his breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.25#Whom young Orestes to the dreary coast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.2.26#Of Pluto sent, a blood-polluted ghost.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.1#"Perverse mankind! whose wills, created free,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.2#Charge all their woes on absolute degree;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.3#All to the dooming gods their guilt translate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.4#And follies are miscall'd the crimes of fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.5#When to his lust AEgysthus gave the rein,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.6#Did fate, or we, the adulterous act constrain?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.7#Did fate, or we, when great Atrides died,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.8#Urge the bold traitor to the regicide?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.9#Hermes I sent, while yet his soul remain'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.10#Sincere from royal blood, and faith profaned;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.11#To warn the wretch, that young Orestes, grown
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.12#To manly years, should re-assert the throne.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.13#Yet, impotent of mind, and uncontroll'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.3.14#He plunged into the gulf which Heaven foretold."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.4.1#Here paused the god; and pensive thus replies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.4.2#Minerva, graceful with her azure eyes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.1#"O thou! from whom the whole creation springs,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.2#The source of power on earth derived to kings!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.3#His death was equal to the direful deed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.4#So may the man of blood be doomed to bleed!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.5#But grief and rage alternate wound my breast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.6#For brave Ulysses, still by fate oppress'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.7#Amidst an isle, around whose rocky shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.8#The forests murmur, and the surges roar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.9#The blameless hero from his wish'd-for home
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.10#A goddess guards in her enchanted dome;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.11#(Atlas her sire, to whose far-piercing eye
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.12#The wonders of the deep expanded lie;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.13#The eternal columns which on earth he rears
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.14#End in the starry vault, and prop the spheres).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.15#By his fair daughter is the chief confined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.16#Who soothes to dear delight his anxious mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.17#Successless all her soft caresses prove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.18#To banish from his breast his country's love;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.19#To see the smoke from his loved palace rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.20#While the dear isle in distant prospect lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.21#With what contentment could he close his eyes!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.22#And will Omnipotence neglect to save
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.23#The suffering virtue of the wise and brave?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.24#Must he, whose altars on the Phrygian shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.25#With frequent rites, and pure, avow'd thy power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.26#Be doom'd the worst of human ills to prove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.5.27#Unbless'd, abandon'd to the wrath of Jove?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.1#"Daughter! what words have pass'd thy lips unweigh'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.2#(Replied the Thunderer to the martial maid;)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.3#Deem not unjustly by my doom oppress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.4#Of human race the wisest and the best.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.5#Neptune, by prayer repentant rarely won,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.6#Afflicts the chief, to avenge his giant son,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.7#Whose visual orb Ulysses robb'd of light;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.8#Great Polypheme, of more than mortal might?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.9#Him young Thousa bore (the bright increase
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.10#Of Phorcys, dreaded in the sounds and seas);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.11#Whom Neptune eyed with bloom of beauty bless'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.12#And in his cave the yielding nymph compress'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.13#For this the god constrains the Greek to roam,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.14#A hopeless exile from his native home,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.15#From death alone exempt--but cease to mourn;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.16#Let all combine to achieve his wish'd return;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.17#Neptune atoned, his wrath shall now refrain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.6.18#Or thwart the synod of the gods in vain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.1#"Father and king adored!" Minerva cried,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.2#"Since all who in the Olympian bower reside
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.3#Now make the wandering Greek their public care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.4#Let Hermes to the Atlantic isle repair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.5#Bid him, arrived in bright Calypso's court,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.6#The sanction of the assembled powers report:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.7#That wise Ulysses to his native land
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.8#Must speed, obedient to their high command.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.9#Meantime Telemachus, the blooming heir
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.10#Of sea-girt Ithaca, demands my care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.11#'Tis mine to form his green, unpractised years
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.12#In sage debates; surrounded with his peers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.13#To save the state, and timely to restrain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.14#The bold intrusion of the suitor-train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.15#Who crowd his palace, and with lawless power
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.16#His herds and flocks in feastful rites devour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.17#To distant Sparta, and the spacious waste
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.18#Of Sandy Pyle, the royal youth shall haste.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.19#There, warm with filial love, the cause inquire
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.20#That from his realm retards his god-like sire;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.21#Delivering early to the voice of fame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.7.22#The promise of a green immortal name."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.1#She said: the sandals of celestial mould,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.2#Fledged with ambrosial plumes, and rich with gold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.3#Surround her feet: with these sublime she sails
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.4#The aerial space, and mounts the winged gales;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.5#O'er earth and ocean wide prepared to soar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.6#Her dreaded arm a beamy javelin bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.7#Ponderous and vast: which, when her fury burns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.8#Proud tyrants humbles, and whole hosts o'erturns.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.9#From high Olympus prone her flight she bends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.10#And in the realms of Ithaca descends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.11#Her lineaments divine, the grave disguise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.12#Of Mentes' form conceal'd from human eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.13#(Mentes, the monarch of the Taphian land);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.14#A glittering spear waved awful in her hand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.15#There in the portal placed, the heaven-born maid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.16#Enormous riot and misrule survey'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.17#On hides of beeves, before the palace gate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.18#(Sad spoils of luxury), the suitors sate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.19#With rival art, and ardour in their mien,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.20#At chess they vie, to captivate the queen;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.21#Divining of their loves.  Attending nigh,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.22#A menial train the flowing bowl supply.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.23#Others, apart, the spacious hall prepare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.24#And form the costly feast with busy care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.25#There young Telemachus, his bloomy face
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.26#Glowing celestial sweet, with godlike grace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.27#Amid the circle shines: but hope and fear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.28#(Painful vicissitude!) his bosom tear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.29#Now, imaged in his mind, he sees restored
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.30#In peace and joy the people's rightful lord;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.31#The proud oppressors fly the vengeful sword.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.32#While his fond soul these fancied triumphs swell'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.33#The stranger guest the royal youth beheld;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.34#Grieved that a visitant so long should wait
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.35#Unmark'd, unhonour'd, at a monarch's gate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.36#Instant he flew with hospitable haste,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.37#And the new friend with courteous air embraced.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.38#"Stranger, whoe'er thou art, securely rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.39#Affianced in my faith, a ready guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.40#Approach the dome, the social banquet share,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.8.41#And then the purpose of thy soul declare."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.1#Thus affable and mild, the prince precedes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.2#And to the dome the unknown celestial leads.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.3#The spear receiving from the hand, he placed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.4#Against a column, fair with sculpture graced;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.5#Where seemly ranged in peaceful order stood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.6#Ulysses' arms now long disused to blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.7#He led the goddess to the sovereign seat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.8#Her feet supported with a stool of state
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.9#(A purple carpet spread the pavement wide);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.10#Then drew his seat, familiar, to her side;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.11#Far from the suitor-train, a brutal crowd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.12#With insolence, and wine, elate and loud:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.13#Where the free guest, unnoted, might relate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.14#If haply conscious, of his father's fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.15#The golden ewer a maid obsequious brings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.16#Replenish'd from the cool, translucent springs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.17#With copious water the bright vase supplies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.18#A silver laver of capacious size;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.19#They wash. The tables in fair order spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.20#They heap the glittering canisters with bread:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.21#Viands of various kinds allure the taste,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.22#Of choicest sort and savour, rich repast!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.23#Delicious wines the attending herald brought;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.24#The gold gave lustre to the purple draught.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.25#Lured with the vapour of the fragrant feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.26#In rush'd the suitors with voracious haste;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.27#Marshall'd in order due, to each a sewer
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.28#Presents, to bathe his hands, a radiant ewer.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.29#Luxurious then they feast. Observant round
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.30#Gay stripling youths the brimming goblets crown'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.31#The rage of hunger quell'd, they all advance
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.32#And form to measured airs the mazy dance;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.33#To Phemius was consign'd the chorded lyre,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.34#Whose hand reluctant touch'd the warbling wire;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.35#Phemius, whose voice divine could sweetest sing
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.9.36#High strains responsive to the vocal string.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.10.1#Meanwhile, in whispers to his heavenly guest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.10.2#His indignation thus the prince express'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.1#"Indulge my rising grief, whilst these (my friend)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.2#With song and dance the pompous revel end.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.3#Light is the dance, and doubly sweet the lays,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.4#When for the dear delight another pays.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.5#His treasured stores those cormarants consume,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.6#Whose bones, defrauded of a regal tomb
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.7#And common turf, lie naked on the plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.8#Or doom'd to welter in the whelming main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.9#Should he return, that troop so blithe and bold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.10#With purple robes inwrought, and stiff with gold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.11#Precipitant in fear would wing their flight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.12#And curse their cumbrous pride's unwieldy weight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.13#But ah, I dream!-the appointed hour is fled.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.14#And hope, too long with vain delusion fed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.15#Deaf to the rumour of fallacious fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.16#Gives to the roll of death his glorious name!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.17#With venial freedom let me now demand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.18#Thy name, thy lineage, and paternal land;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.19#Sincere from whence began thy course, recite,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.20#And to what ship I owe the friendly freight?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.21#Now first to me this visit dost thou deign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.22#Or number'd in my father's social train?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.23#All who deserved his choice he made his own,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.11.24#And, curious much to know, he far was known."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.1#"My birth I boast (the blue-eyed virgin cries)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.2#From great Anchialus, renown'd and wise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.3#Mentes my name; I rule the Taphian race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.4#Whose bounds the deep circumfluent waves embrace;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.5#A duteous people, and industrious isle,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.6#To naval arts inured, and stormy toil.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.7#Freighted with iron from my native land,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.8#I steer my voyage to the Brutian strand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.9#To gain by commerce, for the labour'd mass,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.10#A just proportion of refulgent brass.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.11#Far from your capital my ship resides
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.12#At Reitorus, and secure at anchor rides;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.13#Where waving groves on airy Neign grow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.14#Supremely tall and shade the deeps below.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.15#Thence to revisit your imperial dome,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.16#An old hereditary guest I come;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.17#Your father's friend.  Laertes can relate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.18#Our faith unspotted, and its early date;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.19#Who, press'd with heart-corroding grief and years,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.20#To the gay court a rural shed pretors,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.21#Where, sole of all his train, a matron sage
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.22#Supports with homely fond his drooping age,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.23#With feeble steps from marshalling his vines
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.12.24#Returning sad, when toilsome day declines.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.1#"With friendly speed, induced by erring fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.2#To hail Ulysses' safe return I came;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.3#But still the frown of some celestial power
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.4#With envious joy retards the blissful hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.5#Let not your soul be sunk in sad despair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.6#He lives, he breathes this heavenly vital air,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.7#Among a savage race, whose shelfy bounds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.8#With ceaseless roar the foaming deep surrounds.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.9#The thoughts which roll within my ravish'd breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.10#To me, no seer, the inspiring gods suggest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.11#Nor skill'd nor studious, with prophetic eye
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.12#To judge the winged omens of the sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.13#Yet hear this certain speech, nor deem it vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.14#Though adamantine bonds the chief restrain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.15#The dire restraint his wisdom will defeat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.16#And soon restore him to his regal seat.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.17#But generous youth! sincere and free declare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.18#Are you, of manly growth, his royal heir?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.19#For sure Ulysses in your look appears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.20#The same his features, if the same his years.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.21#Such was that face, on which I dwelt with joy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.22#Ere Greece assembled stemm'd the tides to Troy;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.23#But, parting then for that detested shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.13.24#Our eyes, unhappy never greeted more."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.14.1#"To prove a genuine birth (the prince replies)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.14.2#On female truth assenting faith relies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.14.3#Thus manifest of right, I build my claim
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.14.4#Sure-founded on a fair maternal fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.14.5#Ulysses' son: but happier he, whom fate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.14.6#Hath placed beneath the storms which toss the great!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.14.7#Happier the son, whose hoary sire is bless'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.14.8#With humble affluence, and domestic rest!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.14.9#Happier than I, to future empire born,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.14.10#But doom'd a father's wretch'd fate to mourn!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.15.1#To whom, with aspect mild, the guest divine:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.15.2#"Oh true descendant of a sceptred line!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.15.3#The gods a glorious fate from anguish free
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.15.4#To chaste Penelope's increase decree.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.15.5#But say, yon jovial troops so gaily dress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.15.6#Is this a bridal or a friendly feast?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.15.7#Or from their deed I rightlier may divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.15.8#Unseemly flown with insolence and wine?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.15.9#Unwelcome revellers, whose lawless joy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.15.10#Pains the sage ear, and hurts the sober eye."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.1#"Magnificence of old (the prince replied)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.2#Beneath our roof with virtue could reside;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.3#Unblamed abundance crowned the royal board,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.4#What time this dome revered her prudent lord;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.5#Who now (so Heaven decrees) is doom'd to mourn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.6#Bitter constraint, erroneous and forlorn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.7#Better the chief, on Ilion's hostile plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.8#Had fall'n surrounded with his warlike train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.9#Or safe return'd, the race of glory pass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.10#New to his friends' embrace, and breathed his last!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.11#Then grateful Greece with streaming eyes would raise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.12#Historic marbles to record his praise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.13#His praise, eternal on the faithful stone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.14#Had with transmissive honour graced his son.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.15#Now snatch'd by harpies to the dreary coast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.16#Sunk is the hero, and his glory lost;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.17#Vanish'd at once! unheard of, and unknown!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.18#And I his heir in misery alone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.19#Nor for a dear lost father only flow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.20#The filial tears, but woe succeeds to woe
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.21#To tempt the spouseless queen with amorous wiles
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.22#Resort the nobles from the neighbouring isles;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.23#From Samos, circled with the Ionian main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.24#Dulichium, and Zacynthas' sylvan reign;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.25#Ev'n with presumptuous hope her bed to ascend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.26#The lords of Ithaca their right pretend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.27#She seems attentive to their pleaded vows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.28#Her heart detesting what her ear allows.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.29#They, vain expectants of the bridal hour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.30#My stores in riotous expense devour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.31#In feast and dance the mirthful months employ,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.16.32#And meditate my doom to crown their joy."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.1#With tender pity touch'd, the goddess cried:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.2#"Soon may kind Heaven a sure relief provide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.3#Soon may your sire discharge the vengeance due,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.4#And all your wrongs the proud oppressors rue!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.5#Oh! in that portal should the chief appear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.6#Each hand tremendous with a brazen spear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.7#In radiant panoply his limbs incased
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.8#(For so of old my fathers court he graced,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.9#When social mirth unbent his serious soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.10#O'er the full banquet, and the sprightly bowl);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.11#He then from Ephyre, the fair domain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.12#Of Ilus, sprung from Jason's royal strain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.13#Measured a length of seas, a toilsome length, in vain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.14#For, voyaging to learn the direful art
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.15#To taint with deadly drugs the barbed dart;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.16#Observant of the gods, and sternly just,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.17#Ilus refused to impart the baneful trust;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.18#With friendlier zeal my father's soul was fired,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.19#The drugs he knew, and gave the boon desired.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.20#Appear'd he now with such heroic port,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.21#As then conspicuous at the Taphian court;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.22#Soon should you boasters cease their haughty strife,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.23#Or each atone his guilty love with life.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.24#But of his wish'd return the care resign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.25#Be future vengeance to the powers divine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.26#My sentence hear: with stern distaste avow'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.27#To their own districts drive the suitor-crowd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.28#When next the morning warms the purple east,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.29#Convoke the peerage, and the gods attest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.30#The sorrows of your inmost soul relate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.31#And form sure plans to save the sinking state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.32#Should second love a pleasing flame inspire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.33#And the chaste queen connubial rights require;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.34#Dismiss'd with honour, let her hence repair
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.35#To great Icarius, whose paternal care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.36#Will guide her passion, and reward her choice
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.37#With wealthy dower, and bridal gifts of price.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.38#Then let this dictate of my love prevail:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.39#Instant, to foreign realms prepare to sail,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.40#To learn your father's fortunes; Fame may prove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.41#Or omen'd voice (the messenger of Jove),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.42#Propitious to the search. Direct your toil
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.43#Through the wide ocean first to sandy Pyle;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.44#Of Nestor, hoary sage, his doom demand:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.45#Thence speed your voyage to the Spartan strand;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.46#For young Atrides to the Achaian coast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.47#Arrived the last of all the victor host.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.48#If yet Ulysses views the light, forbear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.49#Till the fleet hours restore the circling year.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.50#But if his soul hath wing'd the destined flight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.51#Inhabitant of deep disastrous night;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.52#Homeward with pious speed repass the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.53#To the pale shade funereal rites ordain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.54#Plant the fair column o'er the vacant grave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.55#A hero's honours let the hero have.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.56#With decent grief the royal dead deplored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.57#For the chaste queen select an equal lord.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.58#Then let revenge your daring mind employ,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.59#By fraud or force the suitor train destroy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.60#And starting into manhood, scorn the boy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.61#Hast thou not heard how young Orestes, fired
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.62#With great revenge, immortal praise acquired?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.63#His virgin-sword AEgysthus' veins imbrued;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.64#The murderer fell, and blood atoned for blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.65#O greatly bless'd with every blooming grace!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.66#With equal steps the paths of glory trace;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.67#Join to that royal youth's your rival name,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.68#And shine eternal in the sphere of fame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.69#But my associates now my stay deplore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.70#Impatient on the hoarse-resounding shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.71#Thou, heedful of advice, secure proceed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.17.72#My praise the precept is, be thine the deed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.18.1#"The counsel of my friend (the youth rejoin'd)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.18.2#Imprints conviction on my grateful mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.18.3#So fathers speak (persuasive speech and mild)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.18.4#Their sage experience to the favourite child.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.18.5#But, since to part, for sweet refection due,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.18.6#The genial viands let my train renew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.18.7#And the rich pledge of plighted faith receive,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.18.8#Worthy the air of Ithaca to give."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.19.1#"Defer the promised boon (the goddess cries,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.19.2#Celestial azure brightening in her eyes),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.19.3#And let me now regain the Reithrian port;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.19.4#From Temese return'd, your royal court
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.19.5#I shall revisit, and that pledge receive;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.19.6#And gifts, memorial of our friendship, leave."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.1#Abrupt, with eagle-speed she cut the sky;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.2#Instant invisible to mortal eye.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.3#Then first he recognized the ethereal guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.4#Wonder and joy alternate fire his breast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.5#Heroic thoughts, infused, his heart dilate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.6#Revolving much his father's doubtful fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.7#At length, composed, he join'd the suitor-throng;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.8#Hush'd in attention to the warbled song.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.9#His tender theme the charming lyrist chose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.10#Minerva's anger, and the dreadful woes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.11#Which voyaging from Troy the victors bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.12#While storms vindictive intercept the store.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.13#The shrilling airs the vaulted roof rebounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.14#Reflecting to the queen the silver sounds.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.15#With grief renew'd the weeping fair descends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.16#Their sovereign's step a virgin train attends:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.17#A veil, of richest texture wrought, she wears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.18#And silent to the joyous hall repairs.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.19#There from the portal, with her mild command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.20.20#Thus gently checks the minstrel's tuneful hand:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.21.1#"Phemius! let acts of gods, and heroes old,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.21.2#What ancient bards in hall and bower have told,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.21.3#Attemper'd to the lyre, your voice employ;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.21.4#Such the pleased ear will drink with silent joy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.21.5#But, oh! forbear that dear disastrous name,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.21.6#To sorrow sacred, and secure of fame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.21.7#My bleeding bosom sickens at the sound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.21.8#And every piercing note inflicts a wound."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.1#"Why, dearest object of my duteous love,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.2#(Replied the prince,) will you the bard reprove?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.3#Oft, Jove's ethereal rays (resistless fire)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.4#The chanters soul and raptured song inspire
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.5#Instinct divine? nor blame severe his choice,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.6#Warbling the Grecian woes with heart and voice;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.7#For novel lays attract our ravish'd ears;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.8#But old, the mind with inattention hears:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.9#Patient permit the sadly pleasing strain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.10#Familiar now with grief, your tears refrain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.11#And in the public woe forget your own;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.12#You weep not for a perish'd lord alone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.13#What Greeks new wandering in the Stygian gloom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.14#Wish your Ulysses shared an equal doom!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.15#Your widow'd hours, apart, with female toil
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.16#And various labours of the loom beguile;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.17#There rule, from palace-cares remote and free;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.22.18#That care to man belongs, and most to me."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.23.1#Mature beyond his years, the queen admires
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.23.2#His sage reply, and with her train retires.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.23.3#Then swelling sorrows burst their former bounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.23.4#With echoing grief afresh the dome resounds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.23.5#Till Pallas, piteous of her plaintive cries,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.23.6#In slumber closed her silver-streaming eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.1#Meantime, rekindled at the royal charms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.2#Tumultuous love each beating bosom warms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.3#Intemperate rage a wordy war began;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.4#But bold Telemachus assumed the man.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.5#"Instant (he cried) your female discord end,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.6#Ye deedless boasters! and the song attend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.7#Obey that sweet compulsion, nor profane
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.8#With dissonance the smooth melodious strain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.9#Pacific now prolong the jovial feast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.10#But when the dawn reveals the rosy east,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.11#I, to the peers assembled, shall propose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.12#The firm resolve, I here in few disclose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.13#No longer live the cankers of my court;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.14#All to your several states with speed resort;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.15#Waste in wild riot what your land allows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.16#There ply the early feast, and late carouse.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.17#But if, to honour lost, 'tis still decreed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.18#For you my bowl shall flow, my flock shall bleed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.19#Judge and revenge my right, impartial Jove!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.20#By him and all the immortal thrones above
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.21#(A sacred oath), each proud oppressor slain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.24.22#Shall with inglorious gore this marble stain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.25.1#Awed by the prince, thus haughty, bold, and young,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.25.2#Rage gnaw'd the lip, and wonder chain'd the tongue.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.25.3#Silence at length the gay Antinous broke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.25.4#Constrain'd a smile, and thus ambiguous spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.25.5#"What god to your untutor'd youth affords
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.25.6#This headlong torrent of amazing words?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.25.7#May Jove delay thy reign, and cumber late
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.25.8#So bright a genius with the toils of state!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.1#"Those toils (Telemachus serene replies)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.2#Have charms, with all their weight, t'allure the wise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.3#Fast by the throne obsequious fame resides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.4#And wealth incessant rolls her golden tides.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.5#Nor let Antinous rage, if strong desire
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.6#Of wealth and fame a youthful bosom fire:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.7#Elect by Jove, his delegate of sway,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.8#With joyous pride the summons I'd obey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.9#Whene'er Ulysses roams the realm of night,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.10#Should factious power dispute my lineal right,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.11#Some other Greeks a fairer claim may plead;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.12#To your pretence their title would precede.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.13#At least, the sceptre lost, I still should reign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.26.14#Sole o'er my vassals, and domestic train."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.27.1#To this Eurymachus: "To Heaven alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.27.2#Refer the choice to fill the vacant throne.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.27.3#Your patrimonial stores in peace possess;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.27.4#Undoubted, all your filial claim confess:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.27.5#Your private right should impious power invade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.27.6#The peers of Ithaca would arm in aid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.27.7#But say, that stranger guest who late withdrew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.27.8#What and from whence? his name and lineage shew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.27.9#His grave demeanour and majestic grace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.27.10#Speak him descended of no vulgar race:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.27.11#Did he some loan of ancient right require,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.27.12#Or came forerunner of your sceptr'd sire?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.28.1#"Oh son of Polybus!" the prince replies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.28.2#"No more my sire will glad these longing eyes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.28.3#The queen's fond hope inventive rumour cheers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.28.4#Or vain diviners' dreams divert her fears.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.28.5#That stranger-guest the Taphian realm obeys,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.28.6#A realm defended with encircling seas.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.28.7#Mentes, an ever-honour'd name, of old
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.28.8#High in Ulysses' social list enroll'd."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.1#Thus he, though conscious of the ethereal guest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.2#Answer'd evasive of the sly request.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.3#Meantime the lyre rejoins the sprightly lay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.4#Love-dittied airs, and dance, conclude the day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.5#But when the star of eve with golden light
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.6#Adorn'd the matron brow of sable night,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.7#The mirthful train dispersing quit the court,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.8#And to their several domes to rest resort.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.9#A towering structure to the palace join'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.10#To this his steps the thoughtful prince inclined:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.11#In his pavilion there, to sleep repairs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.12#The lighted torch, the sage Euryclea bears
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.13#(Daughter of Ops, the just Pisenor's son,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.14#For twenty beeves by great Laertes won;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.15#In rosy prime with charms attractive graced,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.16#Honour'd by him, a gentle lord and chaste,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.17#With dear esteem: too wise, with jealous strife
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.18#To taint the joys of sweet connubial life.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.19#Sole with Telemachus her service ends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.20#A child she nursed him, and a man attends).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.21#Whilst to his couch himself the prince address'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.22#The duteous dame received the purple vest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.23#The purple vest with decent care disposed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.24#The silver ring she pull'd, the door reclosed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.25#The bolt, obedient to the silken cord,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.26#To the strong staple's inmost depth restored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.27#Secured the valves. There, wrapped in silent shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.28#Pensive, the rules the goddess gave he weigh'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.29#Stretch'd on the downy fleece, no rest he knows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:1.29.30#And in his raptured soul the vision glows.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.1#Now reddening from the dawn, the morning ray
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.2#Glow'd in the front of heaven, and gave the day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.3#The youthful hero, with returning light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.4#Rose anxious from the inquietudes of night.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.5#A royal robe he wore with graceful pride,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.6#A two-edged falchion threaten'd by his side,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.7#Embroider'd sandals glitter'd as he trod,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.8#And forth he moved, majestic as a god.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.9#Then by his heralds, restless of delay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.10#To council calls the peers: the peers obey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.11#Soon as in solemn form the assembly sate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.12#From his high dome himself descends in state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.13#Bright in his hand a ponderous javelin shined;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.14#Two dogs, a faithful guard, attend behind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.15#Pallas with grace divine his form improves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.1.16#And gazing crowds admire him as he moves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.2.1#His father's throne he fill'd; while distant stood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.2.2#The hoary peers, and aged wisdom bow'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.1#'Twas silence all.  At last AEgyptius spoke;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.2#AEgyptius, by his age and sorrow broke;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.3#A length of days his soul with prudence crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.4#A length of days had bent him to the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.5#His eldest hope in arms to Ilion came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.6#By great Ulysses taught the path to fame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.7#But (hapless youth) the hideous Cyclops tore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.8#His quivering limbs, and quaff'd his spouting gore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.9#Three sons remain'd; to climb with haughty fires
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.10#The royal bed, Eurynomus aspires;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.11#The rest with duteous love his griefs assuage,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.12#And ease the sire of half the cares of age.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.13#Yet still his Antiphus he loves, he mourns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.3.14#And, as he stood, he spoke and wept by turns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.4.1#"Since great Ulysses sought the Phrygian plains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.4.2#Within these walls inglorious silence reigns.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.4.3#Say then, ye peers! by whose commands we meet?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.4.4#Why here once more in solemn council sit?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.4.5#Ye young, ye old, the weighty cause disclose:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.4.6#Arrives some message of invading foes?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.4.7#Or say, does high necessity of state
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.4.8#Inspire some patriot, and demand debate?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.4.9#The present synod speaks its author wise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.4.10#Assist him, Jove, thou regent of the skies!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.5.1#He spoke. Telemachus with transport glows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.5.2#Embraced the omen, and majestic rose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.5.3#(His royal hand the imperial sceptre sway'd);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.5.4#Then thus, addressing to AEgyptius, said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.1#"Reverend old man! lo here confess'd he stands
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.2#By whom ye meet; my grief your care demands.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.3#No story I unfold of public woes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.4#Nor bear advices of impending foes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.5#Peace the blest land, and joys incessant crown:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.6#Of all this happy realm, I grieve alone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.7#For my lost sire continual sorrows spring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.8#The great, the good; your father and your king.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.9#Yet more; our house from its foundation bows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.10#Our foes are powerful, and your sons the foes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.11#Hither, unwelcome to the queen, they come;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.12#Why seek they not the rich Icarian dome?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.13#If she must wed, from other hands require
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.14#The dowry: is Telemachus her sire?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.15#Yet through my court the noise of revel rings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.16#And waste the wise frugality of kings.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.17#Scarce all my herds their luxury suffice;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.18#Scarce all my wine their midnight hours supplies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.19#Safe in my youth, in riot still they grow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.20#Nor in the helpless orphan dread a foe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.21#But come it will, the time when manhood grants
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.22#More powerful advocates than vain complaints.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.23#Approach that hour! insufferable wrong
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.24#Cries to the gods, and vengeance sleeps too long.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.25#Rise then, ye peers! with virtuous anger rise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.26#Your fame revere, but most the avenging skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.27#By all the deathless powers that reign above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.28#By righteous Themis and by thundering Jove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.29#(Themis, who gives to councils, or denies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.30#Success; and humbles, or confirms the wise),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.31#Rise in my aid! suffice the tears that flow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.32#For my lost sire, nor add new woe to woe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.33#If e'er he bore the sword to strengthen ill,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.34#Or, having power to wrong, betray'd the will,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.35#On me, on me your kindled wrath assuage,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.36#And bid the voice of lawless riot rage.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.37#If ruin to your royal race ye doom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.38#Be you the spoilers, and our wealth consume.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.39#Then might we hope redress from juster laws,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.40#And raise all Ithaca to aid our cause:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.41#But while your sons commit the unpunish'd wrong,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.6.42#You make the arm of violence too strong."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.7.1#While thus he spoke, with rage and grief he frown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.7.2#And dash'd the imperial sceptre to the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.7.3#The big round tear hung trembling in his eye:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.7.4#The synod grieved, and gave a pitying sigh,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.7.5#Then silent sate--at length Antinous burns
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.7.6#With haughty rage, and sternly thus returns:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.8.1#"O insolence of youth! whose tongue affords
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.8.2#Such railing eloquence, and war of words.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.8.3#Studious thy country's worthies to defame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.8.4#Thy erring voice displays thy mother's shame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.8.5#Elusive of the bridal day, she gives
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.8.6#Fond hopes to all, and all with hopes deceives.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.8.7#Did not the sun, through heaven's wide azure roll'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.8.8#For three long years the royal fraud behold?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.8.9#While she, laborious in delusion, spread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.8.10#The spacious loom, and mix'd the various thread:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.8.11#Where as to life the wondrous figures rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.8.12#Thus spoke the inventive queen, with artful sighs:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.9.1#"Though cold in death Ulysses breathes no more,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.9.2#Cease yet awhile to urge the bridal hour:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.9.3#Cease, till to great Laertes I bequeath
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.9.4#A task of grief, his ornaments of death.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.9.5#Lest when the Fates his royal ashes claim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.9.6#The Grecian matrons taint my spotless fame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.9.7#When he, whom living mighty realms obey'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.9.8#Shall want in death a shroud to grace his shade.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.10.1#"Thus she: at once the generous train complies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.10.2#Nor fraud mistrusts in virtue's fair disguise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.10.3#The work she plied; but, studious of delay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.10.4#By night reversed the labours of the day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.10.5#While thrice the sun his annual journey made,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.10.6#The conscious lamp the midnight fraud survey'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.10.7#Unheard, unseen, three years her arts prevail;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.10.8#The fourth her maid unfolds the amazing tale.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.10.9#We saw, as unperceived we took our stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.10.10#The backward labours of her faithless hand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.10.11#Then urged, she perfects her illustrious toils;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.10.12#A wondrous monument of female wiles!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.1#"But you, O peers! and thou, O prince! give ear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.2#(I speak aloud, that every Greek may hear):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.3#Dismiss the queen; and if her sire approves
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.4#Let him espouse her to the peer she loves:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.5#Bid instant to prepare the bridal train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.6#Nor let a race of princes wait in vain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.7#Though with a grace divine her soul is blest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.8#And all Minerva breathes within her breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.9#In wondrous arts than woman more renown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.10#And more than woman with deep wisdom crown'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.11#Though Tyro nor Mycene match her name,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.12#Not great Alemena (the proud boasts of fame);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.13#Yet thus by heaven adorn'd, by heaven's decree
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.14#She shines with fatal excellence, to thee:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.15#With thee, the bowl we drain, indulge the feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.16#Till righteous heaven reclaim her stubborn breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.17#What though from pole to pole resounds her name!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.18#The son's destruction waits the mother's fame:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.19#For, till she leaves thy court, it is decreed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.11.20#Thy bowl to empty and thy flock to bleed."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.1#While yet he speaks, Telemachus replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.2#"Ev'n nature starts, and what ye ask denies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.3#Thus, shall I thus repay a mother's cares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.4#Who gave me life, and nursed my infant years!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.5#While sad on foreign shores Ulysses treads.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.6#Or glides a ghost with unapparent shades;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.7#How to Icarius in the bridal hour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.8#Shall I, by waste undone, refund the dower?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.9#How from my father should I vengeance dread!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.10#How would my mother curse my hated head!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.11#And while In wrath to vengeful fiends she cries,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.12#How from their hell would vengeful fiends arise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.13#Abhorr'd by all, accursed my name would grow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.14#The earth's disgrace, and human-kind my foe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.15#If this displease, why urge ye here your stay?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.16#Haste from the court, ye spoilers, haste away:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.17#Waste in wild riot what your land allows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.18#There ply the early feast, and late carouse.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.19#But if to honour lost, 'tis still decreed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.20#For you my bowl shall flow, my flocks shall bleed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.21#Judge, and assert my right, impartial Jove!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.22#By him, and all the immortal host above
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.23#(A sacred oath), if heaven the power supply,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.12.24#Vengeance I vow, and for your wrongs ye die."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.13.1#With that, two eagles from a mountain's height
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.13.2#By Jove's command direct their rapid flight;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.13.3#Swift they descend, with wing to wing conjoin'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.13.4#Stretch their broad plumes, and float upon the wind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.13.5#Above the assembled peers they wheel on high,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.13.6#And clang their wings, and hovering beat the sky;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.13.7#With ardent eyes the rival train they threat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.13.8#And shrieking loud denounce approaching fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.13.9#They cuff, they tear; their cheeks and neck they rend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.13.10#And from their plumes huge drops of blood descend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.13.11#Then sailing o'er the domes and towers, they fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.13.12#Full toward the east, and mount into the sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.14.1#The wondering rivals gaze, with cares oppress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.14.2#And chilling horrors freeze in every breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.14.3#Till big with knowledge of approaching woes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.14.4#The prince of augurs, Halitherses, rose:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.14.5#Prescient he view'd the aerial tracks, and drew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.14.6#A sure presage from every wing that flew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.15.1#"Ye sons (he cried) of Ithaca, give ear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.15.2#Hear all! but chiefly you, O rivals! hear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.15.3#Destruction sure o'er all your heads impends
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.15.4#Ulysses comes, and death his steps attends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.15.5#Nor to the great alone is death decreed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.15.6#We and our guilty Ithaca must bleed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.15.7#Why cease we then the wrath of heaven to stay?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.15.8#Be humbled all, and lead, ye great! the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.15.9#For lo my words no fancied woes relate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.15.10#I speak from science and the voice of fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.16.1#"When great Ulysses sought the Phrygian shores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.16.2#To shake with war proud Ilion's lofty towers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.16.3#Deeds then undone my faithful tongue foretold:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.16.4#Heaven seal'd my words, and you those deeds behold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.16.5#I see (I cried) his woes, a countless train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.16.6#I see his friends o'erwhelm'd beneath the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.16.7#How twice ten years from shore to shore he roams:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.16.8#Now twice ten years are past, and now he comes!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.1#To whom Eurymachus--"Fly, dotard fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.2#With thy wise dreams, and fables of the sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.3#Go prophesy at home, thy sons advise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.4#Here thou art sage in vain--I better read the skies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.5#Unnumber'd birds glide through the aerial way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.6#Vagrants of air, and unforeboding stray.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.7#Cold in the tomb, or in the deeps below,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.8#Ulysses lies; oh wert thou laid as low!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.9#Then would that busy head no broils suggest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.10#For fire to rage Telemachus' breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.11#From him some bribe thy venal tongue requires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.12#And interest, not the god, thy voice inspires.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.13#His guideless youth, if thy experienced age
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.14#Mislead fallacious into idle rage,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.15#Vengeance deserved thy malice shall repress.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.16#And but augment the wrongs thou would'st redress,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.17#Telemachus may bid the queen repair
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.18#To great Icarius, whose paternal care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.19#Will guide her passion, and reward her choice
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.20#With wealthy dower, and bridal gifts of price.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.21#Till she retires, determined we remain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.22#And both the prince and augur threat in vain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.23#His pride of words, and thy wild dream of fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.24#Move not the brave, or only move their hate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.25#Threat on, O prince! elude the bridal day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.26#Threat on, till all thy stores in waste decay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.27#True, Greece affords a train of lovely dames,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.28#In wealth and beauty worthy of our flames:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.29#But never from this nobler suit we cease;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.17.30#For wealth and beauty less than virtue please."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.1#To whom the youth: "Since then in vain I tell
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.2#My numerous woes, in silence let them dwell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.3#But Heaven, and all the Greeks, have heard my wrongs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.4#To Heaven, and all the Greeks, redress belongs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.5#Yet this I ask (nor be it ask'd in vain),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.6#A bark to waft me o'er the rolling main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.7#The realms of Pyle and Sparta to explore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.8#And seek my royal sire from shore to shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.9#If, or to fame his doubtful fate be known,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.10#Or to be learn'd from oracles alone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.11#If yet he lives, with patience I forbear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.12#Till the fleet hours restore the circling year;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.13#But if already wandering in the train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.14#Of empty shades, I measure back the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.15#Plant the fair column o'er the mighty dead,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.18.16#And yield his consort to the nuptial bed."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.19.1#He ceased; and while abash'd the peers attend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.19.2#Mentor arose, Ulysses' faithful friend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.19.3#(When fierce in arms he sought the scenes of war,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.19.4#"My friend (he cried), my palace be thy care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.19.5#Years roll'd on years my godlike sire decay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.19.6#Guard thou his age, and his behests obey.")
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.19.7#Stern as he rose, he cast his eyes around,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.19.8#That flash'd with rage; and as spoke, he frown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.1#"O never, never more let king be just,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.2#Be mild in power, or faithful to his trust!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.3#Let tyrants govern with an iron rod,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.4#Oppress, destroy, and be the scourge of God;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.5#Since he who like a father held his reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.6#So soon forgot, was just and mild in vain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.7#True, while my friend is grieved, his griefs I share;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.8#Yet now the rivals are my smallest care:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.9#They for the mighty mischiefs they devise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.10#Ere long shall pay--their forfeit lives the price.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.11#But against you, ye Greeks! ye coward train!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.12#Gods! how my soul is moved with just disdain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.13#Dumb ye all stand, and not one tongue affords
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.20.14#His injured prince the little aid of words."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.1#While yet he spoke, Leocritus rejoined:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.2#"O pride of words, and arrogance of mind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.3#Would'st thou to rise in arms the Greeks advise?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.4#Join all your powers? in arms, ye Greeks, arise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.5#Yet would your powers in vain our strength oppose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.6#The valiant few o'ermatch a host of foes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.7#Should great Ulysses stern appear in arms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.8#While the bowl circles and the banquet warms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.9#Though to his breast his spouse with transport flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.10#Torn from her breast, that hour, Ulysses dies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.11#But hence retreating to your domes repair.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.12#To arm the vessel, Mentor! be thy care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.13#And Halitherses! thine: be each his friend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.14#Ye loved the father: go, the son attend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.15#But yet, I trust, the boaster means to stay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.21.16#Safe in the court, nor tempt the watery way."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.22.1#Then, with a rushing sound the assembly bend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.22.2#Diverse their steps: the rival rout ascend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.22.3#The royal dome; while sad the prince explores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.22.4#The neighbouring main, and sorrowing treads the shores.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.22.5#There, as the waters o'er his hands he shed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.22.6#The royal suppliant to Minerva pray'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.23.1#"O goddess! who descending from the skies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.23.2#Vouchsafed thy presence to my wondering eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.23.3#By whose commands the raging deeps I trace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.23.4#And seek my sire through storms and rolling seas!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.23.5#Hear from thy heavens above, O warrior maid!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.23.6#Descend once more, propitious to my aid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.23.7#Without thy presence, vain is thy command:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.23.8#Greece, and the rival train, thy voice withstand."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.24.1#Indulgent to his prayer, the goddess took
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.24.2#Sage Mentor's form, and thus like Mentor spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.1#"O prince, in early youth divinely wise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.2#Born, the Ulysses of thy age to rise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.3#If to the son the father's worth descends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.4#O'er the wide wave success thy ways attends
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.5#To tread the walks of death he stood prepared;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.6#And what he greatly thought, he nobly dared.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.7#Were not wise sons descendant of the wise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.8#And did not heroes from brave heroes rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.9#Vain were my hopes: few sons attain the praise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.10#Of their great sires, and most their sires disgrace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.11#But since thy veins paternal virtue fires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.12#And all Penelope thy soul inspires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.13#Go, and succeed: the rivals' aims despise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.14#For never, never wicked man was wise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.15#Blind they rejoice, though now, ev'n now they fall;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.16#Death hastes amain: one hour o'erwhelms them all!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.17#And lo, with speed we plough the watery way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.18#My power shall guard thee, and my hand convey:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.19#The winged vessel studious I prepare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.20#Through seas and realms companion of thy care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.21#Thou to the court ascend: and to the shores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.22#(When night advances) bear the naval stores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.23#Bread, that decaying man with strength supplies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.24#And generous wine, which thoughtful sorrow flies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.25#Meanwhile the mariners, by my command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.26#Shall speed aboard, a valiant chosen band.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.27#Wide o'er the bay, by vessel vessel rides;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.25.28#The best I choose to waft then o'er the tides."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.26.1#She spoke: to his high dome the prince returns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.26.2#And, as he moves, with royal anguish mourns.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.26.3#'Twas riot all, among the lawless train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.26.4#Boar bled by boar, and goat by goat lay slain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.26.5#Arrived, his hand the gay Antinous press'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.26.6#And thus deriding, with a smile address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.27.1#"Grieve not, O daring prince! that noble heart;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.27.2#Ill suits gay youth the stern heroic part.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.27.3#Indulge the genial hour, unbend thy soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.27.4#Leave thought to age, and drain the flowing bowl.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.27.5#Studious to ease thy grief, our care provides
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.27.6#The bark, to waft thee o'er the swelling tides."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.1#"Is this (returns the prince) for mirth a time?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.2#When lawless gluttons riot, mirth's a crime;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.3#The luscious wines, dishonour'd, lose their taste;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.4#The song is noise, and impious is the feast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.5#Suffice it to have spent with swift decay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.6#The wealth of kings, and made my youth a prey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.7#But now the wise instructions of the sage,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.8#And manly thoughts inspired by manly age,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.9#Teach me to seek redress for all my woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.10#Here, or in Pyle--in Pyle, or here, your foe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.11#Deny your vessels, ye deny in vain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.12#A private voyager I pass the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.13#Free breathe the winds, and free the billows flow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.28.14#And where on earth I live, I live your foe."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.29.1#He spoke and frown'd, nor longer deign'd to stay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.29.2#Sternly his hand withdrew, and strode away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.30.1#Meantime, o'er all the dome, they quaff, they feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.30.2#Derisive taunts were spread from guest to guest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.30.3#And each in jovial mood his mate address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.31.1#"Tremble ye not, O friends, and coward fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.31.2#Doom'd by the stern Telemachus to die?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.31.3#To Pyle or Sparta to demand supplies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.31.4#Big with revenge, the mighty warrior flies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.31.5#Or comes from Ephyre with poisons fraught,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.31.6#And kills us all in one tremendous draught!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.32.1#"Or who can say (his gamesome mate replies)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.32.2#But, while the danger of the deeps he tries
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.32.3#He, like his sire, may sink deprived of breath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.32.4#And punish us unkindly by his death?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.32.5#What mighty labours would he then create,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.32.6#To seize his treasures, and divide his state,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.32.7#The royal palace to the queen convey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.32.8#Or him she blesses in the bridal day!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.1#Meantime the lofty rooms the prince surveys,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.2#Where lay the treasures of the Ithacian race:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.3#Here ruddy brass and gold refulgent blazed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.4#There polished chests embroider'd vestures graced;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.5#Here jars of oil breathed forth a rich perfume;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.6#There casks of wine in rows adorn'd the dome
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.7#(Pure flavorous wine, by gods in bounty given
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.8#And worthy to exalt the feasts of heaven).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.9#Untouch'd they stood, till, his long labours o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.10#The great Ulysses reach'd his native shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.11#A double strength of bars secured the gates;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.12#Fast by the door the wise Euryclea waits;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.13#Euryclea, who great Ops! thy lineage shared,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.33.14#And watch'd all night, all day, a faithful guard.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.34.1#To whom the prince: "O thou whose guardian care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.34.2#Nursed the most wretched king that breathes the air;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.34.3#Untouch'd and sacred may these vessels stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.34.4#Till great Ulysses views his native land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.34.5#But by thy care twelve urns of wine be fill'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.34.6#Next these in worth, and firm these urns be seal'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.34.7#And twice ten measures of the choicest flour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.34.8#Prepared, are yet descends the evening hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.34.9#For when the favouring shades of night arise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.34.10#And peaceful slumbers close my mother's eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.34.11#Me from our coast shall spreading sails convey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.34.12#To seek Ulysses through the watery way."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.35.1#While yet he spoke, she fill'd the walls with cries,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.35.2#And tears ran trickling from her aged eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.35.3#"O whither, whither flies my son (she cried)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.35.4#To realms; that rocks and roaring seas divide?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.35.5#In foreign lands thy father's days decay'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.35.6#And foreign lands contain the mighty dead.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.35.7#The watery way ill-fated if thou try,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.35.8#All, all must perish, and by fraud you die!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.35.9#Then stay, my, child! storms beat, and rolls the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.35.10#Oh, beat those storms, and roll the seas in vain!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.36.1#"Far hence (replied the prince) thy fears be driven:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.36.2#Heaven calls me forth; these counsels are of Heaven.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.36.3#But, by the powers that hate the perjured, swear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.36.4#To keep my voyage from the royal ear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.36.5#Nor uncompell'd the dangerous truth betray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.36.6#Till twice six times descends the lamp of day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.36.7#Lest the sad tale a mother's life impair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.36.8#And grief destroy what time awhile would spare."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.37.1#Thus he. The matron with uplifted eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.37.2#Attests the all-seeing sovereign of the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.37.3#Then studious she prepares the choicest flour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.37.4#The strength of wheat and wines an ample store.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.37.5#While to the rival train the prince returns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.37.6#The martial goddess with impatience burns;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.37.7#Like thee, Telemachus, in voice and size,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.37.8#With speed divine from street to street she flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.37.9#She bids the mariners prepared to stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.37.10#When night descends, embodied on the strand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.37.11#Then to Noemon swift she runs, she flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.37.12#And asks a bark: the chief a bark supplies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.38.1#And now, declining with his sloping wheels,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.38.2#Down sunk the sun behind the western hills
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.38.3#The goddess shoved the vessel from the shores,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.38.4#And stow'd within its womb the naval stores,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.38.5#Full in the openings of the spacious main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.38.6#It rides; and now descends the sailor-train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.1#Next, to the court, impatient of delay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.2#With rapid step the goddess urged her way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.3#There every eye with slumberous chains she bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.4#And dash'd the flowing goblet to the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.5#Drowsy they rose, with heavy fumes oppress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.6#Reel'd from the palace, and retired to rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.7#Then thus, in Mentor's reverend form array'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.8#Spoke to Telemachus the martial maid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.9#"Lo! on the seas, prepared the vessel stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.10#The impatient mariner thy speed demands."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.11#Swift as she spoke, with rapid pace she leads;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.12#The footsteps of the deity he treads.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.13#Swift to the shore they move along the strand;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.39.14#The ready vessel rides, the sailors ready stand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.1#He bids them bring their stores; the attending train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.2#Load the tall bark, and launch into the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.3#The prince and goddess to the stern ascend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.4#To the strong stroke at once the rowers bend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.5#Full from the west she bids fresh breezes blow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.6#The sable billows foam and roar below.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.7#The chief his orders gives; the obedient band
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.8#With due observance wait the chief's command;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.9#With speed the mast they rear, with speed unbind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.10#The spacious sheet, and stretch it to the wind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.11#High o'er the roaring waves the spreading sails
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.12#Bow the tall mast, and swell before the gales;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.13#The crooked keel the parting surge divides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.14#And to the stern retreating roll the tides.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.15#And now they ship their oars, and crown with wine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.16#The holy goblet to the powers divine:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.17#Imploring all the gods that reign above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.40.18#But chief the blue-eyed progeny of Jove.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.41.1#Thus all the night they stem the liquid way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:2.41.2#And end their voyage with the morning ray.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.1#The sacred sun, above the waters raised,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.2#Through heaven's eternal brazen portals blazed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.3#And wide o'er earth diffused his cheering ray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.4#To gods and men to give the golden day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.5#Now on the coast of Pyle the vessel falls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.6#Before old Neleus' venerable walls.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.7#There suppliant to the monarch of the flood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.8#At nine green theatres the Pylians stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.9#Each held five hundred (a deputed train),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.10#At each, nine oxen on the sand lay slain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.11#They taste the entrails, and the altars load
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.12#With smoking thighs, an offering to the god.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.13#Full for the port the Ithacensians stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.14#And furl their sails, and issue on the land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.15#Telemachus already press'd the shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.16#Not first, the power of wisdom march'd before,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.17#And ere the sacrificing throng he join'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.1.18#Admonish'd thus his well-attending mind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.2.1#"Proceed, my son! this youthful shame expel;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.2.2#An honest business never blush to tell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.2.3#To learn what fates thy wretched sire detain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.2.4#We pass'd the wide immeasurable main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.2.5#Meet then the senior far renown'd for sense
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.2.6#With reverend awe, but decent confidence:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.2.7#Urge him with truth to frame his fair replies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.2.8#And sure he will; for wisdom never lies."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.3.1#"Oh tell me, Mentor! tell me, faithful guide
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.3.2#(The youth with prudent modesty replied),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.3.3#How shall I meet, or how accost the sage,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.3.4#Unskill'd in speech, nor yet mature of age?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.3.5#Awful th'approach, and hard the task appears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.3.6#To question wisely men of riper years."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.4.1#To whom the martial goddess thus rejoin'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.4.2#"Search, for some thoughts, thy own suggesting mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.4.3#And others, dictated by heavenly power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.4.4#Shall rise spontaneous in the needful hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.4.5#For nought unprosperous shall thy ways attend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.4.6#Born with good omens, and with heaven thy friend."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.1#She spoke, and led the way with swiftest speed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.2#As swift, the youth pursued the way she led;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.3#and join'd the band before the sacred fire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.4#Where sate, encompass'd with his sons, the sire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.5#The youth of Pylos, some on pointed wood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.6#Transfix'd the fragments, some prepared the food:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.7#In friendly throngs they gather to embrace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.8#Their unknown guests, and at the banquet place,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.9#Pisistratus was first to grasp their hands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.10#And spread soft hides upon the yellow sands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.11#Along the shore the illustrious pair he led,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.12#Where Nestor sate with the youthful Thrasymed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.13#To each a portion of the feast he bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.14#And held the golden goblet foaming o'er;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.15#Then first approaching to the elder guest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.16#The latent goddess in these words address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.17#"Whoe'er thou art, from fortune brings to keep
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.18#These rites of Neptune, monarch of the deep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.19#Thee first it fits, O stranger!  to prepare
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.20#The due libation and the solemn prayer;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.21#Then give thy friend to shed the sacred wine;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.22#Though much thy younger, and his years like mine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.23#He too, I deem, implores the power divine;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.24#For all mankind alike require their grace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.25#All born to want; a miserable race!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.26#He spake, and to her hand preferr'd the bowl;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.27#A secret pleasure touch'd Athena's soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.28#To see the preference due to sacred age
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.29#Regarded ever by the just and sage.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.30#Of Ocean's king she then implores the grace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.31#"O thou! whose arms this ample globe embrace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.32#Fulfil our wish, and let thy glory shine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.33#On Nestor first, and Nestor's royal line;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.34#Next grant the Pylian states their just desires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.35#Pleased with their hecatomb's ascending fires;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.36#Last, deign Telemachus and me to bless,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.5.37#And crown our voyage with desired success."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.6.1#Thus she: and having paid the rite divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.6.2#Gave to Ulysses' son the rosy wine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.6.3#Suppliant he pray'd. And now the victims dress'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.6.4#They draw, divide, and celebrate the feast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.6.5#The banquet done, the narrative old man,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.6.6#Thus mild, the pleasing conference began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.7.1#"Now gentle guests! the genial banquet o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.7.2#It fits to ask ye, what your native shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.7.3#And whence your race? on what adventure say,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.7.4#Thus far you wander through the watery way?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.7.5#Relate if business, or the thirst of gain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.7.6#Engage your journey o'er the pathless main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.7.7#Where savage pirates seek through seas unknown
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.7.8#The lives of others, venturous of their own."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.1#Urged by the precepts by the goddess given,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.2#And fill'd with confidence infused from Heaven,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.3#The youth, whom Pallas destined to be wise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.4#And famed among the sons of men, replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.5#"Inquir'st thou, father! from what coast we came?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.6#(Oh grace and glory of the Grecian name!)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.7#From where high Ithaca o'erlooks the floods,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.8#Brown with o'er-arching shades and pendent woods
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.9#Us to these shores our filial duty draws,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.10#A private sorrow, not a public cause.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.11#My sire I seek, where'er the voice of fame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.12#Has told the glories of his noble name,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.13#The great Ulysses; famed from shore to shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.14#For valour much, for hardy suffering more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.15#Long time with thee before proud Ilion's wall
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.16#In arms he fought; with thee beheld her fall.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.17#Of all the chiefs, this hero's fate alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.18#Has Jove reserved, unheard of, and unknown;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.19#Whether in fields by hostile fury slain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.20#Or sunk by tempests in the gulfy main?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.21#Of this to learn, oppress'd with tender fears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.22#Lo, at thy knee his suppliant son appears.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.23#If or thy certain eye, or curious ear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.24#Have learnt his fate, the whole dark story clear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.25#And, oh! whate'er Heaven destined to betide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.26#Let neither flattery soothe, nor pity hide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.27#Prepared I stand: he was but born to try
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.28#The lot of man; to suffer, and to die.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.29#Oh then, if ever through the ten years' war
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.30#The wise, the good Ulysses claim'd thy care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.31#If e'er he join'd thy council, or thy sword,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.32#True in his deed, and constant to his word;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.33#Far as thy mind through backward time can see
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.34#Search all thy stores of faithful memory:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.8.35#'Tis sacred truth I ask, and ask of thee."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.1#To him experienced Nestor thus rejoin'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.2#"O friend! what sorrows dost thou bring to mind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.3#Shall I the long, laborious scene review,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.4#And open all the wounds of Greece anew?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.5#What toils by sea! where dark in quest of prey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.6#Dauntless we roved; Achilles led the way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.7#What toils by land! where mix'd in fatal fight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.8#Such numbers fell, such heroes sunk to night;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.9#There Ajax great, Achilles there the brave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.10#There wise Patroclus, fill an early grave:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.11#There, too, my son--ah, once my best delight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.12#Once swift of foot, and terrible in fight;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.13#In whom stern courage with soft virtue join'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.14#A faultless body and a blameless mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.15#Antilochus--What more can I relate?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.16#How trace the tedious series of our fate?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.17#Not added years on years my task could close,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.18#The long historian of my country's woes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.19#Back to thy native islands might'st thou sail,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.20#And leave half-heard the melancholy tale.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.21#Nine painful years on that detested shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.22#What stratagems we form'd, what toils we bore!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.23#Still labouring on, till scarce at last we found
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.24#Great Jove propitious, and our conquest crown'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.25#Far o'er the rest thy mighty father shined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.26#In wit, in prudence, and in force of mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.27#Art thou the son of that illustrious sire?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.28#With joy I grasp thee, and with love admire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.29#So like your voices, and your words so wise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.30#Who finds thee younger must consult his eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.31#Thy sire and I were one; nor varied aught
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.32#In public sentence, or in private thought;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.33#Alike to council or the assembly came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.34#With equal souls, and sentiments the same.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.35#But when (by wisdom won) proud Ilion burn'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.36#And in their ships the conquering Greeks return'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.37#'Twas God's high will the victors to divide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.38#And turn the event, confounding human pride;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.39#Some be destroy'd, some scatter'd as the dust
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.40#(Not all were prudent, and not all were just).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.41#Then Discord, sent by Pallas from above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.42#Stern daughter of the great avenger Jove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.43#The brother-kings inspired with fell debate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.44#Who call'd to council all the Achaian state,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.45#But call'd untimely (not the sacred rite
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.46#Observed, nor heedful of the setting light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.47#Nor herald sword the session to proclaim),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.48#Sour with debauch, a reeling tribe the came.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.49#To these the cause of meeting they explain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.50#And Menelaus moves to cross the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.51#Not so the king of men: be will'd to stay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.52#The sacred rites and hecatombs to pay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.53#And calm Minerva's wrath. Oh blind to fate!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.54#The gods not lightly change their love, or hate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.55#With ireful taunts each other they oppose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.56#Till in loud tumult all the Greeks arose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.57#Now different counsels every breast divide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.58#Each burns with rancour to the adverse side;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.59#The unquiet night strange projects entertain'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.60#(So Jove, that urged us to our fate, ordain'd).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.61#We with the rising morn our ships unmoor'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.62#And brought our captives and our stores aboard;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.63#But half the people with respect obey'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.64#The king of men, and at his bidding stay'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.65#Now on the wings of winds our course we keep
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.66#(For God had smooth'd the waters of the deep);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.67#For Tenedos we spread our eager oars,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.68#There land, and pay due victims to the powers;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.69#To bless our safe return, we join in prayer;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.70#But angry Jove dispersed our vows in air,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.71#And raised new discord. Then (so Heaven decreed)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.72#Ulysses first and Neator disagreed!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.73#Wise as he was, by various counsels away'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.74#He there, though late, to please the monarch, stay'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.75#But I, determined, stem the foamy floods,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.76#Warn'd of the coming fury of the gods.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.77#With us, Tydides fear'd, and urged his haste:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.78#And Menelaus came, but came the last,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.79#He join'd our vessels in the Lesbian bay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.80#While yet we doubted of our watery way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.81#If to the right to urge the pilot's toil
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.82#(The safer road), beside the Psyrian isle;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.83#Or the straight course to rocky Chios plough,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.84#And anchor under Mimas' shaggy brow?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.85#We sought direction of the power divine:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.86#The god propitious gave the guiding sign;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.87#Through the mid seas he bid our navy steer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.88#And in Euboea shun the woes we fear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.89#The whistling winds already waked the sky;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.90#Before the whistling winds the vessels fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.91#With rapid swiftness cut the liquid way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.92#And reach Gerestus at the point of day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.93#There hecacombs of bulls, to Neptune slain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.94#High-flaming please the monarch of the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.95#The fourth day shone, when all their labours o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.96#Tydides' vessels touched the wish'd-for shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.97#But I to Pylos scud before the gales,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.98#The god still breathing on my swelling sails;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.99#Separate from all, I safely landed here;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.100#Their fates or fortunes never reach'd my ear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.101#Yet what I learn'd, attend; as here I sat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.102#And ask'd each voyager each hero's fate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.9.103#Curious to know, and willing to relate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.1#"Safe reach'd the Myrmidons their native land,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.2#Beneath Achilles' warlike son's command.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.3#Those, whom the heir of great Apollo's art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.4#Brave Philoctetes, taught to wing the dart;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.5#And those whom Idomen from Ilion's plain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.6#Had led, securely cross'd the dreadful main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.7#How Agamemnon touch'd his Argive coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.8#And how his life by fraud and force he lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.9#And how the murderer, paid his forfeit breath;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.10#What lands so distant from that scene of death
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.11#But trembling heard the fame? and heard, admire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.12#How well the son appeased his slaughter'd sire!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.13#Ev'n to the unhappy, that unjustly bleed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.14#Heaven gives posterity, to avenge the deed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.15#So fell Aegysthus; and mayest thou, my friend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.16#(On whom the virtues of thy sire descend,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.17#Make future times thy equal act adore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.10.18#And be what brave Orestes was before!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.1#The prudent youth replied: "O thou the grace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.2#And lasting glory of the Grecian race!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.3#Just was the vengeance, and to latest days
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.4#Shall long posterity resound the praise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.5#Some god this arm with equal prowess bless!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.6#And the proud suitors shall its force confess;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.7#Injurious men! who while my soul is sore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.8#Of fresh affronts, are meditating more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.9#But Heaven denies this honour to my hand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.10#Nor shall my father repossess the land;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.11#The father's fortune never to return,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.12#And the sad son's to softer and to mourn!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.13#Thus he; and Nestor took the word: "My son,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.14#Is it then true, as distant rumours run,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.15#That crowds of rivals for thy mother's charms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.16#Thy palace fill with insults and alarms?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.17#Say, is the fault, through tame submission, thine?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.18#Or leagued against thee, do thy people join,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.19#Moved by some oracle, or voice divine?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.20#And yet who knows, but ripening lies in fate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.21#An hour of vengeance for the afflicted state;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.22#When great Ulysses shall suppress these harms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.23#Ulysses singly, or all Greece in arms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.24#But if Athena, war's triumphant maid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.25#The happy son will as the father aid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.26#(Whose fame and safety was her constant care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.27#In every danger and in every war:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.28#Never on man did heavenly favour shine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.29#With rays so strong, distinguish'd and divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.30#As those with which Minerva mark'd thy sire)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.31#So might she love thee, so thy soul inspire!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.32#Soon should their hopes in humble dust be laid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.11.33#And long oblivion of the bridal bed."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.12.1#"Ah! no such hope (the prince with sighs replies)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.12.2#Can touch my breast; that blessing Heaven denies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.12.3#Ev'n by celestial favour were it given,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.12.4#Fortune or fate would cross the will of Heaven."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.1#"What words are these, and what imprudence thine?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.2#(Thus interposed the martial maid divine)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.3#Forgetful youth! but know, the Power above
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.4#With ease can save each object of his love;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.5#Wide as his will, extends his boundless grace;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.6#Nor lost in time nor circumscribed by place.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.7#Happier his lot, who, many sorrows' pass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.8#Long labouring gains his natal shore at last;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.9#Than who, too speedy, hastes to end his life
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.10#By some stern ruffian, or adulterous wife.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.11#Death only is the lot which none can miss,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.12#And all is possible to Heaven but this.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.13#The best, the dearest favourite of the sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.13.14#Must taste that cup, for man is born to die."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.1#Thus check'd, replied Ulysses' prudent heir:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.2#"Mentor, no more--the mournful thought forbear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.3#For he no more must draw his country's breath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.4#Already snatch'd by fate, and the black doom of death!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.5#Pass we to other subjects; and engage
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.6#On themes remote the venerable sage
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.7#(Who thrice has seen the perishable kind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.8#Of men decay, and through three ages shined
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.9#Like gods majestic, and like gods in mind);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.10#For much he knows, and just conclusions draws,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.11#From various precedents, and various laws.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.12#O son of Neleus! awful Nestor, tell
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.13#How he, the mighty Agamemnon, fell;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.14#By what strange fraud Aegysthus wrought, relate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.15#(By force he could not) such a hero's fate?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.16#Live Menelaus not in Greece? or where
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.17#Was then the martial brother's pious care?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.18#Condemn'd perhaps some foreign short to tread;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.19#Or sure Aegysthus had not dared the deed."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.20#To whom the full of days: Illustrious youth,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.21#Attend (though partly thou hast guess'd) the truth.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.22#For had the martial Menelaus found
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.23#The ruffian breathing yet on Argive ground;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.24#Nor earth had bid his carcase from the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.25#Nor Grecian virgins shriek'd his obsequies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.26#But fowls obscene dismember'd his remains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.27#And dogs had torn him on the naked plains.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.28#While us the works of bloody Mars employ'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.29#The wanton youth inglorious peace enjoy'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.30#He stretch'd at ease in Argos' calm recess
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.31#(Whose stately steeds luxuriant pastures bless),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.32#With flattery's insinuating art
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.33#Soothed the frail queen, and poison'd all her heard.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.34#At first, with the worthy shame and decent pride,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.35#The royal dame his lawless suit denied.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.36#For virtue's image yet possess'd her mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.37#Taught by a master of the tuneful kind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.38#Atrides, parting for the Trojan war,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.39#Consign'd the youthful consort to his care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.40#True to his charge, the bard preserved her long
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.41#In honour's limits; such the power of song.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.42#But when the gods these objects of their hate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.43#Dragg'd to the destruction by the links of fate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.44#The bard they banish'd from his native soil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.45#And left all helpless in a desert isle;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.46#There he, the sweetest of the sacred train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.47#Sung dying to the rocks, but sung in vain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.48#Then virtue was no more; her guard away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.49#She fell, to lust a voluntary prey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.50#Even to the temple stalk'd the adulterous spouse,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.51#With impious thanks, and mockery of the vows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.52#With images, with garments, and with gold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.53#And odorous fumes from loaded altars roll'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.54#"Meantime from flaming Troy we cut the way
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.55#With Menelaus, through the curling sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.56#But when to Sunium's sacred point we came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.57#Crown'd with the temple of the Athenian dame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.58#Atride's pilot, Phrontes, there expired
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.59#(Phrontes, of all the songs of men admired
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.60#To steer the bounding bark with steady toil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.61#When the storm thickens, and the billows boil);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.62#While yet he exercised the steerman's art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.63#Apollo touch'd him with his gentle dart;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.64#Even with the rudder in his hand, he fell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.65#To pay whole honours to the shades of hell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.66#We check'd our haste, by pious office bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.67#And laid our old companion in the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.68#And now the rites discharged, our course we keep
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.69#Far on the gloomy bosom of the deep:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.70#Soon as Malae's misty tops arise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.71#Sudden the Thunderer blackens all the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.72#And the winds whistle, and the surges roll
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.73#Mountains on mountains, and obscure the pole.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.74#The tempest scatters, and divides our fleet;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.75#Part, the storm urges on the coast of Crete,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.76#Where winding round the rich Cydonian plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.77#The streams of Jardan issue to the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.78#There stands a rock, high, eminent and steep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.79#Whose shaggy brow o'erhangs the shady deep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.80#And views Gortyna on the western side;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.81#On this rough Auster drove the impetuous tide:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.82#With broken force the billows roll'd away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.83#And heaved the fleet into the neighb'ring bay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.84#Thus saved from death, the gain'd the Phaestan shores,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.85#With shatter'd vessels and disabled oars;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.86#But five tall barks the winds and water toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.87#Far from their fellows, on the Aegyptian coast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.88#There wander'd Menelaus through foreign shores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.89#Amassing gold, and gathering naval stores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.90#While cursed Aegysthus the detested deed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.91#By fraud fulfilled, and his great brother bled.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.92#Seven years, the traitor rich Mycenae sway'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.93#And his stern rule the groaning land obey'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.94#The eighth, from Athens to his realm restored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.95#Orestes brandish'd the avenging sword,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.96#Slew the dire pair, and gave to funeral flame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.97#The vile assassin and adulterous dame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.98#That day, ere yet the bloody triumphs cease,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.99#Return'd Atrides to the coast of Greece,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.100#And safe to Argos port his navy brought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.101#With gifts of price and ponderous treasure fraught.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.102#Hence warn'd, my son, beware! nor idly stand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.103#Too long a stranger to thy native land;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.104#Lest heedless absence wear thy wealth away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.105#While lawless feasters in thy palace away;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.106#Perhaps may seize thy realm, and share the spoil;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.107#And though return, with disappointed toil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.108#From thy vain journey, to a rifled isle.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.109#However, my friend, indulge one labour more,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.110#And seek Atrides on the Spartan shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.111#He, wandering long a wider circle made,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.112#And many-languaged nations has survey'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.113#And measured tracks unknown to other ships,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.114#Amid the monstrous wonders of the deeps,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.115#(A length of ocean and unbounded sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.116#Which scarce the sea-fowl in a year o'erfly);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.117#Go then; to Sparta take the watery way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.118#Thy ship and sailors but for orders stay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.119#Or, if my land then choose thy course to bend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.120#My steeds, my chariots, and my songs, attend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.121#Thee to Atrides they shall safe convey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.122#Guides of thy road, companions of thy way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.123#Urge him with truth to frame his wise replies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.124#And sure he will; for Menelaus is wise."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.125#Thus while he speaks the ruddy sun descends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.126#And twilight grey her evening shade extends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.127#Then thus the blue-eyed maid: "O full of days!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.128#Wise are thy words, and just are all thy ways.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.129#Now immolate the tongues, and mix the wine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.130#Sacred to Neptune and the powers divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.131#The lamp of day is quench'd beneath the deep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.132#And soft approach the balmy hours of sleep;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.133#Nor fits it to prolong the heavenly feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.14.134#Timeless, indecent, but retire to rest."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.1#So spake Jove's daughter, the celestial maid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.2#The sober train attended and obey'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.3#The sacred heralds on their hands around
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.4#Pour'd the full urns; the youths the goblets crown'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.5#From bowl to bowl the homely beverage flows;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.6#While to the final sacrifice they rose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.7#The tongues they cast upon the fragrant flame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.8#And pour, above, the consecrated stream.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.9#And now, their thirst by copious draughts allay'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.10#The youthful hero and the Athenian maid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.11#Propose departure from the finish'd rite,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.12#And in their hollow bark to pass the night;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.13#But this hospitable sage denied,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.14#"Forbid it, Jove! and all the gods! (he cried),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.15#Thus from my walls and the much-loved son to send
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.16#Of such a hero, and of such a friend!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.17#Me, as some needy peasant, would ye leave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.18#Whom Heaven denies the blessing to relieve?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.19#Me would ye leave, who boast imperial sway,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.20#When beds of royal state invite your stay?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.21#No--long as life this mortal shall inspire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.22#Or as my children imitate their sire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.23#Here shall the wandering stranger find his home,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.15.24#And hospitable rites adorn the dome."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.1#"Well hast thou spoke (the blue-eyed maid replies),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.2#Beloved old man! benevolent as wise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.3#Be the kind dictates of thy heart obey'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.4#And let thy words Telemachus persuade:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.5#He to thy palace shall thy steps pursue;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.6#I to the ship, to give the orders due,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.7#Prescribe directions and confirm the crew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.8#For I alone sustain their naval cares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.9#Who boast experience from these silver hairs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.10#All youths the rest, whom to this journey move
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.11#Like years, like tempers, and their prince's love
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.12#There in the vessel shall I pass the night;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.13#And, soon as morning paints the fields of light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.14#I go to challenge from the Caucons bold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.15#A debt, contracted in the days of old,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.16#But this, thy guest, received with friendly care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.17#Let thy strong coursers swift to Sparta bear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.18#Prepare thy chariot at the dawn of day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.16.19#And be thy son companion of his way."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.1#Then, turning with the word, Minerva flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.2#And soars an eagle through the liquid skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.3#Vision divine! the throng'd spectators gaze
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.4#In holy wonder fix'd, and still amaze.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.5#But chief the reverend sage admired; he took
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.6#The hand of young Telemachus, and spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.7#"Oh, happy youth! and favoured of the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.8#Distinguished care of guardian deities!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.9#Whose early years for future worth engage,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.10#No vulgar manhood, no ignoble age.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.11#For lo! none other of the course above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.12#Then she, the daughter of almighty Jove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.13#Pallas herself, the war-triumphant maid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.14#Confess'd is thine, as once thy fathers aid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.15#So guide me, goddess! so propitious shine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.16#On me, my consort, and my royal line!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.17#A yearling bullock to thy name shall smoke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.18#Untamed, unconscious of the galling yoke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.19#With ample forehead, and yet tender horns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.17.20#Whose budding honours ductile gold adorns."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.1#Submissive thus the hoary sire preferr'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.2#His holy vow: the favouring goddess heard.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.3#Then, slowly rising, o'er the sandy space
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.4#Precedes the father, follow'd by his race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.5#(A long procession) timely marching home
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.6#In comely order to the regal dome.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.7#There when arrived, on thrones around him placed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.8#His sons and grandsons the wide circle graced.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.9#To these the hospitable sage, in sign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.10#Of social welcome, mix'd the racy wine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.11#(Late from the mellowing cask restored to light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.12#By ten long years refined, and rosy bright).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.13#To Pallas high the foaming bowl he crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.14#And sprinkled large libations on the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.15#Each drinks a full oblivion of his cares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.16#And to the gifts of balmy sleep repairs.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.17#Deep in a rich alcove the prince was laid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.18#And slept beneath the pompous colonnade;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.19#Fast by his side Pisistratus was spread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.20#(In age his equal) on a splendid bed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.21#But in an inner court, securely closed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.18.22#The reverend Nestor and his queen reposed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.1#When now Aurora, daughter of the dawn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.2#With rosy lustre purpled o'er the lawn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.3#The old man early rose, walk'd forth, and sate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.4#On polish'd stone before his palace gate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.5#With unguents smooth the lucid marble shone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.6#Where ancient Neleus sate, a rustic throne;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.7#But he descending to the infernal shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.8#Sage Nestor fill'd it, and the sceptre sway'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.9#His sons around him mild obeisance pay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.10#And duteous take the orders of the day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.11#First Eehephron and Stratius quit their bed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.12#Then Perseus, Aretus, and Thrasymed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.13#The last Pisistratus arose from rest:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.14#They came, and near him placed the stranger-guest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.15#To these the senior thus declared his will:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.16#"My sons! the dictates of your sire fulfil.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.17#To Pallas, first of gods, prepare the feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.18#Who graced our rites, a more than mortal guest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.19#Let one, despatchful, bid some swain to lead
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.20#A well-fed bullock from the grassy mead;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.21#One seek the harbour where the vessels moor,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.22#And bring thy friends, Telemachus! ashore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.23#(Leave only two the galley to attend);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.24#Another Laerceus must we send,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.25#Artist devine, whose skilful hands infold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.26#The victim's horn with circumfusile gold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.27#The rest may here the pious duty share,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.28#And bid the handmaids for the feast prepare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.29#The seats to range, the fragrant wood to bring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.19.30#And limpid waters from the living spring."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.1#He said, and busy each his care bestow'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.2#Already at the gates the bullock low'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.3#Already came the Ithacensian crew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.4#The dexterous smith the tools already drew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.5#His ponderous hammer and his anvil sound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.6#And the strong tongs to turn the metal round.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.7#Nor was Minerva absent from the rite,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.8#She view'd her honours, and enjoyed the sight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.9#With reverend hand the king presents the gold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.10#Which round the intorted horns the gilder roll'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.11#So wrought as Pallas might with pride behold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.12#Young Aretus from forth his bride bower
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.13#Brought the full laver, o'er their hands to pour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.14#And canisters of consecrated flour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.15#Stratius and Echephron the victim led;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.16#The axe was held by warlike Thrasymed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.17#In act to strike; before him Perseus stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.18#The vase extending to receive the blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.19#The king himself initiates to the power:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.20#Scatters with quivering hand the sacred flour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.21#And the stream sprinkles; from the curling brows
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.22#The hair collected in the fire he throws.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.23#Soon as due vows on every part were paid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.24#And sacred wheat upon the victim laid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.25#Strong Thrasymed discharged the speeding blow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.26#Full on his neck, and cut the nerves in two.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.27#Down sunk the heavy beast; the females round
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.28#Maids, wives, and matrons, mix a shrilling sound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.29#Nor scorned the queen the holy choir to join
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.30#(The first born she, of old Clymenus' line:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.31#In youth by Nestor loved, of spotless fame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.32#And loved in age, Eurydice her name).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.33#From earth they rear him, struggling now with death;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.34#And Nestor's youngest stops the vents of breath.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.35#The soul for ever flies; on all sides round
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.36#Streams the black blood, and smokes upon the ground
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.37#The beast they then divide and disunite
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.38#The ribs and limbs, observant of the rite:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.39#On these, in double cauls involved with art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.40#The choicest morsels lay from every part.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.41#The sacred sage before his altar stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.42#Turns the burnt offering with his holy hands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.43#And pours the wine, and bids the flames aspire;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.44#The youth with instruments surround the fire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.45#The thighs now sacrificed, and entrails dress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.46#The assistants part, transfix, and broil the rest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.47#While these officious tend the rites divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.48#The last fair branch of the Nestorean line,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.49#Sweet Polycaste, took the pleasing toil
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.50#To bathe the prince, and pour the fragrant oil.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.51#O'er his fair limbs a flowery vest he throw,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.52#And issued, like a god, to mortal view.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.53#His former seat beside the king he found
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.54#(His people's father with his peers around);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.55#All placed at ease the holy banquet join,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.20.56#And in the dazzling goblet laughs the wine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.1#The rage of thirst and hunger now suppress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.2#The monarch turns him to his royal guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.3#And for the promised journey bids prepare
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.4#The smooth hair'd horses, and the rapid car.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.5#Observant of his word, tire word scarce spoke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.6#The sons obey, and join them to the yoke.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.7#Then bread and wine a ready handmaid brings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.8#And presents, such as suit the state of kings.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.9#The glittering seat Telemachus ascends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.10#His faithful guide Pisistratus attends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.11#With hasty hand the ruling reins he drew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.12#He lash'd the coursers, and the coursers flew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.13#Beneath the bounding yoke alike they hold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.14#Their equal pace, and smoked along the field.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.15#The towers of Pylos sink, its views decay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.16#Fields after fields fly back, till close of day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.21.17#Then sunk the sun, and darken'd all the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.22.1#To Pherae now, Diocleus' stately seat
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.22.2#(Of Alpheus' race), the weary youths retreat.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.22.3#His house affords the hospitable rite,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.22.4#And pleased they sleep (the blessing of the night).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.22.5#But when Aurora, daughter of the dawn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.22.6#With rosy lustre purpled o'er the lawn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.22.7#Again they mount, their journey to renew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.22.8#And from the sounding portico they flew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.22.9#Along the waving fields their way they hold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.22.10#The fields receding as their chariot roll'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.22.11#Then slowly sunk the ruddy globe of light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:3.22.12#And o'er the shaded landscape rush'd the night.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.1.1#And now proud Sparta with their wheels resounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.1.2#Sparta whose walls a range of hills surrounds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.1.3#At the fair dome the rapid labour ends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.1.4#Where sate Atrides 'midst his bridal friends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.1.5#With double vows invoking Hymen's power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.1.6#To bless his son's and daughter's nuptial hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.1#That day, to great Achilles son resign'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.2#Hermione, the fairest of her kind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.3#Was sent to crown the long-protracted joy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.4#Espoused before the final doom of Troy;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.5#With steeds and gilded cars, a gorgeous train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.6#Attend the nymphs to Phthia's distant reign.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.7#Meanwhile at home, to Megapentha's bed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.8#The virgin choir Alector's daughter led.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.9#Brave Megapenthas From a stolen amour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.10#To great Atrides' age his handmaid bore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.11#To Helen's bed the gods alone assign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.12#Hermione, to extend the regal line;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.13#On whom a radiant pomp oh Graces wait,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.2.14#Resembling Venus in attractive state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.3.1#While this gay friendly troop the king surround,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.3.2#With festival and mirth the roofs resound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.3.3#A bard amid the joyous circle sings
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.3.4#High airs attemper'd to the vocal strings;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.3.5#Whilst warbling to the varied strain, advance
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.3.6#Two sprightly youths to form the bounding dance,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.3.7#'Twas then, that issuing through the palace gate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.3.8#The splendid car roll'd slow in regal state:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.3.9#On the bright eminence young Nestor shone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.3.10#And fast beside him great Ulysses' son;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.3.11#Grave Eteoneous saw the pomp appear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.3.12#And speeding, thus address'd the royal ear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.4.1#"Two youths approach, whose semblant features prove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.4.2#Their blood devolving from the source of Jove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.4.3#Is due reception deign'd, or must they bend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.4.4#Their doubtful course to seek a distant friend?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.5.1#"Insensate! (with a sigh the king replies,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.5.2#Too long, misjudging, have I thought thee wise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.5.3#But sure relentless folly steals thy breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.5.4#Obdurate to reject the stranger-guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.5.5#To those dear hospitable rites a foe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.5.6#Which in my wanderings oft relieved my woe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.5.7#Fed by the bounty of another's board,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.5.8#Till pitying Jove my native realm restored--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.5.9#Straight be the coursers from the car released,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.5.10#Conduct the youths to grace the genial feast."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.1#The seneschal, rebuked, in haste withdrew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.2#With equal haste a menial train pursue:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.3#Part led the coursers, from the car enlarged,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.4#Each to a crib with choicest grain surcharged;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.5#Part in a portico, profusely graced
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.6#With rich magnificence, the chariot placed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.7#Then to the dome the friendly pair invite,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.8#Who eye the dazzling roofs with vast delight;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.9#Resplendent as the blaze of summer noon,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.10#Or the pale radiance of the midnight moon.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.11#From room to room their eager view they bend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.12#Thence to the bath, a beauteous pile, descend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.13#Where a bright damsel train attends the guests
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.14#With liquid odours, and embroider'd vests.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.15#Refresh'd, they wait them to the bower of state,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.16#Where, circled with his pears, Atrides sate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.17#Throned next the king, a fair attendant brings
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.18#The purest product of the crystal springs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.19#High on a massy vase of silver mould,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.20#The burnish'd laver flames with solid gold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.21#In solid gold the purple vintage flows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.22#And on the board a second banquet rose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.23#When thus the king, with hospitable port;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.24#"Accept this welcome to the Spartan court:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.25#The waste of nature let the feast repair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.26#Then your high lineage and your names declare;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.27#Say from what sceptred ancestry ye claim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.28#Recorded eminent in deathless fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.29#For vulgar parents cannot stamp their race
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.6.30#With signatures of such majestic grace."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.7.1#Ceasing, benevolent he straight assigns
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.7.2#The royal portion of the choicest chines
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.7.3#To each accepted friend; with grateful haste
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.7.4#They share the honours of the rich repast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.7.5#Sufficed, soft whispering thus to Nestor's son,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.7.6#His head reclined, young Ithacus begun:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.8.1#"View'st thou unmoved, O ever-honour'd most!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.8.2#These prodigies of art, and wondrous cost!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.8.3#Above, beneath, around the palace shines
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.8.4#The sunless treasure of exhausted mines;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.8.5#The spoils of elephants the roofs inlay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.8.6#And studded amber darts the golden ray;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.8.7#Such, and not nobler, in the realms above
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.8.8#My wonder dictates is the dome of Jove."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.1#The monarch took the word, and grave replied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.2#"Presumptuous are the vaunts, and vain the pride
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.3#Of man, who dares in pomp with Jove contest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.4#Unchanged, immortal, and supremely blest!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.5#With all my affluence, when my woes are weigh'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.6#Envy will own the purchase dearly paid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.7#For eight slow-circling years, by tempests toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.8#From Cypress to the far Phoenician coast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.9#(Sidon the capital), I stretch'd my toil
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.10#Through regions fatten'd with the flows of Nile.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.11#Next Aethiopia's utmost bound explore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.12#And the parch'd borders of the Arabian shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.13#Then warp my voyage on the southern gales,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.14#O'er the warm Lybian wave to spread my sails;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.15#That happy clime, where each revolving year
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.16#The teeming ewes a triple offspring bear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.17#And two fair crescents of translucent horn
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.18#The brows of all their young increase adorn:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.19#The shepherd swains, with sure abundance blest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.20#On the fat flock and rural dainties feast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.21#Nor want of herbage makes the dairy fail,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.22#But every season fills the foaming pail.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.23#Whilst, heaping unwash'd wealth, I distant roam,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.24#The best of brothers, at his natal home,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.25#By the dire fury of a traitress wife,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.26#Ends the sad evening of a stormy life;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.27#Whence, with incessant grief my soul annoy'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.28#These riches are possess'd, but not enjoy'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.29#My wars, the copious theme of every tongue,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.30#To you your fathers have recorded long.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.31#How favouring Heaven repaid my glorious toils
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.32#With a sack'd palace, and barbaric spoils.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.33#Oh! had the gods so large a boon denied
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.34#And life, the just equivalent supplied
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.35#To those brave warriors, who, with glory fired
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.36#Far from their country, in my cause expired!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.37#Still in short intervals of pleasing woe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.38#Regardful of the friendly dues I owe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.39#I to the glorious dead, for ever dear!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.40#Indulge the tribute of a grateful tear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.41#But oh! Ulysses--deeper than the rest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.42#That sad idea wounds my anxious breast!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.43#My heart bleeds fresh with agonizing pain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.44#The bowl and tasteful viands tempt in vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.45#Nor sleep's soft power can close my streaming eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.46#When imaged to my soul his sorrows rise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.47#No peril in my cause he ceased to prove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.48#His labours equall'd only by my love:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.49#And both alike to bitter fortune born,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.50#For him to suffer, and for me to mourn!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.51#Whether he wanders on some friendly coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.52#Or glides in Stygian gloom a pensive ghost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.53#No fame reveals; but, doubtful of his doom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.54#His good old sire with sorrow to the tomb
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.55#Declines his trembling steps; untimely care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.56#Withers the blooming vigour of his heir;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.57#And the chaste partner of his bed and throne
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.9.58#Wastes all her widow'd hours in tender moan."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.1#While thus pathetic to the prince he spoke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.2#From the brave youth the streaming passion broke;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.3#Studious to veil the grief, in vain repress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.4#His face he shrouded with his purple vest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.5#The conscious monarch pierced the coy disguise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.6#And view'd his filial love with vast surprise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.7#Dubious to press the tender theme, or wait
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.8#To hear the youth inquire his father's fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.9#In this suspense bright Helen graced the room;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.10#Before her breathed a gale of rich perfume.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.11#So moves, adorn'd with each attractive grace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.12#The silver shafted goddess of the chase!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.13#The seat of majesty Adraste brings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.14#With art illustrious, for the pomp of kings;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.15#To spread the pall (beneath the regal chair)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.16#Of softest wool, is bright Alcippe's care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.17#A silver canister, divinely wrought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.18#In her soft hands the beauteous Phylo brought;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.19#To Sparta's queen of old the radiant vase
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.20#Alcandra gave, a pledge of royal grace;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.21#For Polybus her lord (whose sovereign sway
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.22#The wealthy tribes of Pharian Thebes obey),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.23#When to that court Atrides came, caress'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.24#With vast munificence the imperial guest:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.25#Two lavers from the richest ore refined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.26#With silver tripods, the kind host assign'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.27#And bounteous from the royal treasure told
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.28#Ten equal talents of refulgent gold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.29#Alcandra, consort of his high command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.30#A golden distaff gave to Helen's hand;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.31#And that rich vase, with living sculpture wrought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.32#Which heap'd with wool the beauteous Phylo brought
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.33#The silken fleece, impurpled for the loom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.34#Rivall'd the hyacinth in vernal bloom.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.35#The sovereign seat then Jove born Helen press'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.10.36#And pleasing thus her sceptred lord address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.11.1#"Who grace our palace now, that friendly pair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.11.2#Speak they their lineage, or their names declare?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.11.3#Uncertain of the truth, yet uncontroll'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.11.4#Hear me the bodings of my breast unfold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.11.5#With wonder wrapp'd on yonder check I trace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.11.6#The feature of the Ulyssean race:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.11.7#Diffused o'er each resembling line appear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.11.8#In just similitude, the grace and air
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.11.9#Of young Telemachus! the lovely boy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.11.10#Who bless'd Ulysses with a father's joy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.11.11#What time the Greeks combined their social arms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.11.12#To avenge the stain of my ill-fated charms!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.12.1#"Just is thy thought, (the king assenting cries,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.12.2#Methinks Ulysses strikes my wondering eyes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.12.3#Full shines the father in the filial frame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.12.4#His port, his features, and his shape the same;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.12.5#Such quick regards his sparkling eyes bestow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.12.6#Such wavy ringlets o'er his shoulders flow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.12.7#And when he heard the long disastrous store
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.12.8#Of cares, which in my cause Ulysses bore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.12.9#Dismay'd, heart-wounded with paternal woes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.12.10#Above restraint the tide of sorrow rose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.12.11#Cautious to let the gushing grief appear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.12.12#His purple garment veil'd the falling tear."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.1#"See there confess'd (Pisistratus replies)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.2#The genuine worth of Ithacus the wise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.3#Of that heroic sire the youth is sprung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.4#But modest awe hath chain'd his timorous tongue.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.5#Thy voice, O king! with pleased attention heard,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.6#Is like the dictates of a god revered.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.7#With him, at Nestor's high command, I came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.8#Whose age I honour with a parent's name.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.9#By adverse destiny constrained to sue
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.10#For counsel and redress, he sues to you
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.11#Whatever ill the friendless orphan bears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.12#Bereaved of parents in his infant years,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.13#Still must the wrong'd Telemachus sustain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.14#If, hopeful of your aid, he hopes in vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.15#Affianced in your friendly power alone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.13.16#The youth would vindicate the vacant throne."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.1#"Is Sparta blest, and these desiring eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.2#View my friend's son? (the king exalting cries;)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.3#Son of my friend, by glorious toils approved,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.4#Whose sword was sacred to the man he loved;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.5#Mirror of constant faith, revered and mourn'd--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.6#When Troy was ruin'd, had the chief return'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.7#No Greek an equal space had ere possess'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.8#Of dear affection, in my grateful breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.9#I, to confirm the mutual joys we shared,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.10#For his abode a capital prepared;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.11#Argos, the seat of sovereign rule, I chose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.12#Fair in the plan the future palace rose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.13#Where my Ulysses and his race might reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.14#And portion to his tribes the wide domain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.15#To them my vassals had resign'd a soil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.16#With teeming plenty to reward their toil.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.17#There with commutual zeal we both had strove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.18#In acts of dear benevolence and love:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.19#Brothers in peace, not rivals in command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.20#And death alone dissolved the friendly band!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.21#Some envious power the blissful scene destroys;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.22#Vanish'd are all the visionary joys;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.23#The soul of friendship to my hope is lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.14.24#Fated to wander from his natal coast!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.15.1#He ceased; a gush of grief began to rise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.15.2#Fast streams a tide from beauteous Helen's eyes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.15.3#Fast for the sire the filial sorrows flow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.15.4#The weeping monarch swells the mighty woe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.15.5#Thy cheeks, Pisistratus, the tears bedew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.15.6#While pictured so thy mind appear'd in view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.15.7#Thy martial brother; on the Phrygian plain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.15.8#Extended pale, by swarthy Memnon slain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.15.9#But silence soon the son of Nestor broke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.15.10#And melting with fraternal pity, spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.1#"Frequent, O king, was Nestor wont to raise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.2#And charm attention with thy copious praise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.3#To crowd thy various gifts, the sage assign'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.4#The glory of a firm capacious mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.5#With that superior attribute control
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.6#This unavailing impotence of soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.7#Let not your roof with echoing grief resound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.8#Now for the feast the friendly bowl is crown'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.9#But when, from dewy shade emerging bright,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.10#Aurora streaks the sky with orient light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.11#Let each deplore his dead; the rites of woe
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.12#Are all, alas! the living can bestow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.13#O'er the congenial dust enjoin'd to shear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.14#The graceful curl, and drop the tender tear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.15#Then, mingling in the mournful pomp with you,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.16#I'll pay my brother's ghost a warrior's due,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.17#And mourn the brave Antilochus, a name
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.18#Not unrecorded in the rolls of fame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.19#With strength and speed superior form'd, in fight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.20#To face the foe, or intercept his flight;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.21#Too early snatch'd by fate ere known to me!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.16.22#I boast a witness of his worth in thee."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.1#"Young and mature! (the monarch thus rejoins,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.2#In thee renew'd the soul of Nestor shines;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.3#Form'd by the care of that consummate sage,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.4#In early bloom an oracle of age.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.5#Whene'er his influence Jove vouchsafes to shower,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.6#To bless the natal and the nuptial hour;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.7#From the great sire transmissive to the race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.8#The boon devolving gives distinguish'd grace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.9#Such, happy Nestor! was thy glorious doom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.10#Around thee, full of years, thy offspring bloom.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.11#Expert of arms, and prudent in debate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.12#The gifts of Heaven to guard thy hoary state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.13#But now let each becalm his troubled breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.14#Wash, and partake serene the friendly feast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.15#To move thy suit, Telemachus, delay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.17.16#Till heaven's revolving lamp restores the day."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.1#He said, Asphalion swift the laver brings;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.2#Alternate, all partake the grateful springs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.3#Then from the rites of purity repair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.4#And with keen gust the savoury viands share.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.5#Meantime, with genial joy to warm the soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.6#Bright Helen mix'd a mirth inspiring bowl;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.7#Temper'd with drugs of sovereign use, to assuage
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.8#The boiling bosom of tumultuous rage;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.9#To clear the cloudy front of wrinkled Care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.10#And dry the tearful sluices of Despair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.11#Charm'd with that virtuous draught, the exalted mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.12#All sense of woe delivers to the wind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.13#Though on the blazing pile his parent lay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.14#Or a loved brother groan'd his life away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.15#Or darling son, oppress'd by ruffian force,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.16#Fell breathless at his feet, a mangled corse;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.17#From morn to eve, impassive and serene,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.18#The man entranced would view the dreadful scene
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.19#These drugs, so friendly to the joys of life.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.20#Bright Helen learn'd from Thone's imperial wife;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.21#Who sway'd the sceptre, where prolific Nile
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.22#With various simples clothes the fatten'd soil.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.23#With wholesome herbage mix'd, the direful bane
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.24#Of vegetable venom taints the plain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.25#From Paeon sprung, their patron-god imparts
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.26#To all the Pharian race his healing arts.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.27#The beverage now prepared to inspire the feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.18.28#The circle thus the beauteous queen addressed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.19.1#"Throned in omnipotence, supremest Jove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.19.2#Tempers the fates of human race above;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.19.3#By the firm sanction of his sovereign will,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.19.4#Alternate are decreed our good and ill.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.19.5#To feastful mirth be this white hour assign'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.19.6#And sweet discourse, the banquet of the mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.19.7#Myself, assisting in the social joy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.19.8#Will tell Ulysses' bold exploit in Troy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.19.9#Sole witness of the deed I now declare
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.19.10#Speak you (who saw) his wonders in the war.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.1#"Seam'd o'er with wounds, which his own sabre gave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.2#In the vile habit of a village slave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.3#The foe deceived, he pass'd the tented plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.4#In Troy to mingle with the hostile train.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.5#In this attire secure from searching eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.6#Till happily piercing through the dark disguise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.7#The chief I challenged; he, whose practised wit
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.8#Knew all the serpent mazes of deceit,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.9#Eludes my search; but when his form I view'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.10#Fresh from the bath, with fragrant oils renew'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.11#His limbs in military purple dress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.12#Each brightening grace the genuine Greek confess'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.13#A previous pledge of sacred faith obtain'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.14#Till he the lines and Argive fleet regain'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.15#To keep his stay conceal'd; the chief declared
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.16#The plans of war against the town prepared.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.17#Exploring then the secrets of the state,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.18#He learn'd what best might urge the Dardan fate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.19#And, safe returning to the Grecian host,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.20#Sent many a shade to Pluto's dreary coast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.21#Loud grief resounded through the towers of Troy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.22#But my pleased bosom glow'd with secret joy:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.23#For then, with dire remorse and conscious shame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.24#I view'd the effects of that disastrous flame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.25#Which, kindled by the imperious queen of love,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.26#Constrain'd me from my native realm to rove:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.27#And oft in bitterness of soul deplored
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.28#My absent daughter and my dearer lord;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.29#Admired among the first of human race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.20.30#For every gift of mind and manly grace."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.1#"Right well (replied the king) your speech displays
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.2#The matchless merit of the chief you praise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.3#Heroes in various climes myself have found,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.4#For martial deeds and depth of thought renown'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.5#But Ithacus, unrivall'd in his claim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.6#May boast a title to the loudest fame:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.7#In battle calm he guides the rapid storm,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.8#Wise to resolve, and patient to perform.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.9#What wondrous conduct in the chief appear'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.10#When the vast fabric of the steed we rear'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.11#Some demon, anxious for the Trojan doom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.12#Urged you with great Deiphobus to come,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.13#To explore the fraud; with guile opposed to guile.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.14#Slow-pacing thrice around the insidious pile,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.15#Each noted leader's name you thrice invoke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.16#Your accent varying as their spouses spoke!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.17#The pleasing sounds each latent warrior warm'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.18#But most Tydides' and coy heart alarm'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.19#To quit the steed we both impatient press
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.20#Threatening to answer from the dark recess.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.21#Unmoved the mind of Ithacus remain'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.22#And the vain ardours of our love restrain'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.23#But Anticlus, unable to control,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.24#Spoke loud the language of his yearning soul:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.25#Ulysses straight, with indignation fired
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.26#(For so the common care of Greece required),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.27#Firm to his lips his forceful hands applied,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.28#Till on his tongue the fluttering murmurs died.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.29#Meantime Minerva, from the fraudful horse,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.21.30#Back to the court of Priam bent your course."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.1#"Inclement fate! (Telemachus replies,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.2#Frail is the boasted attribute of wise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.3#The leader mingling with the vulgar host,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.4#Is in the common mass of matter lost!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.5#But now let sleep the painful waste repair
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.6#Of sad reflection and corroding care."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.7#He ceased; the menial fair that round her wait,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.8#At Helen's beck prepare the room of state;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.9#Beneath an ample portico they spread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.10#The downy fleece to form the slumberous bed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.11#And o'er soft palls of purple grain unfold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.12#Rich tapestry, stiff with interwoven gold:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.13#Then, through the illumined dome, to balmy rest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.14#The obsequious herald guides each princely guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.15#While to his regal bower the king ascends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.16#And beauteous Helen on her lord attends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.17#Soon as the morn, in orient purple dress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.18#Unbarr'd the portal of the roseate east,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.19#The monarch rose; magnificent to view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.20#The imperial mantle o'er his vest he threw;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.21#The glittering zone athwart his shoulders cast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.22#A starry falchion low-depending graced;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.23#Clasp'd on his feet the embroidered sandals shine;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.24#And forth he moves, majestic and divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.25#Instant to young Telemachus he press'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.22.26#And thus benevolent his speech addressed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.23.1#"Say, royal youth, sincere of soul report
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.23.2#Whit cause hath led you to the Spartan court?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.23.3#Do public or domestic care constrain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.23.4#This toilsome voyage o'er the surgy main?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.1#"O highly-flavour'd delegate of Jove!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.2#(Replies the prince) inflamed with filial love,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.3#And anxious hope, to hear my parent's doom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.4#A suppliant to your royal court I come:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.5#Our sovereign seat a lewd usurping race
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.6#With lawless riot and misrule disgrace;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.7#To pamper'd insolence devoted fall
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.8#Prime of the flock, and choicest of the stall:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.9#For wild ambition wings their bold desire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.10#And all to mount the imperial bed aspire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.11#But prostrate I implore, O king! relate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.12#The mournful series of my father's fate:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.13#Each known disaster of the man disclose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.14#Born by his mother to a world of woes!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.15#Recite them; nor in erring pity fear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.16#To wound with storied grief the filial ear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.17#If e'er Ulysses, to reclaim your right,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.18#Avow'd his zeal in council or in fight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.19#If Phrygian camps the friendly toils attest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.24.20#To the sire's merit give the son's request."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.1#Deep from his inmost soul Atrides sigh'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.2#And thus, indignant, to the prince replied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.3#"Heavens! would a soft, inglorious, dastard train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.4#An absent hero's nuptial joys profane!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.5#So with her young, amid the woodland shades,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.6#A timorous hind the lion's court invades,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.7#Leaves in the fatal lair the tender fawns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.8#Climbs the green cliff, or feeds the flowery lawns:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.9#Meantime return'd, with dire remorseless sway,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.10#The monarch-savage rends the trembling prey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.11#With equal fury, and with equal fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.12#Ulysses soon shall reassert his claim.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.13#O Jove supreme, whom gods and men revere!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.14#And thou! to whom 'tis given to gild the sphere!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.15#With power congenial join'd, propitious aid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.16#The chief adopted by the martial maid!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.17#Such to our wish the warrior soon restore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.18#As when contending on the Lesbian shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.19#His prowess Philomelidies confess'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.20#And loud-acclaiming Greeks the victor bless'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.21#Then soon the invaders of his bed and throne
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.22#Their love presumptuous shall with life atone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.23#With patient ear, O royal youth, attend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.24#The storied labour of thy father's friend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.25#Fruitful of deeds, the copious tale is long,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.26#But truth severe shall dictate to my tongue:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.27#Learn what I heard the sea-born seer relate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.25.28#Whose eye can pierce the dark recess of fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.1#"Long on the Egyptian coast by calms confined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.2#Heaven to my fleet refused a prosperous wind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.3#No vows had we preferr'd, nor victims slain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.4#For this the gods each favouring gale restrain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.5#Jealous, to see their high behests obey'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.6#Severe, if men the eternal rights evade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.7#High o'er a gulfy sea, the Pharian isle
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.8#Fronts the deep roar of disemboguing Nile:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.9#Her distance from the shore, the course begun
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.10#At dawn, and ending with the setting sun,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.11#A galley measures; when the stiffer gales
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.12#Rise on the poop, and fully stretch the sails.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.13#There, anchor'd vessels safe in harbour lie,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.26.14#Whilst limpid springs the failing cask supply.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.27.1#"And now the twentieth sun, descending, laves
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.27.2#His glowing axle in the western waves:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.27.3#Still with expanded sails we court in vain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.27.4#Propitious winds to waft us o'er the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.27.5#And the pale mariner at once deplores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.27.6#His drooping vigour and exhausted stores.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.27.7#When lo! a bright cerulean form appears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.27.8#Proteus her sire divine. With pity press'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.27.9#Me sole the daughter of the deep address'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.27.10#What time, with hunger pined, my absent mates
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.27.11#Roam the wide isle in search of rural cates,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.27.12#Bait the barb'd steel, and from the fishy flood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.27.13#Appease the afflictive fierce desire of food."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.1#"'Whoe'er thou art (the azure goddess cries)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.2#Thy conduct ill-deserves the praise of wise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.3#Is death thy choice, or misery thy boast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.4#That here inglorious, on a barren coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.5#Thy brave associates droop, a meagre train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.6#With famine pale, and ask thy care in vain?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.7#"Struck with the loud reproach, I straight reply:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.8#'Whate'er thy title in thy native sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.9#A goddess sure! for more than moral grace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.10#Speaks thee descendant of ethereal race;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.11#Deem not that here of choice my fleet remains;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.12#Some heavenly power averse my stay constrains:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.13#O, piteous of my fate, vouchsafe to show
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.14#(For what's sequester'd from celestial view?)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.15#What power becalms the innavigable seas?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.28.16#What guilt provokes him, and what vows appease?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.1#"I ceased, when affable the goddess cried:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.2#'Observe, and in the truths I speak confide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.3#The oracular seer frequents the Pharian coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.4#From whose high bed my birth divine I boast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.5#Proteus, a name tremendous o'er the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.6#The delegate of Neptune's watery reign.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.7#Watch with insidious care his known abode;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.8#There fast in chains constrain the various god;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.9#Who bound, obedient to superior force,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.10#Unerring will prescribe your destined course.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.11#If, studious on your realms, you then demand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.12#Their state, since last you left your natal land,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.13#Instant the god obsequious will disclose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.29.14#Bright tracts of glory or a cloud of woes.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.30.1#"She ceased; and suppliant thus I made reply:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.30.2#'O goddess I on thy aid my hopes rely;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.30.3#Dictate propitious to my duteous ear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.30.4#What arts can captivate the changeful seer;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.30.5#For perilous the assay, unheard the toil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.30.6#To elude the prescience of a god by guile.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.1#"Thus to the goddess mild my suit I end.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.2#Then she: 'Obedient to my rule attend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.3#When through the zone of heaven the mounted sun
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.4#Hath journeyed half, and half remains to run;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.5#The seer, while zephyrs curl the swelling deep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.6#Basks on the breezy shore, in grateful sleep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.7#His oozy limbs. Emerging from the wave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.8#The Phocas swift surround his rocky cave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.9#Frequent and full; the consecrated train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.10#Of her, whose azure trident awes the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.11#There wallowing warm, the enormous herd exhales
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.12#An oily steam, and taints the noontide gales.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.13#To that recess, commodious for surprise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.14#When purple light shall next suffuse the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.15#With me repair; and from thy warrior-band
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.16#Three chosen chiefs of dauntless soul command;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.17#Let their auxiliar force befriend the toil;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.18#For strong the god, and perfected in guile.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.19#Strech'd on the shelly shore, he first surveys
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.20#The flouncing herd ascending from the seas;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.21#Their number summ'd, reposed in sleep profound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.22#The scaly charge their guardian god surround;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.23#So with his battening flocks the careful swain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.24#Abides pavilion'd on the grassy plain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.25#With powers united, obstinately bold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.26#Invade him, couch'd amid the scaly fold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.27#Instant he wears, elusive of the rape,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.28#The mimic force of every savage shape;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.29#Or glides with liquid lapse a murmuring stream,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.30#Or, wrapp'd in flame, he glows at every limb.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.31#Yet, still retentive, with redoubled might,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.32#Through each vain passive form constrain his flight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.33#But when, his native shape renamed, he stands
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.34#Patient of conquest, and your cause demands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.35#The cause that urged the bold attempt declare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.36#And soothe the vanquish'd with a victor's prayer.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.37#The bands releas'd, implore the seer to say
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.38#What godhead interdicts the watery way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.39#Who, straight propitious, in prophetic strain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.40#Will teach you to repass the unmeasured main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.41#She ceased, and bounding from the shelfy shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.31.42#Round the descending nymph the waves resounding roar.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.1#"High wrapp'd in wonder of the future deed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.2#with joy impetuous to the port I speed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.3#The wants of nature with repast suffice,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.4#Till night with grateful shade involved the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.5#And shed ambrosial dews. Fast by the deep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.6#Along the tented shore, in balmy sleep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.7#Our cares were lost. When o'er the eastern lawn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.8#In saffron robes, the daughter of the dawn
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.9#Advanced her rosy steps, before the bay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.10#Due ritual honours to the gods I pay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.11#Then seek the place the sea-born nymph assign'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.12#With three associates of undaunted mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.13#Arrived, to form along the appointed strand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.14#For each a bed, she scoops the hilly sand;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.15#Then, from her azure cave the finny spoils
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.16#Of four vast Phocae takes, to veil her wiles;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.17#Beneath the finny spoils extended prone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.18#Hard toil! the prophet's piercing eye to shun;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.19#New from the corse, the scaly frauds diffuse
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.20#Unsavoury stench of oil, and brackish ooze;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.21#But the bright sea-maid's gentle power implored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.32.22#With nectar'd drops the sickening sense restored.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.1#"Thus till the sun had travell'd half the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.2#Ambush'd we lie, and wait the bold emprise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.3#When, thronging quick to bask in open air,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.4#The flocks of ocean to the strand repair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.5#Couch'd on the sunny sand, the monsters sleep;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.6#Then Proteus, mounting from the hoary deep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.7#Surveys his charge, unknowing of deceit;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.8#(In order told, we make the sum complete.)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.9#Pleased with the false review, secure he lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.10#And leaden slumbers press his drooping eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.11#Rushing impetuous forth, we straight prepare
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.12#A furious onset with the sound of war,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.13#And shouting seize the god; our force to evade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.14#His various arts he soon resumes in aid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.15#A lion now, he curls a surgy mane;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.16#Sudden our hands a spotted paid restrain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.17#Then, arm'd with tusks, and lightning in his eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.18#A boar's obscener shape the god belies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.19#On spiry volumes, there a dragon rides;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.20#Here, from our strict embrace a stream he glides.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.21#At last, sublime, his stately growth he rears
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.22#A tree, and well-dissembled foliage wears.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.23#Vain efforts with superior power compress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.24#Me with reluctance thus the seer address'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.25#'Say, son of Atreus, say what god inspired
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.26#This daring fraud, and what the boon desired?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.27#I thus: 'O thou, whose certain eye foresees
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.28#The fix'd event of fate's remote decrees;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.29#After long woes, and various toil endured,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.30#Still on this desert isle my fleet is moor'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.31#Unfriended of the gales.  All-knowing, say,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.32#What godhead interdicts the watery way?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.33#What vows repentant will the power appease,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.33.34#To speed a prosperous voyage o'er the seas.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.1#"'To Jove (with stern regard the god replies)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.2#And all the offended synod of the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.3#Just hecatombs with due devotion slain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.4#Thy guilt absolved, a prosperous voyage gain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.5#To the firm sanction of thy fate attend!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.6#An exile thou, nor cheering face of friend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.7#Nor sight of natal shore, nor regal dome,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.8#Shalt yet enjoy, but still art doom'd to roam.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.9#Once more the Nile, who from the secret source
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.10#Of Jove's high seat descends with sweepy force,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.11#Must view his billows white beneath thy oar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.12#And altars blaze along his sanguine shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.13#Then will the gods with holy pomp adored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.34.14#To thy long vows a safe return accord.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.35.1#"He ceased: heart wounded with afflictive pain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.35.2#(Doom'd to repeat the perils of the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.35.3#A shelfy track and long!) 'O seer' I cry,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.35.4#'To the stern sanction of the offended sky
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.35.5#My prompt obedience bows. But deign to say
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.35.6#What fate propitious, or what dire dismay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.35.7#Sustain those peers, the relics of our host,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.35.8#Whom I with Nestor on the Phrygian coast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.35.9#Embracing left? Must I the warriors weep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.35.10#Whelm'd in the bottom of the monstrous deep?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.35.11#Or did the kind domestic friend deplore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.35.12#The breathless heroes on their native shore?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.36.1#"'Press not too far,' replied the god: 'but cease
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.36.2#To know what, known, will violate thy peace;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.36.3#Too curious of their doom! with friendly woe
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.36.4#Thy breast will heave, and tears eternal flow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.36.5#Part live! the rest, a lamentable train!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.36.6#Range the dark bounds of Pluto's dreary reign.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.36.7#Two, foremost in the roll of Mars renown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.36.8#Whose arms with conquest in thy cause were crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.36.9#Fell by disastrous fate: by tempests toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.36.10#A third lives wretched on a distant coast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.37.1#"By Neptune rescued from Minerva's hate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.37.2#On Gyrae, safe Oilean Ajax sate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.37.3#His ship o'erwhelm'd; but, frowning on the floods,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.37.4#Impious he roar'd defiance to the gods;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.37.5#To his own prowess all the glory gave:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.37.6#The power defrauding who vouchsafed to save.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.37.7#This heard the raging ruler of the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.37.8#His spear, indignant for such high disdain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.37.9#He launched; dividing with his forky mace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.37.10#The aerial summit from the marble base:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.37.11#The rock rush'd seaward, with impetuous roar
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.37.12#Ingulf'd, and to the abyss the boaster bore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.1#"By Juno's guardian aid, the watery vast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.2#Secure of storms, your royal brother pass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.3#Till, coasting nigh the cape where Malen shrouds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.4#Her spiry cliffs amid surrounding clouds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.5#A whirling gust tumultuous from the shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.6#Across the deep his labouring vessel bore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.7#In an ill-fated hour the coast he gain'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.8#Where late in regal pomp Thyestes reigned;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.9#But, when his hoary honours bow'd to fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.10#Aegysthus govern'd in paternal state,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.11#The surges now subside, the tempest ends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.12#From his tall ship the king of men descends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.13#There fondly thinks the gods conclude his toil:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.14#Far from his own domain salutes the soil;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.15#With rapture oft the urge of Greece reviews,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.16#And the dear turf with tears of joy bedews.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.17#Him, thus exulting on the distant stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.18#A spy distinguish'd from his airy stand;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.19#To bribe whose vigilance, Aegysthus told
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.20#A mighty sum of ill-persuading gold:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.21#There watch'd this guardian of his guilty fear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.22#Till the twelfth moon had wheel'd her pale career;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.23#And now, admonish'd by his eye, to court
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.24#With terror wing'd conveys the dread report.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.25#Of deathful arts expert, his lord employs
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.26#The ministers of blood in dark surprise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.27#And twenty youths, in radiant mail incased,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.28#Close ambush'd nigh the spacious hall he placed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.29#Then bids prepare the hospitable treat:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.30#Vain shows of love to veil his felon hate!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.31#To grace the victor's welcome from the wars,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.32#A train of coursers and triumphal cars
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.33#Magnificent he leads: the royal guest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.34#Thoughtless of ill, accepts the fraudful feast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.35#The troop forth-issuing from the dark recess,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.36#With homicidal rage the king oppress!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.37#So, whilst he feeds luxurious in the stall,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.38#The sovereign of the herd is doomed to fall,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.39#The partners of his fame and toils at Troy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.40#Around their lord, a mighty ruin, lie:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.41#Mix'd with the brave, the base invaders bleed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.38.42#Aegysthus sole survives to boast the deed."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.1#He said: chill horrors shook my shivering soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.2#Rack'd wish convulsive pangs in dust I roll;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.3#And hate, in madness of extreme despair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.4#To view the sun, or breathe the vital air.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.5#But when, superior to the rage of woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.6#I stood restored and tears had ceased to flow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.7#Lenient of grief the pitying god began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.8#'Forget the brother, and resume the man.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.9#To Fate's supreme dispose the dead resign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.10#That care be Fate's, a speedy passage thine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.11#Still lives the wretch who wrought the death deplored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.12#But lives a victim for thy vengeful sword;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.13#Unless with filial rage Orestes glow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.14#And swift prevent the meditated blow:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.15#You timely will return a welcome guest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.39.16#With him to share the sad funereal feast."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.40.1#"He said: new thoughts my beating heart employ,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.40.2#My gloomy soul receives a gleam of joy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.40.3#Fair hope revives; and eager I address'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.40.4#The prescient godhead to reveal the rest:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.40.5#'The doom decreed of those disastrous two
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.40.6#I've heard with pain, but oh! the tale pursue;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.40.7#What third brave son of Mars the Fates constrain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.40.8#To roam the howling desert of the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.40.9#Or, in eternal shade of cold he lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.40.10#Provoke new sorrows from these grateful eyes.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.1#"'That chief (rejoin'd the god) his race derives
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.2#From Ithaca, and wondrous woes survives;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.3#Laertes' son: girt with circumfluous tides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.4#He still calamitous constraint abides.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.5#Him in Calypso's cave of late! view'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.6#When streaming grief his faded cheek bedow'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.7#But vain his prayer, his arts are vain, to move
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.8#The enamour'd goddess, or elude her love:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.9#His vessel sunk, and dear companions lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.10#He lives reluctant on a foreign coast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.11#But oh, beloved by Heaven! reserved to thee
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.12#A happier lot the smiling Fates decree:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.13#Free from that law, beneath whose mortal sway
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.14#Matter is changed, and varying forms decay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.15#Elysium shall be thine: the blissful plains
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.16#Of utmost earth, where Rhadamanthus reigns.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.17#Joys ever young, unmix'd with pain or fear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.18#Fill the wide circle of the eternal year:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.19#Stern winter smiles on that auspicious clime:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.20#The fields are florid with unfading prime;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.21#From the bleak pole no winds inclement blow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.22#Mould the round hail, or flake the fleecy snow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.23#But from the breezy deep the blest inhale
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.24#The fragrant murmurs of the western gale.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.25#This grace peculiar will the gods afford
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.41.26#To thee, the son of Jove, and beauteous Helen's lord.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.1#"He ceased, and plunging in the vast profound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.2#Beneath the god and whirling billows bound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.3#Then speeding back, involved in various thought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.4#My friends attending at the shore I sought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.5#Arrived, the rage of hunger we control
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.6#Till night with silent shade invests the pole;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.7#Then lose the cares of life in pleasing rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.8#Soon as the morn reveals the roseate east,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.9#With sails we wing the masts, our anchors weigh,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.10#Unmoor the fleet, and rush into the sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.11#Ranged on the banks, beneath our equal oars
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.12#White curl the waves, and the vex'd ocean roars
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.13#Then, steering backward from the Pharian isle,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.14#We gain the stream of Jove-descended Nile;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.15#There quit the ships, and on the destined shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.16#With ritual hecatombs the gods adore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.17#Their wrath atoned, to Agamemnon's name
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.18#A cenotaph I raise of deathless fame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.19#These rites to piety and grief discharged,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.20#The friendly gods a springing gale enlarged;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.21#The fleet swift tilting o'er the surges flew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.42.22#Till Grecian cliffs appear'd a blissful view!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.43.1#"Thy patient ear hath heard me long relate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.43.2#A story, fruitful of disastrous fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.43.3#And now, young prince, indulge my fond request;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.43.4#Be Sparta honoured with his royal guest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.43.5#Till, from his eastern goal, the joyous sun
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.43.6#His twelfth diurnal race begins to run.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.43.7#Meantime my train the friendly gifts prepare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.43.8#The sprightly coursers and a polish'd car;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.43.9#With these a goblet of capacious mould,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.43.10#Figured with art to dignify the gold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.43.11#(Form'd for libation to the gods), shall prove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.43.12#A pledge and monument of sacred love."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.1#"My quick return (young Ithacus rejoin'd),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.2#Damps the warm wishes of my raptured mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.3#Did not my fate my needful haste constrain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.4#Charm'd by your speech so graceful and humane,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.5#Lost in delight the circling year would roll,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.6#While deep attention fix'd my listening soul.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.7#But now to Pyle permit my destined way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.8#My loved associates chide my long delay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.9#In dear remembrance of your royal grace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.10#I take the present of the promised vase;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.11#The coursers, for the champaign sports retain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.12#That gift our barren rocks will render vain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.13#Horrid with cliffs, our meagre land allows
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.14#Thin herbage for the mountain goat to browse,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.15#But neither mead nor plain supplies, to feed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.16#The sprightly courser, or indulge his speed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.17#To sea-surrounded realms the gods assign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.44.18#Small tract of fertile lawn, the least to mine."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.45.1#His hand the king with tender passion press'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.45.2#And, smiling, thus the royal youth address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.45.3#"O early worth! a soul so wise, and young,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.45.4#Proclaims you from the sage Ulysses sprung.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.45.5#Selected from my stores, of matchless price,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.45.6#An urn shall recompense your prudent choice;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.45.7#By Vulcan's art, the verge with gold enchased.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.45.8#A pledge the sceptred power of Sidon gave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.45.9#When to his realm I plough'd the orient wave."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.46.1#Thus they alternate; while, with artful care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.46.2#The menial train the regal feast prepare.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.46.3#The firstlings of the flock are doom'd to die:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.46.4#Rich fragrant wines the cheering bowl supply;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.46.5#A female band the gift of Ceres bring;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.46.6#And the gilt roofs with genial triumph ring.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.47.1#Meanwhile, in Ithaca, the suitor powers
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.47.2#In active games divide their jovial hours;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.47.3#In areas varied with mosaic art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.47.4#Some whirl the disk, and some the javelin dart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.47.5#Aside, sequester'd from the vast resort,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.47.6#Antinous sole spectator of the sport;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.47.7#With great Eurymachus, of worth confess'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.47.8#And high descent, superior to the rest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.47.9#Whom young Noemon lowly thus address'd:--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.48.1#"My ship, equipp'd within the neighboring port,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.48.2#The prince, departing for the Pylian court,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.48.3#Requested for his speed; but, courteous, say
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.48.4#When steers he home, or why this long delay?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.48.5#For Elis I should sail with utmost speed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.48.6#To import twelve mares which there luxurious feed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.48.7#And twelve young mules, a strong laborious race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.48.8#New to the plow, unpractised in the trace."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.49.1#Unknowing of the course to Pyle design'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.49.2#A sudden horror seized on either mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.49.3#The prince in rural bower they fondly thought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.49.4#Numbering his flocks and herds, not far remote.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.49.5#"Relate (Antinous cries), devoid of guile,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.49.6#When spread the prince his sale for distant Pyle?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.49.7#Did chosen chiefs across the gulfy main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.49.8#Attend his voyage, or domestic train?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.49.9#Spontaneous did you speed his secret course,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.49.10#Or was the vessel seized by fraud or force?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.50.1#"With willing duty, not reluctant mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.50.2#(Noemon cried), the vessel was resign'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.50.3#Who, in the balance, with the great affairs
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.50.4#Of courts presume to weigh their private cares?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.50.5#With him, the peerage next in power to you;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.50.6#And Mentor, captain of the lordly crew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.50.7#Or some celestial in his reverend form,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.50.8#Safe from the secret rock and adverse storm,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.50.9#Pilot's the course; for when the glimmering ray
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.50.10#Of yester dawn disclosed the tender day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.50.11#Mentor himself I saw, and much admired,"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.50.12#Then ceased the youth, and from the court retired.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.51.1#Confounded and appall'd, the unfinish'd game
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.51.2#The suitors quit, and all to council came.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.51.3#Antinous first the assembled peers address'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.51.4#Rage sparkling in his eyes, and burning in his breast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.52.1#"O shame to manhood! shall one daring boy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.52.2#The scheme of all our happiness destroy?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.52.3#Fly unperceived, seducing half the flower
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.52.4#Of nobles, and invite a foreign power?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.52.5#The ponderous engine raised to crush us all,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.52.6#Recoiling, on his head is sure to fall.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.52.7#Instant prepare me, on the neighbouring strand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.52.8#With twenty chosen mates a vessel mann'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.52.9#For ambush'd close beneath the Samian shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.52.10#His ship returning shall my spies explore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.52.11#He soon his rashness shall with life atone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.52.12#Seek for his father's fate, but find his own."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.53.1#With vast applause the sentence all approve;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.53.2#Then rise, and to the feastful hall remove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.53.3#Swift to the queen the herald Medon ran,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.53.4#Who heard the consult of the dire divan:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.53.5#Before her dome the royal matron stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.53.6#And thus the message of his haste demands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.1#"What will the suitors? must my servant-train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.2#The allotted labours of the day refrain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.3#For them to form some exquisite repast?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.4#Heaven grant this festival may prove their last!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.5#Or, if they still must live, from me remove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.6#The double plague of luxury and love!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.7#Forbear, ye sons of insolence! forbear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.8#In riot to consume a wretched heir.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.9#In the young soul illustrious thought to raise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.10#Were ye not tutor'd with Ulysses' praise?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.11#Have not your fathers oft my lord defined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.12#Gentle of speech, beneficent of mind?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.13#Some kings with arbitrary rage devour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.14#Or in their tyrant-minions vest the power;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.15#Ulysses let no partial favours fall,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.16#The people's parent, he protected all;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.17#But absent now, perfidious and ingrate!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.54.18#His stores ye ravage, and usurp his state."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.55.1#He thus: "O were the woes you speak the worst!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.55.2#They form a deed more odious and accursed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.55.3#More dreadful than your boding soul divines;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.55.4#But pitying Jove avert the dire designs!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.55.5#The darling object of your royal care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.55.6#Is marked to perish in a deathful snare;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.55.7#Before he anchors in his native port,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.55.8#From Pyle re-sailing and the Spartan court;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.55.9#Horrid to speak! in ambush is decreed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.55.10#The hope and heir of Ithaca to bleed!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.56.1#Sudden she sunk beneath the weighty woes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.56.2#The vital streams a chilling horror froze;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.56.3#The big round tear stands trembling in her eye,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.56.4#And on her tongue imperfect accents die.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.56.5#At length in tender language interwove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.56.6#With sighs, she thus expressed her anxious love;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.56.7#"Why rarely would my son his fate explore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.56.8#Ride the wild waves, and quit the safer shore?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.56.9#Did he with all the greatly wretched, crave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.56.10#A blank oblivion, and untimely grave?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.57.1#"Tis not (replied the sage) to Medon given
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.57.2#To know, if some inhabitant of heaven
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.57.3#In his young breast the daring thought inspired
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.57.4#Or if, alone with filial duty fired,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.57.5#The winds end waves he tempts in early bloom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.57.6#Studious to learn his absent father's doom."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.58.1#The sage retired: unable to control
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.58.2#The mighty griefs that swell her labouring soul
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.58.3#Rolling convulsive on the floor is seen
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.58.4#The piteous object of a prostrate queen.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.58.5#Words to her dumb complaint a pause supplies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.58.6#And breath, to waste in unavailing cries.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.58.7#Around their sovereign wept the menial fair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.58.8#To whom she thus address'd her deep despair:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.1#"Behold a wretch whom all the gods consign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.2#To woe! Did ever sorrows equal mine?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.3#Long to my joys my dearest lord is lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.4#His country's buckler, and the Grecian boast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.5#Now from my fond embrace, by tempests torn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.6#Our other column of the state is borne;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.7#Nor took a kind adieu, nor sought consent!--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.8#Unkind confederates in his dire intent!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.9#Ill suits it with your shows of duteous zeal,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.10#From me the purposed voyage to conceal;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.11#Though at the solemn midnight hour he rose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.12#Why did you fear to trouble my repose?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.13#He either had obey'd my fond desire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.14#Or seen his mother pierced with grief expire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.15#Bid Dolius quick attend, the faithful slave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.16#Whom to my nuptial train Icarius gave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.17#To tend the fruit groves: with incessant speed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.18#He shall this violence of death decreed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.19#To good Laertes tell.  Experienced age
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.20#May timely intercept the ruffian rage.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.21#Convene the tribes the murderous plot reveal,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.59.22#And to their power to save his race appeal."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.1#Then Euryclea thus: "My dearest dread;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.2#Though to the sword I bow this hoary head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.3#Or if a dungeon be the pain decreed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.4#I own me conscious of the unpleasing deed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.5#Auxiliar to his flight, my aid implored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.6#With wine and viands I the vessel stored;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.7#A solemn oath, imposed, the secret seal'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.8#Till the twelfth dawn the light of day reveal'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.9#Dreading the effect of a fond mother's fear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.10#He dared not violate your royal ear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.11#But bathe, and, in imperial robes array'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.12#Pay due devotions to the martial maid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.13#And rest affianced in her guardian aid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.14#Send not to good Laertes, nor engage
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.15#In toils of state the miseries of age:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.16#Tis impious to surmise the powers divine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.17#To ruin doom the Jove-descended line;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.18#Long shall the race of just Arcesius reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.60.19#And isles remote enlarge his old domain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.61.1#The queen her speech with calm attention hears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.61.2#Her eyes restrain the silver-streaming tears:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.61.3#She bathes, and robed, the sacred dome ascends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.61.4#Her pious speed a female train attends:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.61.5#The salted cakes in canisters are laid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.61.6#And thus the queen invokes Minerva's aid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.62.1#"Daughter divine of Jove, whose arm can wield
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.62.2#The avenging bolt, and shake the dreadful shield
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.62.3#If e'er Ulysses to thy fane preferr'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.62.4#The best and choicest of his flock and herd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.62.5#Hear, goddess, hear, by those oblations won;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.62.6#And for the pious sire preserve the son;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.62.7#His wish'd return with happy power befriend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.62.8#And on the suitors let thy wrath descend."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.63.1#She ceased; shrill ecstasies of joy declare
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.63.2#The favouring goddess present to the prayer;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.63.3#The suitors heard, and deem'd the mirthful voice
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.63.4#A signal of her hymeneal choice;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.63.5#Whilst one most jovial thus accosts the board:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.64.1#"Too late the queen selects a second lord;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.64.2#In evil hour the nuptial rite intends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.64.3#When o'er her son disastrous death impends."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.64.4#Thus he, unskill'd of what the fates provide!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.64.5#But with severe rebuke Antinous cried:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.1#"These empty vaunts will make the voyage vain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.2#Alarm not with discourse the menial train:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.3#The great event with silent hope attend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.4#Our deeds alone our counsel must commend."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.5#His speech thus ended short, he frowning rose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.6#And twenty chiefs renowned for valour chose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.7#Down to the strand he speeds with haughty strides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.8#Where anchor'd in the bay the vessel rides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.9#Replete with mail and military store,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.10#In all her tackle trim to quit the shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.11#The desperate crew ascend, unfurl the sails
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.12#(The seaward prow invites the tardy gales);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.13#Then take repast till Hesperus display'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.65.14#His golden circlet, in the western shade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.1#Meantime the queen, without reflection due,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.2#Heart-wounded, to the bed of state withdrew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.3#In her sad breast the prince's fortunes roll,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.4#And hope and doubt alternate seize her soul.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.5#So when the woodman's toil her cave surrounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.6#And with the hunter's cry the grove resounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.7#With grief and rage the mother-lion stung.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.8#Fearless herself, yet trembles for her young
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.9#While pensive in the silent slumberous shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.10#Sleep's gentle powers her drooping eyes invade;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.11#Minerva, life-like, on embodied air
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.12#Impress'd the form of Iphthima the fair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.13#(Icarius' daughter she, whose blooming charms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.14#Allured Eumelus to her virgin arms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.15#A sceptred lord, who o'er the fruitful plain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.16#Of Thessaly wide stretched his ample reign:)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.17#As Pallas will'd, along the sable skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.18#To calm the queen, the phantom sister flies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.19#Swift on the regal dome, descending right,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.20#The bolted valves are pervious to her flight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.21#Close to her head the pleasing vision stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.66.22#And thus performs Minerva's high commands
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.67.1#"O why, Penelope, this causeless fear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.67.2#To render sleep's soft blessing unsincere?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.67.3#Alike devote to sorrow's dire extreme
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.67.4#The day-reflection, and the midnight-dream!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.67.5#Thy son the gods propitious will restore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.67.6#And bid thee cease his absence to deplore."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.1#To whom the queen (whilst yet in pensive mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.2#Was in the silent gates of sleep confined):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.3#"O sister to my soul forever dear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.4#Why this first visit to reprove my fear?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.5#How in a realm so distant should you know
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.6#From what deep source ceaseless sorrows flow?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.7#To all my hope my royal lord is lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.8#His country's buckler, and the Grecian boast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.9#And with consummate woe to weigh me down,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.10#The heir of all his honours and his crown,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.11#My darling son is fled! an easy prey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.12#To the fierce storms, or men more fierce than they;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.13#Who, in a league of blood associates sworn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.68.14#Will intercept the unwary youth's return."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.69.1#"Courage resume (the shadowy form replied);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.69.2#In the protecting care of Heaven confide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.69.3#On him attends the blue eyed martial maid:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.69.4#What earthly can implore a surer aid?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.69.5#Me now the guardian goddess deigns to send,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.69.6#To bid thee patient his return attend."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.70.1#The queen replies: "If in the blest abodes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.70.2#A goddess, thou hast commerce with the gods;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.70.3#Say, breathes my lord the blissful realm of light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.70.4#Or lies he wrapp'd in ever-during night?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.71.1#"Inquire not of his doom, (the phantom cries,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.71.2#I speak not all the counsel of the skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.71.3#Nor must indulge with vain discourse, or long,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.71.4#The windy satisfaction of the tongue."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.72.1#Swift through the valves the visionary fair
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.72.2#Repass'd, and viewless mix'd with common air.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.72.3#The queen awakes, deliver'd of her woes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.72.4#With florid joy her heart dilating glows:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.72.5#The vision, manifest of future fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.72.6#Makes her with hope her son's arrival wait.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.73.1#Meantime the suitors plough the watery plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.73.2#Telemachus in thought already slain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.73.3#When sight of lessening Ithaca was lost
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.73.4#Their sail directed for the Samian coast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.73.5#A small but verdant isle appear'd in view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.73.6#And Asteris the advancing pilot knew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.73.7#An ample port the rocks projected form,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.73.8#To break the rolling waves and ruffling storm:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.73.9#That safe recess they gain with happy speed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:4.73.10#And in close ambush wait the murderous deed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.1#The saffron morn, with early blushes spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.2#Now rose refulgent from Tithonus' bed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.3#With new-born day to gladden mortal sight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.4#And gild the courts of heaven with sacred light.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.5#Then met the eternal synod of the sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.6#Before the god, who thunders from on high,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.7#Supreme in might, sublime in majesty.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.8#Pallas, to these, deplores the unequal fates
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.9#Of wise Ulysses and his toils relates:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.10#Her hero's danger touch'd the pitying power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.11#The nymph's seducements, and the magic bower.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.12#Thus she began her plaint:  "Immortal Jove!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.13#And you who fill the blissful seats above!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.14#Let kings no more with gentle mercy sway,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.15#Or bless a people willing to obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.16#But crush the nations with an iron rod,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.17#And every monarch be the scourge of God.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.18#If from your thoughts Ulysses you remove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.19#Who ruled his subjects with a father's love,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.20#Sole in an isle, encircled by the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.21#Abandon'd, banish'd from his native reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.22#Unbless'd he sighs, detained by lawless charms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.23#And press'd unwilling in Calypso's arms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.24#Nor friends are there, nor vessels to convey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.25#Nor oars to cut the immeasurable way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.26#And now fierce traitors, studious to destroy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.27#His only son, their ambush'd fraud employ;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.28#Who, pious, following his great father's fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.1.29#To sacred Pylos and to Sparta came."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.2.1#"What words are these? (replied the power who forms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.2.2#The clouds of night, and darkens heaven with storms;)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.2.3#Is not already in thy soul decreed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.2.4#The chief's return shall make the guilty bleed?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.2.5#What cannot Wisdom do? Thou may'st restore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.2.6#The son in safety to his native shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.2.7#While the fell foes, who late in ambush lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.2.8#With fraud defeated measure back their way."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.1#Then thus to Hermes the command was given:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.2#"Hermes, thou chosen messenger of heaven!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.3#Go, to the nymph be these our orders borne
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.4#'Tis Jove's decree, Ulysses shall return:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.5#The patient man shall view his old abodes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.6#Nor helped by mortal hand, nor guiding gods
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.7#In twice ten days shall fertile Scheria find,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.8#Alone, and floating to the wave and wind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.9#The bold Phaecians there, whose haughty line
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.10#Is mixed with gods, half human, half divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.11#The chief shall honour as some heavenly guest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.12#And swift transport him to his place of rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.13#His vessels loaded with a plenteous store
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.14#Of brass, of vestures, and resplendent ore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.15#(A richer prize than if his joyful isle
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.16#Received him charged with Ilion's noble spoil),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.17#His friends, his country, he shall see, though late:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.3.18#Such is our sovereign will, and such is fate."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.1#He spoke. The god who mounts the winged winds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.2#Fast to his feet the golden pinions binds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.3#That high through fields of air his flight sustain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.4#O'er the wide earth, and o'er the boundless main:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.5#He grasps the wand that causes sleep to fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.6#Or in soft slumber seals the wakeful eye;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.7#Then shoots from heaven to high Pieria's steep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.8#And stoops incumbent on the rolling deep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.9#So watery fowl, that seek their fishy food,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.10#With wings expanded o'er the foaming flood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.11#Now sailing smooth the level surface sweep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.12#Now dip their pinions in the briny deep;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.13#Thus o'er the word of waters Hermes flew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.14#Till now the distant island rose in view:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.15#Then, swift ascending from the azure wave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.16#he took the path that winded to the cave.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.17#Large was the grot, in which the nymph he found
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.18#(The fair-hair'd nymph with every beauty crown'd).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.19#The cave was brighten'd with a rising blaze;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.20#Cedar and frankincense, an odorous pile,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.21#Flamed on the hearth, and wide perfumed the isle;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.22#While she with work and song the time divides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.23#And through the loom the golden shuttle guides.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.24#Without the grot a various sylvan scene
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.25#Appear'd around, and groves of living green;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.26#Poplars and alders ever quivering play'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.27#And nodding cypress form'd a fragrant shade:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.28#On whose high branches, waving with the storm,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.29#The birds of broadest wing their mansions form,--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.30#The chough, the sea-mew, the loquacious crow,--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.31#and scream aloft, and skim the deeps below.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.32#Depending vines the shelving cavern screen.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.33#With purple clusters blushing through the green.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.34#Four limped fountains from the clefts distil:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.35#And every fountain pours a several rill,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.36#In mazy windings wandering down the hill:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.37#Where bloomy meads with vivid greens were crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.38#And glowing violets threw odours round.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.39#A scene, where, if a god should cast his sight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.40#A god might gaze, and wander with delight!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.41#Joy touch'd the messenger of heaven: he stay'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.42#Entranced, and all the blissful haunts surveyed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.43#Him, entering in the cave, Calypso knew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.44#For powers celestial to each other's view
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.45#Stand still confess'd, though distant far they lie
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.46#To habitants of earth, or sea, or sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.47#But sad Ulysses, by himself apart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.48#Pour'd the big sorrows of his swelling heard;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.49#All on the lonely shore he sate to weep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.50#And roll'd his eyes around the restless deep:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.51#Toward his loved coast he roll'd his eyes in vain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.4.52#Till, dimm'd with rising grief, they stream'd again.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.5.1#Now graceful seated on her shining throne,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.5.2#To Hermes thus the nymph divine begun:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.6.1#"God of the golden wand! on what behest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.6.2#Arrivest thou here, an unexpected guest?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.6.3#Loved as thou art, thy free injunctions lay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.6.4#'Tis mine with joy and duty to obey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.6.5#Till now a stranger, in a happy hour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.6.6#Approach, and taste the dainties of my bower."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.7.1#Thus having spoke, the nymph the table spread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.7.2#(Ambrosial cates, with nectar rosy-red);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.7.3#Hermes the hospitable rite partook,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.7.4#Divine refection! then, recruited, spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.1#"What moves this journey from my native sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.2#A goddess asks, nor can a god deny.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.3#Hear then the truth. By mighty Jove's command
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.4#Unwilling have I trod this pleasing land:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.5#For who, self-moved, with weary wing would sweep
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.6#Such length of ocean and unmeasured deep;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.7#A world of waters! far from all the ways
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.8#Where men frequent, or sacred altars blaze!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.9#But to Jove's will submission we must pay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.10#What power so great to dare to disobey?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.11#A man, he says, a man resides with thee,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.12#Of all his kind most worn with misery.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.13#The Greeks, (whose arms for nine long year employ'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.14#Their force on Ilion, in the tenth destroy'd,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.15#At length, embarking in a luckless hour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.16#With conquest proud, incensed Minerva's power:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.17#Hence on the guilty race her vengeance hurl'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.18#With storms pursued them through the liquid world.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.19#There all his vessels sunk beneath the wave!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.20#There all his dear companions found their grave!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.21#Saved from the jaws of death by Heaven's decree,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.22#The tempest drove him to these shores and thee.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.23#Him, Jove now orders to his native lands
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.24#Straight to dismiss: so destiny commands:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.25#Impatient Fate his near return attends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.8.26#And calls him to his country, and his friends."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.1#E'en to her inmost soul the goddess shook;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.2#Then thus her anguish, and her passion broke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.3#"Ungracious gods! with spite and envy cursed!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.4#Still to your own ethereal race the worst!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.5#Ye envy mortal and immortal joy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.6#And love, the only sweet of life destroy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.7#Did ever goddess by her charms engage
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.8#A favour'd mortal, and not feel your rage?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.9#So when Aurora sought Orion's love,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.10#Her joys disturbed your blissful hours above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.11#Till, in Ortygia Dian's winged dart
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.12#Had pierced the hapless hunter to the heart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.13#So when the covert of the thrice-eared field
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.14#Saw stately Ceres to her passion yield,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.15#Scarce could Iasion taste her heavenly charms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.16#But Jove's swift lightning scorched him in her arms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.17#And is it now my turn, ye mighty powers!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.18#Am I the envy of your blissful bowers?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.19#A man, an outcast to the storm and wave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.20#It was my crime to pity, and to save;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.21#When he who thunders rent his bark in twain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.22#And sunk his brave companions in the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.23#Alone, abandon'd, in mid-ocean tossed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.24#The sport of winds, and driven from every coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.25#Hither this man of miseries I led,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.26#Received the friendless, and the hungry fed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.27#Nay promised (vainly promised) to bestow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.28#Immortal life, exempt from age and woe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.29#'Tis past-and Jove decrees he shall remove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.30#Gods as we are, we are but slaves to Jove.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.31#Go then he must (he must, if he ordain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.32#Try all those dangers, all those deeps, again);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.33#But never, never shall Calypso send
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.34#To toils like these her husband and her friend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.35#What ships have I, what sailors to convey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.36#What oars to cut the long laborious way?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.37#Yet I'll direct the safest means to go;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.9.38#That last advice is all I can bestow."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.1#To her the power who hears the charming rod;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.2#"Dismiss the man, nor irritate the god;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.3#Prevent the rage of him who reigns above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.4#For what so dreadful as the wrath of Jove?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.5#Thus having said, he cut the cleaving sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.6#And in a moment vanished from her eye,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.7#The nymph, obedient to divine command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.8#To seek Ulysses, paced along the sand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.9#Him pensive on the lonely beach she found,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.10#With streaming eyes in briny torrents drown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.11#And inly pining for his native shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.12#For now the soft enchantress pleased no more;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.13#For now, reluctant, and constrained by charms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.14#Absent he lay in her desiring arms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.15#In slumber wore the heavy night away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.16#On rocks and shores consumed the tedious day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.17#There sate all desolate, and sighed alone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.18#With echoing sorrows made the mountains groan.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.19#And roll'd his eyes o'er all the restless main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.10.20#Till, dimmed with  rising grief, they streamed again.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.1#Here, on his musing mood the goddess press'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.2#Approaching soft, and thus the chief address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.3#"Unhappy man! to wasting woes a prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.4#No more in sorrows languish life away:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.5#Free as the winds I give thee now to rove:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.6#Go, fell the timber of yon lofty grove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.7#And form a raft, and build the rising ship,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.8#Sublime to bear thee o'er the gloomy deep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.9#To store the vessel let the care be mine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.10#With water from the rock and rosy wine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.11#And life-sustaining bread, and fair array,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.12#And prosperous gales to waft thee on the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.13#These, if the gods with my desire comply
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.14#(The gods, alas, more mighty far than I,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.15#And better skill'd in dark events to come),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.11.16#In peace shall land thee at thy native home."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.12.1#With sighs Ulysses heard the words she spoke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.12.2#Then thus his melancholy silence broke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.12.3#"Some other motive, goddess! sways thy mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.12.4#(Some close design, or turn of womankind),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.12.5#Nor my return the end, nor this the way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.12.6#On a slight raft to pass the swelling sea,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.12.7#Huge, horrid, vast! where scarce in safety sails
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.12.8#The best-built ship, though Jove inspires the gales.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.12.9#The bold proposal how shall I fulfil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.12.10#Dark as I am, unconscious of thy will?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.12.11#Swear, then, thou mean'st not what my soul forebodes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.12.12#Swear by the solemn oath that binds the gods."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.1#Him, while he spoke, with smiles Calypso eyed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.2#And gently grasp'd his hand, and thus replied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.3#"This shows thee, friend, by old experience taught,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.4#And learn'd in all the wiles of human thought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.5#How prone to doubt, how cautious, are the wise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.6#But hear, O earth, and hear, ye sacred skies!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.7#And thou, O Styx! whose formidable floods
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.8#Glide through the shades, and bind the attesting gods!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.9#No form'd design, no meditated end,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.10#Lurks in the counsel of thy faithful friend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.11#Kind the persuasion, and sincere my aim;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.12#The same my practice, were my fate the same.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.13#Heaven has not cursed me with a heart of steel,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.13.14#But given the sense to pity, and to feel."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.14.1#Thus having said, the goddess marched before:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.14.2#He trod her footsteps in the sandy shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.14.3#At the cool cave arrived, they took their state;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.14.4#He filled the throne where Mercury had sate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.14.5#For him the nymph a rich repast ordains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.14.6#Such as the mortal life of man sustains;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.14.7#Before herself were placed the the cates divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.14.8#Ambrosial banquet and celestial wine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.14.9#Their hunger satiate, and their thirst repress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.14.10#Thus spoke Calypso to her godlike guest:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.1#"Ulysses! (with a sigh she thus began;)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.2#O sprung from gods! in wisdom more than man!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.3#Is then thy home the passion of thy heart?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.4#Thus wilt thou leave me, are we thus to part?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.5#Farewell! and ever joyful mayst thou be,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.6#Nor break the transport with one thought of me.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.7#But ah, Ulysses! wert thou given to know
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.8#What Fate yet dooms these still to undergo,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.9#Thy heart might settle in this scene of ease.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.10#And e'en these slighted charms might learn to please.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.11#A willing goddess, and immortal life.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.12#Might banish from thy mind an absent wife.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.13#Am I inferior to a mortal dame?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.14#Less soft my feature less august my frame?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.15#Or shall the daughters of mankind compare
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.15.16#Their earth born beauties with the heavenly fair?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.1#"Alas! for this (the prudent man replies)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.2#Against Ulysses shall thy anger rise?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.3#Loved and adored, O goddess as thou art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.4#Forgive the weakness of a human heart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.5#Though well I see thy graces far above
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.6#The dear, though mortal, object of my love,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.7#Of youth eternal well the difference know,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.8#And the short date of fading charms below;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.9#Yet every day, while absent thus I roam,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.10#I languish to return and die at home.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.11#Whate'er the gods shall destine me to bear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.12#In the black ocean or the watery war,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.13#'Tis mine to master with a constant mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.14#Inured to perils, to the worst resign'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.15#By seas, by wars, so many dangers run;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.16.16#Still I can suffer; their high will he done!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.1#Thus while he spoke, the beamy sun descends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.2#And rising night her friendly shade extends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.3#To the close grot the lonely pair remove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.4#And slept delighted with the gifts of love.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.5#When rose morning call'd them from their rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.6#Ulysses robed him in the cloak and vest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.7#The nymph's fair head a veil transparent graced,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.8#Her swelling loins a radiant zone embraced
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.9#With flowers of gold; an under robe, unbound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.10#In snowy waves flow'd glittering on the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.11#Forth issuing thus, she gave him first to wield
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.12#A weighty axe with truest temper steeled,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.13#And double-edged; the handle smooth and plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.14#Wrought of the clouded olive's easy grain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.15#And next, a wedge to drive with sweepy sway
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.16#Then to the neighboring forest led the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.17#On the lone island's utmost verge there stood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.18#Of poplars, pine, and firs, a lofty wood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.19#Whose leafless summits to the skies aspire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.20#Scorch'd by the sun, or seared by heavenly fire
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.21#(Already dried).  These pointing out to view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.17.22#The nymph just show'd him, and with tears withdrew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.1#Now toils the hero: trees on trees o'erthrown
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.2#Fall crackling round him, and the forests groan:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.3#Sudden, full twenty on the plain are strow'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.4#And lopp'd and lighten'd of their branchy load.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.5#At equal angles these disposed to join,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.6#He smooth'd and squared them by the rule and line,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.7#(The wimbles for the work Calypso found)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.8#With those he pierced them and with clinchers bound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.9#Long and capacious as a shipwright forms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.10#Some bark's broad bottom to out-ride the storms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.11#So large he built the raft; then ribb'd it strong
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.12#From space to space, and nail'd the planks along;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.13#These form'd the sides: the deck he fashion'd last;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.14#Then o'er the vessel raised the taper mast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.15#With crossing sail-yards dancing in the wind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.16#And to the helm the guiding rudder join'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.17#(With yielding osiers fenced, to break the force
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.18#Of surging waves, and steer the steady course).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.19#Thy loom, Calypso, for the future sails
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.20#Supplied the cloth, capacious of the gales.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.21#With stays and cordage last he rigged the ship,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.18.22#And, roll'd on levers, launch'd her in the deep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.19.1#Four days were pass'd, and now the work complete,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.19.2#Shone the fifth morn, when from her sacred seat
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.19.3#The nymph dismiss'd him (odorous garments given),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.19.4#And bathed in fragrant oils that breathed of heaven:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.19.5#Then fill'd two goatskins with her hands divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.19.6#With water one, and one with sable wine:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.19.7#Of every kind, provisions heaved aboard;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.19.8#And the full decks with copious viands stored.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.19.9#The goddess, last, a gentle breeze supplies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.19.10#To curl old Ocean, and to warm the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.1#And now, rejoicing in the prosperous gales,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.2#With beating heart Ulysses spreads his sails;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.3#Placed at the helm he sate, and mark'd the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.4#Nor closed in sleep his ever-watchful eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.5#There view'd the Pleiads, and the Northern Team,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.6#And great Orion's more refulgent beam.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.7#To which, around the axle of the sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.8#The Bear, revolving, points his golden eye:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.9#Who shines exalted on the ethereal plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.10#Nor bathes his blazing forehead in the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.11#Far on the left those radiant fires to keep
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.12#The nymph directed, as he sail'd the deep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.13#Full seventeen nights he cut the foaming way:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.14#The distant land appear'd the following day:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.15#Then swell'd to sight Phaeacia's dusky coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.16#And woody mountains, half in vapours lost;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.17#That lay before him indistinct and vast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.20.18#Like a broad shield amid the watery waste.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.1#But him, thus voyaging the deeps below,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.2#From far, on Solyme's aerial brow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.3#The king of ocean saw, and seeing burn'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.4#(From AEthiopia's happy climes return'd);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.5#The raging monarch shook his azure head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.6#And thus in secret to his soul he said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.7#"Heavens! how uncertain are the powers on high!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.8#Is then reversed the sentence of the sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.9#In one man's favour; while a distant guest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.10#I shared secure the AEthiopian feast?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.11#Behold how near Phoenecia's land he draws;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.12#The land affix'd by Fate's eternal laws
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.13#To end his toils. Is then our anger vain?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.21.14#No; if this sceptre yet commands the main."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.22.1#He spoke, and high the forky trident hurl'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.22.2#Rolls clouds on clouds, and stirs the watery world,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.22.3#At once the face of earth and sea deforms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.22.4#Swells all the winds, and rouses all the storms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.22.5#Down rushed the night: east, west, together roar;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.22.6#And south and north roll mountains to the shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.22.7#Then shook the hero, to despair resign'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.22.8#And question'd thus his yet unconquer'd mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.1#"Wretch that I am! what farther fates attend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.2#This life of toils, and what my destined end?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.3#Too well, alas! the island goddess knew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.4#On the black sea what perils should ensue.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.5#New horrors now this destined head inclose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.6#Untill'd is yet the measure of my woes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.7#With what a cloud the brows of heaven are crown'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.8#What raging winds! what roaring waters round!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.9#'Tis Jove himself the swelling tempest rears;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.10#Death, present death, on every side appears.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.11#Happy! thrice happy! who, in battle slain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.12#Press'd in Atrides' cause the Trojan plain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.13#Oh! had I died before that well-fought wall!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.14#Had some distinguish'd day renown'd my fall
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.15#(Such as was that when showers of javelins fled
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.16#From conquering Troy around Achilles dead),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.17#All Greece had paid me solemn funerals then,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.18#And spread my glory with the sons of men.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.19#A shameful fate now hides my hapless head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.23.20#Unwept, unnoted, and for ever dead!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.1#A mighty wave rush'd o'er him as he spoke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.2#The raft is cover'd, and the mast is broke;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.3#Swept from the deck and from the rudder torn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.4#Far on the swelling surge the chief was borne;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.5#While by the howling tempest rent in twain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.6#Flew sail and sail-yards rattling o'er the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.7#Long-press'd, he heaved beneath the weighty wave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.8#Clogg'd by the cumbrous vest Calypso gave;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.9#At length, emerging, from his nostrils wide
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.10#And gushing mouth effused the briny tide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.11#E'en then not mindless of his last retreat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.12#He seized the raft, and leap'd into his seat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.13#Strong with the fear of death.  In rolling flood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.14#Now here, now there, impell'd the floating wood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.15#As when a heap of gather'd thorns is cast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.16#Now to, now fro, before the autumnal blast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.17#Together clung, it rolls around the field;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.18#So roll'd the float, and so its texture held:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.19#And now the south, and now the north, bear sway,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.20#And now the east the foamy floods obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.21#And now the west wind whirls it o'er the sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.22#The wandering chief with toils on toils oppress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.23#Leucothea saw, and pity touch'd her breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.24#(Herself a mortal once, of Cadmus' strain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.25#But now an azure sister of the main)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.26#Swift as a sea-mew springing from the flood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.27#All radiant on the raft the goddess stood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.28#Then thus address'd him: "Thou whom heaven decrees
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.29#To Neptune's wrath, stern tyrant of the seas!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.30#(Unequal contest!) not his rage and power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.31#Great as he is, such virtue shall devour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.32#What I suggest, thy wisdom will perform:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.33#Forsake thy float, and leave it to the storm;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.34#Strip off thy garments; Neptune's fury brave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.35#With naked strength, and plunge into the wave.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.36#To reach Phaeacia all thy nerves extend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.37#There Fate decrees thy miseries shall end.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.38#This heavenly scarf beneath thy bosom bind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.39#And live; give all thy terrors to the wind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.40#Soon as thy arms the happy shore shall gain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.41#Return the gift, and cast it in the main:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.42#Observe my orders, and with heed obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.24.43#Cast it far off, and turn thy eyes away."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.25.1#With that, her hand the sacred veil bestows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.25.2#Then down the deeps she dived from whence she rose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.25.3#A moment snatch'd the shining form away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.25.4#And all was covered with the curling sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.1#Struck with amaze, yet still to doubt inclined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.2#He stands suspended, and explores his mind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.3#"What shall I do? unhappy me! who knows
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.4#But other gods intend me other woes?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.5#Whoe'er thou art, I shall not blindly join
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.6#Thy pleaded reason, but consult with mine:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.7#For scarce in ken appears that distant isle
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.8#Thy voice foretells me shall conclude my toil.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.9#Thus then I judge: while yet the planks sustain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.10#The wild waves' fury, here I fix'd remain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.11#But, when their texture to the tempest yields,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.12#I launch adventurous on the liquid fields,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.13#Join to the help of gods the strength of man,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.26.14#And take this method, since the best I can."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.1#While thus his thoughts an anxious council hold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.2#The raging god a watery mountain roll'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.3#Like a black sheet the whelming billows spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.4#Burst o'er the float, and thunder'd on his head.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.5#Planks, beams, disparted fly; the scatter'd wood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.6#Rolls diverse, and in fragments strews the flood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.7#So the rude Boreas, o'er the field new-shorn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.8#Tosses and drives the scatter'd heaps of corn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.9#And now a single beam the chief bestrides:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.10#There poised a while above the bounding tides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.11#His limbs discumbers of the clinging vest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.12#And binds the sacred cincture round his breast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.13#Then prone an ocean in a moment flung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.14#Stretch'd wide his eager arms, and shot the seas along.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.15#All naked now, on heaving billows laid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.27.16#Stern Neptune eyed him, and contemptuous said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.28.1#"Go, learn'd in woes, and other foes essay!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.28.2#Go, wander helpless on the watery way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.28.3#Thus, thus find out the destined shore, and then
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.28.4#(If Jove ordains it) mix with happier men.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.28.5#Whate'er thy fate, the ills our wrath could raise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.28.6#Shall last remember'd in thy best of days."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.1#This said, his sea-green steeds divide the foam,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.2#And reach high Aegae and the towery dome.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.3#Now, scarce withdrawn the fierce earth-shaking power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.4#Jove's daughter Pallas watch'd the favouring hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.5#Back to their caves she bade the winds to fly;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.6#And hush'd the blustering brethren of the sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.7#The drier blasts alone of Boreas away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.8#And bear him soft on broken waves away;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.9#With gentle force impelling to that shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.10#Where fate has destined he shall toil no more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.11#And now, two nights, and now two days were pass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.12#Since wide he wander'd on the watery waste;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.13#Heaved on the surge with intermitting breath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.14#And hourly panting in the arms of death.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.15#The third fair morn now blazed upon the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.16#Then glassy smooth lay all the liquid plain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.17#The winds were hush'd, the billows scarcely curl'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.18#And a dead silence still'd the watery world;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.19#When lifted on a ridgy wave he spies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.20#The land at distance, and with sharpen'd eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.21#As pious children joy with vast delight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.22#When a loved sire revives before their sight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.23#(Who, lingering along, has call'd on death in vain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.24#Fix'd by some demon to his bed of pain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.25#Till heaven by miracle his life restore);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.26#So joys Ulysses at the appearing shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.27#And sees (and labours onward as he sees)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.28#The rising forests, and the tufted trees.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.29#And now, as near approaching as the sound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.30#Of human voice the listening ear may wound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.31#Amidst the rocks he heard a hollow roar
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.32#Of murmuring surges breaking on the shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.33#Nor peaceful port was there, nor winding bay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.34#To shield the vessel from the rolling sea,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.35#But cliffs and shaggy shores, a dreadful sight!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.36#All rough with rocks, with foamy billows white.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.37#Fear seized his slacken'd limbs and beating heart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.29.38#As thus he communed with his soul apart;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.1#"Ah me! when, o'er a length of waters toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.2#These eyes at last behold the unhoped-for coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.3#No port receives me from the angry main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.4#But the loud deeps demand me back again.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.5#Above, sharp rocks forbid access; around
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.6#Roar the wild waves; beneath, is sea profound!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.7#No footing sure affords the faithless sand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.8#To stem too rapid, and too deep to stand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.9#If here I enter, my efforts are vain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.10#Dash'd on the cliffs, or heaved into the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.11#Or round the island if my course I bend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.12#Where the ports open, or the shores descend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.13#Back to the seas the rolling surge may sweep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.14#And bury all my hopes beneath the deep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.15#Or some enormous whale the god may send
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.16#(For many such an Amphitrite attend);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.17#Too well the turns of mortal chance I know,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.18#And hate relentless of my heavenly foe."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.19#While thus he thought, a monstrous wave upbore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.20#The chief, and dash'd him on the craggy shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.21#Torn was his skin, nor had the ribs been whole,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.22#But Instant Pallas enter'd in his soul.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.23#Close to the cliff with both his hands he clung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.24#And stuck adherent, and suspended hung;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.25#Till the huge surge roll'd off; then backward sweep
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.26#The refluent tides, and plunge him in the deep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.27#As when the polypus, from forth his cave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.28#Torn with full force, reluctant beats the wave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.29#His ragged claws are stuck with stones and sands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.30#So the rough rock had shagg'd Ulysses hands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.31#And now had perish'd, whelm'd beneath the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.32#The unhappy man; e'en fate had been in vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.33#But all-subduing Pallas lent her power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.34#And prudence saved him in the needful hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.35#Beyond the beating surge his course he bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.36#(A wider circle, but in sight of shore),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.37#With longing eyes, observing, to survey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.38#Some smooth ascent, or safe sequester'd bay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.39#Between the parting rocks at length he spied
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.40#A failing stream with gentler waters glide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.41#Where to the seas the shelving shore declined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.42#And form'd a bay impervious to the wind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.43#To this calm port the glad Ulysses press'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.30.44#And hail'd the river, and its god address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.31.1#"Whoe'er thou art, before whose stream unknown
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.31.2#I bend, a suppliant at thy watery throne,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.31.3#Hear, azure king! nor let me fly in vain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.31.4#To thee from Neptune and the raging main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.31.5#Heaven hears and pities hapless men like me,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.31.6#For sacred even to gods is misery:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.31.7#Let then thy waters give the weary rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.31.8#And save a suppliant, and a man distress'd."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.1#He pray'd, and straight the gentle stream subsides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.2#Detains the rushing current of his tides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.3#Before the wanderer smooths the watery way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.4#And soft receives him from the rolling sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.5#That moment, fainting as he touch'd the shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.6#He dropp'd his sinewy arms: his knees no more
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.7#Perform'd their office, or his weight upheld:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.8#His swoln heart heaved; his bloated body swell'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.9#From mouth and nose the briny torrent ran;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.10#And lost in lassitude lay all the man,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.11#Deprived of voice, of motion, and of breath;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.12#The soul scarce waking in the arms of death.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.13#Soon as warm life its wonted office found,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.14#The mindful chief Leucothea's scarf unbound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.15#Observant of her word, he turn'd aside
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.16#HIs head, and cast it on the rolling tide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.17#Behind him far, upon the purple waves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.32.18#The waters waft it, and the nymph receives.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.33.1#Now parting from the stream, Ulysses found
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.33.2#A mossy bank with pliant rushes crown'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.33.3#The bank he press'd, and gently kiss'd the ground;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.33.4#Where on the flowery herb as soft he lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.33.5#Thus to his soul the sage began to say:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.34.1#"What will ye next ordain, ye powers on high!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.34.2#And yet, ah yet, what fates are we to try?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.34.3#Here by the stream, if I the night out-wear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.34.4#Thus spent already, how shall nature bear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.34.5#The dews descending, and nocturnal air;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.34.6#Or chilly vapours breathing from the flood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.34.7#When morning rises?--If I take the wood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.34.8#And in thick shelter of innumerous boughs
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.34.9#Enjoy the comfort gentle sleep allows;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.34.10#Though fenced from cold, and though my toil be pass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.34.11#What savage beasts may wander in the waste?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.34.12#Perhaps I yet may fall a bloody prey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.34.13#To prowling bears, or lions in the way."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.1#Thus long debating in himself he stood:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.2#At length he took the passage to the wood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.3#Whose shady horrors on a rising brow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.4#Waved high, and frown'd upon the stream below.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.5#There grew two olives, closest of the grove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.6#With roots entwined, the branches interwove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.7#Alike their leaves, but not alike they smiled
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.8#With sister-fruits; one fertile, one was wild.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.9#Nor here the sun's meridian rays had power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.10#Nor wind sharp-piercing, nor the rushing shower;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.11#The verdant arch so close its texture kept:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.12#Beneath this covert great Ulysses crept.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.13#Of gather'd leaves an ample bed he made
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.14#(Thick strewn by tempest through the bowery shade);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.15#Where three at least might winter's cold defy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.16#Though Boreas raged along the inclement sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.17#This store with joy the patient hero found,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.18#And, sunk amidst them, heap'd the leaves around.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.19#As some poor peasant, fated to reside
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.20#Remote from neighbours in a forest wide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.21#Studious to save what human wants require,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.22#In embers heap'd, preserves the seeds of fire:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.23#Hid in dry foliage thus Ulysses lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.24#Till Pallas pour'd soft slumbers on his eyes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.25#And golden dreams (the gift of sweet repose)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:5.35.26#Lull'd all his cares, and banish'd all his woes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.1#While thus the weary wanderer sunk to rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.2#And peaceful slumbers calmed his anxious breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.3#The martial maid from heavens aerial height
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.4#Swift to Phaeacia wing'd her rapid flight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.5#In elder times the soft Phaeacian train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.6#In ease possess'd the wide Hyperian plain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.7#Till the Cyclopean race in arms arose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.8#A lawless nation of gigantic foes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.9#Then great Nausithous from Hyperia far,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.10#Through seas retreating from the sounds of war,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.11#The recreant nation to fair Scheria led,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.12#Where never science rear'd her laurell'd head;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.13#There round his tribes a strength of wall he raised;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.14#To heaven the glittering domes and temples blazed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.15#Just to his realms, he parted grounds from grounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.16#And shared the lands, and gave the lands their bounds.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.17#Now in the silent grave the monarch lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.1.18#And wise Alcinous held the legal sway.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.2.1#To his high palace through the fields of air
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.2.2#The goddess shot; Ulysses was her care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.2.3#There, as the night in silence roll'd away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.2.4#A heaven of charms divine Nausicaa lay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.2.5#Through the thick gloom the shining portals blaze;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.2.6#Two nymphs the portals guard, each nymph a Grace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.2.7#Light as the viewless air the warrior maid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.2.8#Glides through the valves, and hovers round her head;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.2.9#A favourite virgin's blooming form she took,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.2.10#From Dymas sprung, and thus the vision spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.1#"Oh Indolent! to waste thy hours away!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.2#And sleep'st thou careless of the bridal day!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.3#Thy spousal ornament neglected lies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.4#Arise, prepare the bridal train, arise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.5#A just applause the cares of dress impart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.6#And give soft transport to a parent's heart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.7#Haste, to the limpid stream direct thy way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.8#When the gay morn unveils her smiling ray;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.9#Haste to the stream! companion of thy care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.10#Lo, I thy steps attend, thy labours share.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.11#Virgin, awake! the marriage hour is nigh,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.12#See from their thrones thy kindred monarchs sigh!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.13#The royal car at early dawn obtain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.14#And order mules obedient to the rein;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.15#For rough the way, and distant rolls the wave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.16#Where their fair vests Phaeacian virgins lave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.17#In pomp ride forth; for pomp becomes the great
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.18#And majesty derives a grace from state."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.19#Then to the palaces of heaven she sails,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.20#Incumbent on the wings of wafting gales;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.21#The seat of gods; the regions mild of peace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.22#Full joy, and calm eternity of ease.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.23#There no rude winds presume to shake the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.24#No rains descend, no snowy vapours rise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.25#But on immortal thrones the blest repose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.26#The firmament with living splendours glows.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.27#Hither the goddess winged the aerial way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.3.28#Through heaven's eternal gates that blazed with day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.4.1#Now from her rosy car Aurora shed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.4.2#The dawn, and all the orient flamed with red.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.4.3#Up rose the virgin with the morning light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.4.4#Obedient to the vision of the night.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.4.5#The queen she sought, the queen her hours bestowed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.4.6#In curious works; the whirling spindle glow'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.4.7#With crimson threads, while busy damsels call
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.4.8#The snowy fleece, or twist the purpled wool.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.4.9#Meanwhile Phaeacia's peers in council sate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.4.10#From his high dome the king descends in state;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.4.11#Then with a filial awe the royal maid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.4.12#Approach'd him passing, and submissive said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.5.1#"Will my dread sire his ear regardful deign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.5.2#And may his child the royal car obtain?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.5.3#Say, with my garments shall I bend my way?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.5.4#Where through the vales the mazy waters stray?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.5.5#A dignity of dress adorns the great,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.5.6#And kings draw lustre from the robe of state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.5.7#Five sons thou hast; three wait the bridal day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.5.8#And spotless robes become the young and gay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.5.9#So when with praise amid the dance they shine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.5.10#By these my cares adorn'd that praise is mine."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.1#Thus she: but blushes ill-restrain'd betray
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.2#Her thoughts intentive on the bridal day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.3#The conscious sire the dawning blush survey'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.4#And, smiling, thus bespoke the blooming maid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.5#"My child, my darling joy, the car receive;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.6#That, and whate'er our daughter asks, we give."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.7#Swift at the royal nod the attending train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.8#The car prepare, the mules incessant rein,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.9#The blooming virgin with despatchful cares
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.10#Tunics, and stoles, and robes imperial, bears.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.11#The queen, assiduous to her train assigns
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.12#The sumptuous viands, and the flavorous wines.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.13#The train prepare a cruse of curious mould,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.14#A cruse of fragrance, form'd of burnish'd gold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.15#Odour divine! whose soft refreshing streams
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.6.16#Sleek the smooth skin, and scent the snowy limbs.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.7.1#Now mounting the gay seat, the silken reins
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.7.2#Shine in her hand; along the sounding plains
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.7.3#Swift fly the mules; nor rode the nymph alone;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.7.4#Around, a bevy of bright damsels shone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.7.5#They seek the cisterns where Phaeacian dames
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.7.6#Wash their fair garments in the limpid streams;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.7.7#Where, gathering into depth from falling rills,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.7.8#The lucid wave a spacious bason fills.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.7.9#The mules, unharness'd, range beside the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.7.10#Or crop the verdant herbage of the plain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.8.1#Then emulous the royal robes they lave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.8.2#And plunge the vestures in the cleansing wave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.8.3#(The vestures cleansed o'erspread the shelly sand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.8.4#Their snowy lustre whitens all the strand);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.8.5#Then with a short repast relieve their toil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.8.6#And o'er their limbs diffuse ambrosial oil;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.8.7#And while the robes imbibe the solar ray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.8.8#O'er the green mead the sporting virgins play
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.8.9#(Their shining veils unbound). Along the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.8.10#Toss'd and retoss'd, the ball incessant flies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.8.11#They sport, they feast; Nausicaa lifts her voice,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.8.12#And, warbling sweet, makes earth and heaven rejoice.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.9.1#As when o'er Erymanth Diana roves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.9.2#Or wide Tuygetus' resounding groves;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.9.3#A sylvan train the huntress queen surrounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.9.4#Her rattling quiver from her shoulders sounds:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.9.5#Fierce in the sport, along the mountain's brow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.9.6#They bay the boar, or chase the bounding roe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.9.7#High o'er the lawn, with more majestic pace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.9.8#Above the nymphs she treads with stately grace;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.9.9#Distinguish'd excellence the goddess proves;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.9.10#Exults Latona as the virgin moves.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.9.11#With equal grace Nausicaa trod the plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.9.12#And shone transcendent o'er the beauteous train.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.10.1#Meantime (the care and favourite of the skies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.10.2#Wrapp'd in imbowering shade, Ulysses lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.10.3#His woes forgot! but Pallas now address'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.10.4#To break the bands of all-composing rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.10.5#Forth from her snowy hand Nausicaa threw
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.10.6#The various ball; the ball erroneous flew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.10.7#And swam the stream; loud shrieks the virgin train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.10.8#And the loud shriek redoubles from the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.10.9#Waked by the shrilling sound, Ulysses rose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.10.10#And, to the deaf woods wailing, breathed his woes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.11.1#"Ah me! on what inhospitable coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.11.2#On what new region is Ulysses toss'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.11.3#Possess'd by wild barbarians fierce in arms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.11.4#Or men, whose bosom tender pity warms?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.11.5#What sounds are these that gather from he shores?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.11.6#The voice of nymphs that haunt the sylvan bowers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.11.7#The fair-hair'd Dryads of the shady wood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.11.8#Or azure daughters of the silver flood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.11.9#Or human voice? but issuing from the shades,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.11.10#Why cease I straight to learn what sound invades?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.1#Then, where the grove with leaves umbrageous bends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.2#With forceful strength a branch the hero rends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.3#Around his loins the verdant cincture spreads
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.4#A wreathy foliage and concealing shades.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.5#As when a lion in the midnight hours,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.6#Beat by rude blasts, and wet with wintry showers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.7#Descends terrific from the mountains brow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.8#With living flames his rolling eye balls glow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.9#With conscious strength elate, he bends his way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.10#Majestically fierce, to seize his prey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.11#(The steer or stag;) or, with keen hunger bold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.12#Spring o'er the fence and dissipates the fold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.13#No less a terror, from the neighbouring groves
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.14#(Rough from the tossing surge) Ulysses moves;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.15#Urged on by want, and recent from the storms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.16#The brackish ooze his manly grace deforms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.17#Wide o'er the shore with many a piercing cry
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.18#To rocks, to caves, the frightened virgins fly;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.19#All but the nymph; the nymph stood fix'd alone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.20#By Pallas arm'd with boldness not her own.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.21#Meantime in dubious thought the king awaits,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.22#And, self-considering, as he stands, debates;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.23#Distant his mournful story to declare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.24#Or prostrate at her knee address the prayer.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.25#But fearful to offend, by wisdom sway'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.12.26#At awful distance he accosts the maid:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.1#"If from the skies a goddess, or if earth
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.2#(Imperial virgin) boast thy glorious birth,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.3#To thee I bend! If in that bright disguise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.4#Thou visit earth, a daughter of the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.5#Hail, Dian, hail! the huntress of the groves
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.6#So shines majestic, and so stately moves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.7#So breathes an air divine! But if thy race
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.8#Be mortal, and this earth thy native place,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.9#Blest is the father from whose loins you sprung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.10#Blest is the mother at whose breast you hung.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.11#Blest are the brethren who thy blood divide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.12#To such a miracle of charms allied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.13#Joyful they see applauding princes gaze,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.14#When stately in the dance you swim the harmonious maze.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.15#But blest o'er all, the youth with heavenly charms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.16#Who clasps the bright perfection in his arms!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.17#Never, I never view'd till this blast hour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.18#Such finish'd grace! I gaze, and I adore!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.19#Thus seems the palm with stately honours crown'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.20#By Phoebus' altars; thus o'erlooks the ground;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.21#The pride of Delos. (By the Delian coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.22#I voyaged, leader of a warrior-host,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.23#But ah, how changed I from thence my sorrow flows;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.24#O fatal voyage, source of all my woes;)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.25#Raptured I stood, and as this hour amazed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.26#With reverence at the lofty wonder gazed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.27#Raptured I stand! for earth ne'er knew to bear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.28#A plant so stately, or a nymph so fair.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.29#Awed from access, I lift my suppliant hands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.30#For Misery, O queen! before thee stands.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.31#Twice ten tempestuous nights I roll'd, resign'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.32#To roaring blows, and the warring wind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.33#Heaven bade the deep to spare; but heaven, my foe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.34#Spares only to inflict some mightier woe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.35#Inured to cares, to death in all its forms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.36#Outcast I rove, familiar with the storms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.37#Once more I view the face of human kind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.38#Oh let soft pity touch thy generous mind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.39#Unconscious of what air I breathe, I stand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.40#Naked, defenceless on a narrow land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.41#Propitious to my wants a vest supply
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.42#To guard the wretched from the inclement sky:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.43#So may the gods, who heaven and earth control,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.44#Crown the chaste wishes of thy virtuous soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.45#On thy soft hours their choicest blessings shed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.46#Blest with a husband be thy bridal bed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.47#Blest be thy husband with a blooming race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.48#And lasting union crown your blissful days.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.49#The gods, when they supremely bless, bestow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.50#Firm union on their favourites below;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.51#Then envy grieves, with inly-pining hate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.13.52#The good exult, and heaven is in our state."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.14.1#To whom the nymph: "O stranger, cease thy care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.14.2#Wise is thy soul, but man is bore to bear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.14.3#Jove weighs affairs of earth in dubious scales,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.14.4#And the good suffers, while the bad prevails.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.14.5#Bear, with a soul resign'd, the will of Jove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.14.6#Who breathes, must mourn: thy woes are from above.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.14.7#But since thou tread'st our hospitable shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.14.8#'Tis mine to bid the wretched grieve no more,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.14.9#To clothe the naked, and thy way to guide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.14.10#Know, the Phaecian tribes this land divide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.14.11#From great Alcinous' royal loins I spring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.14.12#A happy nation, and a happy king."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.15.1#Then to her maids: "Why, why, ye coward train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.15.2#These fears, this flight? ye fear, and fly in vain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.15.3#Dread ye a foe? dismiss that idle dread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.15.4#'Tis death with hostile step these shores to tread;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.15.5#Safe in the love of heaven, an ocean flows
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.15.6#Around our realm, a barrier from the foes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.15.7#'Tis ours this son of sorrow to relieve,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.15.8#Cheer the sad heart, nor let affliction grieve.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.15.9#By Jove the stranger and the poor are sent;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.15.10#And what to those we give to Jove is lent.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.15.11#Then food supply, and bathe his fainting limbs
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.15.12#Where waving shades obscure the mazy streams."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.16.1#Obedient to the call, the chief they guide
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.16.2#To the calm current of the secret tide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.16.3#Close by the stream a royal dress they lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.16.4#A vest and robe, with rich embroidery gay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.16.5#Then unguents in a vase of gold supply,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.16.6#That breathed a fragrance through the balmy sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.17.1#To them the king: "No longer I detain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.17.2#Your friendly care: retire, ye virgin train!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.17.3#Retire, while from my wearied limbs I lave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.17.4#The foul pollution of the briny wave.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.17.5#Ye gods! since this worn frame refection know,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.17.6#What scenes have I surveyed of dreadful view!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.17.7#But, nymphs, recede! sage chastity denies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.17.8#To raise the blush, or pain the modest eyes."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.1#The nymphs withdrawn, at once into the tide
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.2#Active he bounds; the flashing waves divide
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.3#O'er all his limbs his hands the waves diffuse,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.4#And from his locks compress the weedy ooze;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.5#The balmy oil, a fragrant shower, be sheds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.6#Then, dressed, in pomp magnificently treads.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.7#The warrior-goddess gives his frame to shine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.8#With majesty enlarged, and air divine:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.9#Back from his brows a length of hair unfurls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.10#His hyacinthine locks descend in wavy curls.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.11#As by some artist, to whom Vulcan gives
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.12#His skill divine, a breathing statue lives;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.13#By Pallas taught, he frames the wondrous mould,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.14#And o'er the silver pours the fusile gold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.15#So Pallas his heroic frame improves
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.16#With heavenly bloom, and like a god he moves.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.17#A fragrance breathes around; majestic grace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.18#Attends his steps: the astonished virgins gaze.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.19#Soft he reclines along the murmuring seas,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.18.20#Inhaling freshness from the fanning breeze.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.19.1#The wondering nymph his glorious port survey'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.19.2#And to her damsels, with amazement, said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.20.1#"Not without care divine the stranger treads
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.20.2#This land of joy; his steps some godhead leads:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.20.3#Would Jove destroy him, sure he had been driven
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.20.4#Far from this realm, the favourite isle of heaven.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.20.5#Late, a sad spectacle of woe, he trod
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.20.6#The desert sands, and now be looks a god.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.20.7#Oh heaven! in my connubial hour decree
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.20.8#This man my spouse, or such a spouse as he!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.20.9#But haste, the viands and the bowl provide."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.20.10#The maids the viands and the bowl supplied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.20.11#Eager he fed, for keen his hunger raged,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.20.12#And with the generous vintage thirst assuaged.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.21.1#Now on return her care Nausicaa bends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.21.2#The robes resumes, the glittering car ascends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.21.3#Far blooming o'er the field; and as she press'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.21.4#The splendid seat, the listening chief address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.1#"Stranger, arise! the sun rolls down the day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.2#Lo, to the palace I direct thy way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.3#Where, in high state, the nobles of the land
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.4#Attend my royal sire, a radiant band
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.5#But hear, though wisdom in thy soul presides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.6#Speaks from thy tongue, and every action guides;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.7#Advance at distance, while I pass the plain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.8#Where o'er the furrows waves the golden grain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.9#Alone I reascend--With airy mounds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.10#A strength of wall the guarded city bounds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.11#The jutting land two ample bays divides:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.12#Full through the narrow mouths descend the tides;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.13#The spacious basons arching rocks enclose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.14#A sure defence from every storm that blows.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.15#Close to the bay great Neptune's fane adjoins;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.16#And near, a forum flank'd with marble shines,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.17#Where the bold youth, the numerous fleets to store,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.18#Shape the broad sail, or smooth the taper oar:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.19#For not the bow they bend, nor boast the skill
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.20#To give the feather'd arrow wings to kill;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.21#But the tall mast above the vessel rear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.22#Or teach the fluttering sail to float in air.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.23#They rush into the deep with eager joy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.24#Climb the steep surge, and through the tempest fly;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.25#A proud, unpolish'd race--To me belongs
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.26#The care to shun the blast of slanderous tongues;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.27#Lest malice, prone the virtuous to defame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.28#Thus with wild censure taint my spotless name:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.29#'What stranger this whom thus Nausicaa leads!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.30#Heavens, with what graceful majesty he treads!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.31#Perhaps a native of some distant shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.32#The future consort of her bridal hour:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.33#Or rather some descendant of the skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.34#Won by her prayer, the aerial bridegroom flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.35#Heaven on that hour its choicest influence shed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.36#That gave a foreign spouse to crown her bed!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.37#All, all the godlike worthies that adorn
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.38#This realm, she flies: Phaeacia is her scorn.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.39#And just the blame: for female innocence
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.40#Not only flies the guilt, but shuns the offence:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.41#The unguarded virgin, as unchaste, I blame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.42#And the least freedom with the sex is shame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.43#Till our consenting sires a spouse provide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.44#And public nuptials justify the bride,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.45#But would'st thou soon review thy native plain?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.46#Attend, and speedy thou shalt pass the main:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.47#Nigh where a grove with verdant poplars crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.48#To Pallas sacred, shades the holy ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.49#We bend our way; a bubbling fount distills
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.50#A lucid lake, and thence descends in rills;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.51#Around the grove, a mead with lively green
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.52#Falls by degrees, and forms a beauteous scene;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.53#Here a rich juice the royal vineyard pours;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.54#And there the garden yields a waste of flowers.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.55#Hence lies the town, as far as to the ear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.56#Floats a strong shout along the waves of air.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.57#There wait embower'd, while I ascend alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.58#To great Alcinous on his royal throne.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.59#Arrived, advance, impatient of delay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.60#And to the lofty palace bend thy way:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.61#The lofty palace overlooks the town,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.62#From every dome by pomp superior known;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.63#A child may point the way. With earnest gait
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.64#Seek thou the queen along the rooms of state;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.65#Her royal hand a wondrous work designs,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.66#Around a circle of bright damsels shines;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.67#Part twist the threads, and part the wool dispose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.68#While with the purple orb the spindle glows.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.69#High on a throne, amid the Scherian powers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.70#My royal father shares the genial hours:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.71#But to the queen thy mournful tale disclose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.72#With the prevailing eloquence of woes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.73#So shalt thou view with joy thy natal shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.22.74#Though mountains rise between and oceans roar."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.23.1#She added not, but waving, as she wheel'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.23.2#The silver scourge, it glitter'd o'er the field;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.23.3#With skill the virgin guides the embroider'd rein,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.23.4#Slow rolls the car before the attending train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.23.5#Now whirling down the heavens, the golden day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.23.6#Shot through the western clouds a dewy ray;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.23.7#The grove they reach, where, from the sacred shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.23.8#To Pallas thus the pensive hero pray'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.24.1#"Daughter of Jove! whose arms in thunder wield
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.24.2#The avenging bolt, and shake the dreadful shield;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.24.3#Forsook by thee, in vain I sought thy aid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.24.4#When booming billows closed above my bead;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.24.5#Attend, unconquer'd maid! accord my vows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.24.6#Bid the Great hear, and pitying, heal my woes."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.25.1#This heard Minerva, but forbore to fly
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.25.2#(By Neptune awed) apparent from the sky;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.25.3#Stern god! who raged with vengeance, unrestrain'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:6.25.4#Till great Ulysses hail'd his native land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.1#The patient heavenly man thus suppliant pray'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.2#While the slow mules draws on the imperial maid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.3#Through the proud street she moves, the public gaze;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.4#The turning wheel before the palace stays.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.5#With ready love her brothers, gathering round,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.6#Received the vestures, and the mules unbound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.7#She seeks the bridal bower: a matron there
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.8#The rising fire supplies with busy care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.9#Whose charms in youth her father's heart inflamed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.10#Now worn with age, Eurymedusa named;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.11#The captive dame Phaeacian rovers bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.12#Snatch'd from Epirus, her sweet native shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.13#(A grateful prize), and in her bloom bestow'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.14#On good Alcinous, honor'd as a god;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.15#Nurse of Nausicaa from her infant years,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.1.16#And tender second to a mother's cares.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.2.1#Now from the sacred thicket where he lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.2.2#To town Ulysses took the winding way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.2.3#Propitious Pallas, to secure her care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.2.4#Around him spread a veil of thicken'd air;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.2.5#To shun the encounter of the vulgar crowd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.2.6#Insulting still, inquisitive and loud.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.2.7#When near the famed Phaeacian walls he drew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.2.8#The beauteous city opening to his view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.2.9#His step a virgin met, and stood before:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.2.10#A polish'd urn the seeming virgin bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.2.11#And youthful smiled; but in the low disguise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.2.12#Lay hid the goddess with the azure eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.3.1#"Show me, fair daughter (thus the chief demands),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.3.2#The house of him who rules these happy lands
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.3.3#Through many woes and wanderings, do I come
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.3.4#To good Alcinous' hospitable dome.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.3.5#Far from my native coast, I rove alone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.3.6#A wretched stranger, and of all unknown!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.1#The goddess answer'd: "Father, I obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.2#And point the wandering traveller his way:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.3#Well known to me the palace you inquire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.4#For fast beside it dwells my honour'd sire:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.5#But silent march, nor greet the common train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.6#With question needless, or inquiry vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.7#A race of ragged mariners are these,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.8#Unpolish'd men, and boisterous as their seas
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.9#The native islanders alone their care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.10#And hateful he who breathes a foreign air.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.11#These did the ruler of the deep ordain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.12#To build proud navies, and command the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.13#On canvas wings to cut the watery way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.4.14#No bird so light, no thought so swift as they."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.1#Thus having spoke, the unknown celestial leads:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.2#The footsteps of the duty he treads,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.3#And secret moves along the crowded space,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.4#Unseen of all the rude Phaeacian race.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.5#(So Pallas order'd, Pallas to their eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.6#The mist objected, and condensed the skies.)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.7#The chief with wonder sees the extended streets,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.8#The spreading harbours, and the riding fleets;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.9#He next their princes' lofty domes admires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.10#In separate islands, crown'd with rising spires;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.11#And deep entrenchments, and high walls of stone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.12#That gird the city like a marble zone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.13#At length the kingly palace-gates he view'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.5.14#There stopp'd the goddess, and her speech renew'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.1#"My task is done: the mansion you inquire
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.2#Appears before you: enter, and admire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.3#High-throned, and feasting, there thou shalt behold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.4#The sceptred rulers. Fear not, but be bold:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.5#A decent boldness ever meets with friends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.6#Succeeds, and even a stranger recommends
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.7#First to the queen prefer a suppliant's claim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.8#Alcinous' queen, Arete is her name.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.9#The same her parents, and her power the same.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.10#For know, from ocean's god Nausithous sprung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.11#And Peribaea, beautiful and young
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.12#(Eurymedon's last hope, who ruled of old
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.13#The race of giants, impious, proud, and bold:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.14#Perish'd the nation in unrighteous war,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.15#Perish'd the prince, and left this only heir),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.16#Who now, by Neptune's amorous power compress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.17#Produced a monarch that his people bless'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.18#Father and prince of the Phaeacian name;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.19#From him Rhexenor and Alcinous came.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.20#The first by Phoebus' hurtling arrows fired,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.21#New from his nuptials, hapless youth! expired.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.22#No son survived; Arete heir'd his state,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.23#And her, Alcinous chose his royal mate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.24#With honours yet to womankind unknown.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.25#This queen he graces, and divides the throne;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.26#In equal tenderness her sons conspire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.27#And all the children emulate their sire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.28#When through the streets she gracious deigns to move
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.29#(The public wonder and the public love),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.30#The tongues of all with transport sound her praise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.31#The eyes of all, as on a goddess, gaze.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.32#She feels the triumph of a generous breast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.33#To heal divisions, to relieve the oppress'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.34#In virtue rich; in blessing others, bless'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.35#(to then secure, thy humble suit prefer
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.6.36#And owe thy country and thy friends to her."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.7.1#With that the goddess deign'd no longer stay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.7.2#But o'er the world of waters wing'd her way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.7.3#Forsaking Scheria's ever-pleasing shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.7.4#The winds to Marathon the virgin bore:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.7.5#Thence, where proud Athens rears her towery head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.7.6#With opening streets and shining structures spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.7.7#She pass'd, delighted with the well-known seats;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.7.8#And to Erectheus' sacred dome retreats.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.1#Meanwhile Ulysses at the palace waits,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.2#There stops, and anxious with his soul debates,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.3#Fix'd in amaze before the royal gates.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.4#The front appear'd with radiant splendours gay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.5#Bright as the lamp of night, or orb of day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.6#The walls were massy brass: the cornice high
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.7#Blue metals crown'd in colours of the sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.8#Rich plates of gold the folding doors incase;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.9#The pillars silver, on a brazen base;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.10#Silver the lintels deep-projecting o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.11#And gold the ringlets that command the door.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.12#Two rows of stately dogs, on either hand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.13#In sculptured gold and labour'd silver stood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.14#These Vulcan form'd with art divine, to wait
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.15#Immortal guardians at Alcinous' gate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.16#Alive each animated frame appears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.17#And still to live beyond the power of years,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.18#Fair thrones within from space to space were raised,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.19#Where various carpets with embroidery blessed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.20#The work of matrons: these the princes press'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.21#Day following day, a long-continued feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.22#Refulgent pedestals the walls surround,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.23#Which boys of gold with illuming torches crown'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.24#The polish'd oar, reflecting every ray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.25#Blazed on the banquets with a double day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.26#Full fifty handmaids form the household train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.27#Some turn the mill, or sift the golden grain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.28#Some ply the loom; their busy fingers move
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.29#Like poplar-leaves when Zephyr fans the grove.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.30#Not more renown'd the men of Scheria's isle
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.31#For sailing arts and all the naval toil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.32#Than works of female skill their women's pride,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.33#The flying shuttle through the threads to guide:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.34#Pallas to these her double gifts imparts,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.8.35#Incentive genius, and industrious arts.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.1#Close to the gates a spacious garden lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.2#From storms defended and inclement skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.3#Four acres was the allotted space of ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.4#Fenced with a green enclosure all around.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.5#Tall thriving trees confess'd the fruitful mould:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.6#The reddening apple ripens here to gold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.7#Here the blue fig with luscious juice o'erflows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.8#With deeper red the full pomegranate glows;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.9#The branch here bends beneath the weighty pear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.10#And verdant olives flourish round the year,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.11#The balmy spirit of the western gale
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.12#Eternal breathes on fruits, unthought to fail:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.13#Each dropping pear a following pear supplies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.14#On apples apples, figs on figs arise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.15#The same mild season gives the blooms to blow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.9.16#The buds to harden, and the fruits to grow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.10.1#Here order'd vines in equal ranks appear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.10.2#With all the united labours of the year;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.10.3#Some to unload the fertile branches run,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.10.4#Some dry the blackening clusters in the sun,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.10.5#Others to tread the liquid harvest join:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.10.6#The groaning presses foam with floods of wine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.10.7#Here are the vines in early flower descried,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.10.8#Here grapes discolour'd on the sunnyside,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.10.9#And there in autumn's richest purple dyed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.11.1#Beds of all various herbs, for ever green,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.11.2#In beauteous order terminate the scene.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.12.1#Two plenteous fountains the whole prospect crown'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.12.2#This through the gardens leads its streams around
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.12.3#Visits each plant, and waters all the ground;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.12.4#While that in pipes beneath the palace flows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.12.5#And thence its current on the town bestows:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.12.6#To various use their various streams they bring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.12.7#The people one, and one supplies the king.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.1#Such were the glories which the gods ordain'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.2#To grace Alcinous, and his happy land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.3#E'en from the chief whom men and nations knew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.4#The unwonted scene surprise and rapture drew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.5#In pleasing thought he ran the prospect o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.6#Then hasty enter'd at the lofty door.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.7#Night now approaching, in the palace stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.8#With goblets crown'd, the rulers of the land;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.9#Prepared for rest, and offering to the god
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.10#Who bears the virtue of the sleepy rod,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.11#Unseen he glided through the joyous crowd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.12#With darkness circled, and an ambient cloud.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.13#Direct to great Alcinous' throne he came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.14#And prostrate fell before the imperial dame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.15#Then from around him dropp'd the veil of night;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.16#Sudden he shines, and manifest to sight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.17#The nobles gaze, with awful fear oppress'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.13.18#Silent they gaze, and eye the godlike guest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.14.1#"Daughter of great Rhexenor! (thus began,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.14.2#Low at her knees, the much-enduring man)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.14.3#To thee, thy consort, and this royal train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.14.4#To all that share the blessings of your reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.14.5#A suppliant bends: oh pity human woe!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.14.6#'Tis what the happy to the unhappy owe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.14.7#A wretched exile to his country send,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.14.8#Long worn with griefs, and long without a friend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.14.9#So may the gods your better days increase,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.14.10#And all your joys descend on all your race;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.14.11#So reign for ever on your country's breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.14.12#Your people blessing, by your people bless'd!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.15.1#Then to the genial hearth he bow'd his face,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.15.2#And humbled in the ashes took his place.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.15.3#Silence ensued.  The eldest first began,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.15.4#Echeneus sage, a venerable man!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.15.5#Whose well-taught mind the present age surpass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.15.6#And join'd to that the experience of the last.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.15.7#Fit words attended on his weighty sense,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.15.8#And mild persuasion flow'd in eloquence.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.16.1#"Oh sight (he cried) dishonest and unjust!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.16.2#A guest, a stranger, seated in the dust!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.16.3#To raise the lowly suppliant from the ground
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.16.4#Befits a monarch. Lo! the peers around
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.16.5#But wait thy word, the gentle guest to grace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.16.6#And seat him fair in some distinguish'd place.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.16.7#Let first the herald due libation pay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.16.8#To Jove, who guides the wanderer on his way:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.16.9#Then set the genial banquet in his view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.16.10#And give the stranger-guest a stranger's due."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.1#His sage advice the listening king obeys,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.2#He stretch'd his hand the prudent chief to raise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.3#And from his seat Laodamas removed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.4#(The monarch's offspring, and his best-beloved);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.5#There next his side the godlike hero sate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.6#With stars of silver shone the bed of state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.7#The golden ewer a beauteous handmaid brings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.8#Replenish'd from the cool translucent springs,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.9#Whose polish'd vase with copious streams supplies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.10#A silver layer of capacious size.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.11#The table next in regal order spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.12#The glittering canisters are heap'd with bread:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.13#Viands of various kinds invite the taste,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.14#Of choicest sort and savour, rich repast!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.15#Thus feasting high, Alcinous gave the sign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.16#And bade the herald pour the rosy wine;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.17#"Let all around the due libation pay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.17.18#To Jove, who guides the wanderer on his way."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.18.1#He said. Pontonous heard the king's command;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.18.2#The circling goblet moves from hand to hand;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.18.3#Each drinks the juice that glads the heart of man.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.18.4#Alcinous then, with aspect mild, began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.1#"Princes and peers, attend; while we impart
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.2#To you the thoughts of no inhuman heart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.3#Now pleased and satiate from the social rite
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.4#Repair we to the blessings of the night;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.5#But with the rising day, assembled here,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.6#Let all the elders of the land appear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.7#Pious observe our hospitable laws,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.8#And Heaven propitiate in the stranger's cause;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.9#Then join'd in council, proper means explore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.10#Safe to transport him to the wished-for shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.11#(How distant that, imports us not to know,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.12#Nor weigh the labour, but relieve the woe).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.13#Meantime, nor harm nor anguish let him bear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.14#This interval, Heaven trusts him to our care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.15#But to his native land our charge resign'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.16#Heaven's is his life to come, and all the woes behind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.17#Then must he suffer what the Fates ordain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.18#For Fate has wove the thread of life with pain?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.19#And twins, e'en from the birth, are Misery and Man!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.20#But if, descended from the Olympian bower,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.21#Gracious approach us some immortal power;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.22#If in that form thou comest a guest divine:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.23#Some high event the conscious gods design.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.24#As yet, unbid they never graced our feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.25#The solemn sacrifice call'd down the guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.26#Then manifest of Heaven the vision stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.27#And to our eyes familiar was the god.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.28#Oft with some favour'd traveller they stray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.29#And shine before him all the desert way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.30#With social intercourse, and face to face,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.31#The friends and guardians of our pious race.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.32#So near approach we their celestial kind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.33#By justice, truth, and probity of mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.34#As our dire neighbours of Cyclopean birth
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.19.35#Match in fierce wrong the giant-sons of earth."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.1#"Let no such thought (with modest grace rejoin'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.2#The prudent Greek) possess the royal mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.3#Alas! a mortal, like thyself, am I;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.4#No glorious native of yon azure sky:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.5#In form, ah how unlike their heavenly kind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.6#How more inferior in the gifts of mind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.7#Alas, a mortal! most oppress'd of those
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.8#Whom Fate has loaded with a weight of woes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.9#By a sad train of Miseries alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.10#Distinguish'd long, and second now to none!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.11#By Heaven's high will compell'd from shore to shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.12#With Heaven's high will prepared to suffer more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.13#What histories of toil could I declare!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.14#But still long-wearied nature wants repair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.15#Spent with fatigue, and shrunk with pining fast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.16#My craving bowels still require repast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.17#Howe'er the noble, suffering mind may grieve
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.18#Its load of anguish, and disdain to live,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.19#Necessity demands our daily bread;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.20#Hunger is insolent, and will be fed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.21#But finish, oh ye peers! what you propose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.22#And let the morrow's dawn conclude my woes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.23#Pleased will I suffer all the gods ordain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.24#To see my soil, my son, my friends again.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.25#That view vouchsafed, let instant death surprise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.20.26#With ever-during shade these happy eyes!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.21.1#The assembled peers with general praise approved
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.21.2#His pleaded reason, and the suit he moved.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.21.3#Each drinks a full oblivion of his cares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.21.4#And to the gifts of balmy sleep repairs,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.21.5#Ulysses in the regal walls alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.21.6#Remain'd: beside him, on a splendid throne,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.21.7#Divine Arete and Alcinous shone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.21.8#The queen, an nearer view, the guest survey'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.21.9#Rob'd in the garments her own hands had made,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.21.10#Not without wonder seen. Then thus began,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.21.11#Her words addressing to the godlike man:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.22.1#"Camest thou hither, wondrous stranger I say,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.22.2#From lands remote and o'er a length of sea?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.22.3#Tell, then, whence art thou? whence, that princely air?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.22.4#And robes like these, so recent and so fair?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.1#"Hard is the task, O princess! you impose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.2#(Thus sighing spoke the man of many woes),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.3#The long, the mournful series to relate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.4#Of all my sorrows sent by Heaven and Fate!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.5#Yet what you ask, attend.  An island lies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.6#Beyond these tracts, and under other skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.7#Ogygia named, in Ocean's watery arms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.8#Where dwells Calypso, dreadful in her charms!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.9#Remote from gods or men she holds her reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.10#Amid the terrors of a rolling main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.11#Me, only me, the hand of fortune bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.12#Unblest! to tread that interdicted shore:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.13#When Jove tremendous in the sable deeps
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.14#Launch'd his red lightning at our scattered ships;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.15#Then, all my fleet and all my followers lost.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.16#Sole on a plank on boiling surges toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.17#Heaven drove my wreck the Ogygian Isle to find,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.18#Full nine days floating to the wave and wind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.19#Met by the goddess there with open arms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.20#She bribed my stay with more than human charms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.21#Nay, promised, vainly promised, to bestow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.22#Immortal life, exempt from age and woe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.23#But all her blandishments successless prove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.24#To banish from my breast my country's love.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.25#I stay reluctant seven continued years,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.26#And water her ambrosial couch with tears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.27#The eighth she voluntary moves to part,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.28#Or urged by Jove, or her own changeful heart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.29#A raft was formed to cross the surging sea;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.30#Herself supplied the stores and rich array,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.31#And gave the gales to waft me on my way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.32#In seventeen days appear'd your pleasing coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.33#And woody mountains half in vapours lost.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.34#Joy touched my soul; my soul was joy'd in vain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.35#For angry Neptune roused the raging main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.36#The wild winds whistle, and the billows roar;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.37#The splitting raft the furious tempest tore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.38#And storms vindictive intercept the shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.39#Soon as their rage subsides, the seas I brave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.40#With naked force, and shoot along the wave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.41#To reach this isle; but there my hopes were lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.42#The surge impell'd me on a craggy coast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.43#I chose the safer sea, and chanced to find
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.44#A river's mouth impervious to the wind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.45#And clear of rocks. I fainted by the flood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.46#Then took the shelter of the neighbouring wood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.47#'Twas night, and, covered in the foliage deep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.48#Jove plunged my senses in the death of sleep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.49#All night I slept, oblivious of my pain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.50#Aurora dawned and Phoebus shined in vain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.51#Nor, till oblique he sloped his evening ray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.52#Had Somnus dried the balmy dews away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.53#Then female voices from the shore I heard:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.54#A maid amidst them, goddess-like appear'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.55#To her I sued, she pitied my distress;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.56#Like thee in beauty, nor in virtue less.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.57#Who from such youth could hope considerate care?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.58#In youth and beauty wisdom is but rare!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.59#She gave me life, relieved with just supplies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.60#My wants, and lent these robes that strike your eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.61#This is the truth: and oh, ye powers on high!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.23.62#Forbid that want should sink me to a lie."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.24.1#To this the king: "Our daughter but express'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.24.2#Her cares imperfect to our godlike guest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.24.3#Suppliant to her, since first he chose to pray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.24.4#Why not herself did she conduct the way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.24.5#And with her handmaids to our court convey?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.25.1#"Hero and king (Ulysses thus replied)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.25.2#Nor blame her faultless nor suspect of pride:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.25.3#She bade me follow in the attendant train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.25.4#But fear and reverence did my steps detain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.25.5#Lest rash suspicion might alarm thy mind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.25.6#Man's of a jealous and mistaken kind."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.1#"Far from my soul (he cried) the gods efface
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.2#All wrath ill-grounded, and suspicion base!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.3#Whate'er is honest, stranger, I approve,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.4#And would to Phoebus, Pallas, and to Jove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.5#Such as thou art, thy thought and mine were one,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.6#Nor thou unwilling to be called my son.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.7#In such alliance couldst thou wish to join,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.8#A palace stored with treasures should be thine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.9#But if reluctant, who shall force thy stay?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.10#Jove bids to set the stranger on his way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.11#And ships shall wait thee with the morning ray.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.12#Till then, let slumber cross thy careful eyes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.13#The wakeful mariners shall watch the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.14#And seize the moment when the breezes rise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.15#Then gently waft thee to the pleasing shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.16#Where thy soul rests, and labour is no more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.17#Far as Euboea though thy country lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.18#Our ships with ease transport thee in a day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.19#Thither of old, earth's giant son to view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.20#On wings of wind with Rhadamanth they flew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.21#This land, from whence their morning course begun,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.22#Saw them returning with the setting sun.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.23#Your eyes shall witness and confirm my tale,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.24#Our youth how dexterous, and how fleet our sail,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.25#When justly timed with equal sweep they row,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.26.26#And ocean whitens in long tracks below."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.27.1#Thus he. No word the experienced man replies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.27.2#But thus to heaven (and heavenward lifts his eyes):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.27.3#"O Jove! O father! what the king accords
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.27.4#Do thou make perfect! sacred be his words!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.27.5#Wide o'er the world Alcinous' glory shine!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.27.6#Let fame be his, and ah! my country mine!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.28.1#Meantime Arete, for the hour of rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.28.2#Ordains the fleecy couch, and covering vest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.28.3#Bids her fair train the purple quilts prepare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.28.4#And the thick carpets spread with busy care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.28.5#With torches blazing in their hands they pass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.28.6#And finish'd all their queen's command with haste:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.28.7#Then gave the signal to the willing guest:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.28.8#He rose with pleasure, and retired to rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.28.9#There, soft extended, to the murmuring sound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.28.10#Of the high porch, Ulysses sleeps profound!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.28.11#Within, released from cares, Alcinous lies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:7.28.12#And fast beside were closed Arete's eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.1.1#Now fair Aurora lifts her golden ray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.1.2#And all the ruddy orient flames with day:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.1.3#Alcinous, and the chief, with dawning light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.1.4#Rose instant from the slumbers of the night;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.1.5#Then to the council-seat they bend their way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.1.6#And fill the shining thrones along the bay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.2.1#Meanwhile Minerva, in her guardian care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.2.2#Shoots from the starry vault through fields of air;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.2.3#In form, a herald of the king, she flies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.2.4#From peer to peer, and thus incessant cries;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.3.1#"Nobles and chiefs who rule Phaeacia's states,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.3.2#The king in council your attendance waits;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.3.3#A prince of grace divine your aid implores,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.3.4#O'er unknown seas arrived from unknown shores."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.4.1#She spoke, and sudden with tumultuous sounds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.4.2#Of thronging multitudes the shore rebounds:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.4.3#At once the seats they fill; and every eye
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.4.4#Glazed, as before some brother of the sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.4.5#Pallas with grace divine his form improves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.4.6#More high he treads, and more enlarged he moves:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.4.7#She sheds celestial bloom, regard to draw;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.4.8#And gives a dignity of mien, to awe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.4.9#With strength, the future prize of fame to play,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.4.10#And gather all the honours of the day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.1#Then from his glittering throne Alcinous rose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.2#"Attend (he cried) while we our will disclose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.3#Your present aid this godlike stranger craves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.4#Toss'd by rude tempest through a war of waves;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.5#Perhaps from realms that view the rising day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.6#Or nations subject to the western ray.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.7#Then grant, what here all sons of wine obtain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.8#(For here affliction never pleads in vain);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.9#Be chosen youth prepared, expert to try
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.10#The vast profound and hid the vessel fly;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.11#Launch the tall back, and order every oar;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.12#Then in our court indulge the genial hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.13#Instant, you sailors to this task attend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.14#Swift to the palace, all ye peers ascend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.15#Let none to strangers honours due disclaim:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.16#Be there Demodocus the bard of fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.17#Taught by the gods to please, when high he sings
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.5.18#The vocal lay, responsive to the strings."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.1#Thus spoke the prince; the attending peers obey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.2#In state they move; Alcinous heads the way
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.3#Swift to Demodocus the herald flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.4#At once the sailors to their charge arise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.5#They launch the vessel, and unfurl the sails,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.6#And stretch the swelling canvas to the gales;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.7#Then to the palace move: a gathering throng,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.8#Youth, and white age, tumultuous pour along.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.9#Now all accesses to the dome are fill'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.10#Eight boars, the choicest of the herd, are kill'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.11#Two beeves, twelve fatlings, from the flock they bring
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.12#To crown the feast; so wills the bounteous king,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.13#The herald now arrives, and guides along
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.14#The sacred master of celestial song;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.15#Dear to the Muse!  who gave his days to flow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.16#With mighty blessings, mix'd with mighty woe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.17#With clouds of darkness quench'd his visual ray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.18#But gave him skill to raise the lofty lay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.19#High on a radiant throne sublime in state,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.20#Encircled by huge multitudes, he sate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.21#With silver shone the throne; his lyre, well strung
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.22#To rapturous sounds, at hand Poutonous hung.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.23#Before his seat a polish'd table shines,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.24#And a full goblet foams with generous wines;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.25#His food a herald bore; and now they fed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.6.26#And now the rage of craving hunger fled.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.7.1#Then, fired by all the Muse, aloud he sings
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.7.2#The mighty deeds of demigods and kings;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.7.3#From that fierce wrath the noble song arose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.7.4#That made Ulysses and Achilles foes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.7.5#How o'er the feast they doom the fall of Troy;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.7.6#The stern debate Atrides hears with joy;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.7.7#For Heaven foretold the contest, when he trod
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.7.8#The marble threshold of the Delphic god,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.7.9#Curious to learn the counsels of the sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.7.10#Ere yet he loosed the rage of war on Troy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.8.1#Touch'd at the song, Ulysses straight resign'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.8.2#To soft affliction all his manly mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.8.3#Before his eyes the purple vest he drew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.8.4#Industrious to conceal the falling dew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.8.5#But when the music paused, he ceased to shed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.8.6#The flowing tear, and raised his drooping head;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.8.7#And, lifting to the gods a goblet crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.8.8#He pour'd a pure libation to the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.1#Transported with the song, the listening train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.2#Again with loud applause demand the strain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.3#Again Ulysses veil'd his pensive head.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.4#Again unmann'd, a shower of sorrows shed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.5#Conceal'd he wept; the king observed alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.6#The silent tear, and heard the secret groan;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.7#Then to the bard aloud--"O cease to sing,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.8#Dumb be thy voice and mute the harmonious string;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.9#Enough the feast has pleased, enough the power
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.10#Of heavenly song has crown'd the genial hour!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.11#Incessant in the games your strength display,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.12#Contest, ye brave the honours of the day!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.13#That pleased the admiring stranger may proclaim
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.14#In distant regions the Phaeacian fame:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.15#None wield the gauntlet with so dire a sway,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.16#Or swifter in the race devour the way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.17#None in the leap spring with so strong a bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.9.18#Or firmer, in the wrestling, press the ground."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.10.1#Thus spoke the king; the attending peers obey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.10.2#In state they move, Alcinous lends the way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.10.3#His golden lyre Demodocus unstrung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.10.4#High on a column in the palace hung;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.10.5#And guided by a herald's guardian cares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.10.6#Majestic to the lists of Fame repairs.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.1#Now swarms the populace: a countless throng,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.2#Youth and boar age; and man drives man along.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.3#The games begin; ambitious of the prize,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.4#Acroneus, Thoon, and Eretmeus rise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.5#The prize Ocyalus and Prymneus claim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.6#Anchialus and Ponteus, chiefs of fame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.7#There Proreus, Nautes, Eratreus, appear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.8#And famed Amphialus, Polyneus' heir;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.9#Euryalus, like Mars terrific, rose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.10#When clad in wrath he withers hosts of foes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.11#Naubolides with grace unequall'd shone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.12#Or equall'd by Laodamas alone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.13#With these came forth Ambasineus the strong:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.11.14#And three brave sons, from great Alcinous sprung.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.1#Ranged in a line the ready racers stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.2#Start from the goal, and vanish o'er the strand:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.3#Swift as on wings of winds, upborne they fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.4#And drifts of rising dust involve the sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.5#Before the rest, what space the hinds allow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.6#Between the mule and ox, from plough to plough,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.7#Clytonius sprung: he wing'd the rapid way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.8#And bore the unrivall'd honours of the day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.9#With fierce embrace the brawny wrestlers join;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.10#The conquest, great Euryalus, is thine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.11#Amphialus sprung forward with a bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.12#Superior in the leap, a length of ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.13#From Elatreus' strong arm the discus flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.14#And sings with unmatch'd force along the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.15#And Laodam whirls high, with dreadful sway,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.12.16#The gloves of death, victorious in the fray.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.13.1#While thus the peerage in the games contends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.13.2#In act to speak, Laodamas ascends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.14.1#"O friends (he cries), the stranger seems well skill'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.14.2#To try the illustrious labours of the field:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.14.3#I deem him brave: then grant the brave man's claim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.14.4#Invite the hero to his share of fame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.14.5#What nervous arms he boasts! how firm his tread!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.14.6#His limbs how turn'd! how broad his shoulders spread!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.14.7#By age unbroke!--but all-consuming care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.14.8#Destroys perhaps the strength that time would spare:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.14.9#Dire is the ocean, dread in all its forms!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.14.10#Man must decay when man contends with storms."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.15.1#"Well hast thou spoke (Euryalus replies):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.15.2#Thine is the guest, invite him thou to rise."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.15.3#Swift as the word, advancing from the crowd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.15.4#He made obeisance, and thus spoke aloud:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.16.1#"Vouchsafes the reverend stranger to display
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.16.2#His manly worth, and share the glorious day?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.16.3#Father, arise! for thee thy port proclaims
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.16.4#Expert to conquer in the solemn games.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.16.5#To fame arise! for what more fame can yield
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.16.6#Than the swift race, or conflict of the field?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.16.7#Steal from corroding care one transient day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.16.8#To glory give the space thou hast to stay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.16.9#Short is the time, and lo! e'en now the gales
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.16.10#Call thee aboard, and stretch the swelling sails."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.1#To whom with sighs Ulysses gave reply:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.2#"Ah why the ill-suiting pastime must I try?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.3#To gloomy care my thoughts alone are free;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.4#Ill the gay sorts with troubled hearts agree;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.5#Sad from my natal hour my days have ran,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.6#A much-afflicted, much-enduring man!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.7#Who, suppliant to the king and peers, implores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.8#A speedy voyage to his native shore."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.9#"Wise wanders, Laodam, thy erring tongue
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.10#The sports of glory to the brave belong
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.11#(Retorts Euryalus): he bears no claim
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.12#Among the great, unlike the sons of Fame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.13#A wandering merchant he frequents the main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.14#Some mean seafarer in pursuit of gain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.15#Studious of freight, in naval trade well skill'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.16#But dreads the athletic labours of the field."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.17#Incensed, Ulysses with a frown replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.18#"O forward to proclaim thy soul unwise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.19#With partial hands the gods their gifts dispense;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.20#Some greatly think, some speak with manly sense;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.21#Here Heaven an elegance of form denies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.22#But wisdom the defect of form supplies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.23#This man with energy of thought controls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.24#And steals with modest violence our souls;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.25#He speaks reservedly, but he speaks with force,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.26#Nor can one word be changed but for a worse;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.27#In public more than mortal he appears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.28#And as he moves, the praising crowd reveres;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.29#While others, beauteous as the etherial kind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.30#The nobler portion went, a knowing mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.31#In outward show Heaven gives thee to excel.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.32#But Heaven denies the praise of thinking well
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.33#I'll bear the brave a rude ungovern'd tongue,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.34#And, youth, my generous soul resents the wrong.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.35#Skill'd in heroic exercise, I claim
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.36#A post of honour with the sons of Fame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.37#Such was my boast while vigour crown'd my days,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.38#Now care surrounds me, and my force decays;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.39#Inured a melancholy part to bear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.40#In scenes of death, by tempest and by war
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.41#Yet thus by woes impair'd, no more I waive
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.17.42#To prove the hero--slander stings the brave."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.18.1#Then gliding forward with a furious bound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.18.2#He wrench'd a rocky fragment from the ground
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.18.3#By far more ponderous, and more huge by far
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.18.4#Than what Phaeacia's sons discharged in air.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.18.5#Fierce from his arm the enormous load he flings;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.18.6#Sonorous through the shaded air it sings;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.18.7#Couch'd to the earth, tempestuous as it flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.18.8#The crowd gaze upward while it cleaves the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.18.9#Beyond all marks, with many a giddy round
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.18.10#Down-rushing, it up-turns a hill of ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.19.1#That Instant Pallas, bursting from a cloud,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.19.2#Fix'd a distinguish'd mark, and cried aloud:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.20.1#"E'en he who, sightless, wants his visual ray
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.20.2#May by his touch alone award the day:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.20.3#Thy signal throw transcends the utmost bound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.20.4#Of every champion by a length of ground:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.20.5#Securely bid the strongest of the train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.20.6#Arise to throw; the strongest throws in vain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.1#She spoke: and momentary mounts the sky:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.2#The friendly voice Ulysses hears with joy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.3#Then thus aloud (elate with decent pride)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.4#"Rise, ye Phaecians, try your force (he cried):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.5#If with this throw the strongest caster vie,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.6#Still, further still, I bid the discus fly.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.7#Stand forth, ye champions, who the gauntlet wield,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.8#Or ye, the swiftest racers of the field!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.9#Stand forth, ye wrestlers, who these pastimes grace!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.10#I wield the gauntlet, and I run the race.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.11#In such heroic games I yield to none,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.12#Or yield to brave Laodamas alone:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.13#Shall I with brave Laodamas contend?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.14#A friend is sacred, and I style him friend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.15#Ungenerous were the man, and base of heart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.16#Who takes the kind, and pays the ungrateful part:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.17#Chiefly the man, in foreign realms confined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.18#Base to his friend, to his own interest blind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.19#All, all your heroes I this day defy;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.20#Give me a man that we our might may try.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.21#Expert in every art, I boast the skill
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.22#To give the feather'd arrow wings to kill;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.23#Should a whole host at once discharge the bow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.24#My well-aim'd shaft with death prevents the foe:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.25#Alone superior in the field of Troy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.26#Great Philoctetes taught the shaft to fly.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.27#From all the sons of earth unrivall'd praise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.28#I justly claim; but yield to better days,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.29#To those famed days when great Alcides rose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.30#And Eurytus, who bade the gods be foes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.31#(Vain Eurytus, whose art became his crime,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.32#Swept from the earth, he perish'd in his prime:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.33#Sudden the irremeable way he trod,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.34#Who boldly durst defy the bowyer god).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.35#In fighting fields as far the spear I throw
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.36#As flies an arrow from the well-drawn bow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.37#Sole in the race the contest I decline,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.38#Stiff are my weary joints, and I resign;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.39#By storms and hunger worn; age well may fail,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.21.40#When storms and hunger doth at once assail."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.22.1#Abash'd, the numbers hear the godlike man,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.22.2#Till great Alcinous mildly thus began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.23.1#"Well hast thou spoke, and well thy generous tongue
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.23.2#With decent pride refutes a public wrong:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.23.3#Warm are thy words, but warm without offence;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.23.4#Fear only fools, secure in men of sense;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.23.5#Thy worth is known. Then hear our country's claim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.23.6#And bear to heroes our heroic fame:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.23.7#In distant realms our glorious deeds display,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.23.8#Repeat them frequent in the genial day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.23.9#When, blest with ease, thy woes and wanderings end,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.23.10#Teach them thy consort, bid thy sons attend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.23.11#How, loved of Jove, he crown'd our sires with praise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.23.12#How we their offspring dignify our race.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.24.1#"Let other realms the deathful gauntlet wield,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.24.2#Or boast the glories of the athletic field:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.24.3#We in the course unrivall'd speed display,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.24.4#Or through cerulean billows plough the way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.24.5#To dress, to dance, to sing, our sole delight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.24.6#The feast or bath by day, and love by night:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.24.7#Rise, then, ye skill'd in measures; let him bear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.24.8#Your fame to men that breathe a distant air;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.24.9#And faithful say, to you the powers belong
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.24.10#To race, to sail, to dance, to chant the song.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.25.1#"But, herald, to the palace swift repair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.25.2#And the soft lyre to grace our pastimes bear."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.1#Swift at the word, obedient to the king,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.2#The herald flies the tuneful lyre to bring.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.3#Up rose nine seniors, chosen to survey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.4#The future games, the judges of the day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.5#With instant care they mark a spacious round
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.6#And level for the dance the allotted ground:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.7#The herald bears the lyre: intent to play,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.8#The bard advancing meditates the lay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.9#Skill'd in the dance, tall youths, a blooming band,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.10#Graceful before the heavenly minstrel stand:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.11#Light bounding from the earth, at once they rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.12#Their feet half-viewless quiver in the skies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.13#Ulysses gazed, astonish'd to survey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.14#The glancing splendours as their sandals play.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.15#Meantime the bard, alternate to the strings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.16#The loves of Mars and Cytherea sings:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.17#How the stern god, enamour'd with her charms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.18#Clasp'd the gay panting goddess in his arms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.19#By bribes seduced; and how the sun, whose eye
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.20#Views the broad heavens, disclosed the lawless joy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.21#Stung to the soul, indignant through the skies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.22#To his black forge vindictive Vulcan flies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.23#Arrived, his sinewy arms incessant place
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.24#The eternal anvil on the massy base.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.25#A wondrous net he labours, to betray
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.26#The wanton lovers, as entwined they lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.27#Indissolubly strong; Then instant bears
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.28#To his immortal dome the finish'd snares:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.29#Above, below, around, with art dispread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.30#The sure inclosure folds the genial bed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.31#Whose texture even the search of gods deceives,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.32#Thin as the filmy threads the spider weaves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.33#Then, as withdrawing from the starry bowers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.34#He feigns a journey to the Lemnian shores,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.35#His favourite isle: observant Mars descries
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.36#His wish'd recees, and to the goddess flies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.37#He glows, he burns, the fair-hair'd queen of love
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.38#Descends, smooth gliding from the courts of Jove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.39#Gay blooming in full charms: her hand he press'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.26.40#With eager joy, and with a sigh address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.27.1#"Come, my beloved! and taste the soft delights:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.27.2#Come, to repose the genial bed invites:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.27.3#Thy absent spouse, neglectful of thy charms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.27.4#Prefers his barbarous Sintians to thy arms!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.28.1#Then, nothing loth, the enamour'd fair he led,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.28.2#And sunk transported on the conscious bed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.28.3#Down rush'd the toils, inwrapping as they lay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.28.4#The careless lovers in their wanton play:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.28.5#In vain they strive; the entangling snares deny
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.28.6#(Inextricably firm) the power to fly.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.28.7#Warn'd by the god who sheds the golden day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.28.8#Stern Vulcan homeward treads the starry way:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.28.9#Arrived, he sees, he grieves, with rage he burns:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.28.10#Full horribly he roars, his voice all heaven returns.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.1#"O Jove (he cried) O all ye powers above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.2#See the lewd dalliance of the queen of love!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.3#Me, awkward me, she scorns; and yields her charms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.4#To that fair lecher, the strong god of arms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.5#If I am lame, that stain my natal hour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.6#By fate imposed; such me my parent bore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.7#Why was I born? See how the wanton lies!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.8#Oh sight tormenting to a husband's eyes!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.9#But yet, I trust, this once e'en Mars would fly
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.10#His fair-one's arms--he thinks her, once, too nigh.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.11#But there remain, ye guilty, in my power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.12#Till Jove refunds his shameless daughter's dower.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.13#Too dear I prized a fair enchanting face:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.29.14#Beauty unchaste is beauty in disgrace."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.30.1#Meanwhile the gods the dome of Vulcan throng;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.30.2#Apollo comes, and Neptune comes along;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.30.3#With these gay Hermes trod the starry plain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.30.4#But modesty withheld the goddess train.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.30.5#All heaven beholds, imprison'd as they lie,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.30.6#And unextinguish'd laughter shakes the sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.30.7#Then mutual, thus they spoke: "Behold on wrong
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.30.8#Swift vengeance waits; and art subdues the strong!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.30.9#Dwells there a god on all the Olympian brow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.30.10#More swift than Mars, and more than Vulcan slow?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.30.11#Yet Vulcan conquers, and the god of arms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.30.12#Must pay the penalty for lawless charms."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.31.1#Thus serious they; but he who gilds the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.31.2#The gay Apollo, thus to Hermes cries:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.31.3#"Wouldst thou enchain'd like Mars, O Hermes, lie
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.31.4#And bear the shame like Mars to share the joy?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.32.1#"O envied shame! (the smiling youth rejoin'd;)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.32.2#And thrice the chains, and thrice more firmly bind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.32.3#Gaze all ye gods, and every goddess gaze,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.32.4#Yet eager would I bless the sweet disgrace."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.33.1#Loud laugh the rest, e'en Neptune laughs aloud,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.33.2#Yet sues importunate to loose the god.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.33.3#"And free, (he cries) O Vulcan! free from shame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.33.4#Thy captives; I ensure the penal claim."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.34.1#"Will Neptune (Vulcan then) the faithless trust?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.34.2#He suffers who gives surety for the unjust:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.34.3#But say, if that lewd scandal of the sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.34.4#To liberty restored, perfidious fly:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.34.5#Say, wilt thou bear the mulct?" He instant cries,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.34.6#"The mulct I bear, if Mars perfidious flies."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.35.1#To whom appeased: "No more I urge delay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.35.2#When Neptune sues, my part is to obey."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.35.3#Then to the snares his force the god applies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.35.4#They burst; and Mars to Thrace indignant flies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.35.5#To the soft Cyprian shores the goddess moves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.35.6#To visit Paphos and her blooming groves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.35.7#Where to the Power an hundred altars rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.35.8#And breathing odours scent the balmy skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.35.9#Concealed she bathes in consecrated bowers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.35.10#The Graces unguents shed, ambrosial showers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.35.11#Unguents that charm the gods! she last assumes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.35.12#Her wondrous robes; and full the goddess blooms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.36.1#Thus sung the bard: Ulysses hears with joy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.36.2#And loud applauses read the vaulted sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.37.1#Then to the sports his sons the king commands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.37.2#Each blooming youth before the monarch stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.37.3#In dance unmatch'd! A wondrous ball is brought
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.37.4#(The work of Polypus, divinely wrought);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.37.5#This youth with strength enormous bids it fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.37.6#And bending backward whirls it to the sky;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.37.7#His brother, springing with an active bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.37.8#At distance intercepts it from the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.37.9#The ball dismissed, in dance they skim the strand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.37.10#Turn and return, and scarce imprint the sand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.37.11#The assembly gazes with astonished eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.37.12#And sends in shouts applauses to the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.38.1#Then thus Ulysses: "Happy king, whose name
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.38.2#The brightest shines in all the rolls of fame!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.38.3#In subjects happy with surprise I gaze;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.38.4#Thy praise was just; their skill transcends thy praise."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.39.1#Pleas'd with his people's fame, the monarch hears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.39.2#And thus benevolent accosts the peers:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.39.3#"Since wisdom's sacred guidance he pursues,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.39.4#Give to the stranger-guest a stranger's dues:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.39.5#Twelve princes in our realm dominion share,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.39.6#O'er whom supreme, imperial power I bear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.39.7#Bring gold, a pledge of love: a talent bring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.39.8#A vest, a robe, and imitate your king.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.39.9#Be swift to give: that he this night may share
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.39.10#The social feast of joy, with joy sincere.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.39.11#And thou, Euryalus, redeem thy wrong;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.39.12#A generous heart repairs a slanderous tongue."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.40.1#The assenting peers, obedient to the king,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.40.2#In haste their heralds send the gifts to bring.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.40.3#Then thus Euryalus: "O prince, whose sway
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.40.4#Rules this bless'd realm, repentant I obey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.40.5#Be his this sword, whose blade of brass displays
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.40.6#A ruddy gleam; whose hilt a silver blaze;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.40.7#Whose ivory sheath, inwrought with curious pride,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.40.8#Adds graceful terror to the wearer's side."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.41.1#He said, and to his hand the sword consign'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.41.2#"And if (he cried) my words affect thy mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.41.3#Far from thy mind those words, ye whirlwinds, bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.41.4#And scatter them, ye storms, in empty air!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.41.5#Crown, O ye heavens, with joy his peaceful hours,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.41.6#And grant him to his spouse, and native shores."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.42.1#"And blest be thou, my friend, (Ulysses cries,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.42.2#Crown him with every joy, ye favouring skies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.42.3#To thy calm hours continued peace afford,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.42.4#And never, never mayst thou want this sword,"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.43.1#He said, and o'er his shoulder flung the blade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.43.2#Now o'er the earth ascends the evening shade:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.43.3#The precious gifts the illustrious heralds bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.43.4#And to the court the embodied peers repair.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.43.5#Before the queen Alcinous' sons unfold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.43.6#The vests, the robes, and heaps of shining gold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.43.7#Then to the radiant thrones they move in state:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.43.8#Aloft, the king in pomp imperial sate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.44.1#Thence to the queen: "O partner of our reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.44.2#O sole beloved! command thy menial train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.44.3#A polish'd chest and stately robes to bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.44.4#And healing waters for the bath prepare;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.44.5#That, bathed, our guest may bid his sorrows cease,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.44.6#Hear the sweet song, and taste the feast in peace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.44.7#A bowl that flames with gold, of wondrous frame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.44.8#Ourself we give, memorial of our name;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.44.9#To raise in offerings to almighty Jove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.44.10#And every god that treads the courts above."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.1#Instant the queen, observant of the king,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.2#Commands her train a spacious vase to bring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.3#The spacious vase with ample streams suffice,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.4#Heap the high wood, and bid the flames arise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.5#The flames climb round it with a fierce embrace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.6#The fuming waters bubble o'er the blaze.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.7#Herself the chest prepares; in order roll'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.8#The robes, the vests are ranged, and heaps of gold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.9#And adding a rich dress inwrought with art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.10#A gift expressive of her bounteous heart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.11#Thus spoke to Ithacus: "To guard with bands
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.12#Insolvable these gifts, thy care demands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.13#Lest, in thy slumbers on the watery main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.45.14#The hand of rapine make our bounty vain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.1#Then bending with full force around he roll'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.2#A labyrinth of bands in fold on fold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.3#Closed with Circaean art. A train attends
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.4#Around the bath: the bath the king ascends
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.5#(Untasted joy, since that disastrous hour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.6#He sail'd ill-fated from Calypso's bower);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.7#Where, happy as the gods that range the sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.8#He feasted every sense with every joy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.9#He bathes; the damsels with officious toil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.10#Shed sweets, shed unguents, in a shower of oil;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.11#Then o'er his limbs a gorgeous robe he spreads,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.12#And to the feast magnificently treads.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.13#Full where the dome its shining valves expands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.14#Nausicaa blooming as a goddess stands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.15#With wondering eyes the hero she survey'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.46.16#And graceful thus began the royal maid:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.47.1#"Hail, godlike stranger! and when heaven restores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.47.2#To thy fond wish thy long-expected shores,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.47.3#This ever grateful in remembrance bear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.47.4#To me thou owest, to me, the vital air."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.48.1#"O royal maid! (Ulysses straight returns)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.48.2#Whose worth the splendours of thy race adorns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.48.3#So may dread Jove (whose arm in vengeance forms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.48.4#The writhen bolt, and blackens heaven with storms),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.48.5#Restore me safe, through weary wanderings toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.48.6#To my dear country's ever-pleasing coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.48.7#As while the spirit in this bosom glows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.48.8#To thee, my goddess, I address my vows;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.48.9#My life, thy gift I boast!" He said, and sate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.48.10#Fast by Alcinous on a throne of state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.1#Now each partakes the feast, the wine prepares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.2#Portions the food, and each his portion shares.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.3#The bard a herald guides; the gazing throng
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.4#Pay low obeisance as he moves along:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.5#Beneath a sculptur'd arch he sits enthroned,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.6#The peers encircling form an awful round.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.7#Then, from the chine, Ulysses carves with art
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.8#Delicious food, an honorary part:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.9#"This, let the master of the lyre receive,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.10#A pledge of love! 'tis all a wretch can give.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.11#Lives there a man beneath the spacious skies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.12#Who sacred honours to the bard denies?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.13#The Muse the bard inspires, exalts his mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.49.14#The muse indulgent loves the harmonious kind."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.50.1#The herald to his hand the charge conveys,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.50.2#Not fond of flattery, nor unpleased with praise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.1#When now the rage of hunger was allay'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.2#Thus to the lyrist wise Ulysses said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.3#"O more than man! thy soul the muse inspires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.4#Or Phoebus animates with all his fires;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.5#For who, by Phoebus uninform'd, could know
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.6#The woe of Greece, and sing so well the woe?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.7#Just to the tale, as present at the fray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.8#Or taught the labours of the dreadful day:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.9#The song recalls past horrors to my eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.10#And bids proud Ilion from her ashes rise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.11#Once more harmonious strike the sounding string,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.12#The Epaean fabric, framed by Pallas, sing:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.13#How stern Ulysses, furious to destroy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.14#With latent heroes sack'd imperial Troy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.15#If faithful thou record the tale of Fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.16#The god himself inspires thy breast with flame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.17#And mine shall be the task henceforth to raise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.51.18#In every land thy monument of praise."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.1#Full of the god he raised his lofty strain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.2#How the Greeks rush'd tumultuous to the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.3#How blazing tents illumined half the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.4#While from the shores the winged navy flies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.5#How e'en in Ilion's walls, in deathful bands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.6#Came the stern Greeks by Troy's assisting hands:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.7#All Troy up-heaved the steed; of differing mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.8#Various the Trojans counsell'd: part consign'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.9#The monster to the sword, part sentence gave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.10#To plunge it headlong in the whelming wave;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.11#The unwise award to lodge it in the towers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.12#An offering sacred to the immortal powers:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.13#The unwise prevail, they lodge it in the walls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.14#And by the gods' decree proud Ilion falls:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.15#Destruction enters in the treacherous wood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.52.16#And vengeful slaughter, fierce for human blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.53.1#He sung the Greeks stern-issuing from the steed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.53.2#How Ilion burns, how all her fathers bleed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.53.3#How to thy dome, Deiphobus! ascends
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.53.4#The Spartan king; how Ithacus attends
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.53.5#(Horrid as Mars); and how with dire alarms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.53.6#He fights--subdues, for Pallas strings his arms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.54.1#Thus while he sung, Ulysses' griefs renew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.54.2#Tears bathe his cheeks, and tears the ground bedew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.54.3#As some fond matron views in mortal fight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.54.4#Her husband falling in his country's right;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.54.5#Frantic through clashing swords she runs, she flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.54.6#As ghastly pale he groans, and faints and dies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.54.7#Close to his breast she grovels on the ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.54.8#And bathes with floods of tears the gaping wound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.54.9#She cries, she shrieks: the fierce insulting foe
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.54.10#Relentless mocks her violence of woe:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.54.11#To chains condemn'd, as wildly she deplores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.54.12#A widow, and a slave on foreign shores.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.1#So from the sluices of Ulysses' eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.2#Fast fell the tears, and sighs succeeded sighs:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.3#Conceal'd he grieved: the king observed alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.4#The silent tear, and heard the secret groan;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.5#Then to the bard aloud: "O cease to sing,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.6#Dumb be thy voice, and mute the tuneful string;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.7#To every note his tears responsive flow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.8#And his great heart heaves with tumultuous woe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.9#Thy lay too deeply moves: then cease the lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.10#And o'er the banquet every heart be gay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.11#This social right demands: for him the sails,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.12#Floating in air, invite the impelling gales:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.13#His are the gifts of love: the wise and good
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.55.14#Receive the stranger as a brother's blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.1#"But, friend, discover faithful what I crave;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.2#Artful concealment ill becomes the brave:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.3#Say what thy birth, and what the name you bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.4#Imposed by parents in the natal hour?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.5#(For from the natal hour distinctive names,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.6#One common right, the great and lowly claims:)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.7#Say from what city, from what regions toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.8#And what inhabitants those regions boast?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.9#So shalt thou instant reach the realm assign'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.10#In wondrous ships, self-moved, instinct with mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.11#No helm secures their course, no pilot guides;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.12#Like man intelligent, they plough the tides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.13#Conscious of every coast, and every bay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.14#That lies beneath the sun's all-seeing ray;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.15#Though clouds and darkness veil the encumber'd sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.16#Fearless through darkness and through clouds they fly;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.17#Though tempests rage, though rolls the swelling main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.18#The seas may roll, the tempests rage in vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.19#E'en the stern god that o'er the waves presides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.20#Safe as they pass, and safe repass the tides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.21#With fury burns; while careless they convey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.22#Promiscuous every guest to every bay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.23#These ears have heard my royal sire disclose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.24#A dreadful story, big with future woes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.25#How Neptune raged, and how, by his command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.26#Firm rooted in a surge a ship should stand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.27#A monument of wrath; how mound on mound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.28#Should bury these proud towers beneath the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.29#But this the gods may frustrate or fulfil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.30#As suits the purpose of the Eternal Will.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.31#But say through what waste regions hast thou stray'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.32#What customs noted, and what coasts survey'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.33#Possess'd by wild barbarians fierce in arms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.34#Or men whose bosom tender pity warms?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.35#Say why the fate of Troy awaked thy cares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.36#Why heaved thy bosom, and why flowed thy tears?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.37#Just are the ways of Heaven: from Heaven proceed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.38#The woes of man; Heaven doom'd the Greeks to bleed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.39#A theme of future song! Say, then, if slain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.40#Some dear-loved brother press'd the Phrygian plain?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.41#Or bled some friend, who bore a brother's part,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:8.56.42#And claim'd by merit, not by blood, the heart?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.1.1#Then thus Ulysses: "Thou whom first in sway,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.1.2#As first in virtue, these thy realms obey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.1.3#How sweet the products of a peaceful reign!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.1.4#The heaven-taught poet and enchanting strain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.1.5#The well-filled palace, the perpetual feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.1.6#A land rejoicing, and a people bless'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.1.7#How goodly seems it ever to employ
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.1.8#Man's social days in union and in joy;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.1.9#The plenteous hoard high-heap'd with cates divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.1.10#And o'er the foaming bowl the laughing wine!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.2.1#"Amid these joys, why seels thy mind to know
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.2.2#The unhappy series of a wanderer's woe?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.2.3#Rememberance sad, whose image to review,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.2.4#Alas, I must open all my wounds anew!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.2.5#And oh, what first, what last shall I relate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.2.6#Of woes unnumbered sent by Heaven and Fate?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.3.1#"Know first the man (though now a wretch distress'd)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.3.2#Who hopes thee, monarch, for his future guest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.3.3#Behold Ulysses! no ignoble name,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.3.4#Earth sounds my wisdom and high heaven my fame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.1#"My native soil is Ithaca the fair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.2#Where high Neritus waves his woods in air;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.3#Dulichium, Same and Zaccynthus crown'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.4#With shady mountains spread their isles around.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.5#(These to the north and night's dark regions run,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.6#Those to Aurora and the rising sun).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.7#Low lies our isle, yet bless'd in fruitful stores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.8#Strong are her sons, though rocky are her shores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.9#And none, ah none no lovely to my sight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.10#Of all the lands that heaven o'erspreads with light.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.11#In vain Calypso long constrained my stay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.12#With sweet, reluctant, amorous delay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.13#With all her charms as vainly Circe strove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.14#And added magic to secure my love.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.15#In pomps or joys, the palace or the grot,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.16#My country's image never was forgot;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.17#My absent parents rose before my sight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.4.18#And distant lay contentment and delight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.1#"Hear, then, the woes which mighty Jove ordain'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.2#To wait my passage from the Trojan land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.3#The winds from Ilion to the Cicons' shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.4#Beneath cold Ismarus our vessels bore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.5#We boldly landed on the hostile place,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.6#And sack'd the city, and destroy'd the race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.7#Their wives made captive, their possessions shared,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.8#And every soldier found a like reward
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.9#I then advised to fly; not so the rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.10#Who stay'd to revel, and prolong the feast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.11#The fatted sheep and sable bulls they slay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.12#And bowls flow round, and riot wastes the day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.13#Meantime the Cicons, to their holds retired,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.14#Call on the Cicons, with new fury fired;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.15#With early morn the gather'd country swarms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.16#And all the continent is bright with arms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.17#Thick as the budding leaves or rising flowers
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.18#O'erspread the land, when spring descends in showers:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.19#All expert soldiers, skill'd on foot to dare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.20#Or from the bounding courser urge the war.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.21#Now fortune changes (so the Fates ordain);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.22#Our hour was come to taste our share of pain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.23#Close at the ships the bloody fight began,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.24#Wounded they wound, and man expires on man.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.25#Long as the morning sun increasing bright
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.26#O'er heaven's pure azure spreads the glowing light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.27#Promiscuous death the form of war confounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.28#Each adverse battle gored with equal wounds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.29#But when his evening wheels o'erhung the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.30#Then conquest crown'd the fierce Ciconian train.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.31#Six brave companions from each ship we lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.32#The rest escape in haste, and quit the coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.33#With sails outspread we fly the unequal strife,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.34#Sad for their loss, but joyful of our life.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.35#Yet as we fled, our fellows' rites we paid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.5.36#And thrice we call'd on each unhappy shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.1#"Meanwhile the god, whose hand the thunder forms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.2#Drives clouds on clouds, and blackens heaven with storms:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.3#Wide o'er the waste the rage of Boreas sweeps,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.4#And night rush'd headlong on the shaded deeps.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.5#Now here, now there, the giddy ships are borne,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.6#And all the rattling shrouds in fragments torn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.7#We furl'd the sail, we plied the labouring oar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.8#Took down our masts, and row'd our ships to shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.9#Two tedious days and two long nights we lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.10#O'erwatch'd and batter'd in the naked bay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.11#But the third morning when Aurora brings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.12#We rear the masts, we spread the canvas wings;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.13#Refresh'd and careless on the deck reclined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.14#We sit, and trust the pilot and the wind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.15#Then to my native country had I sail'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.16#But, the cape doubled, adverse winds prevail'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.17#Strong was the tide, which by the northern blast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.18#Impell'd, our vessels on Cythera cast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.19#Nine days our fleet the uncertain tempest bore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.20#Far in wide ocean, and from sight of shore:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.21#The tenth we touch'd, by various errors toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.22#The land of Lotus and the flowery coast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.23#We climb'd the beach, and springs of water found,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.24#Then spread our hasty banquet on the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.25#Three men were sent, deputed from the crew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.26#(A herald one) the dubious coast to view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.27#And learn what habitants possess'd the place.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.28#They went, and found a hospitable race:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.29#Not prone to ill, nor strange to foreign guest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.30#They eat, they drink, and nature gives the feast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.31#The trees around them all their food produce:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.32#Lotus the name: divine, nectareous juice!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.33#(Thence call'd Lo'ophagi); which whose tastes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.34#Insatiate riots in the sweet repasts,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.35#Nor other home, nor other care intends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.36#But quits his house, his country, and his friends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.37#The three we sent, from off the enchanting ground
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.38#We dragg'd reluctant, and by force we bound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.39#The rest in haste forsook the pleasing shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.40#Or, the charm tasted, had return'd no more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.41#Now placed in order on their banks, they sweep
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.42#The sea's smooth face, and cleave the hoary deep:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.43#With heavy hearts we labour through the tide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.6.44#To coasts unknown, and oceans yet untried.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.1#"The land of Cyclops first, a savage kind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.2#Nor tamed by manners, nor by laws confined:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.3#Untaught to plant, to turn the glebe, and sow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.4#They all their products to free nature owe:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.5#The soil, untill'd, a ready harvest yields,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.6#With wheat and barley wave the golden fields;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.7#Spontaneous wines from weighty clusters pour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.8#And Jove descends in each prolific shower,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.9#By these no statues and no rights are known,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.10#No council held, no monarch fills the throne;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.11#But high on hills, or airy cliffs, they dwell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.12#Or deep in caves whose entrance leads to hell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.13#Each rules his race, his neighbour not his care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.7.14#Heedless of others, to his own severe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.1#"Opposed to the Cyclopean coast, there lay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.2#An isle, whose hill their subject fields survey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.3#Its name Lachaea, crown'd with many a grove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.4#Where savage goats through pathless thickets rove:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.5#No needy mortals here, with hunger bold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.6#Or wretched hunters through the wintry cold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.7#Pursue their flight; but leave them safe to bound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.8#From hill to hill, o'er all the desert ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.9#Nor knows the soil to feed the fleecy care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.10#Or feels the labours of the crooked share;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.11#But uninhabited, untill'd, unsown,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.12#It lies, and breeds the bleating goat alone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.13#For there no vessel with vermilion prore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.14#Or bark of traffic, glides from shore to shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.15#The rugged race of savages, unskill'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.16#The seas to traverse, or the ships to build,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.17#Gaze on the coast, nor cultivate the soil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.18#Unlearn'd in all the industrious art of toil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.19#Yet here all produces and all plants abound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.20#Sprung from the fruitful genius of the ground;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.21#Fields waving high with heavy crops are seen,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.22#And vines that flourish in eternal green,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.23#Refreshing meads along the murmuring main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.8.24#And fountains streaming down the fruitful plain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.1#"A port there is, inclosed on either side,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.2#Where ships may rest, unanchor'd and untied;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.3#Till the glad mariners incline to sail,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.4#And the sea whitens with the rising gale,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.5#High at the head, from out the cavern'd rock,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.6#In living rills a gushing fountain broke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.7#Around it, and above, for ever green,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.8#The busy alders form'd a shady scene;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.9#Hither some favouring god, beyond our thought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.10#Through all surrounding shade our navy brought;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.11#For gloomy night descended on the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.12#Nor glimmer'd Phoebe in the ethereal plain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.13#But all unseen the clouded island lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.14#And all unseen the surge and rolling sea,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.15#Till safe we anchor'd in the shelter'd bay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.16#Our sails we gather'd, cast our cables o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.17#And slept secure along the sandy shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.18#Soon as again the rosy morning shone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.19#Reveal'd the landscape and the scene unknown,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.20#With wonder seized, we view the pleasing ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.21#And walk delighted, and expatiate round.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.22#Roused by the woodland nymphs at early dawn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.23#The mountain goats came bounding o'er the lawn:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.24#In haste our fellows to the ships repair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.25#For arms and weapons of the sylvan war;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.26#Straight in three squadrons all our crew we part,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.27#And bend the bow, or wing the missile dart;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.28#The bounteous gods afford a copious prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.29#And nine fat goats each vessel bears away:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.30#The royal bark had ten. Our ships complete
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.9.31#We thus supplied (for twelve were all the fleet).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.1#"Here, till the setting sun roll'd down the light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.2#We sat indulging in the genial rite:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.3#Nor wines were wanting; those from ample jars
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.4#We drain'd, the prize of our Ciconian wars.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.5#The land of Cyclops lay in prospect near:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.6#The voice of goats and bleating flocks we hear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.7#And from their mountains rising smokes appear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.8#Now sunk the sun, and darkness cover'd o'er
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.9#The face of things: along the sea-beat shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.10#Satiate we slept: but, when the sacred dawn
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.11#Arising glitter'd o'er the dewy lawn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.12#I call'd my fellows, and these words address'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.13#'My dear associates, here indulge your rest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.14#While, with my single ship, adventurous, I
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.15#Go forth, the manners of you men to try;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.16#Whether a race unjust, of barbarous might,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.17#Rude and unconscious of a stranger's right;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.18#Or such who harbour pity in their breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.10.19#Revere the gods, and succour the distress'd,'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.1#"This said, I climb'd my vessel's lofty side;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.2#My train obey'd me, and the ship untied.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.3#In order seated on their banks, they sweep
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.4#Neptune's smooth face, and cleave the yielding deep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.5#When to the nearest verge of land we drew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.6#Fast by the sea a lonely cave we view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.7#High, and with darkening laurels covered o'er;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.8#Were sheep and goats lay slumbering round the shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.9#Near this, a fence of marble from the rock,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.10#Brown with o'eraching pine and spreading oak.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.11#A giant shepherd here his flock maintains
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.12#Far from the rest, and solitary reigns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.13#In shelter thick of horrid shade reclined;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.14#And gloomy mischiefs labour in his mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.15#A form enormous! far unlike the race
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.16#Of human birth, in stature, or in face;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.17#As some lone mountain's monstrous growth he stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.18#Crown'd with rough thickets, and a nodding wood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.19#I left my vessel at the point of land,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.20#And close to guard it, gave our crew command:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.21#With only twelve, the boldest and the best,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.22#I seek the adventure, and forsake the rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.23#Then took a goatskin fill'd with precious wine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.24#The gift of Maron of Evantheus' line
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.25#(The priest of Phoebus at the Ismarian shrine).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.26#In sacred shade his honour'd mansion stood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.27#Amidst Apollo's consecrated wood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.28#Him, and his house, Heaven moved my mind to save,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.29#And costly presents in return he gave;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.30#Seven golden talents to perfection wrought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.31#A silver bowl that held a copious draught,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.32#And twelve large vessels of unmingled wine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.33#Mellifluous, undecaying, and divine!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.34#Which now, some ages from his race conceal'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.35#The hoary sire in gratitude reveal'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.36#Such was the wine: to quench whose fervent steam
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.37#Scarce twenty measures from the living stream
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.38#To cool one cup sufficed: the goblet crown'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.39#Breathed aromatic fragrances around.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.40#Of this an ample vase we heaved aboard,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.41#And brought another with provisions stored.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.42#My soul foreboded I should find the bower
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.43#Of some fell monster, fierce with barbarous power;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.44#Some rustic wretch, who lived in Heaven's despite,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.45#Contemning laws, and trampling on the right.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.46#The cave we found, but vacant all within
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.47#(His flock the giant tended on the green):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.48#But round the grot we gaze; and all we view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.49#In order ranged our admiration drew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.50#The bending shelves with loads of cheeses press'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.51#The folded flocks each separate from the rest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.52#(The larger here, and there the lesser lambs,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.53#The new-fallen young here bleating for their dams:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.54#The kid distinguish'd from the lambkin lies);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.55#The cavern echoes with responsive cries.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.56#Capacious chargers all around were laid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.57#Full pails, and vessels of the milking trade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.58#With fresh provisions hence our fleet to store
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.59#My friends advise me, and to quit the shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.60#Or drive a flock of sheep and goats away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.61#Consult our safety, and put off to sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.62#Their wholesome counsel rashly I declined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.63#Curious to view the man of monstrous kind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.64#And try what social rites a savage lends:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.11.65#Dire rites, alas! and fatal to my friends
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.1#"Then first a fire we kindle, and prepare
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.2#For his return with sacrifice and prayer;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.3#The loaden shelves afford us full repast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.4#We sit expecting. Lo! he comes at last,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.5#Near half a forest on his back he bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.6#And cast the ponderous burden at the door.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.7#It thunder'd as it fell. We trembled then,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.8#And sought the deep recesses of the den.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.9#New driven before him through the arching rock,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.10#Came tumbling, heaps on heaps, the unnumber'd flock.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.11#Big-udder'd ewes, and goats of female kind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.12#(The males were penn'd in outward courts behind);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.13#Then, heaved on high, a rock's enormous weight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.14#To the cave's mouth he roll'd, and closed the gate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.15#(Scarce twenty four-wheel'd cars, compact and strong,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.16#The massy load could bear, or roll along).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.17#He next betakes him to his evening cares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.18#And, sitting down, to milk his flocks prepares;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.19#Of half their udders eases first the dams,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.20#Then to the mother's teat submits the lambs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.21#Half the white stream to hardening cheese be press'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.22#And high in wicker-baskets heap'd: the rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.23#Reserved in bowls, supplied his nightly feast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.24#His labour done, he fired the pile, that gave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.25#A sudden blaze, and lighted all the cave.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.26#We stand discover'd by the rising fires;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.12.27#Askance the giant glares, and thus inquires:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.13.1#"'What are ye, guests? on what adventure, say,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.13.2#Thus far ye wander through the watery way?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.13.3#Pirates perhaps, who seek through seas unknown
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.13.4#The lives of others, and expose your own?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.14.1#"His voice like thunder through the cavern sounds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.14.2#My bold companions thrilling fear confounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.14.3#Appall'd at sight of more than mortal man!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.14.4#At length, with heart recover'd, I began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.1#"'From Troy's famed fields, sad wanderers o'er the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.2#Behold the relics of the Grecian train:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.3#Through various seas, by various perils toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.4#And forced by storms, unwilling on your coast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.5#Far from our destined course and native land,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.6#Such was our fate, and such high Jove's command!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.7#Nor what we are befits us to disclaim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.8#Atrides' friends (in arms a mighty name),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.9#Who taught proud Troy and all her sons to bow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.10#Victors of late, but humble suppliants now!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.11#Low at thy knee thy succour we implore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.12#Respect us, human, and relieve us, poor.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.13#At least, some hospitable gift bestow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.14#'Tis what the happy to the unhappy owe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.15#'Tis what the gods require: those gods revere;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.16#The poor and stranger are their constant care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.17#To Jove their cause, and their revenge belongs,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.15.18#He wanders with them, and he feels their wrongs."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.16.1#"'Fools that ye are (the savage thus replies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.16.2#His inward fury blazing at his eyes),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.16.3#Or strangers, distant far from our abodes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.16.4#To bid me reverence or regard the gods.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.16.5#Know then, we Cyclops are a race above
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.16.6#Those air-bred people, and their goat-nursed Jove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.16.7#And learn, our power proceeds with thee and thine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.16.8#Not as he wills, but as ourselves incline.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.16.9#But answer, the good ship that brought ye o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.16.10#Where lies she anchor'd? near or off the shore?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.17.1#"Thus he. His meditated fraud I find
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.17.2#(Versed in the turns of various human-kind):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.17.3#And, cautious thus: 'Against a dreadful rock,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.17.4#Fast by your shore the gallant vessel broke.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.17.5#Scarce with these few I 'scaped; of all my train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.17.6#Whom angry Neptune, whelm'd beneath the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.17.7#The scattered wreck the winds blew back again.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.1#"He answer'd with his deed: his bloody hand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.2#Snatch'd two, unhappy! of my martial band;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.3#And dash'd like dogs against the stony floor:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.4#The pavement swims with brains and mingled gore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.5#Torn limb from limb, he spreads his horrid feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.6#And fierce devours it like a mountain beast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.7#He sucks the marrow, and the blood he drains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.8#Nor entrails, flesh, nor solid bone remains.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.9#We see the death from which we cannot move,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.10#And humbled groan beneath the hand of Jove.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.11#His ample maw with human carnage fill'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.12#A milky deluge next the giant swill'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.13#Then stretch'd in length o'er half the cavern'd rock,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.14#Lay senseless, and supine, amidst the flock.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.15#To seize the time, and with a sudden wound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.16#To fix the slumbering monster to the ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.17#My soul impels me! and in act I stand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.18#To draw the sword; but wisdom held my hand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.19#A deed so rash had finished all our fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.20#No mortal forces from the lofty gate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.21#Could roll the rock. In hopeless grief we lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.22#And sigh, expecting the return of day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.23#Now did the rosy-fingered morn arise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.24#And shed her sacred light along the skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.25#He wakes, he lights the fire, he milks the dams,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.26#And to the mother's teats submits the lambs.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.27#The task thus finish'd of his morning hours,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.28#Two more he snatches, murders, and devours.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.29#Then pleased, and whistling, drives his flock before,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.30#Removes the rocky mountain from the door,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.31#And shuts again: with equal ease disposed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.32#As a light quiver's lid is oped and closed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.33#His giant voice the echoing region fills:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.18.34#His flocks, obedient, spread o'er all the hills.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.1#"Thus left behind, even in the last despair
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.2#I thought, devised, and Pallas heard my prayer.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.3#Revenge, and doubt, and caution, work'd my breast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.4#But this of many counsels seem'd the best:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.5#The monster's club within the cave I spied,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.6#A tree of stateliest growth, and yet undried,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.7#Green from the wood: of height and bulk so vast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.8#The largest ship might claim it for a mast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.9#This shorten'd of its top, I gave my train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.10#A fathom's length, to shape it and to plane;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.11#The narrower end I sharpen'd to a spire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.12#Whose point we harden'd with the force of fire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.13#And hid it in the dust that strew'd the cave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.14#Then to my few companions, bold and brave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.15#Proposed, who first the venturous deed should try,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.16#In the broad orbit of his monstrous eye
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.17#To plunge the brand and twirl the pointed wood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.18#When slumber next should tame the man of blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.19#Just as I wished, the lots were cast on four:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.20#Myself the fifth. We stand and wait the hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.21#He comes with evening: all his fleecy flock
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.22#Before him march, and pour into the rock:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.23#Not one, or male or female, stayed behind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.24#(So fortune chanced, or so some god designed);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.25#Then heaving high the stone's unwieldy weight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.26#He roll'd it on the cave and closed the gate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.27#First down he sits, to milk the woolly dams,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.28#And then permits their udder to the lambs.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.29#Next seized two wretches more, and headlong cast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.30#Brain'd on the rock; his second dire repast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.31#I then approach'd him reeking with their gore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.32#And held the brimming goblet foaming o'er;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.33#'Cyclop! since human flesh has been thy feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.34#Now drain this goblet, potent to digest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.35#Know hence what treasures in our ship we lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.36#And what rich liquors other climates boast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.37#We to thy shore the precious freight shall bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.38#If home thou send us and vouchsafe to spare.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.39#But oh! thus furious, thirsting thus for gore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.40#The sons of men shall ne'er approach thy shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.19.41#And never shalt thou taste this nectar more,'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.20.1#"He heard, he took, and pouring down his throat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.20.2#Delighted, swill'd the large luxurious draught,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.20.3#'More! give me more (he cried): the boon be thine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.20.4#Whoe'er thou art that bear'st celestial wine!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.20.5#Declare thy name: not mortal is this juice,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.20.6#Such as the unbless'd Cyclopaean climes produce
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.20.7#(Though sure our vine the largest cluster yields,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.20.8#And Jove's scorn'd thunder serves to drench our fields);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.20.9#But this descended from the bless'd abodes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.20.10#A rill of nectar, streaming from the gods.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.21.1#"He said, and greedy grasped the heady bowl,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.21.2#Thrice drained, and poured the deluge on his soul.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.21.3#His sense lay covered with the dozy fume;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.21.4#While thus my fraudful speech I reassume.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.21.5#'Thy promised boon, O Cyclop! now I claim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.21.6#And plead my title; Noman is my name.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.21.7#By that distinguish'd from my tender years,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.21.8#'Tis what my parents call me, and my peers.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.22.1#"The giant then: 'Our promis'd grace receive,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.22.2#The hospitable boon we mean to give:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.22.3#When all thy wretched crew have felt my power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.22.4#Noman shall be the last I will devour.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.1#"He said: then nodding with the fumes of wine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.2#Droop'd his huge head, and snoring lay supine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.3#His neck obliquely o'er his shoulders hung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.4#Press'd with the weight of sleep that tames the strong:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.5#There belch'd the mingled streams of wine and blood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.6#And human flesh, his indigested food.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.7#Sudden I stir the embers, and inspire
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.8#With animating breath the seeds of fire:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.9#Each drooping spirit with bold words repair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.10#And urged my train the dreadful deed to dare.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.11#The stake now glow'd beneath the burning bed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.12#(Green as it was) and sparkled fiery red,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.13#Then forth the vengeful instrument I bring;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.14#With beating hearts my fellows form a ring.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.15#Urged my some present god, they swift let fall
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.16#The pointed torment on his visual ball.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.17#Myself above them from a rising ground
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.18#Guide the sharp stake, and twirl it round and round.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.19#As when a shipwright stands his workmen o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.20#Who ply the wimble, some huge beam to bore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.21#Urged on all hands, it nimbly spins about,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.22#The grain deep-piercing till it scoops it out:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.23#In his broad eye he whirls the fiery wood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.24#From the pierced pupil spouts the boiling blood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.25#Singed are his brows; the scorching lids grow black;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.26#The jelly bubbles, and the fibres crack.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.27#And as when armourers temper in the ford
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.28#The keen-edged pole-axe, or the shining sword,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.29#The red-hot metal hisses in the lake,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.30#Thus in his eye-ball hiss'd the plunging stake.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.31#He sends a dreadful groan, the rocks around
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.32#Through all their inmost winding caves resound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.33#Scared we recoiled.  Forth with frantic hand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.34#He tore and dash'd on earth and gory brand;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.35#Then calls the Cyclops, all that round him dwell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.36#With voice like thunder, and a direful yell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.37#From all their dens the one-eyed race repair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.38#From rifted rocks, and mountains bleak in air.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.39#All haste assembled, at his well-known roar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.23.40#Inquire the cause, and crowd the cavern door.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.24.1#"'What hurts thee, Polypheme? what strange affright
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.24.2#Thus breaks our slumbers, and disturbs the night?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.24.3#Does any mortal, in the unguarded hour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.24.4#Of sleep, oppress thee, or by fraud or power?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.24.5#Or thieves insidious thy fair flock surprise?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.24.6#Thus they; the Cyclop from his den replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.1#"'Friends, Noman kills me; Noman in the hour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.2#Of sleep, oppresses me with fraudful power.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.3#'If no man hurt thee, but the hand divine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.4#Inflict disease, it fits thee to resign:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.5#To Jove or to thy father Neptune pray.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.6#The brethren cried, and instant strode away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.7#"Joy touch'd my secret soul and conscious heart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.8#Pleased with the effect of conduct and of art.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.9#Meantime the Cyclop, raging with his wound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.10#Spreads his wide arms, and searches round and round:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.11#At last, the stone removing from the gate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.12#With hands extended in the midst he sate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.13#And search'd each passing sheep, and fell it o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.14#Secure to seize us ere we reach'd the door
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.15#(Such as his shallow wit he deem'd was mine);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.16#But secret I revolved the deep design:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.17#'Twas for our lives my labouring bosom wrought;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.18#Each scheme I turn'd, and sharpen'd every thought;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.19#This way and that I cast to save my friends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.25.20#Till one resolve my varying counsel ends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.1#"Strong were the rams, with native purple fair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.2#Well fed, and largest of the fleecy care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.3#These, three and three, with osier bands we tied
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.4#(The twining bands the Cyclop's bed supplied);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.5#The midmost bore a man, the outward two
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.6#Secured each side: so bound we all the crew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.7#One ram remain'd, the leader of the flock:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.8#In his deep fleece my grasping hands I lock,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.9#And fast beneath, in wooly curls inwove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.10#There cling implicit, and confide in Jove.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.11#When rosy morning glimmer'd o'er the dales,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.12#He drove to pasture all the lusty males:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.13#The ewes still folded, with distended thighs
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.14#Unmilk'd lay bleating in distressful cries.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.15#But heedless of those cares, with anguish stung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.16#He felt their fleeces as they pass'd along
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.17#(Fool that he was.) and let them safely go,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.26.18#All unsuspecting of their freight below.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.1#"The master ram at last approach'd the gate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.2#Charged with his wool, and with Ulysses' fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.3#Him while he pass'd, the monster blind bespoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.4#'What makes my ram the lag of all the flock?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.5#First thou wert wont to crop the flowery mead,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.6#First to the field and river's bank to lead,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.7#And first with stately step at evening hour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.8#Thy fleecy fellows usher to their bower.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.9#Now far the last, with pensive pace and slow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.10#Thou movest, as conscious of thy master's woe!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.11#Seest thou these lids that now unfold in vain?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.12#(The deed of Noman and his wicked train!)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.13#Oh! did'st thou feel for thy afflicted lord,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.14#And would but Fate the power of speech afford.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.15#Soon might'st thou tell me, where in secret here
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.16#The dastard lurks, all trembling with his fear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.17#Swung round and round, and dash'd from rock to rock,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.18#His battered brains should on the pavement smoke
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.19#No ease, no pleasure my sad heart receives,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.27.20#While such a monster as vile Noman lives.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.1#"The giant spoke, and through the hollow rock
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.2#Dismiss'd the ram, the father of the flock.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.3#No sooner freed, and through the inclosure pass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.4#First I release myself, my fellows last:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.5#Fat sheep and goats in throngs we drive before,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.6#And reach our vessel on the winding shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.7#With joy the sailors view their friends return'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.8#And hail us living whom as dead they mourn'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.9#Big tears of transport stand in every eye:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.10#I check their fondness, and command to fly.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.11#Aboard in haste they heave the wealthy sheep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.12#And snatch their oars, and rush into the deep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.13#"Now off at sea, and from the shallows clear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.14#As far as human voice could reach the ear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.15#With taunts the distant giant I accost:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.16#'Hear me, O Cyclop! hear, ungracious host!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.17#'Twas on no coward, no ignoble slave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.18#Thou meditatest thy meal in yonder cave;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.19#But one, the vengeance fated from above
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.20#Doom'd to inflict; the instrument of Jove.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.21#Thy barbarous breach of hospitable bands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.28.22#The god, the god revenges by my hands.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.1#"These words the Cyclop's burning rage provoke;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.2#From the tall hill he rends a pointed rock;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.3#High o'er the billows flew the massy load,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.4#And near the ship came thundering on the flood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.5#It almost brush'd the helm, and fell before:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.6#The whole sea shook, and refluent beat the shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.7#The strong concussion on the heaving tide
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.8#Roll'd back the vessel to the island's side:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.9#Again I shoved her off: our fate to fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.10#Each nerve we stretch, and every oar we ply.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.11#Just 'scaped impending death, when now again
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.12#We twice as far had furrow'd back the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.13#Once more I raise my voice; my friends, afraid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.14#With mild entreaties my design dissuade:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.15#'What boots the godless giant to provoke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.16#Whose arm may sink us at a single stroke?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.17#Already when the dreadful rock he threw,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.18#Old Ocean shook, and back his surges flew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.19#The sounding voice directs his aim again;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.29.20#The rock o'erwhelms us, and we 'scaped in vain.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.30.1#"But I, of mind elate, and scorning fear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.30.2#Thus with new taunts insult the monster's ear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.30.3#'Cyclop! if any, pitying thy disgrace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.30.4#Ask, who disfigured thus that eyeless face?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.30.5#Say 'twas Ulysses: 'twas his deed declare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.30.6#Laertes' son, of Ithaca the fair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.30.7#Ulysses, far in fighting fields renown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.30.8#Before whose arm Troy tumbled to the ground.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.1#"The astonished savage with a roar replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.2#'Oh heavens! oh faith of ancient prophecies!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.3#This, Telemus Eurymedes foretold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.4#(The mighty seer who on these hills grew old;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.5#Skill'd the dark fates of mortals to declare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.6#And learn'd in all wing'd omens of the air);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.7#Long since he menaced, such was Fate's command;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.8#And named Ulysses as the destined hand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.9#I deem'd some godlike giant to behold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.10#Or lofty hero, haughty, brave, and bold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.11#Not this weak pigmy wretch, of mean design,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.12#Who, not by strength subdued me, but by wine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.13#But come, accept our gifts, and join to pray
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.14#Great Neptune's blessing on the watery way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.15#For his I am, and I the lineage own;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.16#The immortal father no less boasts the son.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.17#His power can heal me, and relight my eye;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.18#And only his, of all the gods on high.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.19#"'Oh! could this arm (I thus aloud rejoin'd)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.20#From that vast bulk dislodge thy bloody mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.21#And send thee howling to the realms of night!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.22#As sure as Neptune cannot give thee sight.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.23#"Thus I; while raging he repeats his cries,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.24#With hands uplifted to the starry skies?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.25#'Hear me, O Neptune; thou whose arms are hurl'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.26#From shore to shore, and gird the solid world;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.27#If thine I am, nor thou my birth disown,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.28#And if the unhappy Cyclop be thy son,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.29#Let not Ulysses breathe his native air,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.30#Laertes' son, of Ithaca the fair.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.31#If to review his country be his fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.32#Be it through toils and sufferings long and late;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.33#His lost companions let him first deplore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.34#Some vessel, not his own, transport him o'er;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.35#And when at home from foreign sufferings freed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.36#More near and deep, domestic woes succeed!'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.37#With imprecations thus he fill'd the air,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.38#And angry Neptune heard the unrighteous prayer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.39#A larger rock then heaving from the plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.40#He whirl'd it round: it sung across the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.41#It fell, and brush'd the stern: the billows roar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.42#Shake at the weight, and refluent beat the shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.43#With all our force we kept aloof to sea,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.44#And gain'd the island where our vessels lay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.45#Our sight the whole collected navy cheer'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.46#Who, waiting long, by turns had hoped and fear'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.47#There disembarking on the green sea side,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.48#We land our cattle, and the spoil divide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.49#Of these due shares to every sailor fall;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.50#The master ram was voted mine by all;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.51#And him (the guardian of Ulysses' fate)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.52#With pious mind to heaven I consecrate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.53#But the great god, whose thunder rends the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.54#Averse, beholds the smoking sacrifice;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.55#And sees me wandering still from coast to coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.56#And all my vessels, all my people, lost!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.57#While thoughtless we indulge the genial rite,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.58#As plenteous cates and flowing bowls invite;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.59#Till evening Phoebus roll'd away the light;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.60#Stretch'd on the shore in careless ease we rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.61#Till ruddy morning purpled o'er the east;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.62#Then from their anchors all our ships unbind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.63#And mount the decks, and call the willing wind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.64#Now, ranged in order on our banks we sweep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.65#With hasty strokes the hoarse-resounding deep;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.66#Blind to the future, pensive with our fears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:9.31.67#Glad for the living, for the dead in tears."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.1#"AT length we reach'd AEolias's sea-girt shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.2#Where great Hippotades the sceptre bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.3#A floating isle! high-raised by toil divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.4#Strong walls of brass the rocky coast confine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.5#Six blooming youths, in private grandeur bred,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.6#And six fair daughters, graced the royal bed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.7#These sons their sisters wed, and all remain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.8#Their parents' pride, and pleasure of their reign.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.9#All day they feast, all day the bowls flow round,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.10#And joy and music through the isle resound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.11#At night each pair on splendid carpets lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.12#And crown'd with love the pleasures of the day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.13#This happy port affords our wandering fleet
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.14#A month's reception, and a safe retreat.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.15#Full oft the monarch urged me to relate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.16#The fall of Ilion, and the Grecian fate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.17#Full oft I told: at length for parting moved;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.18#The king with mighty gifts my suit approved.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.19#The adverse winds in leathern bags he braced,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.20#Compress'd their force, and lock'd each struggling blast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.21#For him the mighty sire of gods assign'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.22#The tempest's lood, the tyrant of the wind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.23#His word alone the listening storms obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.24#To smooth the deep, or swell the foamy sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.25#These in my hollow ship the monarch hung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.26#Securely fetter'd by a silver thong:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.27#But Zephyrus exempt, with friendly gales
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.28#He charged to fill, and guide the swelling sails:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.1.29#Rare gift! but O, what gift to fools avails!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.2.1#"Nine prosperous days we plied the labouring oar;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.2.2#The tenth presents our welcome native shore:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.2.3#The hills display the beacon's friendly light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.2.4#And rising mountains gain upon our sight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.2.5#Then first my eyes, by watchful toils oppress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.2.6#Complied to take the balmy gifts of rest:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.2.7#Then first my hands did from the rudder part
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.2.8#(So much the love of home possess'd my heart):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.2.9#When lo! on board a fond debate arose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.2.10#What rare device those vessels might inclose?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.2.11#What sum, what prize from AEolus I brought?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.2.12#Whilst to his neighbour each express'd his thought:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.1#"'Say, whence ye gods, contending nations strive
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.2#Who most shall please, who most our hero give?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.3#Long have his coffers groan'd with Trojan spoils:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.4#Whilst we, the wretched partners of his toils,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.5#Reproach'd by want, our fruitless labours mourn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.6#And only rich in barren fame return.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.7#Now AEolus, ye see, augments his store:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.8#But come, my friends, these mystic gifts explore,'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.9#They said: and (oh cursed fate!) the thongs unbound!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.10#The gushing tempest sweeps the ocean round;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.11#Snatch'd in the whirl, the hurried navy flew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.12#The ocean widen'd and the shores withdrew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.13#Roused from my fatal sleep I long debate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.14#If still to live, or desperate plunge to fate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.15#Thus doubting, prostrate on the deck I lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.3.16#Till all the coward thoughts of death gave way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.1#"Meanwhile our vessels plough the liquid plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.2#And soon the known AEolian coast regain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.3#Our groan the rocks remurmur'd to the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.4#We leap'd on shore, and with a scanty feast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.5#Our thirst and hunger hastily repress'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.6#That done, two chosen heralds straight attend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.7#Our second progress to my royal friend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.8#And him amidst his jovial sons we found;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.9#The banquet steaming, and the goblets crown'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.10#There humbly stoop'd with conscious shame and awe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.11#Nor nearer than the gate presumed to draw.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.12#But soon his sons their well-known guest descried,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.13#And starting from their couches loudly cried:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.14#'Ulysses here! what demon could'st thou meet
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.15#To thwart thy passage, and repel thy fleet?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.16#Wast thou not furnish'd by our choicest care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.17#For Greece, for home and all thy soul held dear?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.18#Thus they, In silence long my fate I mourn'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.19#At length these words with accents low return'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.20#`Me, lock'd in sleep, my faithless crew bereft
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.21#Of all the blessing of your godlike gift!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.22#But grant, oh grant, our loss we may retrieve;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.4.23#A favour you, and you alone can give.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.5.1#"Thus I with art to move their pity tried,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.5.2#And touch'd the youths; but their stern sire replied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.5.3#'Vile wretch, begone! this instant I command
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.5.4#Thy fleet accursed to leave our hallow'd land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.5.5#His baneful suit pollutes these bless'd abodes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.5.6#Whose fate proclaims him hateful to the gods.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.1#"Thus fierce he said: we sighing went our way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.2#And with desponding hearts put off to sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.3#The sailors spent with toils their folly mourn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.4#But mourn in vain; no prospect of return
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.5#Six days and nights a doubtful course we steer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.6#The next proud Lamos' stately towers appear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.7#And Laestrygonia's gates arise distinct in air.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.8#The shepherd, quitting here at night the plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.9#Calls, to succeed his cares, the watchful swain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.10#But he that scorns the chains of sleep to wear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.11#And adds the herdsman's to the shepherd's care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.12#So near the pastures, and so short the way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.13#His double toils may claim a double pay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.6.14#And join the labours of the night and day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.7.1#"Within a long recess a bay there lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.7.2#Edged round with cliffs high pointing to the skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.7.3#The jutting shores that swell on either side
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.7.4#Contract its mouth, and break the rushing tide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.7.5#Our eager sailors seize the fair retreat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.7.6#And bound within the port their crowded fleet:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.7.7#For here retired the sinking billows sleep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.7.8#And smiling calmness silver'd o'er the deep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.7.9#I only in the bay refused to moor,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.7.10#And fix'd without, my halsers to the shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.1#"From thence we climb'd a point, whose airy brow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.2#Commands the prospect of the plains below;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.3#No tracks of beasts, or signs of men, we found,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.4#But smoky volumes rolling from the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.5#Two with our herald thither we command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.6#With speed to learn what men possess'd the land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.7#They went, and kept the wheel's smooth-beaten road
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.8#Which to the city drew the mountain wood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.9#When lo! they met, beside a crystal spring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.10#The daughter of Antiphates the king;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.11#She to Artacia's silver streams came down;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.12#(Artacia's streams alone supply the town);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.13#The damsel they approach, and ask'd what race
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.14#The people were? who monarch of the place?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.15#With joy the maid the unwary strangers heard
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.16#And show'd them where the royal dome appear'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.17#They went; but as they entering saw the queen
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.18#Of size enormous, and terrific mien
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.19#(Not yielding to some bulky mountain's height),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.20#A sudden horror struck their aching sight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.21#Swift at her call her husband scour'd away
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.22#To wreak his hunger on the destined prey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.23#One for his food the raging glutton slew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.8.24#But two rush'd out, and to the navy flew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.1#"Balk'd of his prey, the yelling monster flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.2#And fills the city with his hideous cries;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.3#A ghastly band of giants hear the roar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.4#And, pouring down the mountains, crowd the shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.5#Fragments they rend from off the craggy brow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.6#And dash the ruins on the ships below;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.7#The crackling vessels burst; hoarse groans arise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.8#And mingled horrors echo to the skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.9#The men like fish, they struck upon the flood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.10#And cramm'd their filthy throats with human food.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.11#Whilst thus their fury rages at the bay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.12#My sword our cables cut, I call'd to weigh;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.13#And charged my men, as they from fate would fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.14#Each nerve to strain, each bending oar to ply.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.15#The sailors catch the word, their oars they seize,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.16#And sweep with equal strokes the smoky seas;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.17#Clear of the rocks the impatient vessel flies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.18#Whilst in the port each wretch encumber'd dies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.19#With earnest haste my frighted sailors press,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.20#While kindling transports glow'd at our success;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.21#But the sad fate that did our friends destroy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.9.22#Cool'd every breast, and damp'd the rising joy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.1#"Now dropp'd our anchors in the Aeaean bay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.2#Where Circe dwelt, the daughter of the Day!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.3#Her mother Perse, of old Ocean's strain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.4#Thus from the Lun descended, and the Main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.5#(From the same lineage stern Aeaetes came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.6#The far-famed brother of the enchantress dame);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.7#Goddess, the queen, to whom the powers belong
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.8#Of dreadful magic and commanding song.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.9#Some god directing to this peaceful bay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.10#Silent we came, and melancholy lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.11#Spent and o'erwatch'd. Two days and nights roll'd on,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.12#And now the third succeeding morning shone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.13#I climb'd a cliff, with spear and sword in hand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.14#Whose ridge o'erlook'd a shady length of land;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.15#To learn if aught of mortal works appear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.16#Or cheerful voice of mortal strike the ear?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.17#From the high point I mark'd, in distant view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.18#A stream of curling smoke ascending blue,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.19#And spiry tops, the tufted trees above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.10.20#Of Circe's palace bosom'd in the grove.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.1#"Thither to haste, the region to explore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.2#Was first my thought: but speeding back to shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.3#I deem'd it best to visit first my crew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.4#And send our spies the dubious coast to view.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.5#As down the hill I solitary go,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.6#Some power divine, who pities human woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.7#Sent a tall stag, descending from the wood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.8#To cool his fervour in the crystal flood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.9#Luxuriant on the wave-worn bank he lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.10#Stretch'd forth and panting in the sunny ray.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.11#I launch'd my spear, and with a sudden wound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.12#Transpierced his back, and fix'd him to the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.13#He falls, and mourns his fate with human cries:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.14#Through the wide wound the vital spirit flies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.15#I drew, and casting on the river's side
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.16#The bloody spear, his gather'd feet I tied
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.17#With twining osiers which the bank supplied.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.18#An ell in length the pliant wisp I weaved,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.19#And the huge body on my shoulders heaved:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.20#Then leaning on my spear with both my hands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.21#Upbore my load, and press'd the sinking sands
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.22#With weighty steps, till at the ship I threw
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.11.23#The welcome burden, and bespoke my crew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.12.1#"'Cheer up, my friends! it is not yet our fate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.12.2#To glide with ghosts through Pluto's gloomy gate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.12.3#Food in the desert land, behold! is given!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.12.4#Live, and enjoy the providence of heaven.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.1#"The joyful crew survey his mighty size,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.2#And on the future banquet feast their eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.3#As huge in length extended lay the beast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.4#Then wash their hands, and hasten to the feast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.5#There, till the setting sun roll'd down the light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.6#They sate indulging in the genial rite.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.7#When evening rose, and darkness cover'd o'er
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.8#The face of things, we slept along the shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.9#But when the rosy morning warm'd the east,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.10#My men I summon'd, and these words address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.11#"'Followers and friends, attend what I propose:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.12#Ye sad companions of Ulysses' woes!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.13#We know not here what land before us lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.14#Or to what quarter now we turn our eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.15#Or where the sun shall set, or where shall rise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.16#Here let us think (if thinking be not vain)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.17#If any counsel, any hope remain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.18#Alas! from yonder promontory's brow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.19#I view'd the coast, a region flat and low;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.20#An isle encircled with the boundless flood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.21#A length of thickets, and entangled wood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.22#Some smoke I saw amid the forest rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.13.23#And all around it only seas and skies!'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.14.1#"With broken hearts my sad companions stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.14.2#Mindful of Cyclops and his human food,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.14.3#And horrid Laestrygons, the men of blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.14.4#Presaging tears apace began to rain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.14.5#But tears in mortal miseries are vain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.14.6#In equal parts I straight divide my band,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.14.7#And name a chief each party to command;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.14.8#I led the one, and of the other side
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.14.9#Appointed brave Eurylochus the guide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.14.10#Then in the brazen helm the lots we throw,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.14.11#And fortune casts Eurylochus to go;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.14.12#He march'd with twice eleven in his train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.14.13#Pensive they march, and pensive we remain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.1#"The palace in a woody vale they found,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.2#High raised of stone; a shaded space around;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.3#Where mountain wolves and brindled lions roam,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.4#(By magic tamed,) familiar to the dome.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.5#With gentle blandishment our men they meet,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.6#And wag their tails, and fawning lick their feet.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.7#As from some feast a man returning late,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.8#His faithful dogs all meet him at the gate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.9#Rejoicing round, some morsel to receive,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.10#(Such as the good man ever used to give,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.11#Domestic thus the grisly beasts drew near;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.12#They gaze with wonder not unmix'd with fear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.13#Now on the threshold of the dome they stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.14#And heard a voice resounding through the wood:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.15#Placed at her loom within, the goddess sung;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.16#The vaulted roofs and solid pavement rung.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.17#O'er the fair web the rising figures shine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.18#Immortal labour! worthy hands divine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.19#Polites to the rest the question moved
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.15.20#(A gallant leader, and a man I loved):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.16.1#"'What voice celestial, chanting to the loom
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.16.2#(Or nymph, or goddess), echoes from the room?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.16.3#Say, shall we seek access?' With that they call;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.16.4#And wide unfold the portals of the hall.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.1#"The goddess, rising, asks her guests to stay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.2#Who blindly follow where she leads the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.3#Eurylochus alone of all the band,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.4#Suspecting fraud, more prudently remain'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.5#On thrones around with downy coverings graced,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.6#With semblance fair, the unhappy men she placed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.7#Milk newly press'd, the sacred flour of wheat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.8#And honey fresh, and Pramnian wines the treat:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.9#But venom'd was the bread, and mix'd the bowl,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.10#With drugs of force to darken all the soul:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.11#Soon in the luscious feast themselves they lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.12#And drank oblivion of their native coast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.13#Instant her circling wand the goddess waves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.14#To hogs transforms them, and the sty receives.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.15#No more was seen the human form divine;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.16#Head, face, and members, bristle into swine:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.17#Still cursed with sense, their minds remain alone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.18#And their own voice affrights them when they groan.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.19#Meanwhile the goddess in disdain bestows
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.20#The mast and acorn, brutal food! and strows
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.21#The fruits and cornel, as their feast, around;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.17.22#Now prone and grovelling on unsavoury ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.18.1#"Eurylochus, with pensive steps and slow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.18.2#Aghast returns; the messenger of woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.18.3#And bitter fate. To speak he made essay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.18.4#In vain essay'd, nor would his tongue obey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.18.5#His swelling heart denied the words their way:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.18.6#But speaking tears the want of words supply,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.18.7#And the full soul bursts copious from his eye.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.18.8#Affrighted, anxious for our fellows' fates,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.18.9#We press to hear what sadly he relates:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.1#"We went, Ulysses! (such was thy command)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.2#Through the lone thicket and the desert land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.3#A palace in a woody vale we found
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.4#Brown with dark forests, and with shades around.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.5#A voice celestial echoed through the dome,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.6#Or nymph or goddess, chanting to the loom.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.7#Access we sought, nor was access denied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.8#Radiant she came: the portals open'd wide:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.9#The goddess mild invites the guests to stay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.10#They blindly follow where she leads the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.11#I only wait behind of all the train:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.12#I waited long, and eyed the doors in vain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.13#The rest are vanish'd, none repass'd the gate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.19.14#And not a man appears to tell their fate.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.20.1#"I heard, and instant o'er my shoulder flung
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.20.2#The belt in which my weighty falchion hung
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.20.3#(A beamy blade): then seized the bended bow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.20.4#And bade him guide the way, resolved to go.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.20.5#He, prostrate falling, with both hands embraced
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.20.6#My knees, and weeping thus his suit address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.21.1#"'O king, beloved of Jove, thy servant spare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.21.2#And ah, thyself the rash attempt forbear!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.21.3#Never, alas! thou never shalt return,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.21.4#Or see the wretched for whose loss we mourn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.21.5#With what remains from certain ruin fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.21.6#And save the few not fated yet to die.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.1#"I answer'd stern: 'Inglorious then remain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.2#Here feast and loiter, and desert thy train.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.3#Alone, unfriended, will I tempt my way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.4#The laws of fate compel, and I obey.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.5#This said, and scornful turning from the shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.6#My haughty step, I stalk'd the valley o'er.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.7#Till now approaching nigh the magic bower,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.8#Where dwelt the enchantress skill'd in herbs of power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.9#A form divine forth issued from the wood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.10#(Immortal Hermes with the golden rod)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.11#In human semblance. On his bloomy face
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.12#Youth smiled celestial, with each opening grace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.13#He seized my hand, and gracious thus began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.14#'Ah whither roam'st thou, much-enduring man?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.15#O blind to fate! what led thy steps to rove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.16#The horrid mazes of this magic grove?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.17#Each friend you seek in yon enclosure lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.18#All lost their form, and habitants of sties.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.19#Think'st thou by wit to model their escape?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.20#Sooner shalt thou, a stranger to thy shape,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.21#Fall prone their equal: first thy danger know,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.22#Then take the antidote the gods bestow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.23#The plant I give through all the direful bower
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.24#Shall guard thee, and avert the evil hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.25#Now hear her wicked arts: Before thy eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.26#The bowl shall sparkle, and the banquet rise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.27#Take this, nor from the faithless feast abstain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.28#For temper'd drugs and poison shall be vain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.29#Soon as she strikes her wand, and gives the word,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.30#Draw forth and brandish thy refulgent sword,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.31#And menace death: those menaces shall move
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.32#Her alter'd mind to blandishment and love.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.33#Nor shun the blessing proffer'd to thy arms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.34#Ascend her bed, and taste celestial charms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.35#So shall thy tedious toils a respite find,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.36#And thy lost friends return to human kind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.37#But swear her first by those dread oaths that tie
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.38#The powers below, the blessed in the sky;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.39#Lest to thee naked secret fraud be meant,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.22.40#Or magic bind thee cold and impotent.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.1#"Thus while he spoke, the sovereign plant he drew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.2#Where on the all-bearing earth unmark'd it grew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.3#And show'd its nature and its wondrous power:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.4#Black was the root, but milky white the flower;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.5#Moly the name, to mortals hard to find,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.6#But all is easy to the ethereal kind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.7#This Hermes gave, then, gliding off the glade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.8#Shot to Olympus from the woodland shade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.9#While, full of thought, revolving fates to come,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.10#I speed my passage to the enchanted dome.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.11#Arrived, before the lofty gates I stay'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.12#The lofty gates the goddess wide display'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.13#She leads before, and to the feast invites;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.14#I follow sadly to the magic rites.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.15#Radiant with starry studs, a silver seat
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.16#Received my limbs: a footstool eased my feet,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.17#She mix'd the potion, fraudulent of soul;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.18#The poison mantled in the golden bowl.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.19#I took, and quaff'd it, confident in heaven.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.20#Then waved the wand, and then the word was given.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.21#'Hence to thy fellows! (dreadful she began:)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.23.22#Go, be a beast!'--I heard, and yet was man.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.24.1#"Then, sudden whirling, like a waving flame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.24.2#My beamy falchion, I assault the dame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.24.3#Struck with unusual fear, she trembling cries,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.24.4#She faints, she falls; she lifts her weeping eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.25.1#"'What art thou? say! from whence, from whom you came?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.25.2#O more than human! tell thy race, thy name.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.25.3#Amazing strength, these poisons to sustain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.25.4#Not mortal thou, nor mortal is thy brain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.25.5#Or art thou he, the man to come (foretold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.25.6#By Hermes, powerful with the wand of gold),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.25.7#The man from Troy, who wander'd ocean round;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.25.8#The man for wisdom's various arts renown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.25.9#Ulysses? Oh! thy threatening fury cease;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.25.10#Sheathe thy bright sword, and join our hands in peace!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.25.11#Let mutual joys our mutual trust combine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.25.12#And love, and love-born confidence, be thine.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.26.1#"'And how, dread Circe! (furious I rejoin)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.26.2#Can love, and love-born confidence, be mine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.26.3#Beneath thy charms when my companions groan,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.26.4#Transform'd to beasts, with accents not their own?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.26.5#O thou of fraudful heart, shall I be led
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.26.6#To share thy feast-rites, or ascend thy bed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.26.7#That, all unarm'd, thy vengeance may have vent,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.26.8#And magic bind me, cold and impotent?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.26.9#Celestial as thou art, yet stand denied;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.26.10#Or swear that oath by which the gods are tied,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.26.11#Swear, in thy soul no latent frauds remain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.26.12#Swear by the vow which never can be vain.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.1#"The goddess swore: then seized my hand, and led
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.2#To the sweet transports of the genial bed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.3#Ministrant to the queen, with busy care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.4#Four faithful handmaids the soft rites prepare;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.5#Nymphs sprung from fountains, or from shady woods,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.6#Or the fair offspring of the sacred floods.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.7#One o'er the couches painted carpets threw,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.8#Whose purple lustre glow'd against the view:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.9#White linen lay beneath. Another placed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.10#The silver stands, with golden flaskets graced:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.11#With dulcet beverage this the beaker crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.12#Fair in the midst, with gilded cups around:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.13#That in the tripod o'er the kindled pile
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.14#The water pours; the bubbling waters boil;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.15#An ample vase receives the smoking wave;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.16#And, in the bath prepared, my limbs I lave:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.17#Reviving sweets repair the mind's decay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.18#And take the painful sense of toil away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.19#A vest and tunic o'er me next she threw,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.20#Fresh from the bath, and dropping balmy dew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.21#Then led and placed me on the sovereign seat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.22#With carpets spread; a footstool at my feet.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.23#The golden ewer a nymph obsequious brings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.24#Replenish'd from the cool translucent springs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.25#With copious water the bright vase supplies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.26#A silver laver of capacious size.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.27#I wash'd. The table in fair order spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.28#They heap the glittering canisters with bread:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.29#Viands of various kinds allure the taste,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.30#Of choicest sort and savour, rich repast!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.31#Circe in vain invites the feast to share;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.32#Absent I ponder, and absorb'd in care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.33#While scenes of woe rose anxious in my breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.27.34#The queen beheld me, and these words address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.28.1#"'Why sits Ulysses silent and apart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.28.2#Some hoard of grief close harbour'd at his heart
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.28.3#Untouch'd before thee stand the cates divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.28.4#And unregarded laughs the rosy wine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.28.5#Can yet a doubt or any dread remain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.28.6#When sworn that oath which never can be vain?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.29.1#"I answered: 'Goddess! human is my breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.29.2#By justice sway'd, by tender pity press'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.29.3#Ill fits it me, whose friends are sunk to beasts,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.29.4#To quaff thy bowls, or riot in thy feasts.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.29.5#Me would'st thou please? for them thy cares employ,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.29.6#And them to me restore, and me to joy.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.1#"With that she parted: in her potent hand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.2#She bore the virtue of the magic wand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.3#Then, hastening to the sties, set wide the door,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.4#Urged forth, and drove the bristly herd before;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.5#Unwieldy, out they rush'd with general cry,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.6#Enormous beasts, dishonest to the eye.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.7#Now touch'd by counter-charms they change again,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.8#And stand majestic, and recall'd to men.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.9#Those hairs of late that bristled every part,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.10#Fall off, miraculous effect of art!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.11#Till all the form in full proportion rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.12#More young, more large, more graceful to my eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.13#They saw, they knew me, and with eager pace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.14#Clung to their master in a long embrace:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.15#Sad, pleasing sight! with tears each eye ran o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.16#And sobs of joy re-echoed through the bower;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.17#E'en Circe wept, her adamantine heart
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.30.18#Felt pity enter, and sustain'd her part.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.31.1#"'Son of Laertes! (then the queen began)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.31.2#Oh much-enduring, much experienced man!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.31.3#Haste to thy vessel on the sea-beat shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.31.4#Unload thy treasures, and the galley moor;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.31.5#Then bring thy friends, secure from future harms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.31.6#And in our grottoes stow thy spoils and arms,'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.32.1#"She said. Obedient to her high command
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.32.2#I quit the place, and hasten to the strand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.32.3#My sad companions on the beach I found,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.32.4#Their wistful eyes in floods of sorrow drown'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.1#"As from fresh pastures and the dewy field
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.2#(When loaded cribs their evening banquet yield)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.3#The lowing herds return; around them throng
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.4#With leaps and bounds their late imprison'd young,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.5#Rush to their mothers with unruly joy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.6#And echoing hills return the tender cry:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.7#So round me press'd, exulting at my sight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.8#With cries and agonies of wild delight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.9#The weeping sailors; nor less fierce their joy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.10#Than if return'd to Ithaca from Troy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.11#'Ah master! ever honour'd, ever dear!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.12#(These tender words on every side I hear)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.13#What other joy can equal thy return?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.14#Not that loved country for whose sight we mourn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.15#The soil that nursed us, and that gave us breath:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.33.16#But ah! relate our lost companions' death.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.34.1#"I answer'd cheerful: 'Haste, your galley moor,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.34.2#And bring our treasures and our arms ashore:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.34.3#Those in yon hollow caverns let us lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.34.4#Then rise, and follow where I lead the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.34.5#Your fellows live; believe your eyes, and come
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.34.6#To taste the joys of Circe's sacred dome.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.35.1#"With ready speed the joyful crew obey:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.35.2#Alone Eurylochus persuades their stay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.36.1#"'Whither (he cried), ah whither will ye run?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.36.2#Seek ye to meet those evils ye should shun?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.36.3#Will you the terrors of the dome explore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.36.4#In swine to grovel, or in lions roar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.36.5#Or wolf-like howl away the midnight hour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.36.6#In dreadful watch around the magic bower?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.36.7#Remember Cyclops, and his bloody deed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.36.8#The leader's rashness made the soldiers bleed.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.37.1#"I heard incensed, and first resolved to speed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.37.2#My flying falchion at the rebel's head.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.37.3#Dear as he was, by ties of kindred bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.37.4#This hand had stretch'd him breathless on the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.37.5#But all at once my interposing train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.37.6#For mercy pleaded, nor could plead in vain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.37.7#'Leave here the man who dares his prince desert,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.37.8#Leave to repentance and his own sad heart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.37.9#To guard the ship. Seek we the sacred shades
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.37.10#Of Circe's palace, where Ulysses leads.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.38.1#"This with one voice declared, the rising train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.38.2#Left the black vessel by the murmuring main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.38.3#Shame touch'd Eurylochus' alter'd breast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.38.4#He fear'd my threats, and follow'd with the rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.1#"Meanwhile the goddess, with indulgent cares
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.2#And social joys, the late transform'd repairs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.3#The bath, the feast, their fainting soul renews:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.4#Rich in refulgent robes, and dropping balmy dews:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.5#Brightening with joy, their eager eyes behold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.6#Each other's face, and each his story told;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.7#Then gushing tears the narrative confound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.8#And with their sobs the vaulted roof resound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.9#When hush'd their passion, thus the goddess cries:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.10#'Ulysses, taught by labours to be wise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.11#Let this short memory of grief suffice.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.12#To me are known the various woes ye bore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.13#In storms by sea, in perils on the shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.14#Forget whatever was in Fortune's power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.15#And share the pleasures of this genial hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.16#Such be your mind as ere ye left your coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.17#Or learn'd to sorrow for a country lost.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.18#Exiles and wanderers now, where'er ye go,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.19#Too faithful memory renews your woe:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.20#The cause removed, habitual griefs remain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.39.21#And the soul saddens by the use of pain.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.40.1#"Her kind entreaty moved the general breast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.40.2#Tired with long toil, we willing sunk to rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.40.3#We plied the banquet, and the bowl we crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.40.4#Till the full circle of the year came round.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.40.5#But when the seasons following in their train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.40.6#Brought back the months, the days, and hours again;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.40.7#As from a lethargy at once they rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.40.8#And urge their chief with animating cries:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.1#"'Is this, Ulysses, our inglorious lot?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.2#And is the name of Ithaca forgot?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.3#Shall never the dear land in prospect rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.4#Or the loved palace glitter in our eyes?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.5#"Melting I heard; yet till the sun's decline
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.6#Prolong'd the feast, and quaff'd the rosy wine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.7#But when the shades came on at evening hour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.8#And all lay slumbering in the dusky bower,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.9#I came a suppliant to fair Circe's bed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.10#The tender moment seized, and thus I said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.11#'Be mindful, goddess! of thy promise made;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.12#Must sad Ulysses ever be delay'd?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.13#Around their lord my sad companions mourn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.14#Each breast beats homeward, anxious to return:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.15#If but a moment parted from thy eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.41.16#Their tears flow round me, and my heart complies.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.42.1#"'Go then (she cried), ah go! yet think, not I,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.42.2#Not Circe, but the Fates, your wish deny.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.42.3#Ah, hope not yet to breathe thy native air!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.42.4#Far other journey first demands thy care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.42.5#To tread the uncomfortable paths beneath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.42.6#And view the realms of darkness and of death.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.42.7#There seek the Theban bard, deprived of sight;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.42.8#Within, irradiate with prophetic light;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.42.9#To whom Persephone, entire and whole,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.42.10#Gave to retain the unseparated soul:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.42.11#The rest are forms, of empty ether made;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.42.12#Impassive semblance, and a flitting shade.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.43.1#"Struck at the word, my very heart was dead:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.43.2#Pensive I sate: my tears bedew'd the bed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.43.3#To hate the light and life my soul begun,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.43.4#And saw that all was grief beneath the sun:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.43.5#Composed at length the gushing tears suppress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.43.6#And my toss'd limbs now wearied into rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.43.7#'How shall I tread (I cried), ah, Circe! say,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.43.8#The dark descent, and who shall guide the way?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.43.9#Can living eyes behold the realms below?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.43.10#What bark to waft me, and what wind to blow?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.1#"'Thy fated road (the magic power replied),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.2#Divine Ulysses! ask no mortal guide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.3#Rear but the mast, the spacious sail display,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.4#The northern winds shall wing thee on thy way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.5#Soon shalt thou reach old Ocean's utmost ends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.6#Where to the main the shelving shore descends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.7#The barren trees of Proserpine's black woods,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.8#Poplars and willows trembling o'er the floods:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.9#There fix thy vessel in the lonely bay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.10#And enter there the kingdoms void of day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.11#Where Phlegethon's loud torrents, rushing down,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.12#Hiss in the flaming gulf of Acheron;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.13#And where, slow rolling from the Stygian bed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.14#Cocytus' lamentable waters spread:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.15#Where the dark rock o'erhangs the infernal lake,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.16#And mingling streams eternal murmurs make.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.17#First draw thy falchion, and on every side
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.18#Trench the black earth a cubit long and wide:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.19#To all the shades around libations pour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.20#And o'er the ingredients strew the hallow'd flour:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.21#New wine and milk, with honey temper'd bring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.22#And living water from the crystal spring.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.23#Then the wan shades and feeble ghosts implore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.24#With promised offerings on thy native shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.25#A barren cow, the stateliest of the isle,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.26#And heap'd with various wealth, a blazing pile:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.27#These to the rest; but to the seer must bleed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.28#A sable ram, the pride of all thy breed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.29#These solemn vows and holy offerings paid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.30#To all the phantom nations of the dead,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.31#Be next thy care the sable sheep to place
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.32#Full o'er the pit, and hellward turn their face:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.33#But from the infernal rite thine eye withdraw,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.34#And back to Ocean glance with reverend awe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.35#Sudden shall skim along the dusky glades
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.36#Thin airy shoals, and visionary shades.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.37#Then give command the sacrifice to haste,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.38#Let the flay'd victims in the flame be cast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.39#And sacred vows and mystic song applied
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.40#To grisly Pluto and his gloomy bride.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.41#Wide o'er the pool thy falchion waved around
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.42#Shall drive the spectres from unbidden ground:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.43#The sacred draught shall all the dead forbear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.44#Till awful from the shades arise the seer.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.45#Let him, oraculous, the end, the way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.46#The turns of all thy future fate display,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.44.47#Thy pilgrimage to come, and remnant of thy day.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.1#"So speaking, from the ruddy orient shone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.2#The morn, conspicuous on her golden throne.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.3#The goddess with a radiant tunic dress'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.4#My limbs, and o'er me cast a silken vest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.5#Long flowing robes, of purest white, array
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.6#The nymph, that added lustre to the day:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.7#A tiar wreath'd her head with many a fold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.8#Her waist was circled with a zone of gold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.9#Forth issuing then, from place to place I flew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.10#Rouse man by man, and animate my crew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.11#'Rise, rise, my mates! 'tis Circe gives command:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.12#Our journey calls us; haste, and quit the land.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.13#All rise and follow, yet depart not all,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.45.14#For Fate decreed one wretched man to fall.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.46.1#"A youth there was, Elpenor was he named,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.46.2#Not much for sense, nor much for courage famed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.46.3#The youngest of our band, a vulgar soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.46.4#Born but to banquet, and to drain the bowl.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.46.5#He, hot and careless, on a turret's height
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.46.6#With sleep repair'd the long debauch of night:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.46.7#The sudden tumult stirred him where he lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.46.8#And down he hasten'd, but forgot the way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.46.9#Full headlong from the roof the sleeper fell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.46.10#And snapp'd the spinal joint, and waked in hell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.47.1#"The rest crowd round me with an eager look;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.47.2#I met them with a sigh, and thus bespoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.47.3#'Already, friends! ye think your toils are o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.47.4#Your hopes already touch your native shore:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.47.5#Alas! far otherwise the nymph declares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.47.6#Far other journey first demands our cares;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.47.7#To tread the uncomfortable paths beneath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.47.8#The dreary realms of darkness and of death;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.47.9#To seek Tiresias' awful shade below,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.47.10#And thence our fortunes and our fates to know.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.48.1#"My sad companions heard in deep despair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.48.2#Frantic they tore their manly growth of hair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.48.3#To earth they fell: the tears began to rain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.48.4#But tears in mortal miseries are vain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.48.5#Sadly they fared along the sea-beat shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.48.6#Still heaved their hearts, and still their eyes ran o'er.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.48.7#The ready victims at our bark we found,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.48.8#The sable ewe and ram together bound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.48.9#For swift as thought the goddess had been there,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.48.10#And thence had glided, viewless as the air:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.48.11#The paths of gods what mortal can survey?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:10.48.12#Who eyes their motion? who shall trace their way?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.1.1#"Now to the shores we bend, a mournful train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.1.2#Climb the tall bark, and launch into the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.1.3#At once the mast we rear, at once unbind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.1.4#The spacious sheet, and stretch it to the wind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.1.5#Then pale and pensive stand, with cares oppress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.1.6#And solemn horror saddens every breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.1.7#A freshening breeze the magic power supplied,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.1.8#While the wing'd vessel flew along the tide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.1.9#Our oars we shipp'd; all day the swelling sails
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.1.10#Full from the guiding pilot catch'd the gales.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.2.1#"Now sunk the sun from his aerial height,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.2.2#And o'er the shaded billows rush'd the night;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.2.3#When lo! we reach'd old Ocean's utmost bounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.2.4#Where rocks control his waves with ever-during mounds.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.3.1#"There in a lonely land, and gloomy cells,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.3.2#The dusky nation of Cimmeria dwells;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.3.3#The sun ne'er views the uncomfortable seats,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.3.4#When radiant he advances, or retreats:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.3.5#Unhappy race! whom endless night invades,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.3.6#Clouds the dull air, and wraps them round in shades.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.4.1#"The ship we moor on these obscure abodes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.4.2#Disbark the sheep, an offering to the gods;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.4.3#And, hellward bending, o'er the beach descry
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.4.4#The doleful passage to the infernal sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.4.5#The victims, vow'd to each Tartarian power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.4.6#Eurylochus and Perimedes bore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.5.1#"Here open'd hell, all hell I here implored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.5.2#And from the scabbard drew the shining sword:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.5.3#And trenching the black earth on every side,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.5.4#A cavern form'd, a cubit long and wide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.5.5#New wine, with honey-temper'd milk, we bring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.5.6#Then living waters from the crystal spring:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.5.7#O'er these was strew'd the consecrated flour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.5.8#And on the surface shone the holy store.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.6.1#"Now the wan shades we hail, the infernal gods,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.6.2#To speed our course, and waft us o'er the floods:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.6.3#So shall a barren heifer from the stall
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.6.4#Beneath the knife upon your altars fall;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.6.5#So in our palace, at our safe return,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.6.6#Rich with unnumber'd gifts the pile shall burn;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.6.7#So shall a ram, the largest of the breed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.6.8#Black as these regions, to Tiresias bleed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.1#"Thus solemn rites and holy vows we paid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.2#To all the phantom-nations of the dead;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.3#Then died the sheep: a purple torrent flow'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.4#And all the caverns smoked with streaming blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.5#When lo! appear'd along the dusky coasts,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.6#Thin, airy shoals of visionary ghosts:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.7#Fair, pensive youths, and soft enamour'd maids;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.8#And wither'd elders, pale and wrinkled shades;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.9#Ghastly with wounds the forms of warriors slain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.10#Stalk'd with majestic port, a martial train:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.11#These and a thousand more swarm'd o'er the ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.12#And all the dire assembly shriek'd around.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.13#Astonish'd at the sight, aghast I stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.14#And a cold fear ran shivering through my blood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.15#Straight I command the sacrifice to haste,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.16#Straight the flay'd victims to the flames are cast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.17#And mutter'd vows, and mystic song applied
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.7.18#To grisly Pluto, and his gloomy bride.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.8.1#"Now swift I waved my falchion o'er the blood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.8.2#Back started the pale throngs, and trembling stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.8.3#Round the black trench the gore untasted flows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.8.4#Till awful from the shades Tiresias rose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.9.1#"There wandering through the gloom I first survey'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.9.2#New to the realms of death, Elpenor's shade:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.9.3#His cold remains all naked to the sky
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.9.4#On distant shores unwept, unburied lie.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.9.5#Sad at the sight I stand, deep fix'd in woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.9.6#And ere I spoke the tears began to flow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.10.1#"'O say what angry power Elpenor led
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.10.2#To glide in shades, and wander with the dead?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.10.3#How could thy soul, by realms and seas disjoin'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.10.4#Outfly the nimble sail, and leave the lagging wind?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.1#"The ghost replied: 'To hell my doom I owe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.2#Demons accursed, dire ministers of woe!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.3#My feet, through wine unfaithful to their weight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.4#Betray'd me tumbling from a towery height:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.5#Staggering I reel'd, and as I reel'd I fell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.6#Lux'd the neck-joint--my soul descends to hell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.7#But lend me aid, I now conjure thee lend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.8#By the soft tie and sacred name of friend!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.9#By thy fond consort! by thy father's cares!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.10#By loved Telemachus' blooming years?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.11#For well I know that soon the heavenly powers
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.12#Will give thee back to-day, and Circe's shores:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.13#There pious on my cold remains attend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.14#There call to mind thy poor departed friend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.15#The tribute of a tear is all I crave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.16#And the possession of a peaceful grave.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.17#But if, unheard, in vain compassion plead,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.18#Revere the gods. The gods avenge the dead!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.19#A tomb along the watery margin raise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.20#The tomb with manly arms and trophies grace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.21#To show posterity Elpenor was.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.22#There high in air, memorial of my name,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.11.23#Fix the smooth oar, and bid me live to fame.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.12.1#"To whom with tears: 'These rites, O mournful shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.12.2#Due to thy ghost, shall to thy ghost be paid.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.13.1#"Still as I spoke the phantom seem'd to moan,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.13.2#Tear follow'd tear, and groan succeeded groan.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.13.3#But, as my waving sword the blood surrounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.13.4#The shade withdrew, and mutter'd empty sounds.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.14.1#"There as the wondrous visions I survey'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.14.2#All pale ascends my royal mother's shade:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.14.3#A queen, to Troy she saw our legions pass;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.14.4#Now a thin form is all Anticlea was!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.14.5#Struck at the sight I melt with filial woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.14.6#And down my cheek the pious sorrows flow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.14.7#Yet as I shook my falchion o'er the blood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.14.8#Regardless of her son the parent stood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.15.1#"When lo! the mighty Theban I behold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.15.2#To guide his steps he bore a staff of gold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.15.3#Awful he trod; majestic was his look!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.15.4#And from his holy lips these accents broke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.16.1#"'Why, mortal, wanderest thou from cheerful day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.16.2#To tread the downward, melancholy way?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.16.3#What angry gods to these dark regions led
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.16.4#Thee, yet alive, companion of the deed?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.16.5#But sheathe thy poniard, while my tongue relates
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.16.6#Heaven's steadfast purpose, and thy future fates.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.17.1#"While yet he spoke, the prophet I obey'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.17.2#And in the scabbard plunged the glittering blade:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.17.3#Eager he quaff'd the gore, and then express'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.17.4#Dark things to come, the counsels of his breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.1#"Weary of light, Ulysses here explores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.2#A prosperous voyage to his native shores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.3#But know--by me unerring Fates disclose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.4#New trains of dangers, and new scenes of woes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.5#I see, I see, thy bark by Neptune toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.6#For injured Cyclops, and his eyeball lost!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.7#Yet to thy woes the gods decree an end,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.8#If Heaven thou please: and how to please attend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.9#Where on Trinacrian rocks the ocean roars,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.10#Graze numerous herds along the verdant shores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.11#Though hunger press, yet fly the dangerous prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.12#The herds are sacred to the god of day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.13#Who all surveys with his extensive eye,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.14#Above, below, on earth, and in the sky!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.15#Rob not the god; and so propitious gales
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.16#Attend thy voyage, and impel thy sails:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.17#But, if his herds ye seize, beneath the waves
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.18#I see thy friends o'erwhelm'd in liquid graves!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.19#The direful wreck Ulysses scarce survives!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.20#Ulysses at his country scarce arrives!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.21#Strangers thy guides! nor there thy labours end;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.22#New foes arise; domestic ills attend!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.23#There foul adulterers to thy bride resort,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.24#And lordly gluttons riot in thy court.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.25#But vengeance hastes amain! These eyes behold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.26#The deathful scene, princes on princes roll'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.27#That done, a people far from sea explore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.28#Who ne'er knew salt, or heard the billows roar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.29#Or saw gay vessel stem the watery plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.30#A painted wonder flying on the main!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.31#Bear on thy back an oar: with strange amaze
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.32#A shepherd meeting thee, the oar surveys,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.33#And names a van: there fix it on the plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.34#To calm the god that holds the watery reign;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.35#A threefold offering to his altar bring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.36#A bull, a ram, a boar; and hail the ocean king.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.37#But home return'd, to each ethereal power
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.38#Slay the due victim in the genial hour:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.39#So peaceful shalt thou end thy blissful days,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.40#And steal thyself from life by slow decays:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.41#Unknown to pain, in age resign thy breath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.42#When late stern Neptune points the shaft with death:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.43#To the dark grave retiring as to rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.18.44#Thy people blessing, by thy people bless'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.19.1#"Unerring truths, O man, my lips relate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.19.2#This is thy life to come, and this is fate.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.20.1#"To whom unmoved: 'If this the gods prepare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.20.2#What Heaven ordains the wise with courage bear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.20.3#But say, why yonder on the lonely strands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.20.4#Unmindful of her son, Anticlea stands?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.20.5#Why to the ground she bends her downcast eye?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.20.6#Why is she silent, while her son is nigh?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.20.7#The latent cause, O sacred seer, reveal!'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.21.1#"'Nor this (replies the seer) will I conceal.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.21.2#Know, to the spectres that thy beverage taste,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.21.3#The scenes of life recur, and actions past:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.21.4#They, seal'd with truth, return the sure reply;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.21.5#The rest, repell'd, a train oblivious fly.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.22.1#"The phantom-prophet ceased, and sunk from sight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.22.2#To the black palace of eternal night.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.1#"Still in the dark abodes of death I stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.2#When near Anticlea moved, and drank the blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.3#Straight all the mother in her soul awakes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.4#And, owning her Ulysses, thus she speaks;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.5#'Comest thou, my son, alive, to realms beneath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.6#The dolesome realms of darkness and of death!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.7#Comest thou alive from pure, ethereal day?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.8#Dire is the region, dismal is the way!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.9#Here lakes profound, there floods oppose their waves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.10#There the wide sea with all his billows raves!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.11#Or (since to dust proud Troy submits her towers)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.12#Comest thou a wanderer from the Phrygian shores?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.13#Or say, since honour call'd thee to the field,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.23.14#Hast thou thy Ithaca, thy bride, beheld?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.24.1#"'Source of my life,' I cried, 'from earth I fly
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.24.2#To seek Tiresias in the nether sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.24.3#To learn my doom; for, toss'd from woe to woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.24.4#In every land Ulysses finds a foe:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.24.5#Nor have these eyes beheld my native shores,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.24.6#Since in the dust proud Troy submits her towers.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.25.1#"'But, when thy soul from her sweet mansion fled,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.25.2#Say, what distemper gave thee to the dead?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.25.3#Has life's fair lamp declined by slow decays,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.25.4#Or swift expired it in a sudden blaze?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.25.5#Say, if my sire, good old Laertes, lives?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.25.6#If yet Telemachus, my son, survives?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.25.7#Say, by his rule is my dominion awed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.25.8#Or crush'd by traitors with an iron rod?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.25.9#Say, if my spouse maintains her royal trust;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.25.10#Though tempted, chaste, and obstinately just?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.25.11#Or if no more her absent lord she wails,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.25.12#But the false woman o'er the wife prevails?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.1#"Thus I, and thus the parent-shade returns:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.2#'Thee, ever thee, thy faithful consort mourns:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.3#Whether the night descends or day prevails,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.4#Thee she by night, and thee by day bewails.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.5#Thee in Telemachus thy realm obeys;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.6#In sacred groves celestial rites he pays,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.7#And shares the banquet in superior state,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.8#Graced with such honours as become the great
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.9#Thy sire in solitude foments his care:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.10#The court is joyless, for thou art not there!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.11#No costly carpets raise his hoary head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.12#No rich embroidery shines to grace his bed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.13#Even when keen winter freezes in the skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.14#Rank'd with his slaves, on earth the monarch lies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.15#Deep are his sighs, his visage pale, his dress
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.16#The garb of woe and habit of distress.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.17#And when the autumn takes his annual round,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.18#The leafy honours scattering on the ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.19#Regardless of his years, abroad he lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.20#His bed the leaves, his canopy the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.21#Thus cares on cares his painful days consume,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.26.22#And bow his age with sorrow to the tomb!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.27.1#"'For thee, my son, I wept my life away;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.27.2#For thee through hell's eternal dungeons stray:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.27.3#Nor came my fate by lingering pains and slow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.27.4#Nor bent the silver-shafted queen her bow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.27.5#No dire disease bereaved me of my breath;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.27.6#Thou, thou, my son, wert my disease and death;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.27.7#Unkindly with my love my son conspired,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.27.8#For thee I lived, for absent thee expired.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.28.1#"Thrice in my arms I strove her shade to bind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.28.2#Thrice through my arms she slipp'd like empty wind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.28.3#Or dreams, the vain illusions of the mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.28.4#Wild with despair, I shed a copious tide
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.28.5#Of flowing tears, and thus with sighs replied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.29.1#"'Fliest thou, loved shade, while I thus fondly mourn!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.29.2#Turn to my arms, to my embraces turn!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.29.3#Is it, ye powers that smile at human harms!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.29.4#Too great a bliss to weep within her arms?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.29.5#Or has hell's queen an empty image sent,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.29.6#That wretched I might e'en my joys lament?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.1#"'O son of woe,' the pensive shade rejoin'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.2#'O most inured to grief of all mankind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.3#"'Tis not the queen of hell who thee deceives;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.4#All, all are such, when life the body leaves:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.5#No more the substance of the man remains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.6#Nor bounds the blood along the purple veins:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.7#These the funereal flames in atoms bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.8#To wander with the wind in empty air:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.9#While the impassive soul reluctant flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.10#Like a vain dream, to these infernal skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.11#But from the dark dominions speed the way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.12#And climb the steep ascent to upper day:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.13#To thy chaste bride the wondrous story tell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.30.14#The woes, the horrors, and the laws of hell.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.31.1#"Thus while she spoke, in swarms hell's empress brings
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.31.2#Daughters and wives of heroes and of kings;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.31.3#Thick and more thick they gather round the blood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.31.4#Ghost thronged on ghost (a dire assembly) stood!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.31.5#Dauntless my sword I seize: the airy crew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.31.6#Swift as it flash'd along the gloom, withdrew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.31.7#Then shade to shade in mutual forms succeeds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.31.8#Her race recounts, and their illustrious deeds.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.1#"Tyro began, whom great Salmoneus bred;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.2#The royal partner of famed Cretheus' bed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.3#For fair Enipeus, as from fruitful urns
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.4#He pours his watery store, the virgin burns;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.5#Smooth flows the gentle stream with wanton pride,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.6#And in soft mazes rolls a silver tide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.7#As on his banks the maid enamour'd roves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.8#The monarch of the deep beholds and loves;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.9#In her Enipeus' form and borrow'd charms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.10#The amorous god descends into her arms:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.11#Around, a spacious arch of waves he throws,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.12#And high in air the liquid mountain rose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.13#Thus in surrounding floods conceal'd, he proves
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.14#The pleasing transport, and completes his loves.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.15#Then, softly sighing, he the fair address'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.16#And as he spoke her tender hand he press'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.17#'Hail, happy nymph! no vulgar births are owed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.18#To the prolific raptures of a god:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.19#Lo! when nine times the moon renews her horn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.20#Two brother heroes shall from thee be born;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.21#Thy early care the future worthies claim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.22#To point them to the arduous paths of fame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.23#But in thy breast the important truth conceal,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.24#Nor dare the secret of a god reveal:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.25#For know, thou Neptune view'st! and at my nod
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.32.26#Earth trembles, and the waves confess their god.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.33.1#"He added not, but mounting spurn'd the plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.33.2#Then plunged into the chambers of the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.34.1#"Now in the time's full process forth she brings
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.34.2#Jove's dread vicegerents in two future kings;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.34.3#O'er proud Iolcos Pelias stretch'd his reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.34.4#And godlike Neleus ruled the Pylian plain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.34.5#Then, fruitful, to her Cretheus' royal bed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.34.6#She gallant Pheres and famed Aeson bred;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.34.7#From the same fountain Amythaon rose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.34.8#Pleased with the din of scar; and noble shout of foes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.35.1#"There moved Antiope, with haughty charms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.35.2#Who bless'd the almighty Thunderer in her arms:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.35.3#Hence sprung Amphion, hence brave Zethus came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.35.4#Founders of Thebes, and men of mighty name;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.35.5#Though bold in open field, they yet surround
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.35.6#The town with walls, and mound inject on mound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.35.7#Here ramparts stood, there towers rose high in air,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.35.8#And here through seven wide portals rush'd the war.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.36.1#"There with soft step the fair Alcmena trod,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.36.2#Who bore Alcides to the thundering god:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.36.3#And Megara, who charm'd the son of Jove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.36.4#And soften'd his stern soul to tender love.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.37.1#"Sullen and sour, with discontented mien,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.37.2#Jocasta frown'd, the incestuous Theban queen;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.37.3#With her own son she join'd in nuptial bands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.37.4#Though father's blood imbrued his murderous hands
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.37.5#The gods and men the dire offence detest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.37.6#The gods with all their furies rend his breast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.37.7#In lofty Thebes he wore the imperial crown,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.37.8#A pompous wretch! accursed upon a throne.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.37.9#The wife self-murder'd from a beam depends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.37.10#And her foul soul to blackest hell descends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.37.11#Thence to her son the choicest plagues she brings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.37.12#And the fiends haunt him with a thousand stings.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.1#"And now the beauteous Chloris I descry,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.2#A lovely shade, Amphion's youngest joy!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.3#With gifts unnumber'd Neleus sought her arms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.4#Nor paid too dearly for unequall'd charms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.5#Great in Orchomenos, in Pylos great,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.6#He sway'd the sceptre with imperial state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.7#Three gallant sons the joyful monarch told,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.8#Sage Nestor, Periclimenus the bold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.9#And Chromius last; but of the softer race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.10#One nymph alone, a myracle of grace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.11#Kings on their thrones for lovely Pero burn;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.12#The sire denies, and kings rejected mourn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.13#To him alone the beauteous prize he yields,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.14#Whose arm should ravish from Phylacian fields
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.15#The herds of Iphyclus, detain'd in wrong;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.16#Wild, furious herds, unconquerably strong!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.17#This dares a seer, but nought the seer prevails,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.18#In beauty's cause illustriously he fails;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.19#Twelve moons the foe the captive youth detains
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.20#In painful dungeons, and coercive chains;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.21#The foe at last from durance where he lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.22#His heart revering, give him back to day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.23#Won by prophetic knowledge, to fulfil
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.38.24#The steadfast purpose of the Almighty will.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.39.1#"With graceful port advancing now I spied,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.39.2#Leda the fair, the godlike Tyndar's bride:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.39.3#Hence Pollux sprung, who wields the furious sway
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.39.4#The deathful gauntlet, matchless in the fray;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.39.5#And Castor, glorious on the embattled plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.39.6#Curbs the proud steeds, reluctant to the rein:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.39.7#By turns they visit this ethereal sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.39.8#And live alternate, and alternate die:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.39.9#In hell beneath, on earth, in heaven above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.39.10#Reign the twin-gods, the favourite sons of Jove.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.1#"There Ephimedia trod the gloomy plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.2#Who charm'd the monarch of the boundless main:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.3#Hence Ephialtes, hence stern Otus sprung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.4#More fierce than giants, more than giants strong;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.5#The earth o'erburden'd groan'd beneath their weight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.6#None but Orion e'er surpassed their height:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.7#The wondrous youths had scarce nine winters told,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.8#When high in air, tremendous to behold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.9#Nine ells aloft they rear'd their towering head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.10#And full nine cubits broad their shoulders spread.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.11#Proud of their strength, and more than mortal size,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.12#The gods they challenge, and affect the skies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.13#Heaved on Olympus tottering Ossa stood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.14#On Ossa, Pelion nods with all his wood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.15#Such were they youths I had they to manhood grown
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.16#Almighty Jove had trembled on his throne,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.17#But ere the harvest of the beard began
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.18#To bristle on the chin, and promise man,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.19#His shafts Apollo aim'd; at once they sound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.40.20#And stretch the giant monsters o'er the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.41.1#"There mournful Phaedra with sad Procris moves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.41.2#Both beauteous shades, both hapless in their loves;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.41.3#And near them walk'd with solemn pace and slow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.41.4#Sad Adriadne, partner of their woe:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.41.5#The royal Minos Ariadne bred,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.41.6#She Theseus loved, from Crete with Theseus fled:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.41.7#Swift to the Dian isle the hero flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.41.8#And towards his Athens bears the lovely prize;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.41.9#There Bacchus with fierce rage Diana fires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.41.10#The goddess aims her shaft, the nymph expires.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.42.1#"There Clymene and Mera I behold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.42.2#There Eriphyle weeps, who loosely sold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.42.3#Her lord, her honour, for the lust of gold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.42.4#But should I all recount, the night would fail,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.42.5#Unequal to the melancholy tale:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.42.6#And all-composing rest my nature craves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.42.7#Here in the court, or yonder on the waves;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.42.8#In you I trust, and in the heavenly powers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.42.9#To land Ulysses on his native shores."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.43.1#He ceased; but left so charming on their ear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.43.2#His voice, that listening still they seem'd to hear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.43.3#Till, rising up, Arete silence broke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.43.4#Stretch'd out her snowy hand, and thus she spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.44.1#"What wondrous man heaven sends us in our guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.44.2#Through all his woes the hero shines confess'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.44.3#His comely port, his ample frame express
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.44.4#A manly air, majestic in distress.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.44.5#He, as my guest, is my peculiar care:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.44.6#You share the pleasure, then in bounty share
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.44.7#To worth in misery a reverence pay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.44.8#And with a generous hand reward his stay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.44.9#For since kind heaven with wealth our realm has bless'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.44.10#Give it to heaven by aiding the distress'd."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.45.1#Then sage Echeneus, whose grave reverend brow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.45.2#The hand of time had silvered o'er with snow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.45.3#Mature in wisdom rose: "Your words (he cries)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.45.4#Demand obedience, for your words are wise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.45.5#But let our king direct the glorious way
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.45.6#To generous acts; our part is to obey."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.46.1#"While life informs these limbs (the king replied),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.46.2#Well to deserve, be all my cares employed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.46.3#But here this night the royal guest detain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.46.4#Till the sun flames along the ethereal plain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.46.5#Be it my task to send with ample stores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.46.6#The stranger from our hospitable shores:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.46.7#Tread you my steps! 'Tis mine to lead the race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.46.8#The first in glory, as the first in place."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.47.1#To whom the prince: "This night with joy I stay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.47.2#O monarch great in virtue as in sway!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.47.3#If thou the circling year my stay control,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.47.4#To raise a bounty noble as thy soul;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.47.5#The circling year I wait, with ampler stores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.47.6#And fitter pomp to hail my native shores:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.47.7#Then by my realms due homage would be paid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.47.8#For wealthy kings are loyally obeyed!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.48.1#"O king! for such thou art, and sure thy blood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.48.2#Through veins (he cried) of royal fathers flow'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.48.3#Unlike those vagrants who on falsehood live,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.48.4#Skill'd in smooth tales, and artful to deceive;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.48.5#Thy better soul abhors the liar's part,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.48.6#Wise is thy voice, and noble is thy heart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.48.7#Thy words like music every breast control,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.48.8#Steal through the ear, and win upon the soul;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.48.9#soft, as some song divine, thy story flows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.48.10#Nor better could the Muse record thy woes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.49.1#"But say, upon the dark and dismal coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.49.2#Saw'st thou the worthies of the Grecian host?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.49.3#The godlike leaders who, in battle slain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.49.4#Fell before Troy, and nobly press'd the plain?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.49.5#And lo! a length of night behind remains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.49.6#The evening stars still mount the ethereal plains.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.49.7#Thy tale with raptures I could hear thee tell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.49.8#Thy woes on earth, the wondrous scenes in hell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.49.9#Till in the vault of heaven the stars decay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.49.10#And the sky reddens with the rising day."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.50.1#"O worthy of the power the gods assign'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.50.2#(Ulysses thus replies), a king in mind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.50.3#Since yet the early hour of night allows
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.50.4#Time for discourse, and time for soft repose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.50.5#If scenes of misery can entertain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.50.6#Woes I unfold, of woes a dismal train.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.50.7#Prepare to heir of murder and of blood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.50.8#Of godlike heroes who uninjured stood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.50.9#Amidst a war of spears in foreign lands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.50.10#Yet bled at home, and bled by female hands.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.51.1#"Now summon'd Proserpine to hell's black hall
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.51.2#The heroine shades: they vanish'd at her call.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.51.3#When lo! advanced the forms of heroes slain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.51.4#By stern AEgysthus, a majestic train:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.51.5#And, high above the rest Atrides press'd the plain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.51.6#He quaff'd the gore; and straight his soldier knew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.51.7#And from his eyes pour'd down the tender dew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.51.8#His arms he stretch'd; his arms the touch deceive,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.51.9#Nor in the fond embrace, embraces give:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.51.10#His substance vanish'd, and his strength decay'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.51.11#Now all Atrides is an empty shade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.52.1#"Moved at the sight, I for a apace resign'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.52.2#To soft affliction all my manly mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.52.3#At last with tears: 'O what relentless doom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.52.4#Imperial phantom, bow'd thee to the tomb?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.52.5#Say while the sea, and while the tempest raves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.52.6#Has Fate oppress'd thee in the roaring waves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.52.7#Or nobly seized thee in the dire alarms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.52.8#Of war and slaughter, and the clash of arms?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.1#"The ghost returns: 'O chief of human kind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.2#For active courage and a patient mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.3#Nor while the sea, nor while the tempest raves
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.4#Has Fate oppress'd me on the roaring waves!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.5#Nor nobly seized me in the dire alarms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.6#Of war and slaughter, and the clash of arms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.7#Stabb'd by a murderous hand Atrides died,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.8#A foul adulterer, and a faithless bride;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.9#E'en in my mirth, and at the friendly feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.10#O'er the full bowl, the traitor stabb'd his guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.11#Thus by the gory arm of slaughter falls
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.12#The stately ox, and bleeds within the stalls.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.13#But not with me the direful murder ends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.14#These, these expired! their crime, they were my friends:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.15#Thick as the boars, which some luxurious lord
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.16#Kills for the feast, to crown the nuptial board.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.17#When war has thunder'd with its loudest storms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.18#Death thou hast seen in all her ghastly forms:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.19#In duel met her on the listed ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.20#When hand to hand they wound return for wound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.21#But never have the eyes astonish'd view'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.22#So vile a deed, so dire a scene of blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.23#E'en in the flow of joy, when now the bowl
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.24#Glows in our veins, and opens every soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.25#We groan, we faint; with blood the doom is dyed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.26#And o'er the pavement floats the dreadful tide--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.27#Her breast all gore, with lamentable cries,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.28#The bleeding innocent Cassandra dies!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.29#Then though pale death froze cold in every vein,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.30#My sword I strive to wield, but strive in vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.31#Nor did my traitress wife these eyelids close,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.32#Or decently in death my limbs compose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.33#O woman, woman, when to ill thy mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.34#Is bent, all hell contains no fouler fiend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.35#And such was mine! who basely plunged her sword
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.36#Through the fond bosom where she reign'd adored!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.37#Alas! I hoped the toils of war o'ercome,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.38#To meet soft quiet and repose at home;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.39#Delusive hope! O wife, thy deeds disgrace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.40#The perjured sex, and blacken all the race;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.41#And should posterity one virtuous find,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.53.42#Name Clytemnestra, they will curse the kind.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.54.1#"Oh injured shade (I cried) what mighty woes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.54.2#To thy imperial race from woman rose!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.54.3#By woman here thou tread'st this mournful strand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.54.4#And Greece by woman lies a desert land.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.1#"'Warn'd by my ills beware, (the shade replies,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.2#Nor trust the sex that is so rarely wise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.3#When earnest to explore thy secret breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.4#Unfold some trifle, but conceal the rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.5#But in thy consort cease to fear a foe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.6#For thee she feels sincerity of woe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.7#When Troy first bled beneath the Grecian arms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.8#She shone unrivall'd with a blaze of charms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.9#Thy infant son her fragrant bosom press'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.10#Hung at her knee, or wanton'd at her breast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.11#But now the years a numerous train have ran;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.12#The blooming boy is ripen'd into man;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.13#Thy eyes shall see him burn with noble fire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.14#The sire shall bless his son, the son his sire;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.15#But my Orestes never met these eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.16#Without one look the murder'd father dies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.17#Then from a wretched friend this wisdom learn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.18#E'en to thy queen disguised, unknown, return;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.19#For since of womankind so few are just,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.55.20#Think all are false, nor e'en the faithful trust.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.56.1#"'But, say, resides my son in royal port,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.56.2#In rich Orchomenos, or Sparta's court?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.56.3#Or say in Pyle? for yet he views the light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.56.4#Nor glides a phantom through the realms of night.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.57.1#"Then I: 'Thy suit is vain, nor can I say
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.57.2#If yet he breathes in realms of cheerful day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.57.3#Or pale or wan beholds these nether skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.57.4#Truth I revere; for wisdom never lies.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.58.1#"Thus in a tide of tears our sorrows flow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.58.2#And add new horror to the realms of woe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.58.3#Till side by side along the dreary coast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.58.4#Advanced Achilles' and Patroclus' ghost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.58.5#A friendly pair! near these the Pylian stray'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.58.6#And towering Ajax, an illustrious shade!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.58.7#War was his joy, and pleased with loud alarms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.58.8#None but Pelides brighter shone in arms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.59.1#"Through the thick gloom his friend Achilles knew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.59.2#And as he speaks the tears descend in dew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.60.1#"'Comest thou alive to view the Stygian bounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.60.2#Where the wan spectres walk eternal rounds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.60.3#Nor fear'st the dark and dismal waste to tread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.60.4#Throng'd with pale ghosts, familiar with the dead?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.61.1#"To whom with sighs: 'I pass these dreadful gates
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.61.2#To seek the Theban, and consult the Fates;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.61.3#For still, distress'd, I rove from coast to coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.61.4#Lost to my friends, and to my country lost.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.61.5#But sure the eye of Time beholds no name
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.61.6#So bless'd as thine in all the rolls of fame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.61.7#Alive we hail'd thee with our guardian gods,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.61.8#And dead thou rulest a king in these abodes.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.1#"'Talk not of ruling in this dolorous gloom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.2#Nor think vain words (he cried) can ease my doom.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.3#Rather I'd choose laboriously to bear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.4#A weight of woes, and breathe the vital air,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.5#A slave to some poor hind that toils for bread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.6#Than reign the sceptred monarch of the dead.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.7#But say, if in my steps my son proceeds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.8#And emulates his godlike father's deeds?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.9#If at the clash of arms, and shout of foes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.10#Swells his bold heart, his bosom nobly glows?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.11#Say if my sire, the reverend Peleus, reigns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.12#Great in his Phthia, and his throne maintains;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.13#Or, weak and old, my youthful arm demands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.14#To fix the sceptre steadfast in his hands?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.15#O might the lamp of life rekindled burn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.16#And death release me from the silent urn!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.17#This arm, that thunder'd o'er the Phrygian plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.18#And swell'd the ground with mountains of the slain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.19#Should vindicate my injured father's fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.62.20#Crush the proud rebel, and assert his claim.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.1#"'Illustrious shade (I cried), of Peleus' fates
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.2#No circumstance the voice of Fame relates:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.3#But hear with pleased attention the renown,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.4#The wars and wisdom of thy gallant son.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.5#With me from Scyros to the field of fame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.6#Radiant in arms the blooming hero came.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.7#When Greece assembled all her hundred states,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.8#To ripen counsels, and decide debates,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.9#Heavens! how he charm'd us with a flow of sense,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.10#And won the heart with manly eloquence!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.11#He first was seen of all the peers to rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.12#The third in wisdom, where they all were wise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.13#But when, to try the fortune of the day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.14#Host moved toward host in terrible array,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.15#Before the van, impatient for the fight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.16#With martial port he strode, and stern delight:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.17#Heaps strew'd on heaps beneath his falchion groan'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.18#And monuments of dead deform'd the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.19#The time would fail should I in order tell
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.20#What foes were vanquish'd, and what numbers fell:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.21#How, lost through love, Eurypylus was slain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.22#And round him bled his bold Cetaean train.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.23#To Troy no hero came of nobler line,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.63.24#Or if of nobler, Memnon, it was thine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.1#"When Ilion in the horse received her doom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.2#And unseen armies ambush'd in its womb,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.3#Greece gave her latent warriors to my care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.4#'Twas mine on Troy to pour the imprison'd war:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.5#Then when the boldest bosom beat with fear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.6#When the stern eyes of heroes dropp'd a tear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.7#Fierce in his look his ardent valour glow'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.8#Flush'd in his cheek, or sallied in his blood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.9#Indignant in the dark recess he stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.10#Pants for the battle, and the war demands:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.11#His voice breathed death, and with a martial air
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.12#He grasp'd his sword, and shook his glittering spear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.13#And when the gods our arms with conquest crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.14#When Troy's proud bulwarks smoked upon the ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.15#Greece, to reward her soldier's gallant toils,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.64.16#Heap'd high his navy with unnumber'd spoils.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.65.1#"Thus great in glory, from the din of war
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.65.2#Safe he return'd, without one hostile scar;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.65.3#Though spears in iron tempests rain'd around,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.65.4#Yet innocent they play'd, and guiltless of a wound.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.66.1#"While yet I spoke, the shade with transport glow'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.66.2#Rose in his majesty, and nobler trod;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.66.3#With haughty stalk he sought the distant glades
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.66.4#Of warrior kings, and join'd the illustrious shades.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.1#"Now without number ghost by ghost arose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.2#All wailing with unutterable woes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.3#Alone, apart, in discontented mood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.4#A gloomy shade the sullen Ajax stood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.5#For ever sad, with proud disdain he pined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.6#And the lost arms for ever stung his mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.7#Though to the contest Thetis gave the laws,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.8#And Pallas, by the Trojans, judged the cause.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.9#O why was I victorious in the strife?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.10#O dear bought honour with so brave a life!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.11#With him the strength of war, the soldier's pride,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.12#Our second hope to great Achilles, died!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.13#Touch'd at the sight from tears I scarce refrain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.14#And tender sorrow thrills in every vein;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.15#Pensive and sad I stand, at length accost
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.16#With accents mild the inexorable ghost:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.17#'Still burns thy rage? and can brave souls resent
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.18#E'en after death? Relent, great shade, relent!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.19#Perish those arms which by the gods' decree
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.20#Accursed our army with the loss of thee!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.21#With thee we fall; Greece wept thy hapless fates,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.22#And shook astonish'd through her hundred states;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.23#Not more, when great Achilles press'd the ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.24#And breathed his manly spirit through the wound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.25#O deem thy fall not owed to man's decree,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.26#Jove hated Greece, and punish'd Greece in thee!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.27#Turn then; oh peaceful turn, thy wrath control,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.67.28#And calm the raging tempest of thy soul.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.68.1#"While yet I speak, the shade disdains to stay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.68.2#In silence turns, and sullen stalks away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.69.1#"Touch'd at his sour retreat, through deepest night,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.69.2#Through hell's black bounds I had pursued his flight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.69.3#And forced the stubborn spectre to reply;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.69.4#But wondrous visions drew my curious eye.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.69.5#High on a throne, tremendous to behold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.69.6#Stern Minos waves a mace of burnish'd gold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.69.7#Around ten thousand thousand spectres stand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.69.8#Through the wide dome of Dis, a trembling band
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.69.9#Still as they plead, the fatal lots he rolls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.69.10#Absolves the just, and dooms the guilty souls.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.70.1#"The huge Orion, of portentous size,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.70.2#Swift through the gloom a giant-hunter flies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.70.3#A ponderous mace of brass with direful sway
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.70.4#Aloft he whirls, to crush the savage prey!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.70.5#Stern beasts in trains that by his truncheon fell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.70.6#Now grisly forms, shoot o'er the lawns of hell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.71.1#"There Tityus large and long, in fetters bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.71.2#O'erspreads nine acres of infernal ground;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.71.3#Two ravenous vultures, furious for their food,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.71.4#Scream o'er the fiend, and riot in his blood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.71.5#Incessant gore the liver in his breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.71.6#The immortal liver grows, and gives the immortal feast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.71.7#For as o'er Panope's enamell'd plains
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.71.8#Latona journey'd to the Pythian fanes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.71.9#With haughty love the audacious monster strove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.71.10#To force the goddess, and to rival Jove.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.1#"There Tantalus along the Stygian bounds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.2#Pours out deep groans (with groans all hell resounds);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.3#E'en in the circling floods refreshment craves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.4#And pines with thirst amidst a sea of waves;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.5#When to the water he his lip applies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.6#Back from his lip the treacherous water flies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.7#Above, beneath, around his hapless head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.8#Trees of all kinds delicious fruitage spread;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.9#There figs, sky-dyed, a purple hue disclose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.10#Green looks the olive, the pomegranate glows.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.11#There dangling pears exalting scents unfold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.12#And yellow apples ripen into gold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.13#The fruit he strives to seize; but blasts arise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.72.14#Toss it on high, and whirl it to the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.73.1#"I turn'd my eye, and as I turn'd survey'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.73.2#A mournful vision! the Sisyphian shade;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.73.3#With many a weary step, and many a groan,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.73.4#Up the high hill he heaves a huge round stone;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.73.5#The huge round stone, resulting with a bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.73.6#Thunders impetuous down, and smokes along the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.73.7#Again the restless orb his toil renews,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.73.8#Dust mounts in clouds, and sweat descends in dews.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.1#"Now I the strength of Hercules behold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.2#A towering spectre of gigantic mould,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.3#A shadowy form! for high in heaven's abodes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.4#Himself resides, a god among the gods;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.5#There in the bright assemblies of the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.6#He nectar quaffs, and Hebe crowns his joys.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.7#Here hovering ghosts, like fowl, his shade surround,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.8#And clang their pinions with terrific sound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.9#Gloomy as night he stands, in act to throw
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.10#The aerial arrow from the twanging bow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.11#Around his breast a wondrous zone is roll'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.12#Where woodland monsters grin in fretted gold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.13#There sullen lions sternly seem to roar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.14#The bear to growl to foam the tusky boar;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.15#There war and havoc and destruction stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.16#And vengeful murder red with human blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.17#Thus terribly adorned the figures shine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.18#Inimitably wrought with skill divine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.19#The mighty good advanced with awful look,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.74.20#And, turning his grim visage, sternly spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.75.1#"'O exercise in grief! by arts refined;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.75.2#O taught to bear the wrongs of base mankind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.75.3#Such, such was I! Still toss'd from care to care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.75.4#While in your world I drew the vital air!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.75.5#E'en I, who from the Lord of Thunders rose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.75.6#Bore toils and dangers, and a weight of woes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.75.7#To a base monarch still a slave confined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.75.8#(The hardest bondage to a generous mind!)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.75.9#Down to these worlds I trod the dismal way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.75.10#And dragg'd the three-mouth'd dog to upper day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.75.11#E'en hell I conquer'd, through the friendly aid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.75.12#Of Maia's offspring, and the martial maid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.76.1#"Thus he, nor deign'd for our reply to stay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.76.2#But, turning, stalk'd with giant-strides away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.1#"Curious to view the kings of ancient days,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.2#The mighty dead that live in endless praise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.3#Resolved I stand; and haply had survey'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.4#The godlike Theseus, and Pirithous' shade;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.5#But swarms of spectres rose from deepest hell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.6#With bloodless visage, and with hideous yell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.7#They scream, they shriek; and groans and dismal sounds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.8#Stun my scared ears, and pierce hell's utmost bounds.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.9#No more my heart the dismal din sustains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.10#And my cold blood hangs shivering in my veins;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.11#Lest Gorgon, rising from the infernal lakes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.12#With horrors arm'd, and curls of hissing snakes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.13#Should fix me stiffen'd at the monstrous sight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.14#A stony image, in eternal night!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.15#Straight from the direful coast to purer air
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.16#I speed my flight, and to my mates repair.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.17#My mates ascend the ship; they strike their oars;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.18#The mountains lessen, and retreat the shores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.19#Swift o'er the waves we fly; the freshening gales
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:11.77.20#Sing through the shrouds, and stretch the swelling sails."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.1.1#"Thus o'er the rolling surge the vessel flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.1.2#Till from the waves the AEaean hills arise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.1.3#Here the gay Morn resides in radiant bowers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.1.4#Here keeps here revels with the dancing Hours;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.1.5#Here Phoebus, rising in the ethereal way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.1.6#Through heaven's bright portals pours the beamy day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.1.7#At once we fix our halsers on the land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.1.8#At once descend, and press the desert sand:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.1.9#There, worn and wasted, lose our cares in sleep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.1.10#To the hoarse murmurs of the rolling deep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.2.1#"Soon as the morn restored the day, we paid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.2.2#Sepulchral honours to Elpenor's shade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.2.3#Now by the axe the rushing forest bends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.2.4#And the huge pile along the shore ascends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.2.5#Around we stand, a melancholy train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.2.6#And a loud groan re-echoes from the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.2.7#Fierce o'er the pyre, by fanning breezes spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.2.8#The hungry flames devour the silent dead.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.2.9#A rising tomb, the silent dead to grace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.2.10#Fast by the roarings of the main we place;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.2.11#The rising tomb a lofty column bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.2.12#And high above it rose the tapering oar.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.3.1#"Meantime the goddess our return survey'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.3.2#From the pale ghosts and hell's tremendous shade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.3.3#Swift she descends: a train of nymphs divine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.3.4#Bear the rich viands and the generous wine:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.3.5#In act to speak the power of magic stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.3.6#And graceful thus accosts the listening bands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.4.1#"'O sons of woe? decreed by adverse fates
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.4.2#Alive to pass through hell's eternal gates!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.4.3#All, soon or late, are doom'd that path to tread;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.4.4#More wretched you! twice number'd with the dead!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.4.5#This day adjourn your cares, exalt your souls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.4.6#Indulge the taste, and drain the sparkling bowls;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.4.7#And when the morn unveils her saffron ray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.4.8#Spread your broad sails, and plough the liquid way:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.4.9#Lo, I this night, your faithful guide, explain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.4.10#Your woes by land, your dangers on the main.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.5.1#"The goddess spoke. In feasts we waste the day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.5.2#Till Phoebus downward plunged his burning ray;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.5.3#Then sable night ascends, and balmy rest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.5.4#Seals every eye, and calms the troubled breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.5.5#Then curious she commands me to relate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.5.6#The dreadful scenes of Pluto's dreary state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.5.7#She sat in silence while the tale I tell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.5.8#The wondrous visions and the laws of hell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.6.1#"Then thus: 'The lot of man the gods dispose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.6.2#These ills are past: now hear thy future woes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.6.3#O prince attend; some favouring power be kind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.6.4#And print the important story on thy mind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.1#"'Next, where the Sirens dwells, you plough the seas;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.2#Their song is death, and makes destruction please.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.3#Unblest the man, whom music wins to stay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.4#Nigh the cursed shore and listen to the lay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.5#No more that wretch shall view the joys of life
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.6#His blooming offspring, or his beauteous wife!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.7#In verdant meads they sport; and wide around
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.8#Lie human bones that whiten all the ground:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.9#The ground polluted floats with human gore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.10#And human carnage taints the dreadful shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.11#Fly swift the dangerous coast: let every ear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.12#Be stopp'd against the song! 'tis death to hear!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.13#Firm to the mast with chains thyself be bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.14#Nor trust thy virtue to the enchanting sound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.15#If, mad with transport, freedom thou demand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.7.16#Be every fetter strain'd, and added band to band.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.8.1#"'These seas o'erpass'd, be wise! but I refrain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.8.2#To mark distinct thy voyage o'er the main:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.8.3#New horrors rise! let prudence be thy guide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.8.4#And guard thy various passage through the tide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.1#"'High o'er the main two rocks exalt their brow,'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.2#The boiling billows thundering roll below;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.3#Through the vast waves the dreadful wonders move,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.4#Hence named Erratic by the gods above.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.5#No bird of air, no dove of swiftest wing,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.6#That bears ambrosia to the ethereal king,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.7#Shuns the dire rocks: in vain she cuts the skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.8#The dire rocks meet, and crush her as she flies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.9#Not the fleet bark, when prosperous breezes play,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.10#Ploughs o'er that roaring surge its desperate way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.11#O'erwhelm'd it sinks: while round a smoke expires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.12#And the waves flashing seem to burn with fires.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.13#Scarce the famed Argo pass'd these raging floods,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.14#The sacred Argo, fill'd with demigods!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.15#E'en she had sunk, but Jove's imperial bride
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.9.16#Wing'd her fleet sail, and push'd her o'er the tide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.1#"'High in the air the rock its summit shrouds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.2#In brooding tempests, and in rolling clouds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.3#Loud storms around, and mists eternal rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.4#Beat its bleak brow, and intercept the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.5#When all the broad expansion, bright with day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.6#Glows with the autumnal or the summer ray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.7#The summer and the autumn glow in vain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.8#The sky for ever lowers, for ever clouds remain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.9#Impervious to the step of man it stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.10#Though borne by twenty feet, though arm'd with twenty hands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.11#Smooth as the polish of the mirror rise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.12#The slippery sides, and shoot into the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.13#Full in the centre of this rock display'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.14#A yawning cavern casts a dreadful shade:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.15#Nor the fleet arrow from the twanging bow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.16#Sent with full force, could reach the depth below.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.17#Wide to the west the horrid gulf extends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.18#And the dire passage down to hell descends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.19#O fly the dreadful sight! expand thy sails,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.20#Ply the strong oar, and catch the nimble gales;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.21#Here Scylla bellows from the dire abodes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.22#Tremendous pest, abhorr'd by man and gods!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.23#Hideous her voice, and with less terrors roar
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.24#The whelps of lions in the midnight hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.25#Twelve feet, deform'd and foul, the fiend dispreads;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.26#Six horrid necks she rears, and six terrific heads;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.27#Her jaws grin dreadful with three rows of teeth;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.28#Jaggy they stand, the gaping den of death;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.29#Her parts obscene the raging billows hide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.30#Her bosom terribly o'erlooks the tide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.31#When stung with hunger she embroils the flood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.32#The sea-dog and the dolphin are her food;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.33#She makes the huge leviathan her prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.34#And all the monsters of the watery way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.35#The swiftest racer of the azure plain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.36#Here fills her sails, and spreads her oars in vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.37#Fell Scylla rises, in her fury roars,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.10.38#At once six mouths expands, at once six men devours.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.1#"'Close by, a rock of less enormous height
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.2#Breaks the wild waves, and forms a dangerous strait;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.3#Full on its crown a fig's green branches rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.4#And shoot a leafy forest to the skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.5#Beneath, Charybdis holds her boisterous reign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.6#'Midst roaring whirlpools, and absorbs the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.7#Thrice in her gulfs the boiling seas subside,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.8#Thrice in dire thunders she refunds the tide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.9#Oh, if thy vessel plough the direful waves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.10#When seas retreating roar within her caves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.11#Ye perish all! though he who rules the main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.12#Lends his strong aid, his aid he lends in vain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.13#Ah, shun the horrid gulf! by Scylla fly.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.11.14#'Tis better six to lose, than all to die.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.12.1#"I then: 'O nymph propitious to my prayer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.12.2#Goddess divine, my guardian power, declare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.12.3#Is the foul fiend from human vengeance freed?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.12.4#Or, if I rise in arms, can Scylla bleed?'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.1#"Then she: 'O worn by toils, O broke in fight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.2#Still are new toils and war thy dire delight?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.3#Will martial flames for ever fire thy mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.4#And never, never be to Heaven resign'd?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.5#How vain thy efforts to avenge the wrong!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.6#Deathless the pest! impenetrably strong!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.7#Furious and fell, tremendous to behold!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.8#E'en with a look she withers all the bold!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.9#She mocks the weak attempts of human might;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.10#Oh, fly her rage! thy conquest is thy flight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.11#If but to seize thy arms thou make delay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.12#Again thy fury vindicates her prey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.13#Her six mouths yawn, and six are snatch'd away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.14#From her foul wound Crataeis gave to air
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.15#This dreadful pest! To her direct thy prayer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.16#To curb the monster in her dire abodes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.17#And guard thee through the tumult of the floods.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.18#Thence to Trinacria's shore you bend your way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.19#Where graze thy herds, illustrious source of day!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.20#Seven herds, seven flocks enrich the sacred plains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.21#Each herd, each flock full fifty heads contains;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.22#The wondrous kind a length of age survey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.23#By breed increase not, nor by death decay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.24#Two sister goddesses possess the plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.25#The constant guardian of the woolly train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.26#Lampetie fair, and Phaethusa young,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.27#From Phoebus and the bright Neaea sprung;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.28#Here, watchful o'er the flocks, in shady bowers
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.29#And flowery meads, they waste the joyous hours.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.30#Rob not the gods! and so propitious gales
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.31#Attend thy voyage, and impel thy sails;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.32#But if thy impious hands the flocks destroy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.33#The gods, the gods avenge it, and ye die!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.34#'Tis thine alone (thy friends and navy lost)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.13.35#Through tedious toils to view thy native coast.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.14.1#She ceased: and now arose the morning ray;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.14.2#Swift to her dome the goddess held her way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.14.3#Then to my mates I measured back the plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.14.4#Climb'd the tall bark, and rush'd into the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.14.5#Then, bending to the stroke, their oars they drew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.14.6#To their broad breasts, and swift the galley flew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.14.7#Up sprung a brisker breeze; with freshening gales
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.14.8#The friendly goddess stretch'd the swelling sails;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.14.9#We drop our oars; at ease the pilot guides;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.14.10#The vessel light along the level glides.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.14.11#When, rising sad and slow, with pensive look,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.14.12#Thus to the melancholy train I spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.15.1#"'O friends, oh ever partners of my woes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.15.2#Attend while I what Heaven foredooms disclose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.15.3#Hear all! Fate hangs o'er all; on you it lies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.15.4#To live or perish! to be safe, be wise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.16.1#"'In flowery meads the sportive Sirens play,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.16.2#Touch the soft lyre, and tune the vocal lay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.16.3#Me, me alone, with fetters firmly bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.16.4#The gods allow to hear the dangerous sound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.16.5#Hear and obey; if freedom I demand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.16.6#Be every fetter strain'd, be added band to band.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.1#"While yet I speak the winged galley flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.2#And lo! the Siren shores like mists arise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.3#Sunk were at once the winds; the air above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.4#And waves below, at once forgot to move;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.5#Some demon calm'd the air and smooth'd the deep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.6#Hush'd the loud winds, and charm'd the waves to sleep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.7#Now every sail we furl, each oar we ply;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.8#Lash'd by the stroke, the frothy waters fly.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.9#The ductile wax with busy hands I mould,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.10#And cleft in fragments, and the fragments roll'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.11#The aerial region now grew warm with day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.12#The wax dissolved beneath the burning ray;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.13#Then every ear I barr'd against the strain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.14#And from access of frenzy lock'd the brain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.15#Now round the masts my mates the fetters roll'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.16#And bound me limb by limb with fold on fold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.17#Then bending to the stroke, the active train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.17.18#Plunge all at once their oars, and cleave the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.18.1#"While to the shore the rapid vessel flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.18.2#Our swift approach the Siren choir descries;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.18.3#Celestial music warbles from their tongue,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.18.4#And thus the sweet deluders tune the song:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.19.1#"'Oh stay, O pride of Greece! Ulysses, stay!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.19.2#Oh cease thy course, and listen to our lay!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.19.3#Blest is the man ordain'd our voice to hear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.19.4#The song instructs the soul, and charms the ear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.19.5#Approach! thy soul shall into raptures rise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.19.6#Approach! and learn new wisdom from the wise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.19.7#We know whate'er the kings of mighty name
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.19.8#Achieved at Ilion in the field of fame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.19.9#Whate'er beneath the sun's bright journey lies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.19.10#Oh stay, and learn new wisdom from the wise!'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.20.1#"Thus the sweet charmers warbled o'er the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.20.2#My soul takes wing to meet the heavenly strain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.20.3#I give the sign, and struggle to be free;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.20.4#Swift row my mates, and shoot along the sea;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.20.5#New chains they add, and rapid urge the way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.20.6#Till, dying off, the distant sounds decay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.20.7#Then scudding swiftly from the dangerous ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.20.8#The deafen'd ear unlock'd, the chains unbound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.1#"Now all at once tremendous scenes unfold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.2#Thunder'd the deeps, the smoky billows roll'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.3#Tumultuous waves embroil the bellowing flood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.4#All trembling, deafen'd, and aghast we stood!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.5#No more the vessel plough'd the dreadful wave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.6#Fear seized the mighty, and unnerved the brave;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.7#Each dropp'd his oar; but swift from man to man
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.8#With looks serene I turn'd, and thus began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.9#'O friends! O often tried in adverse storms!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.10#With ills familiar in more dreadful forms!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.11#Deep in the dire Cyclopean den you lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.12#Yet safe return'd--Ulysses led the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.13#Learn courage hence, and in my care confide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.14#Lo! still the same Ulysses is your guide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.15#Attend my words! your oars incessant ply;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.16#Strain every nerve, and bid the vessel fly.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.17#If from yon jostling rocks and wavy war
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.18#Jove safety grants, he grants it to your care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.19#And thou, whose guiding hand directs our way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.20#Pilot, attentive listen and obey!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.21#Bear wide thy course, nor plough those angry waves
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.22#Where rolls yon smoke, yon tumbling ocean raves;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.23#Steer by the higher rock; lest whirl'd around
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.24#We sink, beneath the circling eddy drown'd.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.25#While yet I speak, at once their oars they seize,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.26#Stretch to the stroke, and brush the working seas.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.27#Cautious the name of Scylla I suppress'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.21.28#That dreadful sound had chill'd the boldest breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.22.1#"Meantime, forgetful of the voice divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.22.2#All dreadful bright my limbs in armour shine;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.22.3#High on the deck I take my dangerous stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.22.4#Two glittering javelins lighten in my hand;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.22.5#Prepared to whirl the whizzing spear I stay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.22.6#Till the fell fiend arise to seize her prey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.22.7#Around the dungeon, studious to behold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.22.8#The hideous pest, my labouring eyes I roll'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.22.9#In vain! the dismal dungeon, dark as night,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.22.10#Veils the dire monster, and confounds the sight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.1#"Now through the rocks, appall'd with deep dismay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.2#We bend our course, and stem the desperate way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.3#Dire Scylla there a scene of horror forms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.4#And here Charybdis fills the deep with storms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.5#When the tide rushes from her rumbling caves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.6#The rough rock roars, tumultuous boil the waves;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.7#They toss, they foam, a wild confusion raise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.8#Like waters bubbling o'er the fiery blaze;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.9#Eternal mists obscure the aerial plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.10#And high above the rock she spouts the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.11#When in her gulfs the rushing sea subsides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.12#She drains the ocean with the refluent tides;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.13#The rock re-bellows with a thundering sound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.23.14#Deep, wondrous deep, below appears the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.1#"Struck with despair, with trembling hearts we view'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.2#The yawning dungeon, and the tumbling flood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.3#When lo! fierce Scylla stoop'd to seize her prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.4#Stretch'd her dire jaws, and swept six men away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.5#Chiefs of renown! loud-echoing shrieks arise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.6#I turn, and view them quivering in the skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.7#They call, and aid with outstretch'd arms implore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.8#In vain they call! those arms are stretch'd no more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.9#As from some rock that overhangs the flood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.10#The silent fisher casts the insidious food,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.11#With fraudful care he waits the finny prize,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.12#And sudden lifts it quivering to the skies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.13#So the foul monster lifts her prey on high,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.14#So pant the wretches struggling in the sky;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.15#In the wide dungeon she devours her food,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.16#And the flesh trembles while she churns the blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.17#Worn as I am with griefs, with care decay'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.18#Never, I never scene so dire survey'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.19#My shivering blood, congeal'd, forgot to flow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.24.20#Aghast I stood, a monument of woe!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.25.1#"Now from the rocks the rapid vessel flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.25.2#And the hoarse din like distant thunder dies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.25.3#To Sol's bright isle our voyage we pursue,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.25.4#And now the glittering mountains rise to view.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.25.5#There, sacred to the radiant god of day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.25.6#Graze the fair herds, the flocks promiscuous stray:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.25.7#Then suddenly was heard along the main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.25.8#To low the ox, to blest the woolly train.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.25.9#Straight to my anxious thoughts the sound convey'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.25.10#The words of Circe and the Theban shade;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.25.11#Warn'd by their awful voice these shores to shun,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.25.12#With cautious fears oppress'd I thus begun:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.26.1#"'O friends! O ever exorcised in care!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.26.2#Hear Heaven's commands, and reverence what ye hear!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.26.3#To fly these shores the prescient Theban shade
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.26.4#And Circe warn! Oh be their voice obey'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.26.5#Some mighty woe relentless Heaven forebodes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.26.6#Fly these dire regions, and revere the gods!'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.27.1#"While yet I spoke, a sudden sorrow ran
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.27.2#Through every breast, and spread from man to man,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.27.3#Till wrathful thus Eurylochus began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.1#"'O cruel thou! some Fury sure has steel'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.2#That stubborn soul, by toil untaught to yield!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.3#From sleep debarr'd, we sink from woes to woes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.4#And cruel' enviest thou a short repose?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.5#Still must we restless rove, new seas explore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.6#The sun descending, and so near the shore?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.7#And lo! the night begins her groomy reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.8#And doubles all the terrors of the main:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.9#Oft in the dead of night loud winds rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.10#Lash the wild surge, and bluster in the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.11#Oh, should the fierce south-west his rage display,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.12#And toss with rising storms the watery way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.13#Though gods descend from heaven's aerial plain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.14#To lend us aid, the gods descend in vain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.15#Then while the night displays her awful shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.16#Sweet time of slumber! be the night obey'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.17#Haste ye to land! and when the morning ray
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.18#Sheds her bright beam, pursue the destined way.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.19#A sudden joy in every bosom rose:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.28.20#So will'd some demon, minister of woes!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.29.1#"To whom with grief: 'O swift to be undone!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.29.2#Constrain'd I act what wisdom bids me shun.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.29.3#But yonder herbs and yonder flocks forbear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.29.4#Attest the heavens, and call the gods to hear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.29.5#Content, an innocent repast display,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.29.6#By Circe given, and fly the dangerous prey.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.1#'Thus I: and while to shore the vessel flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.2#With hands uplifted they attest the skies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.3#Then, where a fountain's gurgling waters play,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.4#They rush to land, and end in feasts the day:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.5#They feed; they quaff; and now (their hunger fled)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.6#Sigh for their friends devour'd, and mourn the dead;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.7#Nor cease the tears' till each in slumber shares
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.8#A sweet forgetfulness of human cares.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.9#Now far the night advanced her gloomy reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.10#And setting stars roll'd down the azure plain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.11#When at the voice of Jove wild whirlwinds rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.12#And clouds and double darkness veil the skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.13#The moon, the stars, the bright ethereal host
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.14#Seem as extinct, and all their splendours lost:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.15#The furious tempest roars with dreadful sound:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.16#Air thunders, rolls the ocean, groans the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.17#All night it raged: when morning rose to land
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.18#We haul'd our bark, and moor'd it on the strand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.19#Where in a beauteous grotto's cool recess
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.30.20#Dance the green Nerolds of the neighbouring seas.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.31.1#"There while the wild winds whistled o'er the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.31.2#Thus careful I address'd the listening train:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.32.1#"'O friends, be wise! nor dare the flocks destroy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.32.2#Of these fair pastures: if ye touch, ye die.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.32.3#Warn'd by the high command of Heaven, be awed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.32.4#Holy the flocks, and dreadful is the god!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.32.5#That god who spreads the radiant beams of light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.32.6#And views wide earth and heaven's unmeasured height.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.1#"And now the moon had run her monthly round,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.2#The south-east blustering with a dreadful sound:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.3#Unhurt the beeves, untouch'd the woolly train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.4#Low through the grove, or touch the flowery plain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.5#Then fail'd our food: then fish we make our prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.6#Or fowl that screaming haunt the watery way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.7#Till now from sea or flood no succour found,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.8#Famine and meagre want besieged us round.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.9#Pensive and pale from grove to grove I stray'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.10#From the loud storms to find a sylvan shade;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.11#There o'er my hands the living wave I pour;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.12#And Heaven and Heaven's immortal thrones implore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.13#To calm the roarings of the stormy main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.14#And guide me peaceful to my realms again.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.15#Then o'er my eyes the gods soft slumbers shed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.33.16#While thus Eurylochus arising said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.1#"'O friends, a thousand ways frail mortals lead
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.2#To the cold tomb, and dreadful all to tread;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.3#But dreadful most, when by a slow decay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.4#Pale hunger wastes the manly strength away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.5#Why cease ye then to implore the powers above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.6#And offer hecatombs to thundering Jove?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.7#Why seize ye not yon beeves, and fleecy prey?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.8#Arise unanimous; arise and slay!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.9#And if the gods ordain a safe return,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.10#To Phoebus shrines shall rise, and altars burn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.11#But should the powers that o'er mankind preside
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.12#Decree to plunge us in the whelming tide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.13#Better to rush at once to shades below
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.34.14#Than linger life away, and nourish woe.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.35.1#"Thus he: the beeves around securely stray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.35.2#When swift to ruin they invade the prey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.35.3#They seize, they kill!--but for the rite divine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.35.4#The barley fail'd, and for libations wine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.35.5#Swift from the oak they strip the shady pride;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.35.6#And verdant leaves the flowery cake supplied.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.36.1#"With prayer they now address the ethereal train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.36.2#Slay the selected beeves, and flay the slain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.36.3#The thighs, with fat involved, divide with art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.36.4#Strew'd o'er with morsels cut from every part.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.36.5#Water, instead of wine, is brought in urns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.36.6#And pour'd profanely as the victim burns.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.36.7#The thighs thus offer'd, and the entrails dress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.36.8#They roast the fragments, and prepare the feast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.37.1#"'Twas then soft slumber fled my troubled brain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.37.2#Back to the bark I speed along the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.37.3#When lo! an odour from the feast exhales,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.37.4#Spreads o'er the coast and scents the tainted gales;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.37.5#A chilly fear congeal'd my vital blood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.37.6#And thus, obtesting Heaven, I mourn'd aloud;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.38.1#"'O sire of men and gods, immortal Jove!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.38.2#O all ye blissful powers that reign above!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.38.3#Why were my cares beguiled in short repose?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.38.4#O fatal slumber, paid with lasting woes!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.38.5#A deed so dreadful all the gods alarms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.38.6#Vengeance is on the wing, and Heaven in arms!'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.39.1#"Meantime Lampetie mounts the aerial way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.39.2#And kindles into rage the god of day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.40.1#"'Vengeance, ye powers (he cries), and then whose hand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.40.2#Aims the red bolt, and hurls the writhen brand!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.40.3#Slain are those herds which I with pride survey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.40.4#When through the ports of heaven I pour the day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.40.5#Or deep in ocean plunge the burning ray.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.40.6#Vengeance, ye gods! or I the skies forego,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.40.7#And bear the lamp of heaven to shades below.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.41.1#"To whom the thundering Power: 'O source of day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.41.2#Whose radiant lamp adorns the azure way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.41.3#Still may thy beams through heaven's bright portal rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.41.4#The joy of earth, the glory of the skies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.41.5#Lo! my red arm I bare, my thunders guide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.41.6#To dash the offenders in the whelming tide.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.42.1#"To fair Calypso, from the bright abodes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.42.2#Hermes convey'd these counsels of the gods.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.43.1#"Meantime from man to man my tongue exclaims,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.43.2#My wrath is kindled, and my soul in flames.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.43.3#In vain! I view perform'd the direful deed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.43.4#Beeves, slain in heaps, along the ocean bleed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.1#"Now heaven gave signs of wrath: along the ground
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.2#Crept the raw hides, and with a bellowing sound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.3#Roar'd the dead limbs; the burning entrails groan'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.4#Six guilty days my wretched mates employ
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.5#In impious feasting, and unhallowed joy;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.6#The seventh arose, and now the sire of gods
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.7#Rein'd the rough storms; and calm'd the tossing floods:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.8#With speed the bark we climb; the spacious sails.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.9#Loosed from the yards invite the impelling gales.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.10#Past sight of shore, along the surge we bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.11#And all above is sky, and ocean all around;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.12#When lo! a murky cloud the thunderer forms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.13#Full o'er our heads, and blackens heaven with storms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.14#Night dwells o'er all the deep: and now outflies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.15#The gloomy west, and whistles in the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.16#The mountain-billows roar! the furious blast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.17#Howls o'er the shroud, and rends it from the mast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.18#The mast gives way, and, crackling as it bends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.19#Tears up the deck; then all at once descends:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.20#The pilot by the tumbling ruin slain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.21#Dash'd from the helm, falls headlong in the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.22#Then Jove in anger bids his thunders roll,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.23#And forky lightnings flash from pole to pole:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.24#Fierce at our heads his deadly bolt he aims,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.25#Red with uncommon wrath, and wrapp'd in flames:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.26#Full on the bark it fell; now high, now low,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.27#Toss'd and retoss'd, it reel'd beneath the blow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.28#At once into the main the crew it shook:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.29#Sulphurous odours rose, and smouldering smoke.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.30#Like fowl that haunt the floods, they sink, they rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.31#Now lost, now seen, with shrieks and dreadful cries;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.32#And strive to gain the bark, but Jove denies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.33#Firm at the helm I stand, when fierce the main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.34#Rush'd with dire noise, and dash'd the sides in twain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.35#Again impetuous drove the furious blast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.36#Snapp'd the strong helm, and bore to sea the mast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.37#Firm to the mast with cords the helm I bind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.38#And ride aloft, to Providence resign'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.39#Through tumbling billows and a war of wind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.40#"Now sunk the west, and now a southern breeze,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.41#More dreadful than the tempest lash'd the seas;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.42#For on the rocks it bore where Scylla raves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.43#And dire Charybdis rolls her thundering waves.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.44#All night I drove; and at the dawn of day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.45#Fast by the rocks beheld the desperate way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.46#Just when the sea within her gulfs subsides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.47#And in the roaring whirlpools rush the tides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.48#Swift from the float I vaulted with a bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.49#The lofty fig-tree seized, and clung around;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.50#So to the beam the bat tenacious clings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.51#And pendent round it clasps his leather wings.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.52#High in the air the tree its boughs display'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.53#And o'er the dungeon cast a dreadful shade;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.54#All unsustain'd between the wave and sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.55#Beneath my feet the whirling billows fly.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.56#What time the judge forsakes the noisy bar
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.57#To take repast, and stills the wordy war,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.58#Charybdis, rumbling from her inmost caves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.59#The mast refunded on her refluent waves.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.60#Swift from the tree, the floating mass to gain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.61#Sudden I dropp'd amidst the flashing main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.62#Once more undaunted on the ruin rode,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.63#And oar'd with labouring arms along the flood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.64#Unseen I pass'd by Scylla's dire abodes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.65#So Jove decreed (dread sire of men and gods).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.66#Then nine long days I plow'd the calmer seas,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.67#Heaved by the surge, and wafted by the breeze.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.68#Weary and wet the Ogygian shores I gain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.69#When the tenth sun descended to the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.70#There, in Calypso's ever-fragrant bowers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.71#Refresh'd I lay, and joy beguiled the hours.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.72#"My following fates to thee, O king, are known,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.73#And the bright partner of thy royal throne.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.74#Enough: in misery can words avail?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:12.44.75#And what so tedious as a twice-told tale?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.1.1#He ceased; but left so pleasing on their ear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.1.2#His voice, that listening still they seem'd to hear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.1.3#A pause of silence hush'd the shady rooms:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.1.4#The grateful conference then the king resumes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.1#"Whatever toils the great Ulysses pass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.2#Beneath this happy roof they end at last;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.3#No longer now from shore to shore to roam,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.4#Smooth seas and gentle winds invite him home.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.5#But hear me, princes! whom these walls inclose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.6#For whom my chanter sings: and goblet flows
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.7#With wine unmix'd (an honour due to age,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.8#To cheer the grave, and warm the poet's rage);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.9#Though labour'd gold and many a dazzling vest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.10#Lie heap'd already for our godlike guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.11#Without new treasures let him not remove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.12#Large, and expressive of the public love:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.13#Each peer a tripod, each a vase bestow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.2.14#A general tribute, which the state shall owe."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.3.1#This sentence pleased: then all their steps address'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.3.2#To separate mansions, and retired to rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.1#Now did the rosy-finger'd morn arise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.2#And shed her sacred light along the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.3#Down to the haven and the ships in haste
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.4#They bore the treasures, and in safety placed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.5#The king himself the vases ranged with care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.6#Then bade his followers to the feast prepare.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.7#A victim ox beneath the sacred hand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.8#Of great Alcinous falls, and stains the sand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.9#To Jove the Eternal (power above all powers!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.10#Who wings the winds, and darkens heaven with showers)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.11#The flames ascend: till evening they prolong
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.12#The rites, more sacred made by heavenly song;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.13#For in the midst, with public honours graced,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.14#Thy lyre divine, Demodocus! was placed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.15#All, but Ulysses, heard with fix'd delight;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.16#He sate, and eyed the sun, and wish'd the night;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.17#Slow seem'd the sun to move, the hours to roll,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.18#His native home deep-imaged in his soul.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.19#As the tired ploughman, spent with stubborn toil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.20#Whose oxen long have torn the furrow'd soil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.21#Sees with delight the sun's declining ray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.22#When home with feeble knees he bends his way
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.23#To late repast (the day's hard labour done);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.24#So to Ulysses welcome set the sun;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.25#Then instant to Alcinous and the rest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.4.26#(The Scherian states) he turn'd, and thus address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.1#"O thou, the first in merit and command!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.2#And you the peers and princes of the land!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.3#May every joy be yours! nor this the least,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.4#When due libation shall have crown'd the feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.5#Safe to my home to send your happy guest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.6#Complete are now the bounties you have given,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.7#Be all those bounties but confirm'd by Heaven!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.8#So may I find, when all my wanderings cease,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.9#My consort blameless, and my friends in peace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.10#On you be every bliss; and every day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.11#In home-felt joys, delighted roll away;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.12#Yourselves, your wives, your long-descending race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.13#May every god enrich with every grace!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.14#Sure fix'd on virtue may your nation stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.5.15#And public evil never touch the land!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.6.1#His words well weigh'd, the general voice approved
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.6.2#Benign, and instant his dismission moved,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.6.3#The monarch to Pontonus gave the sign.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.6.4#To fill the goblet high with rosy wine;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.6.5#"Great Jove the Father first (he cried) implore;'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.6.6#Then send the stranger to his native shore."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.7.1#The luscious wine the obedient herald brought;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.7.2#Around the mansion flow'd the purple draught;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.7.3#Each from his seat to each immortal pours,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.7.4#Whom glory circles in the Olympian bowers
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.7.5#Ulysses sole with air majestic stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.7.6#The bowl presenting to Arete's hands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.7.7#Then thus: "O queen, farewell! be still possess'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.7.8#Of dear remembrance, blessing still and bless'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.7.9#Till age and death shall gently call thee hence,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.7.10#(Sure fate of every mortal excellence!)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.7.11#Farewell! and joys successive ever spring
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.7.12#To thee, to thine, the people, and the king!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.8.1#Thus he: then parting prints the sandy shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.8.2#To the fair port: a herald march'd before,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.8.3#Sent by Alcinous; of Arete's train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.8.4#Three chosen maids attend him to the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.8.5#This does a tunic and white vest convey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.8.6#A various casket that, of rich inlay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.8.7#And bread and wine the third. The cheerful mates
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.8.8#Safe in the hollow poop dispose the cates;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.8.9#Upon the deck soft painted robes they spread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.8.10#With linen cover'd, for the hero's bed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.8.11#He climbed the lofty stern; then gently press'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.8.12#The swelling couch, and lay composed to rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.9.1#Now placed in order, the Phaeacian train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.9.2#Their cables loose, and launch into the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.9.3#At once they bend, and strike their equal oars,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.9.4#And leave the sinking hills and lessening shores.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.9.5#While on the deck the chief in silence lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.9.6#And pleasing slumbers steal upon his eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.9.7#As fiery coursers in the rapid race
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.9.8#Urged by fierce drivers through the dusty space,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.9.9#Toss their high heads, and scour along the plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.9.10#So mounts the bounding vessel o'er the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.9.11#Back to the stern the parted billows flow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.9.12#And the black ocean foams and roars below.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.10.1#Thus with spread sails the winged galley flies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.10.2#Less swift an eagle cuts the liquid skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.10.3#Divine Ulysses was her sacred load,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.10.4#A man, in wisdom equal to a god!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.10.5#Much danger, long and mighty toils he bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.10.6#In storms by sea, and combats on the shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.10.7#All which soft sleep now banish'd from his breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.10.8#Wrapp'd in a pleasing, deep, and death-like rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.1#But when the morning-star with early ray
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.2#Flamed in the front of heaven, and promised day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.3#Like distant clouds the mariner descries
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.4#Fair Ithaca's emerging hills arise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.5#Far from the town a spacious port appears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.6#Sacred to Phorcys' power, whose name it bears;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.7#Two craggy rocks projecting to the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.8#The roaring wind's tempestuous rage restrain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.9#Within the waves in softer murmurs glide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.10#And ships secure without their halsers ride.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.11#High at the head a branching olive grows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.12#And crowns the pointed cliffs with shady boughs.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.13#Beneath, a gloomy grotto's cool recess
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.14#Delights the Nereids of the neighbouring seas,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.15#Where bowls and urns were form'd of living stone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.16#And massy beams in native marble shone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.17#On which the labours of the nymphs were roll'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.18#Their webs divine of purple mix'd with gold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.19#Within the cave the clustering bees attend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.20#Their waxen works, or from the roof depend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.21#Perpetual waters o'er the pavement glide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.22#Two marble doors unfold on either side;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.23#Sacred the south, by which the gods descend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.24#But mortals enter at the northern end.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.25#Thither they bent, and haul'd their ship to land
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.26#(The crooked keel divides the yellow sand).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.27#Ulysses sleeping on his couch they bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.28#And gently placed him on the rocky shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.29#His treasures next, Alcinous' gifts, they laid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.30#In the wild olive's unfrequented shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.31#Secure from theft; then launch'd the bark again,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.32#Resumed their oars, and measured back the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.33#Nor yet forgot old Ocean's dread supreme,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.34#The vengeance vow'd for eyeless Polypheme.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.35#Before the throne of mighty Jove lie stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.11.36#And sought the secret counsels of the god.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.1#"Shall then no more, O sire of gods! be mine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.2#The rights and honours of a power divine?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.3#Scorn'd e'en by man, and (oh severe disgrace!)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.4#By soft Phaeacians, my degenerate race!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.5#Against yon destined head in vain I swore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.6#And menaced vengeance, ere he reach'd his shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.7#To reach his natal shore was thy decree;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.8#Mild I obey'd, for who shall war with thee?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.9#Behold him landed, careless and asleep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.10#From all the eluded dangers of the deep;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.11#Lo where he lies, amidst a shining store
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.12#Of brass, rich garments, and refulgent ore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.13#And bears triumphant to his native isle
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.12.14#A prize more worth than Ilion's noble spoil."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.13.1#To whom the Father of the immortal powers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.13.2#Who swells the clouds, and gladdens earth with showers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.13.3#"Can mighty Neptune thus of man complain?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.13.4#Neptune, tremendous o'er the boundless main!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.13.5#Revered and awful e'en in heaven's abodes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.13.6#Ancient and great! a god above the gods!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.13.7#If that low race offend thy power divine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.13.8#(Weak, daring creatures!) is not vengeance thine?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.13.9#Go, then, the guilty at thy will chastise."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.13.10#He said. The shaker of the earth replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.14.1#"This then, I doom: to fix the gallant ship,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.14.2#A mark of vengeance on the sable deep;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.14.3#To warn the thoughtless, self-confiding train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.14.4#No more unlicensed thus to brave the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.14.5#Full in their port a Shady hill shall rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.14.6#If such thy will."--" We will it (Jove replies).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.14.7#E'en when with transport blackening all the strand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.14.8#The swarming people hail their ship to land,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.14.9#Fix her for ever, a memorial stone:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.14.10#Still let her seem to sail, and seem alone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.14.11#The trembling crowds shall see the sudden shade
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.14.12#Of whelming mountains overhang their head!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.15.1#With that the god whose earthquakes rock the ground
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.15.2#Fierce to Phaeacia cross'd the vast profound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.15.3#Swift as a swallow sweeps the liquid way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.15.4#The winged pinnace shot along the sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.15.5#The god arrests her with a sudden stroke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.15.6#And roots her down an everlasting rock.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.15.7#Aghast the Scherians stand in deep surprise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.15.8#All press to speak, all question with their eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.15.9#What hands unseen the rapid bark restrain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.15.10#And yet it swims, or seems to swim, the main!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.15.11#Thus they, unconscious of the deed divine;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.15.12#Till great Alcinous, rising, own'd the sign.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.16.1#"Behold the long predestined day I (he cries;)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.16.2#O certain faith of ancient prophecies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.16.3#These ears have heard my royal sire disclose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.16.4#A dreadful story, big with future woes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.16.5#How, moved with wrath, that careless we convey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.16.6#Promiscuous every guest to every bay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.16.7#Stern Neptune raged; and how by his command
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.16.8#Firm rooted in the surge a ship should stand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.16.9#(A monument of wrath); and mound on mound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.16.10#Should hide our walls, or whelm beneath the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.17.1#"The Fates have follow'd as declared the seer.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.17.2#Be humbled, nations! and your monarch hear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.17.3#No more unlicensed brave the deeps, no more
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.17.4#With every stranger pass from shore to shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.17.5#On angry Neptune now for mercy call;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.17.6#To his high name let twelve black oxen fall.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.17.7#So may the god reverse his purposed will,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.17.8#Nor o'er our city hang the dreadful hill."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.18.1#The monarch spoke: they trembled and obey'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.18.2#Forth on the sands the victim oxen led;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.18.3#The gathered tribes before the altars stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.18.4#And chiefs and rulers, a majestic band.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.18.5#The king of ocean all the tribes implore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.18.6#The blazing altars redden all the shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.19.1#Meanwhile Ulysses in his country lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.19.2#Released from sleep, and round him might survey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.19.3#The solitary shore and rolling sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.19.4#Yet had his mind through tedious absence lost
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.19.5#The dear resemblance of his native coast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.19.6#Besides, Minerva, to secure her care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.19.7#Diffused around a veil of thickened air;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.19.8#For so the gods ordain'd to keep unseen
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.19.9#His royal person from his friends and queen;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.19.10#Till the proud suitors for their crimes afford
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.19.11#An ample vengeance to their injured lord.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.20.1#Now all the land another prospect bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.20.2#Another port appear'd, another shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.20.3#And long-continued ways, and winding floods,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.20.4#And unknown mountains, crown'd with unknown woods
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.20.5#Pensive and slow, with sudden grief oppress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.20.6#The king arose, and beat his careful breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.20.7#Cast a long look o'er all the coast and main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.20.8#And sought, around, his native realm in vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.20.9#Then with erected eyes stood fix'd in woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.20.10#And as he spoke, the tears began to flow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.1#"Ye gods (he cried), upon what barren coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.2#In what new region, is Ulysses toss'd?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.3#Possess'd by wild barbarians, fierce in arms?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.4#Or men whose bosom tender pity warms?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.5#Where shall this treasure now in safely be?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.6#And whither, whither its sad owner fly?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.7#Ah, why did I Alcinous' grace implore?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.8#Ah, why forsake Phaeacia's happy shore?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.9#Some juster prince perhaps had entertain'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.10#And safe restored me to my native land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.11#Is this the promised, long-expected coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.12#And this the faith Phaeacia's rulers boast?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.13#O righteous gods! of all the great, how few
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.14#Are just to Heaven, and to their promise true!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.15#But he, the power to whose all-seeing eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.16#The deeds of men appear without disguise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.17#'Tis his alone to avenge the wrongs I bear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.18#For still the oppress'd are his peculiar care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.19#To count these presents, and from thence to prove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.21.20#Their faith is mine; the rest belongs to Jove."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.1#Then on the sands he ranged his wealthy store,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.2#The gold, the vests, the tripods number'd o'er:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.3#All these he found, but still in error lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.4#Disconsolate he wanders on the coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.5#Sighs for his country, and laments again
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.6#To the deaf rocks, and hoarse-resounding main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.7#When lo! the guardian goddess of the wise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.8#Celestial Pallas, stood before his eyes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.9#In show a youthful swain, of form divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.10#Who seem'd descended from some princely line.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.11#A graceful robe her slender body dress'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.12#Around her shoulders flew the waving vest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.13#Her decent hand a shining javelin bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.14#And painted sandals on her feet she wore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.15#To whom the king: "Whoe'er of human race
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.16#Thou art, that wanderest in this desert place,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.17#With joy to thee, as to some god I bend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.18#To thee my treasures and myself commend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.19#O tell a wretch in exile doom'd to stray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.20#What air I breathe, what country I survey?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.21#The fruitful continent's extremest bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.22.22#Or some fair isle which Neptune's arms surround?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.1#"From what far clime (said she) remote from fame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.2#Arrivest thou here, a stranger to our name?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.3#Thou seest an island, not to those unknown
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.4#Whose hills are brighten'd by the rising sun,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.5#Nor those that placed beneath his utmost reign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.6#Behold him sinking in the western main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.7#The rugged soil allows no level space
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.8#For flying chariots, or the rapid race;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.9#Yet, not ungrateful to the peasant's pain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.10#Suffices fulness to the swelling grain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.11#The loaded trees their various fruits produce,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.12#And clustering grapes afford a generous juice;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.13#Woods crown our mountains, and in every grove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.14#The bounding goats and frisking heifers rove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.15#Soft rains and kindly dews refresh the field,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.16#And rising springs eternal verdure yield.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.17#E'en to those shores is Ithaca renown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.23.18#Where Troy's majestic ruins strew the ground."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.24.1#At this, the chief with transport was possess'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.24.2#His panting heart exulted in his breast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.24.3#Yet, well dissembling his untimely joys,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.24.4#And veiling truth in plausible disguise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.24.5#Thus, with an air sincere, in fiction bold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.24.6#His ready tale the inventive hero told:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.1#"Oft have I heard in Crete this island's name;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.2#For 'twas from Crete, my native soil, I came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.3#Self-banished thence.  I sail'd before the wind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.4#And left my children and my friends behind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.5#From fierce Idomeneus' revenge I flew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.6#Whose son, the swift Orsilochus, I slew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.7#(With brutal force he seized my Trojan prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.8#Due to the toils of many a bloody day).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.9#Unseen I 'scaped, and favour'd by the night,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.10#In a Phoenician vessel took my flight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.11#For Pyle or Elis bound; but tempests toss'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.12#And raging billows drove us on your coast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.13#In dead of night an unknown port we gain'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.14#Spent with fatigue, and slept secure on land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.15#But ere the rosy morn renew'd the day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.16#While in the embrace of pleasing sleep I lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.17#Sudden, invited by auspicious gales,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.18#They land my goods, and hoist their flying sails.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.19#Abandon'd here, my fortune I deplore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.25.20#A hapless exile on a foreign shore,"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.26.1#Thus while he spoke, the blue-eyed maid began
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.26.2#With pleasing smiles to view the godlike man;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.26.3#Then changed her form: and now, divinely bright,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.26.4#Jove's heavenly daughter stood confess'd to sight;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.26.5#Like a fair virgin in her beauty's bloom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.26.6#Skill'd in the illustrious labours of the loom.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.1#"O still the same Ulysses! (she rejoin'd,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.2#In useful craft successfully refined!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.3#Artful in speech, in action, and in mind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.4#Sufficed it not, that, thy long labours pass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.5#Secure thou seest thy native shore at last?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.6#But this to me? who, like thyself, excel
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.7#In arts of counsel and dissembling well;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.8#To me? whose wit exceeds the powers divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.9#No less than mortals are surpass'd by thine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.10#Know'st thou not me; who made thy life my care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.11#Through ten years' wandering, and through ten years' war;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.12#Who taught thee arts, Alcinous to persuade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.13#To raise his wonder, and engage his aid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.14#And now appear, thy treasures to protect,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.15#Conceal thy person, thy designs direct,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.16#And tell what more thou must from Fate expect;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.17#Domestic woes far heavier to be borne!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.18#The pride of fools, and slaves' insulting scorn?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.19#But thou be silent, nor reveal thy state;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.20#Yield to the force of unresisted Fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.21#And bear unmoved the wrongs of base mankind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.27.22#The last, and hardest, conquest of the mind."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.1#"Goddess of wisdom! (Ithacus replies,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.2#He who discerns thee must be truly wise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.3#So seldom view'd and ever in disguise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.4#When the bold Argives led their warring powers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.5#Against proud Ilion's well-defended towers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.6#Ulysses was thy care, celestial maid!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.7#Graced with thy sight, and favoured with thy aid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.8#But when the Trojan piles in ashes lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.9#And bound for Greece we plough'd the watery way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.10#Our fleet dispersed, and driven from coast to coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.11#Thy sacred presence from that hour I lost;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.12#Till I beheld thy radiant form once more,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.13#And heard thy counsels on Phaeacia's shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.14#But, by the almighty author of thy race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.15#Tell me, oh tell, is this my native place?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.16#For much I fear, long tracts of land and sea
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.17#Divide this coast from distant Ithaca;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.18#The sweet delusion kindly you impose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.28.19#To soothe my hopes, and mitigate my woes."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.1#Thus he. The blue-eyed goddess thus replies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.2#"How prone to doubt, how cautious are the wise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.3#Who, versed in fortune, fear the flattering show,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.4#And taste not half the bliss the gods bestow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.5#The more shall Pallas aid thy just desires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.6#And guard the wisdom which herself inspires.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.7#Others long absent from their native place,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.8#Straight seek their home, and fly with eager pace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.9#To their wives' arms, and children's dear embrace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.10#Not thus Ulysses; he decrees to prove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.11#His subjects' faith, and queen's suspected love;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.12#Who mourn'd her lord twice ten revolving years,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.13#And wastes the days in grief, the nights in tears.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.14#But Pallas knew (thy friends and navy lost)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.15#Once more 'twas given thee to behold thy coast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.16#Yet how could I with adverse Fate engage,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.17#And mighty Neptune's unrelenting rage?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.18#Now lift thy longing eyes, while I restore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.19#The pleasing prospect of thy native shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.20#Bebold the port of Phorcys! fenced around
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.21#With rocky mountains, and with olives crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.22#Behold the gloomy grot! whose cool recess
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.23#Delights the Nereids of the neighbouring seas;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.24#Whose now-neglected altars in thy reign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.25#Blush'd with the blood of sheep and oxen slain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.26#Behold! where Neritus the clouds divides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.29.27#And shakes the waving forests on his sides."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.30.1#So spake the goddess; and the prospect clear'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.30.2#The mists dispersed, and all the coast appeared.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.30.3#The king with joy confess'd his place of birth,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.30.4#And on his knees salutes his mother earth;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.30.5#Then, with his suppliant hands upheld in air,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.30.6#Thus to the sea-green sisters sends his prayer;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.31.1#"All hail! ye virgin daughters of the main!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.31.2#Ye streams, beyond my hopes, beheld again!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.31.3#To you once more your own Ulysses bows;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.31.4#Attend his transports, and receive his vows!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.31.5#If Jove prolong my days, and Pallas crown
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.31.6#The growing virtues of my youthful son,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.31.7#To you shall rites divine be ever paid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.31.8#And grateful offerings on your altars laid."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.32.1#Thus then Minerva: "From that anxious breast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.32.2#Dismiss those cares, and leave to heaven the rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.32.3#Our task be now thy treasured stores to save,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.32.4#Deep in the close recesses of the cave;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.32.5#Then future means consult." She spoke, and trod
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.32.6#The shady grot, that brighten'd with the god.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.32.7#The closest caverns of the grot she sought;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.32.8#The gold, the brass, the robes, Ulysses brought;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.32.9#These in the secret gloom the chief disposed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.32.10#The entrance with a rock the goddess closed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.33.1#Now, seated in the olive's sacred shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.33.2#Confer the hero and the martial maid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.33.3#The goddess of the azure eyes began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.33.4#"Son of Laertes! much-experienced man!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.33.5#The suitor-train thy earliest care demand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.33.6#Of that luxurious race to rid the land;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.33.7#Three years thy house their lawless rule has seen,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.33.8#And proud addresses to the matchless queen.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.33.9#But she thy absence mourns from day to day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.33.10#And inly bleeds, and silent wastes away;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.33.11#Elusive of the bridal hour, she gives
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.33.12#Fond hopes to all, and all with hopes deceives."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.34.1#To this Ulysses: "O celestial maid!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.34.2#Praised be thy counsel, and thy timely aid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.34.3#Else had I seen my native walls in vain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.34.4#Like great Atrides, just restored and slain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.34.5#Vouchsafe the means of vengeance to debate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.34.6#And plan with all thy arts the scene of fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.34.7#Then, then be present, and my soul inspire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.34.8#As when we wrapp'd Troy's heaven-built walls in fire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.34.9#Though leagued against me hundred heroes stand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.34.10#Hundreds shall fall, if Pallas aid my hand."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.1#She answer'd: "In the dreadful day of fight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.2#Know, I am with thee, strong in all my might.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.3#If thou but equal to thyself be found,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.4#What gasping numbers then shall press the ground!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.5#What human victims stain the feastful floor!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.6#How wide the pavements float with guilty gore!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.7#It fits thee now to wear a dark disguise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.8#And secret walk unknown to mortal eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.9#For this, my hand shall wither every grace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.10#And every elegance of form and face;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.11#O'er thy smooth skin a bark of wrinkles spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.12#Turn hoar the auburn honours of thy head;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.13#Disfigure every limb with coarse attire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.14#And in thy eyes extinguish all the fire;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.15#Add all the wants and the decays of life;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.16#Estrange thee from thy own; thy son, thy wife;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.17#From the loathed object every sight shall turn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.35.18#And the blind suitors their destruction scorn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.1#"Go first the master of thy herds to find,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.2#True to his charge, a loyal swain and kind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.3#For thee he sighs; and to the loyal heir
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.4#And chaste Penelope extends his care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.5#At the Coracian rock he now resides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.6#Where Arethusa's sable water glides;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.7#The sable water and the copious mast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.8#Swell the fat herd; luxuriant, large repast!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.9#With him rest peaceful in the rural cell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.10#And all you ask his faithful tongue shall tell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.11#Me into other realms my cares convey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.12#To Sparta, still with female beauty gay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.13#For know, to Sparta thy loved offspring came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.36.14#To learn thy fortunes from the voice of Fame."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.37.1#At this the father, with a father's care:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.37.2#"Must he too suffer? he, O goddess! bear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.37.3#Of wanderings and of woes a wretched share?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.37.4#Through the wild ocean plough the dangerous way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.37.5#And leave his fortunes and his house a prey?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.37.6#Why would'st not thou, O all-enlighten'd mind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.37.7#Inform him certain, and protect him, kind?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.38.1#To whom Minerva: "Be thy soul at rest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.38.2#And know, whatever heaven ordains is best.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.38.3#To fame I sent him, to acquire renown;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.38.4#To other regions is his virtue known;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.38.5#Secure he sits, near great Atrides placed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.38.6#With friendships strengthen'd, and with honours graced,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.38.7#But lo! an ambush waits his passage o'er;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.38.8#Fierce foes insidious intercept the shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.38.9#In vain; far sooner all the murderous brood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.38.10#This injured land shall fatten with their blood."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.1#She spake, then touch'd him with her powerful wand:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.2#The skin shrunk up, and wither'd at her hand;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.3#A swift old age o'er all his members spread;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.4#A sudden frost was sprinkled on his head;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.5#Nor longer in the heavy eye-ball shined
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.6#The glance divine, forth-beaming from the mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.7#His robe, which spots indelible besmear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.8#In rags dishonest flutters with the air:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.9#A stag's torn hide is lapp'd around his reins;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.10#A rugged staff his trembling hand sustains;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.11#And at his side a wretched scrip was hung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.12#Wide-patch'd, and knotted to a twisted thong.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.13#So looked the chief, so moved: to mortal eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.14#Object uncouth! a man of miseries!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.15#While Pallas, cleaving the wild fields of air,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:13.39.16#To Sparta flies, Telemachus her care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.1#But he, deep-musing, o'er the mountains stray'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.2#Through mazy thickets of the woodland shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.3#And cavern'd ways, the shaggy coast along
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.4#With cliffs and nodding forests overhung.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.5#Eumaeus at his sylvan lodge he sought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.6#A faithful servant, and without a fault.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.7#Ulysses found him busied as he sate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.8#Before the threshold of his rustic gate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.9#Around the mansion in a circle shone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.10#A rural portico of rugged stone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.11#(In absence of his lord with honest toil
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.12#His own industrious hands had raised the pile).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.13#The wall was stone from neighbouring quarries borne,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.14#Encircled with a fence of native thorn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.15#And strong with pales, by many a weary stroke
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.16#Of stubborn labour hewn from heart of oak:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.17#Frequent and thick. Within the space were rear'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.18#Twelve ample cells, the lodgments of his herd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.19#Full fifty pregnant females each contain'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.20#The males without (a smaller race) remain'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.21#Doom'd to supply the suitors' wasteful feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.22#A stock by daily luxury decreased;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.23#Now scarce four hundred left. These to defend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.24#Four savage dogs, a watchful guard, attend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.25#Here sat Eumaeus, and his cares applied
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.26#To form strong buskins of well-season'd hide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.27#Of four assistants who his labour share,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.28#Three now were absent on the rural care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.29#The fourth drove victims to a suitor train:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.30#But he, of ancient faith, a simple swain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.31#Sigh'd, while he furnish'd the luxurious board,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.1.32#And wearied Heaven with wishes for his lord.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.2.1#Soon as Ulysses near the inclosure drew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.2.2#With open mouths the furious mastiffs flew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.2.3#Down sat the sage, and cautious to withstand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.2.4#Let fall the offensive truncheon from his hand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.2.5#Sudden, the master runs; aloud he calls;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.2.6#And from his hasty hand the leather falls:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.2.7#With showers of stones he drives then far away:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.2.8#The scattering dogs around at distance bay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.3.1#"Unhappy stranger! (thus the faithful swain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.3.2#Began with accent gracious and humane),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.3.3#What sorrow had been mine, if at my gate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.3.4#Thy reverend age had met a shameful fate!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.3.5#Enough of woes already have I known;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.3.6#Enough my master's sorrows and my own.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.3.7#While here (ungrateful task!) his herds I feed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.3.8#Ordain'd for lawless rioters to bleed!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.3.9#Perhaps, supported at another's board!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.3.10#Far from his country roams my hapless lord;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.3.11#Or sigh'd in exile forth his latest breath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.3.12#Now cover'd with the eternal shade of death!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.4.1#"But enter this my homely roof, and see
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.4.2#Our woods not void of hospitality.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.4.3#Then tell me whence thou art, and what the share
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.4.4#Of woes and wanderings thou wert born to bear."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.5.1#He said, and, seconding the kind request,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.5.2#With friendly step precedes his unknown guest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.5.3#A shaggy goat's soft hide beneath him spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.5.4#And with fresh rushes heap'd an ample bed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.5.5#Jove touch'd the hero's tender soul, to find
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.5.6#So just reception from a heart so kind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.5.7#And "Oh, ye gods! with all your blessings grace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.5.8#(He thus broke forth) this friend of human race!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.1#The swain replied: "It never was our guise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.2#To slight the poor, or aught humane despise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.3#For Jove unfold our hospitable door,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.4#'Tis Jove that sends the stranger and the poor,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.5#Little, alas! is all the good I can
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.6#A man oppress'd, dependent, yet a man:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.7#Accept such treatment as a swain affords,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.8#Slave to the insolence of youthful lords!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.9#Far hence is by unequal gods removed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.10#That man of bounties, loving and beloved!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.11#To whom whate'er his slave enjoys is owed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.12#And more, had Fate allow'd, had been bestow'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.13#But Fate condemn'd him to a foreign shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.14#Much have I sorrow'd, but my Master more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.15#Now cold he lies, to death's embrace resign'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.16#Ah, perish Helen! perish all her kind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.17#For whose cursed cause, in Agamemnon's name,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.6.18#He trod so fatally the paths of fame."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.1#His vest succinct then girding round his waist,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.2#Forth rush'd the swain with hospitable haste.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.3#Straight to the lodgments of his herd he run,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.4#Where the fat porkers slept beneath the sun;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.5#Of two, his cutlass launch'd the spouting blood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.6#These quarter'd, singed, and fix'd on forks of wood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.7#All hasty on the hissing coals he threw;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.8#And smoking, back the tasteful viands drew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.9#Broachers and all then an the board display'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.10#The ready meal, before Ulysses laid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.11#With flour imbrown'd; next mingled wine yet new,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.12#And luscious as the bees' nectareous dew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.13#Then sate, companion of the friendly feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.14#With open look; and thus bespoke his guest:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.15#"Take with free welcome what our hands prepare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.16#Such food as falls to simple servants' share;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.17#The best our lords consume; those thoughtless peers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.18#Rich without bounty, guilty without fears;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.19#Yet sure the gods their impious acts detest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.20#And honour justice and the righteous breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.21#Pirates and conquerors of harden'd mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.22#The foes of peace, and scourges of mankind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.23#To whom offending men are made a prey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.24#When Jove in vengeance gives a land away;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.25#E'en these, when of their ill-got spoils possess'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.26#Find sure tormentors in the guilty breast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.27#Some voice of God close whispering from within,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.28#'Wretch! this is villainy, and this is sin.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.29#But these, no doubt, some oracle explore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.30#That tells, the great Ulysses is no more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.31#Hence springs their confidence, and from our sighs
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.32#Their rapine strengthens, and their riots rise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.33#Constant as Jove the night and day bestows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.34#Bleeds a whole hecatomb, a vintage flows.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.35#None match'd this hero's wealth, of all who reign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.36#O'er the fair islands of the neighbouring main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.37#Nor all the monarchs whose far-dreaded sway
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.38#The wide-extended continents obey:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.39#First, on the main land, of Ulysses' breed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.40#Twelve herds, twelve flocks, on ocean's margin feed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.41#As many stalls for shaggy goats are rear'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.42#As many lodgments for the tusky herd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.43#Two foreign keepers guard: and here are seen
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.44#Twelve herds of goats that graze our utmost green;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.45#To native pastors is their charge assign'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.46#And mine the care to feed the bristly kind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.47#Each day the fattest bleeds of either herd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.48#All to the suitors' wasteful board preferr'd."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.49#Thus he, benevolent: his unknown guest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.50#With hunger keen devours the savoury feast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.51#While schemes of vengeance ripen in his breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.52#Silent and thoughtful while the board he eyed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.53#Eumaeus pours on high the purple tide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.54#The king with smiling looks his joy express'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.7.55#And thus the kind inviting host address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.8.1#"Say now, what man is he, the man deplored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.8.2#So rich, so potent, whom you style your lord?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.8.3#Late with such affluence and possessions bless'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.8.4#And now in honour's glorious bed at rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.8.5#Whoever was the warrior, he must be
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.8.6#To fame no stranger, nor perhaps to me:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.8.7#Who (so the gods and so the Fates ordain'd)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.8.8#Have wander'd many a sea, and many a land."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.1#"Small is the faith the prince and queen ascribe
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.2#(Replied Eumaeus) to the wandering tribe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.3#For needy strangers still to flattery fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.4#And want too oft betrays the tongue to lie.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.5#Each vagrant traveller, that touches here,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.6#Deludes with fallacies the royal ear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.7#To dear remembrance makes his image rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.8#And calls the springing sorrows from her eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.9#Such thou mayst be. But he whose name you crave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.10#Moulders in earth, or welters on the wave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.11#Or food for fish or dogs his relics lie,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.12#Or torn by birds are scatter'd through the sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.13#So perish'd he: and left (for ever lost)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.14#Much woe to all, but sure to me the most.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.15#So mild a master never shall I find;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.16#Less dear the parents whom I left behind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.17#Less soft my mother, less my father kind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.18#Not with such transport would my eyes run o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.19#Again to hail them in their native shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.20#As loved Ulysses once more to embrace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.21#Restored and breathing in his natal place.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.22#That name for ever dread, yet ever dear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.23#E'en in his absence I pronounce with fear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.24#In my respect, he bears a prince's part;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.9.25#But lives a very brother in my heart."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.10.1#Thus spoke the faithful swain, and thus rejoin'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.10.2#The master of his grief, the man of patient mind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.10.3#"Ulysses, friend! shall view his old abodes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.10.4#(Distrustful as thou art), nor doubt the gods.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.10.5#Nor speak I rashly, but with faith averr'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.10.6#And what I speak attesting Heaven has heard.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.10.7#If so, a cloak and vesture be my meed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.10.8#Till his return no title shall I plead,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.10.9#Though certain be my news, and great my need.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.10.10#Whom want itself can force untruths to tell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.10.11#My soul detests him as the gates of hell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.11.1#"Thou first be witness, hospitable Jove!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.11.2#And every god inspiring social love!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.11.3#And witness every household power that waits,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.11.4#Guard of these fires, and angel of these gates!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.11.5#Ere the next moon increase or this decay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.11.6#His ancient realms Ulysses shall survey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.11.7#In blood and dust each proud oppressor mourn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.11.8#And the lost glories of his house return."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.1#"Nor shall that meed be thine, nor ever more
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.2#Shall loved Ulysses hail this happy shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.3#(Replied Eumaeus): to the present hour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.4#Now turn thy thought, and joys within our power.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.5#From sad reflection let my soul repose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.6#The name of him awakes a thousand woes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.7#But guard him, gods! and to these arms restore!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.8#Not his true consort can desire him more;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.9#Not old Laertes, broken with despair:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.10#Not young Telemachus, his blooming heir.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.11#Alas, Telemachus! my sorrows flow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.12#Afresh for thee, my second cause of woe!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.13#Like some fair plant set by a heavenly hand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.14#He grew, he flourish'd, and he bless'd the land;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.15#In all the youth his father's image shined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.16#Bright in his person, brighter in his mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.17#What man, or god, deceived his better sense,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.18#Far on the swelling seas to wander hence?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.19#To distant Pylos hapless is he gone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.20#To seek his father's fate and find his own!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.21#For traitors wait his way, with dire design
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.22#To end at once the great Arcesian line.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.23#But let us leave him to their wills above;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.24#The fates of men are in the hand of Jove.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.25#And now, my venerable guest! declare
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.26#Your name, your parents, and your native air:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.27#Sincere from whence begun, your course relate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.12.28#And to what ship I owe the friendly freight?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.13.1#Thus he: and thus (with prompt invention bold)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.13.2#The cautious chief his ready story told.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.1#"On dark reserve what better can prevail,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.2#Or from the fluent tongue produce the tale,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.3#Than when two friends, alone, in peaceful place
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.4#Confer, and wines and cates the table grace;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.5#But most, the kind inviter's cheerful face?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.6#Thus might we sit, with social goblets crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.7#Till the whole circle of the year goes round:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.8#Not the whole circle of the year would close
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.9#My long narration of a life of woes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.10#But such was Heaven's high will! Know then, I came
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.11#From sacred Crete, and from a sire of fame:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.12#Castor Hylacides (that name he bore),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.13#Beloved and honour'd in his native shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.14#Bless'd in his riches, in his children more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.15#Sprung of a handmaid, from a bought embrace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.16#I shared his kindness with his lawful race:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.17#But when that fate, which all must undergo,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.18#From earth removed him to the shades below,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.19#The large domain his greedy sons divide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.20#And each was portion'd as the lots decide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.21#Little, alas! was left my wretched share,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.22#Except a house, a covert from the air:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.23#But what by niggard fortune was denied,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.24#A willing widow's copious wealth supplied.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.25#My valour was my plea, a gallant mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.26#That, true to honour, never lagg'd behind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.27#(The sex is ever to a soldier kind).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.28#Now wasting years my former strength confound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.29#And added woes have bow'd me to the ground;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.30#Yet by the stubble you may guess the grain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.31#And mark the ruins of no vulgar man.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.32#Me, Pallas gave to lead the martial storm,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.33#And the fair ranks of battle to deform;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.34#Me, Mars inspired to turn the foe to flight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.35#And tempt the secret ambush of the night.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.36#Let ghastly Death in all his forms appear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.37#I saw him not, it was not mine to fear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.38#Before the rest I raised my ready steel,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.39#The first I met, he yielded, or he fell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.40#But works of peace my soul disdain'd to bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.41#The rural labour, or domestic care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.42#To raise the mast, the missile dart to wing,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.43#And send swift arrows from the bounding string,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.44#Were arts the gods made grateful to my mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.45#Those gods, who turn (to various ends design'd)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.46#The various thoughts and talents of mankind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.47#Before the Grecians touch'd the Trojan plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.48#Nine times commander or by land or main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.49#In foreign fields I spread my glory far,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.50#Great in the praise, rich in the spoils of war;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.51#Thence charged with riches, as increased in fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.52#To Crete return'd, an honourable name.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.53#But when great Jove that direful war decreed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.54#Which roused all Greece, and made the mighty bleed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.55#Our states myself and Idomen employ
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.56#To lead their fleets, and carry death to Troy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.57#Nine years we warr'd; the tenth saw Ilion fall;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.58#Homeward we sail'd, but heaven dispersed us all.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.59#One only month my wife enjoy'd my stay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.60#So will'd the god who gives and takes away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.61#Nine ships I mann'd, equipp'd with ready stores,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.62#Intent to voyage to the Aegyptian shores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.63#In feast and sacrifice my chosen train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.64#Six days consum'd; the seventh we plough'd the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.65#Crete's ample fields diminish to our eye;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.66#Before the Boreal blast the vessels fly;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.67#Safe through the level seas we sweep our way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.68#The steersman governs, and the ships obey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.69#The fifth fair morn we stem the Aegyptian tide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.70#And tilting o'er the bay the vessels ride:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.71#To anchor there my fellows I command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.72#And spies commission to explore the land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.73#But, sway'd by lust of gain, and headlong will,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.74#The coasts they ravage, and the natives kill.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.75#The spreading clamour to their city flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.76#And horse and foot in mingled tumult rise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.77#The reddening dawn reveals the circling fields,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.78#Horrid with bristly spears, and glancing shields.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.79#Jove thunder'd on their side. Our guilty head
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.80#We turn'd to flight; the gathering vengeance spread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.81#On all parts round, and heaps on heaps lie dead.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.82#I then explored my thought, what course to prove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.83#(And sure the thought was dictated by Jove):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.84#Oh, had he left me to that happier doom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.85#And saved a life of miseries to come!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.86#The radiant helmet from my brows unlaced,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.87#And low on earth my shield and javelin cast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.88#I meet the monarch with a suppliant's face,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.89#Approach his chariot, and his knees embrace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.90#He heard, he saved, he placed me at his side;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.91#My state he pitied, and my tears he dried,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.92#Restrain'd the rage the vengeful foe express'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.93#And turn'd the deadly weapons from my breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.94#Pious! to guard the hospitable rite,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.14.95#And fearing Jove, whom mercy's works delight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.1#"In Aegypt thus with peace and plenty bless'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.2#I lived (and happy still have lived) a guest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.3#On seven bright years successive blessings wait;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.4#The next changed all the colour of my fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.5#A false Phoenician, of insiduous mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.6#Versed in vile arts, and foe to humankind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.7#With semblance fair invites me to his home;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.8#I seized the proffer (ever fond to roam):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.9#Domestic in his faithless roof I stay'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.10#Till the swift sun his annual circle made.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.11#To Libya then he mediates the way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.12#With guileful art a stranger to betray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.13#And sell to bondage in a foreign land:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.14#Much doubting, yet compell'd I quit the strand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.15#Through the mid seas the nimble pinnace sails,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.16#Aloof from Crete, before the northern gales:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.17#But when remote her chalky cliffs we lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.18#And far from ken of any other coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.19#When all was wild expanse of sea and air,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.20#Then doom'd high Jove due vengeance to prepare.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.21#He hung a night of horrors o'er their head
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.22#(The shaded ocean blacken'd as it spread):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.23#He launch'd the fiery bolt: from pole to pole
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.24#Broad burst the lightnings, deep the thunders roll;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.25#In giddy rounds the whirling ship is toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.26#An all in clouds of smothering sulphur lost.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.27#As from a hanging rock's tremendous height,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.28#The sable crows with intercepted flight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.29#Drop endlong; scarr'd, and black with sulphurous hue,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.30#So from the deck are hurl'd the ghastly crew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.31#Such end the wicked found! but Jove's intent
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.32#Was yet to save the oppress'd and innocent.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.33#Placed on the mast (the last resource of life)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.34#With winds and waves I held unequal strife:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.35#For nine long days the billows tilting o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.36#The tenth soft wafts me to Thesprotia's shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.37#The monarch's son a shipwreck'd wretch relieved,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.38#The sire with hospitable rites received,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.39#And in his palace like a brother placed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.40#With gifts of price and gorgeous garments graced
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.41#While here I sojourn'd, oft I heard the fame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.42#How late Ulysses to the country came.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.43#How loved, how honour'd in this court he stay'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.44#And here his whole collected treasure laid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.45#I saw myself the vast unnumber'd store
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.46#Of steel elaborate, and refulgent ore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.47#And brass high heap'd amidst the regal dome;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.48#Immense supplies for ages yet to come!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.49#Meantime he voyaged to explore the will
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.50#Of Jove, on high Dodona's holy hill,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.51#What means might best his safe return avail,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.52#To come in pomp, or bear a secret sail?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.53#Full oft has Phidon, whilst he pour'd the wine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.54#Attesting solemn all the powers divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.55#That soon Ulysses would return, declared
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.56#The sailors waiting, and the ships prepared.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.57#But first the king dismiss'd me from his shores,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.58#For fair Dulichium crown'd with fruitful stores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.59#To good Acastus' friendly care consign'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.60#But other counsels pleased the sailors' mind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.61#New frauds were plotted by the faithless train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.62#And misery demands me once again.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.63#Soon as remote from shore they plough the wave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.64#With ready hands they rush to seize their slave;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.65#Then with these tatter'd rags they wrapp'd me round
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.66#(Stripp'd of my own), and to the vessel bound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.67#At eve, at Ithaca's delightful land
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.68#The ship arriv'd: forth issuing on the sand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.69#They sought repast; while to the unhappy kind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.70#The pitying gods themselves my chains unbind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.71#Soft I descended, to the sea applied
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.72#My naked breast, and shot along the tide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.73#Soon pass'd beyond their sight, I left the flood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.74#And took the spreading shelter of the wood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.75#Their prize escaped the faithless pirates mourn'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.76#But deem'd inquiry vain, and to their ships return'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.77#Screen'd by protecting gods from hostile eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.78#They led me to a good man and a wise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.79#To live beneath thy hospitable care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.15.80#And wait the woes Heaven dooms me yet to bear."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.1#"Unhappy guest! whose sorrows touch my mind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.2#(Thus good Eumaeus with a sigh rejoin'd,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.3#For real sufferings since I grieve sincere,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.4#Check not with fallacies the springing tear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.5#Nor turn the passion into groundless joy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.6#For him whom Heaven has destined to destroy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.7#Oh! had he perish'd on some well-fought day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.8#Or in his friend's embraces died away!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.9#That grateful Greece with streaming eyes might raise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.10#Historic marbles to record his praise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.11#His praise, eternal on the faithful stone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.12#Had with transmissive honours graced his son.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.13#Now, snatch'd by harpies to the dreary coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.14#Sunk is the hero, and his glory lost!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.15#While pensive in this solitary den,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.16#Far from gay cities and the ways of men,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.17#I linger life; nor to the court repair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.18#But when my constant queen commands my care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.19#Or when, to taste her hospitable board,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.20#Some guest arrives, with rumours of her lord;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.21#And these indulge their want, and those their woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.22#And here the tears and there the goblets flow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.23#By many such have I been warn'd; but chief
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.24#By one Aetolian robb'd of all belief,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.25#Whose hap it was to this our roof to roam,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.26#For murder banish'd from his native home.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.27#He swore, Ulysses on the coast of Crete
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.28#Stay'd but a season to refit his fleet;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.29#A few revolving months should waft him o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.30#Fraught with bold warriors, and a boundless store
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.31#O thou! whom age has taught to understand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.32#And Heaven has guided with a favouring hand!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.33#On god or mortal to obtrude a lie
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.34#Forbear, and dread to flatter as to die.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.35#Nor for such ends my house and heart are free,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.16.36#But dear respect to Jove, and charity."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.17.1#"And why, O swain of unbelieving mind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.17.2#(Thus quick replied the wisest of mankind)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.17.3#Doubt you my oath? yet more my faith to try,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.17.4#A solemn compact let us ratify,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.17.5#And witness every power that rules the sky!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.17.6#If here Ulysses from his labours rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.17.7#Be then my prize a tunic and a vest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.17.8#And where my hopes invite me, straight transport
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.17.9#In safety to Dulichium's friendly court.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.17.10#But if he greets not thy desiring eye,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.17.11#Hurl me from yon dread precipice on high:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.17.12#The due reward of fraud and perjury."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.18.1#"Doubtless, O guest! great laud and praise were mine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.18.2#(Replied the swain, for spotless faith divine),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.18.3#If after social rites and gifts bestow'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.18.4#I stain'd my hospitable hearth with blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.18.5#How would the gods my righteous toils succeed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.18.6#And bless the hand that made a stranger bleed?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.18.7#No more--the approaching hours of silent night
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.18.8#First claim refection, then to rest invite;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.18.9#Beneath our humble cottage let us haste,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.18.10#And here, unenvied, rural dainties taste."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.19.1#Thus communed these; while to their lowly dome
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.19.2#The full-fed swine return'd with evening home;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.19.3#Compell'd, reluctant, to their several sties,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.19.4#With din obstreperous, and ungrateful cries.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.19.5#Then to the slaves: "Now from the herd the best
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.19.6#Select in honour of our foreign guest:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.19.7#With him let us the genial banquet share,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.19.8#For great and many are the griefs we bear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.19.9#While those who from our labours heap their board
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.19.10#Blaspheme their feeder, and forget their lord."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.1#Thus speaking, with despatchful hand he took
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.2#A weighty axe, and cleft the solid oak;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.3#This on the earth he piled; a boar full fed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.4#Of five years' age, before the pile was led:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.5#The swain, whom acts of piety delight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.6#Observant of the gods, begins the rite;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.7#First shears the forehead of the bristly boar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.8#And suppliant stands, invoking every power
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.9#To speed Ulysses to his native shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.10#A knotty stake then aiming at his head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.11#Down dropped he groaning, and the spirit fled.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.12#The scorching flames climb round on every side;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.13#Then the singed members they with skill divide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.14#On these, in rolls of fat involved with art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.15#The choicest morsels lay from every part.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.16#Some in the flames bestrew'd with flour they threw;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.17#Some cut in fragments from the forks they drew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.18#These while on several tables they dispose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.19#A priest himself the blameless rustic rose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.20#Expert the destined victim to dispart
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.21#In seven just portions, pure of hand and heart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.22#One sacred to the nymphs apart they lay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.23#Another to the winged sons of May;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.24#The rural tribe in common share the rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.25#The king the chine, the honour of the feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.26#Who sate delighted at his servant's board;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.27#The faithful servant joy'd his unknown lord.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.28#"Oh be thou dear (Ulysses cried) to Jove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.20.29#As well thou claim'st a grateful stranger's love!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.1#"Be then thy thanks (the bounteous swain replied)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.2#Enjoyment of the good the gods provide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.3#From God's own hand descend our joys and woes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.4#These he decrees, and he but suffers those:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.5#All power is his, and whatsoe'er he wills,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.6#The will itself, omnipotent, fulfils."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.7#This said, the first-fruits to the gods he gave;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.8#Then pour'd of offer'd wine the sable wave:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.9#In great Ulysses' hand he placed the bowl,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.10#He sate, and sweet refection cheer'd his soul.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.11#The bread from canisters Mesaulius gave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.12#(Eumaeus' proper treasure bought this slave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.13#And led from Taphos, to attend his board,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.14#A servant added to his absent lord);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.15#His task it was the wheaten loaves to lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.16#And from the banquet take the bowls away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.17#And now the rage of hunger was repress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.21.18#And each betakes him to his couch to rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.1#Now came the night, and darkness cover'd o'er
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.2#The face of things; the winds began to roar;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.3#The driving storm the watery west-wind pours,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.4#And Jove descends in deluges of showers.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.5#Studious of rest and warmth, Ulysses lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.6#Foreseeing from the first the storm would rise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.7#In mere necessity of coat and cloak,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.8#With artful preface to his host he spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.9#"Hear me, my friends! who this good banquet grace;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.10#'Tis sweet to play the fool in time and place,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.11#And wine can of their wits the wise beguile,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.12#Make the sage frolic, and the serious smile,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.13#The grave in merry measures frisk about,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.14#And many a long-repented word bring out.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.15#Since to be talkative I now commence,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.16#Let wit cast off the sullen yoke of sense.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.17#Once I was strong (would Heaven restore those days!)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.18#And with my betters claim'd a share of praise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.19#Ulysses, Menelaus, led forth a band,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.20#And join'd me with them ('twas their own command);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.21#A deathful ambush for the foe to lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.22#Beneath Troy walls by night we took our way:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.23#There, clad in arms, along the marshes spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.24#We made the osier-fringed bank our bed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.25#Full soon the inclemency of heaven I feel,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.26#Nor had these shoulders covering, but of steel.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.27#Sharp blew the north; snow whitening all the fields
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.28#Froze with the blast, and gathering glazed our shields.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.29#There all but I, well fenced with cloak and vest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.30#Lay cover'd by their ample shields at rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.31#Fool that I was! I left behind my own,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.32#The skill of weather and of winds unknown,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.33#And trusted to my coat and shield alone!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.34#When now was wasted more than half the night,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.35#And the stars faded at approaching light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.36#Sudden I jogg'd Ulysses, who was laid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.22.37#Fast by my side, and shivering thus I said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.23.1#"'Here longer in this field I cannot lie;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.23.2#The winter pinches, and with cold I die,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.23.3#And die ashamed (O wisest of mankind),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.23.4#The only fool who left his cloak behind.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.24.1#"He thought and answer'd: hardly waking yet,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.24.2#Sprung in his mind a momentary wit
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.24.3#(That wit, which or in council or in fight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.24.4#Still met the emergence, and determined right).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.24.5#'Hush thee (he cried, soft whispering in my ear),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.24.6#Speak not a word, lest any Greek may hear'--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.24.7#And then (supporting on his arm his head),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.24.8#'Hear me, companions! (thus aloud he said:)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.24.9#Methinks too distant from the fleet we lie:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.24.10#E'en now a vision stood before my eye,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.24.11#And sure the warning vision was from high:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.24.12#Let from among us some swift courier rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.24.13#Haste to the general, and demand supplies.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.25.1#"Up started Thoas straight, Andraemon's son,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.25.2#Nimbly he rose, and cast his garment down!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.25.3#Instant, the racer vanish'd off the ground;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.25.4#That instant in his cloak I wrapp'd me round:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.25.5#And safe I slept, till brightly-dawning shone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.25.6#The morn conspicuous on her golden throne.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.26.1#"Oh were my strength as then, as then my age!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.26.2#Some friend would fence me from the winter's rage.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.26.3#Yet, tatter'd as I look, I challenged then
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.26.4#The honours and the offices of men:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.26.5#Some master, or some servant would allow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.26.6#A cloak and vest--but I am nothing now!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.27.1#"Well hast thou spoke (rejoin'd the attentive swain):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.27.2#Thy lips let fall no idle word or vain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.27.3#Nor garment shalt thou want, nor aught beside,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.27.4#Meet for the wandering suppliant to provide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.27.5#But in the morning take thy clothes again,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.27.6#For here one vest suffices every swain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.27.7#No change of garments to our hinds is known;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.27.8#But when return'd, the good Ulysses' son
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.27.9#With better hand shall grace with fit attires
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.27.10#His guest, and send thee where thy soul desires."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.1#The honest herdsman rose, as this he said,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.2#And drew before the hearth the stranger's bed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.3#The fleecy spoils of sheep, a goat's rough hide
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.4#He spreads; and adds a mantle thick and wide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.5#With store to heap above him, and below,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.6#And guard each quarter as the tempests blow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.7#There lay the king, and all the rest supine;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.8#All, but the careful master of the swine:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.9#Forth hasted he to tend his bristly care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.10#Well arm'd, and fenced against nocturnal air:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.11#His weighty falchion o'er his shoulder tied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.12#His shaggy cloak a mountain goat supplied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.13#With his broad spear the dread of dogs and men,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.14#He seeks his lodging in the rocky den.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.15#There to the tusky herd he bends his way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:14.28.16#Where, screen'd from Boreas, high o'erarch'd they lay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.1#Now had Minerva reach'd those ample plains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.2#Famed for the dance, where Menelaus reigns:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.3#Anxious she flies to great Ulysses' heir,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.4#His instant voyage challenged all her care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.5#Beneath the royal portico display'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.6#With Nestor's son Telemachus was laid:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.7#In sleep profound the son of Nestor lies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.8#Not thine, Ulysses! Care unseal'd his eyes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.9#Restless he grieved, with various fears oppress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.10#And all thy fortunes roll'd within his breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.11#When, "O Telemachus! (the goddess said)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.12#Too long in vain, too widely hast thou stray'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.13#Thus leaving careless thy paternal right
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.14#The robbers' prize, the prey to lawless might.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.15#On fond pursuits neglectful while you roam,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.16#E'en now the hand of rapine sacks the dome.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.17#Hence to Atrides; and his leave implore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.18#To launch thy vessel for thy natal shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.19#Fly, whilst thy mother virtuous yet withstands
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.20#Her kindred's wishes, and her sire's commands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.21#Through both, Eurymachus pursues the dame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.22#And with the noblest gifts asserts his claim.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.23#Hence, therefore, while thy stores thy own remain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.24#Thou know'st the practice of the female train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.25#Lost in the children of the present spouse,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.26#They slight the pledges of their former vows;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.27#Their love is always with the lover past;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.28#Still the succeeding flame expels the last.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.29#Let o'er thy house some chosen maid preside,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.30#Till Heaven decrees to bless thee in a bride.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.31#But now thy more attentive ears incline,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.32#Observe the warnings of a power divine;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.33#For thee their snares the suitor lords shall lay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.34#In Samos' sands, or straits of Ithaca;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.35#To seize thy life shall lurk the murderous band,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.36#Ere yet thy footsteps press thy native land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.37#No!--sooner far their riot and their lust
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.38#All-covering earth shall bury deep in dust!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.39#Then distant from the scatter'd islands steer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.40#Nor let the night retard thy full career;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.41#Thy heavenly guardian shall instruct the gales
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.42#To smooth thy passage and supply thy sails:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.43#And when at Ithaca thy labour ends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.44#Send to the town the vessel with thy friends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.45#But seek thou first the master of the swine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.46#(For still to thee his loyal thoughts incline);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.47#There pass the night: while he his course pursues
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.48#To bring Penelope the wish'd-for news,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.49#That thou, safe sailing from the Pylian strand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.50#Art come to bless her in thy native land."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.51#Thus spoke the goddess, and resumed her flight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.52#To the pure regions of eternal light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.53#Meanwhile Pisistratus he gently shakes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.1.54#And with these words the slumbering youth awakes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.2.1#"Rise, son of Nestor; for the road prepare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.2.2#And join the harness'd coursers to the car."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.3.1#"What cause (he cried) can justify our flight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.3.2#To tempt the dangers of forbidding night?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.3.3#Here wait we rather, till approaching day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.3.4#Shall prompt our speed, and point the ready way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.3.5#Nor think of flight before the Spartan king
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.3.6#Shall bid farewell, and bounteous presents bring;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.3.7#Gifts, which to distant ages safely stored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.3.8#The sacred act of friendship shall record."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.4.1#Thus he. But when the dawn bestreak'd the east,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.4.2#The king from Helen rose, and sought his guest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.4.3#As soon as his approach the hero knew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.4.4#The splendid mantle round him first he threw,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.4.5#Then o'er his ample shoulders whirl'd the cloak,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.4.6#Respectful met the monarch, and bespoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.5.1#"Hail, great Atrides, favour'd of high Jove!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.5.2#Let not thy friends in vain for licence move.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.5.3#Swift let us measure back the watery way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.5.4#Nor check our speed, impatient of delay."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.1#"If with desire so strong thy bosom glows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.2#Ill (said the king) should I thy wish oppose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.3#For oft in others freely I reprove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.4#The ill-timed efforts of officious love;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.5#Who love too much, hate in the like extreme,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.6#And both the golden mean alike condemn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.7#Alike he thwarts the hospitable end,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.8#Who drives the free, or stays the hasty friend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.9#True friendship's laws are by this rule express'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.10#Welcome the coming, speed the parting guest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.11#Yet, stay, my friends, and in your chariot take
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.12#The noblest presents that our love can make;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.13#Meantime commit we to our women's care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.14#Some choice domestic viands to prepare;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.15#The traveller, rising from the banquet gay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.16#Eludes the labours of the tedious way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.17#Then if a wider course shall rather please,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.18#Through spacious Argos and the realms of Greece,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.19#Atrides in his chariot shall attend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.20#Himself thy convoy to each royal friend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.21#No prince will let Ulysses' heir remove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.22#Without some pledge, some monument of love:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.23#These will the caldron, these the tripod give;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.24#From those the well-pair'd mules we shall receive,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.6.25#Or bowl emboss'd whose golden figures live."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.7.1#To whom the youth, for prudence famed, replied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.7.2#"O monarch, care of heaven! thy people's pride!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.7.3#No friend in Ithaca my place supplies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.7.4#No powerful hands are there, no watchful eyes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.7.5#My stores exposed and fenceless house demand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.7.6#The speediest succour from my guardian hand;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.7.7#Lest, in a search too anxious and too vain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.7.8#Of one lost joy, I lose what yet remain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.1#His purpose when the generous warrior heard,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.2#He charged the household cates to be prepared.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.3#Now with the dawn, from his adjoining home,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.4#Was Boethoedes Eteoneus come;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.5#Swift at the word he forms the rising blaze,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.6#And o'er the coals the smoking fragments lays.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.7#Meantime the king, his son, and Helen went
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.8#Where the rich wardrobe breathed a costly scent;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.9#The king selected from the glittering rows
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.10#A bowl; the prince a silver beaker chose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.11#The beauteous queen revolved with careful eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.12#Her various textures of unnumber'd dyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.13#And chose the largest; with no vulgar art
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.14#Her own fair hands embroider'd every part;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.15#Beneath the rest it lay divinely bright,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.16#Like radiant Hesper o'er the gems of night,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.17#Then with each gift they hasten'd to their guest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.18#And thus the king Ulysses' heir address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.19#"Since fix'd are thy resolves, may thundering Jove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.20#With happiest omens thy desires approve!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.21#This silver bowl, whose costly margins shine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.22#Enchased with old, this valued gift be thine;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.23#To me this present, of Vulcanian frame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.24#From Sidon's hospitable monarch came;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.25#To thee we now consign the precious load,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.8.26#The pride of kings, and labour of a god."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.9.1#Then gave the cup, while Megapenthe brought
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.9.2#The silver vase with living sculpture wrought.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.9.3#The beauteous queen, advancing next, display'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.9.4#The shining veil, and thus endearing said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.10.1#"Accept, dear youth, this monument of love,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.10.2#Long since, in better days, by Helen wove:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.10.3#Safe in thy mother's care the vesture lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.10.4#To deck thy bride and grace thy nuptial day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.10.5#Meantime may'st thou with happiest speed regain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.10.6#Thy stately palace, and thy wide domain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.1#She said, and gave the veil; with grateful look
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.2#The prince the variegated present took.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.3#And now, when through the royal dome they pass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.4#High on a throne the king each stranger placed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.5#A golden ewer the attendant damsel brings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.6#Replete with water from the crystal springs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.7#With copious streams the shining vase supplies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.8#A silver layer of capacious size.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.9#They wash. The tables in fair order spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.10#The glittering canisters are crown'd with bread;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.11#Viands of various kinds allure the taste,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.12#Of choicest sort and savour; rich repast!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.13#Whilst Eteoneus portions out the shares
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.14#Atrides' son the purple draught prepares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.15#And now (each sated with the genial feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.16#And the short rage of thirst and hunger ceased)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.17#Ulysses' son, with his illustrious friend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.18#The horses join, the polish'd car ascend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.19#Along the court the fiery steeds rebound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.20#And the wide portal echoes to the sound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.21#The king precedes; a bowl with fragrant wine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.22#(Libation destined to the powers divine)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.23#His right hand held: before the steed he stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.11.24#Then, mix'd with prayers, he utters these commands:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.12.1#"Farewell, and prosper, youths! let Nestor know
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.12.2#What grateful thoughts still in this bosom glow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.12.3#For all the proofs of his paternal care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.12.4#Through the long dangers of the ten years' war."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.12.5#"Ah! doubt not our report (the prince rejoin'd)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.12.6#Of all the virtues of thy generous mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.12.7#And oh! return'd might we Ulysses meet!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.12.8#To him thy presents show, thy words repeat:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.12.9#How will each speech his grateful wonder raise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.12.10#How will each gift indulge us in thy praise!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.13.1#Scarce ended thus the prince, when on the right
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.13.2#Advanced the bird of Jove: auspicious sight!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.13.3#A milk-white fowl his clinching talons bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.13.4#With care domestic pampered at the floor.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.13.5#Peasants in vain with threatening cries pursue,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.13.6#In solemn speed the bird majestic flew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.13.7#Full dexter to the car; the prosperous sight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.13.8#Fill'd every breast with wonder and delight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.14.1#But Nestor's son the cheerful silence broke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.14.2#And in these words the Spartan chief bespoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.14.3#"Say if to us the gods these omens send,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.14.4#Or fates peculiar to thyself portend?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.15.1#Whilst yet the monarch paused, with doubts oppress'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.15.2#The beauteous queen relieved his labouring breast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.15.3#"Hear me (she cried), to whom the gods have given
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.15.4#To read this sign, and mystic sense of heaven,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.15.5#As thus the plumy sovereign of the air
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.15.6#Left on the mountain's brow his callow care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.15.7#And wander'd through the wide ethereal way
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.15.8#To pour his wrath on yon luxurious prey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.15.9#So shall thy godlike father, toss'd in vain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.15.10#Through all the dangers of the boundless main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.15.11#Arrive (or if perchance already come)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.15.12#From slaughter'd gluttons to release the dome."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.16.1#"Oh! if this promised bliss by thundering Jove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.16.2#(The prince replied) stand fix'd in fate above;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.16.3#To thee, as to some god, I'll temples raise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.16.4#And crown thy altars with the costly blaze."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.17.1#He said; and bending o'er his chariot, flung
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.17.2#Athwart the fiery steeds the smarting thong;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.17.3#The bounding shafts upon the harness play,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.17.4#Till night descending intercepts the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.17.5#To Diocles at Pherae they repair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.17.6#Whose boasted sire was sacred Alpheus' heir;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.17.7#With him all night the youthful stranger stay'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.17.8#Nor found the hospitable rites unpaid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.17.9#But soon as morning from her orient bed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.17.10#Had tinged the mountains with her earliest red,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.17.11#They join'd the steeds, and on the chariot sprung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.17.12#The brazen portals in their passage rung.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.18.1#To Pylos soon they came; when thus begun
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.18.2#To Nestor's heir Ulysses' godlike son:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.19.1#"Let not Pisistratus in vain be press'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.19.2#Nor unconsenting hear his friend's request;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.19.3#His friend by long hereditary claim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.19.4#In toils his equal, and in years the same.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.19.5#No farther from our vessel, I implore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.19.6#The courses drive; but lash them to the shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.19.7#Too long thy father would his friend detain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.19.8#I dread his proffer'd kindness urged in vain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.1#The hero paused, and ponder'd this request,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.2#While love and duty warr'd within his breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.3#At length resolved, he turn'd his ready hand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.4#And lash'd his panting coursers to the strand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.5#There, while within the poop with care he stored
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.6#The regal presents of the Spartan lord,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.7#"With speed begone (said he); call every mate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.8#Ere yet to Nestor I the tale relate:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.9#'Tis true, the fervour of his generous heart
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.10#Brooks no repulse, nor couldst thou soon depart:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.11#Himself will seek thee here, nor wilt thou find,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.12#In words alone, the Pylian monarch kind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.13#But when, arrived, he thy return shall know
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.14#How will his breast with honest fury glow!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.15#This said, the sounding strokes his horses fire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.20.16#And soon he reached the palace of his sire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.21.1#"Now (cried Telemachus) with speedy care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.21.2#Hoist every sail, and every oar prepare."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.21.3#Swift as the word his willing mates obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.21.4#And seize their seats, impatient for the sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.1#Meantime the prince with sacrifice adores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.2#Minerva, and her guardian aid implores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.3#When lo! a wretch ran breathless to the shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.4#New from his crime; and reeking yet with gore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.5#A seer he was, from great Melampus sprung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.6#Melampus, who in Pylos flourish'd long,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.7#Till, urged by wrongs, a foreign realm he chose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.8#Far from the hateful cause of all his woes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.9#Neleus his treasures one long year detains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.10#As long he groan'd in Philacus' chains:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.11#Meantime, what anguish and what rage combined
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.12#For lovely Pero rack'd his labouring mind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.13#Yet 'scaped he death; and vengeful of his wrong
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.14#To Pylos drove the lowing herds along:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.15#Then (Neleus vanquish'd, and consign'd the fair
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.16#To Bias' arms) he so sought a foreign air;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.17#Argos the rich for his retreat he chose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.18#There form'd his empire; there his palace rose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.19#From him Antiphates and Mantius came:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.20#The first begot Oicleus great in fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.21#And he Amphiaraus, immortal name!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.22#The people's saviour, and divinely wise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.23#Beloved by Jove, and him who gilds the skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.24#Yet short his date of life! by female pride he dies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.25#From Mantius Clitus, whom Aurora's love
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.26#Snatch'd for his beauty to the thrones above;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.27#And Polyphides, on whom Phoebus shone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.28#With fullest rays, Amphiaraus now gone;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.29#In Hyperesia's groves he made abode,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.30#And taught mankind the counsels of the god.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.31#From him sprung Theoclymenus, who found
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.32#(The sacred wine yet foaming on the ground)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.33#Telemachus: whom, as to Heaven he press'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.22.34#His ardent vows, the stranger thus address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.23.1#"O thou! that dost thy happy course prepare
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.23.2#With pure libations and with solemn prayer:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.23.3#By that dread power to whom thy vows are paid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.23.4#By all the lives of these; thy own dear head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.23.5#Declare sincerely to no foe's demand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.23.6#Thy name, thy lineage, and paternal land."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.24.1#"Prepare, then (said Telemachus), to know
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.24.2#A tale from falsehood free, not free from woe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.24.3#From Ithaca, of royal birth I came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.24.4#And great Ulysses (ever honour'd name!)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.24.5#Once was my sire, though now, for ever lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.24.6#In Stygian gloom he glides a pensive ghost!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.24.7#Whose fate inquiring through the world we rove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.24.8#The last, the wretched proof of filial love."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.25.1#The stranger then: "Nor shall I aught conceal,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.25.2#But the dire secret of my fate reveal.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.25.3#Of my own tribe an Argive wretch I slew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.25.4#Whose powerful friends the luckless deed pursue
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.25.5#With unrelenting rage, and force from home
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.25.6#The blood-stain'd exile, ever doom'd to roam.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.25.7#But bear, oh bear me o'er yon azure flood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.25.8#Receive the suppliant! spare my destined blood!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.1#"Stranger (replied the prince) securely rest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.2#Affianced in our faith; henceforth our guest."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.3#Thus affable, Ulysses' godlike heir
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.4#Takes from the stranger's hand the glittering spear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.5#He climbs the ship, ascends the stern with haste
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.6#And by his side the guest accepted placed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.7#The chief his order gives: the obedient band,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.8#With due observance wait the chief's command:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.9#With speed the mast they rear, with speed unbind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.10#The spacious sheet, and stretch it to the wind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.11#Minerva calls; the ready gales obey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.12#With rapid speed to whirl them o'er the sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.13#Crunus they pass'd, next Chalcis roll'd away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.14#With thickening darkness closed the doubtful day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.15#The silver Phaea's glittering rills they lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.16#And skimm'd along by Elis' sacred coast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.17#Then cautious through the rocky reaches wind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.26.18#And turning sudden, shun the death design'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.27.1#Meantime, the king, Eumaeus, and the rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.27.2#Sate in the cottage, at their rural feast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.27.3#The banquet pass'd, and satiate every man,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.27.4#To try his host, Ulysses thus began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.1#"Yet one night more, my friends, indulge your guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.2#The last I purpose in your walls to rest:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.3#To-morrow for myself I must provide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.4#And only ask your counsel, and a guide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.5#Patient to roam the street, by hunger led,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.6#And bless the friendly hand that gives me bread.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.7#There in Ulysses' roof I may relate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.8#Ulysses' wanderings to his royal mate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.9#Or, mingling with the suitors' haughty train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.10#Not undeserving some support obtain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.11#Hermes to me his various gifts imparts.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.12#Patron of industry and manual arts:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.13#Few can with me in dexterous works contend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.14#The pyre to build, the stubborn oak to rend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.15#To turn the tasteful viand o'er the flame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.16#Or foam the goblet with a purple stream.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.17#Such are the tasks of men of mean estate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.28.18#Whom fortune dooms to serve the rich and great."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.1#"Alas! (Eumaeus with a sigh rejoin'd).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.2#How sprung a thought so monstrous in thy mind?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.3#If on that godless race thou would'st attend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.4#Fate owes thee sure a miserable end!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.5#Their wrongs and blasphemies ascend the sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.6#And pull descending vengeance from on high.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.7#Not such, my friend, the servants of their feast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.8#A blooming train in rich embroidery dress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.9#With earth's whole tribute the bright table bends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.10#And smiling round celestial youth attends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.11#Stay, then: no eye askance beholds thee here;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.12#Sweet is thy converse to each social ear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.13#Well pleased, and pleasing, in our cottage rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.14#Till good Telemachus accepts his guest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.15#With genial gifts, and change of fair attires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.29.16#And safe conveys thee where thy soul desires."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.1#To him the man of woes; "O gracious Jove!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.2#Reward this stranger's hospitable love!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.3#Who knows the son of sorrow to relieve,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.4#Cheers the sad heart, nor lets affliction grieve.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.5#Of all the ills unhappy mortals know,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.6#A life of wanderings is the greatest woe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.7#On all their weary ways wait care and pain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.8#And pine and penury, a meagre train.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.9#To such a man since harbour you afford,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.10#Relate the farther fortunes of your lord;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.11#What cares his mother's tender breast engage,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.12#And sire forsaken on the verge of age;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.13#Beneath the sun prolong they yet their breath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.30.14#Or range the house of darkness and of death?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.1#To whom the swain: "Attend what you enquire;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.2#Laertes lives, the miserable sire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.3#Lives, but implores of every power to lay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.4#The burden down, and wishes for the day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.5#Torn from his offspring in the eve of life,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.6#Torn from the embraces of his tender wife,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.7#Sole, and all comfortless, he wastes away
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.8#Old age, untimely posting ere his day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.9#She too, sad mother! for Ulysses lost
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.10#Pined out her bloom, and vanish'd to a ghost;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.11#(So dire a fate, ye righteous gods! avert
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.12#From every friendly, every feeling heart!)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.13#While yet she was, though clouded o'er with grief.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.14#Her pleasing converse minister'd relief:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.15#With Climene, her youngest daughter, bred,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.16#One roof contain'd us, and one table fed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.17#But when the softly-stealing pace of time
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.18#Crept on from childhood into youthful prime,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.19#To Samos' isle she sent the wedded fair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.20#Me to the fields; to tend the rural care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.21#Array'd in garments her own hands had wove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.22#Nor less the darling object of her love.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.23#Her hapless death my brighter days o'ercast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.24#Yet Providence deserts me not at last;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.25#My present labours food and drink procure,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.26#And more, the pleasure to relieve the poor.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.27#Small is the comfort from the queen to hear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.28#Unwelcome news, or vex the royal ear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.29#Blank and discountenanced the servants stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.30#Nor dare to question where the proud command;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.31#No profit springs beneath usurping powers;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.32#Want feeds not there where luxury devours,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.33#Nor harbours charity where riot reigns:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.31.34#Proud are the lords, and wretched are the swains."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.1#The suffering chief at this began to melt;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.2#And, "O Eumaeus! thou (he cries) hast felt
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.3#The spite of fortune too! her cruel hand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.4#Snatch'd thee an infant from thy native land!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.5#Snatch'd from thy parents' arms, thy parents' eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.6#To early wants! a man of miseries!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.7#The whole sad story, from its first, declare:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.8#Sunk the fair city by the rage of war,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.9#Where once thy parents dwelt? or did they keep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.10#In humbler life, the lowing herds and sheep?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.11#So left perhaps to tend the fleecy train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.12#Rude pirates seized, and shipp'd thee o'er the main?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.13#Doom'd a fair prize to grace some prince's board,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.32.14#The worthy purchase of a foreign lord."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.1#"If then my fortunes can delight my friend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.2#A story fruitful of events attend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.3#Another's sorrow may thy ears enjoy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.4#And wine the lengthen'd intervals employ.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.5#Long nights the now declining year bestows;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.6#A part we consecrate to soft repose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.7#A part in pleasing talk we entertain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.8#For too much rest itself becomes a pain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.9#Let those, whom sleep invites, the call obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.10#Their cares resuming with the dawning day:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.11#Here let us feast, and to the feast be join'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.12#Discourse, the sweeter banquet of the mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.13#Review the series of our lives, and taste
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.14#The melancholy joy of evils pass'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.15#For he who much has suffer'd, much will know,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.33.16#And pleased remembrance builds delight on woe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.1#"Above Ortygia lies an isle of fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.2#Far hence remote, and Syria is the name
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.3#(There curious eyes inscribed with wonder trace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.4#The sun's diurnal, and his annual race);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.5#Not large, but fruitful; stored with grass to keep
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.6#The bellowing oxen and the bleating sheep;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.7#Her sloping hills the mantling vines adorn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.8#And her rich valleys wave with golden corn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.9#No want, no famine, the glad natives know,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.10#Nor sink by sickness to the shades below;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.11#But when a length of years unnerves the strong,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.12#Apollo comes, and Cynthia comes along.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.13#They bend the silver bow with tender skill,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.14#And, void of pain, the silent arrows kill.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.15#Two equal tribes this fertile land divide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.16#Where two fair cities rise with equal pride.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.17#But both in constant peace one prince obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.18#And Ctesius there, my father, holds the sway.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.19#Freighted, it seems, with toys of every sort,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.20#A ship of Sidon anchor'd in our port;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.21#What time it chanced the palace entertain'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.22#Skill'd in rich works, a woman of their land:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.23#This nymph, where anchor'd the Phoenician train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.24#To wash her robes descending to the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.25#A smooth tongued sailor won her to his mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.26#(For love deceives the best of womankind).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.27#A sudden trust from sudden liking grew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.28#She told her name, her race, and all she knew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.29#'I too (she cried) from glorious Sidon came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.30#My father Arybas, of wealthy fame:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.31#But, snatch'd by pirates from my native place,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.34.32#The Taphians sold me to this man's embrace.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.35.1#"'Haste then (the false designing youth replied),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.35.2#Haste to thy country; love shall be thy guide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.35.3#Haste to thy father's house, thy father's breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.35.4#For still he lives, and lives with riches blest.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.1#"'Swear first (she cried), ye sailors! to restore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.2#A wretch in safety to her native shore.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.3#Swift as she ask'd, the ready sailors swore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.4#She then proceeds: 'Now let our compact made
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.5#Be nor by signal nor by word betray'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.6#Nor near me any of your crew descried,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.7#By road frequented, or by fountain side.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.8#Be silence still our guard. The monarch's spies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.9#(For watchful age is ready to surmise)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.10#Are still at hand; and this, revealed, must be
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.11#Death to yourselves, eternal chains to me.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.12#Your vessel loaded, and your traffic pass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.13#Despatch a wary messenger with haste;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.14#Then gold and costly treasures will I bring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.15#And more, the infant offspring of the king.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.16#Him, child-like wandering forth, I'll lead away
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.36.17#(A noble prize!) and to your ship convey.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.1#"Thus spoke the dame, and homeward took the road.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.2#A year they traffic, and their vessel load.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.3#Their stores complete, and ready now to weigh,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.4#A spy was sent their summons to convey:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.5#An artist to my father's palace came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.6#With gold and amber chains, elaborate frame:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.7#Each female eye the glittering links employ;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.8#They turn, review, and cheapen every toy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.9#He took the occasion, as they stood intent,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.10#Gave her the sign, and to his vessel went.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.11#She straight pursued, and seized my willing arm;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.12#I follow'd, smiling, innocent of harm.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.13#Three golden goblets in the porch she found
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.14#(The guests not enter'd, but the table crown'd);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.15#Hid in her fraudful bosom these she bore:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.16#Now set the sun, and darken'd all the shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.17#Arriving then, where tilting on the tides
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.18#Prepared to launch the freighted vessel rides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.19#Aboard they heave us, mount their decks, and sweep
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.20#With level oar along the glassy deep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.21#Six calmy days and six smooth nights we sail,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.22#And constant Jove supplied the gentle gale.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.23#The seventh, the fraudful wretch (no cause descried),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.24#Touch'd by Diana's vengeful arrow, died.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.25#Down dropp'd the caitiff-corse, a worthless load,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.26#Down to the deep; there roll'd, the future food
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.27#Of fierce sea-wolves, and monsters of the flood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.28#An helpless infant I remain'd behind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.29#Thence borne to Ithaca by wave and wind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.30#Sold to Laertes by divine command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.37.31#And now adopted to a foreign land."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.38.1#To him the king: "Reciting thus thy cares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.38.2#My secret soul in all thy sorrow shares;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.38.3#But one choice blessing (such is Jove's high will)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.38.4#Has sweeten'd all thy bitter draught of ill:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.38.5#Torn from thy country to no hapless end,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.38.6#The gods have, in a master, given a friend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.38.7#Whatever frugal nature needs is thine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.38.8#(For she needs little), daily bread and wine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.38.9#While I, so many wanderings past, and woes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.38.10#Live but on what thy poverty bestows."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.1#So passed in pleasing dialogue away
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.2#The night; then down to short repose they lay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.3#Till radiant rose the messenger of day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.4#While in the port of Ithaca, the band
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.5#Of young Telemachus approach'd the land;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.6#Their sails they loosed, they lash'd the mast aside,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.7#And cast their anchors, and the cables tied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.8#Then on the breezy shore, descending, join
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.9#In grateful banquet o'er the rosy wine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.10#When thus the prince: "Now each his course pursue;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.11#I to the fields, and to the city you.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.12#Long absent hence, I dedicate this day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.13#My swains to visit, and the works survey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.14#Expect me with the morn, to pay the skies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.39.15#Our debt of safe return in feast and sacrifice."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.40.1#Then Theoclymenus: "But who shall lend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.40.2#Meantime, protection to thy stranger friend?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.40.3#Straight to the queen and palace shall I fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.40.4#Or yet more distant, to some lord apply?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.1#The prince return'd: "Renown'd in days of yore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.2#Has stood our father's hospitable door;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.3#No other roof a stranger should receive,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.4#No other hands than ours the welcome give.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.5#But in my absence riot fills the place,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.6#Nor bears the modest queen a stranger's face;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.7#From noiseful revel far remote she flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.8#But rarely seen, or seen with weeping eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.9#No--let Eurymachus receive my guest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.10#Of nature courteous, and by far the best;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.11#He woos the queen with more respectful flame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.12#And emulates her former husband's fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.13#With what success, 'tis Jove's alone to know,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.41.14#And the hoped nuptials turn to joy or woe."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.42.1#Thus speaking, on the right up-soar'd in air
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.42.2#The hawk, Apollo's swift-wing'd messenger:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.42.3#His dreadful pounces tore a trembling dove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.42.4#The clotted feathers, scatter'd from above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.42.5#Between the hero and the vessel pour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.42.6#Thick plumage mingled with a sanguine shower.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.43.1#The observing augur took the prince aside,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.43.2#Seized by the hand, and thus prophetic cried:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.43.3#"Yon bird, that dexter cuts the aerial road,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.43.4#Rose ominous, nor flies without a god:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.43.5#No race but thine shall Ithaca obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.43.6#To thine, for ages, Heaven decrees the sway."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.44.1#"Succeed the omens, gods! (the youth rejoin'd:)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.44.2#Soon shall my bounties speak a grateful mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.44.3#And soon each envied happiness attend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.44.4#The man who calls Telemachus his friend."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.44.5#Then to Peiraeus: "Thou whom time has proved
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.44.6#A faithful servant, by thy prince beloved!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.44.7#Till we returning shall our guest demand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.44.8#Accept this charge with honour, at our hand."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.45.1#To this Peiraeus: "Joyful I obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.45.2#Well pleased the hospitable rites to pay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.45.3#The presence of thy guest shall best reward
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.45.4#(If long thy stay) the absence of my lord."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.46.1#With that, their anchors he commands to weigh,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.46.2#Mount the tall bark, and launch into the sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.46.3#All with obedient haste forsake the shores,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.46.4#And, placed in order, spread their equal oars.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.46.5#Then from the deck the prince his sandals takes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.46.6#Poised in his hand the pointed javelin shakes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.46.7#They part; while, lessening from the hero's view
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.46.8#Swift to the town the well-row'd galley flew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.46.9#The hero trod the margin of the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:15.46.10#And reach'd the mansion of his faithful swain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.1.1#Soon as the morning blush'd along the plains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.1.2#Ulysses, and the monarch of the swains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.1.3#Awake the sleeping fires, their meals prepare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.1.4#And forth to pasture send the bristly care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.1.5#The prince's near approach the dogs descry,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.1.6#And fawning round his feet confess their joy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.1.7#Their gentle blandishment the king survey'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.1.8#Heard his resounding step, and instant said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.2.1#"Some well-known friend, Eumaeus, bends this way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.2.2#His steps I hear; the dogs familiar play."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.3.1#While yet he spoke, the prince advancing drew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.3.2#Nigh to the lodge, and now appear'd in view.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.3.3#Transported from his seat Eumaeus sprung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.3.4#Dropp'd the full bowl, and round his bosom hung;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.3.5#Kissing his cheek, his hand, while from his eye
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.3.6#The tears rain'd copious in a shower of joy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.3.7#As some fond sire who ten long winters grieves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.3.8#From foreign climes an only son receives
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.3.9#(Child of his age), with strong paternal joy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.3.10#Forward he springs, and clasps the favourite boy:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.3.11#So round the youth his arms Eumaeus spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.3.12#As if the grave had given him from the dead.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.4.1#"And is it thou? my ever-dear delight!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.4.2#Oh, art thou come to bless my longing sight?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.4.3#Never, I never hoped to view this day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.4.4#When o'er the waves you plough'd the desperate way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.4.5#Enter, my child! Beyond my hopes restored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.4.6#Oh give these eyes to feast upon their lord.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.4.7#Enter, oh seldom seen! for lawless powers
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.4.8#Too much detain thee from these sylvan bowers,"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.4.9#The prince replied: "Eumaeus, I obey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.4.10#To seek thee, friend, I hither took my way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.4.11#But say, if in the court the queen reside
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.4.12#Severely chaste, or if commenced a bride?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.5.1#Thus he; and thus the monarch of the swains:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.5.2#"Severely chaste Penelope remains;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.5.3#But, lost to every joy, she wastes the day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.5.4#In tedious cares, and weeps the night away."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.1#He ended, and (receiving as they pass
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.2#The javelin pointed with a star of brass),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.3#They reach'd the dome; the dome with marble shined.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.4#His seat Ulysses to the prince resign'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.5#"Not so (exclaims the prince with decent grace)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.6#For me, this house shall find an humbler place:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.7#To usurp the honours due to silver hairs
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.8#And reverend strangers modest youth forbears."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.9#Instant the swain the spoils of beasts supplies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.10#And bids the rural throne with osiers rise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.11#There sate the prince: the feast Eumaeus spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.12#And heap'd the shining canisters with bread.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.13#Thick o'er the board the plenteous viands lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.14#The frugal remnants of the former day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.15#Then in a bowl he tempers generous wines,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.16#Around whose verge a mimic ivy twines.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.17#And now, the rage of thirst and hunger fled,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.6.18#Thus young Ulysses to Eumaeus said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.7.1#"Whence, father, from what shore this stranger, say?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.7.2#What vessel bore him o'er the watery way?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.7.3#To human step our land impervious lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.7.4#And round the coast circumfluent oceans rise."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.8.1#The swain returns: "A tale of sorrows hear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.8.2#In spacious Crete he drew his natal air;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.8.3#Long doom'd to wander o'er the land and main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.8.4#For Heaven has wove his thread of life with pain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.8.5#Half breathless 'scaping to the land he flew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.8.6#From Thesprot mariners, a murderous crew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.8.7#To thee, my son, the suppliant I resign;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.8.8#I gave him my protection, grant him thine."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.1#"Hard task (he cries) thy virtue gives thy friend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.2#Willing to aid, unable to defend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.3#Can strangers safely in the court reside,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.4#'Midst the swell'd insolence of lust and pride?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.5#E'en I unsafe: the queen in doubt to wed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.6#Or pay due honours to the nuptial bed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.7#Perhaps she weds regardless of her fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.8#Deaf to the mighty Ulyssean name.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.9#However, stranger! from our grace receive
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.10#Such honours as befit a prince to give;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.11#Sandals, a sword and robes, respect to prove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.12#And safe to sail with ornaments of love.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.13#Till then, thy guest amid the rural train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.14#Far from the court, from danger far, detain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.15#'Tis mine with food the hungry to supply,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.16#And clothe the naked from the inclement sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.17#Here dwell in safety from the suitors' wrongs,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.18#And the rude insults of ungovern'd tongues.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.19#For should'st thou suffer, powerless to relieve,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.20#I must behold it, and can only grieve.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.21#The brave, encompass'd by an hostile train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.9.22#O'erpower'd by numbers, is but brave in vain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.1#To whom, while anger in his bosom glows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.2#With warmth replies the man of mighty woes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.3#"Since audience mild is deign'd, permit my tongue
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.4#At once to pity and resent thy wrong.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.5#My heart weeps blood to see a soul so brave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.6#Live to base insolence or power a slave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.7#But tell me, dost thou, prince, dost thou behold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.8#And hear their midnight revels uncontroll'd?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.9#Say, do thy subjects in bold faction rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.10#Or priests in fabled oracles advise?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.11#Or are thy brothers, who should aid thy power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.12#Turn'd mean deserters in the needful hour?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.13#Oh that I were from great Ulysses sprung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.14#Or that these wither'd nerves like thine were strung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.15#Or, heavens! might he return! (and soon appear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.16#He shall, I trust; a hero scorns despair:)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.17#Might he return, I yield my life a prey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.18#To my worst foe, if that avenging day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.19#Be not their last: but should I lose my life,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.20#Oppress'd by numbers in the glorious strife,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.21#I chose the nobler part, and yield my breath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.22#Rather than bear dishonor, worse than death;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.23#Than see the hand of violence invade
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.24#The reverend stranger and the spotless maid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.25#Than see the wealth of kings consumed in waste,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.10.26#The drunkard's revel, and the gluttons' feast."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.1#Thus he, with anger flashing from his eye;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.2#Sincere the youthful hero made reply:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.3#"Nor leagued in factious arms my subjects rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.4#Nor priests in fabled oracles advise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.5#Nor are my brothers, who should aid my power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.6#Turn'd mean deserters in the needful hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.7#Ah me! I boast no brother; heaven's dread King
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.8#Gives from our stock an only branch to spring:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.9#Alone Laertes reign'd Arcesius' heir,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.10#Alone Ulysses drew the vital air,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.11#And I alone the bed connubial graced,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.12#An unbless'd offspring of a sire unbless'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.13#Each neighbouring realm, conducive to our woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.14#Sends forth her peers, and every peer a foe:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.15#The court proud Samos and Dulichium fills,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.16#And lofty Zacinth crown'd with shady hills.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.17#E'en Ithaca and all her lords invade
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.18#The imperial sceptre, and the regal bed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.19#The queen, averse to love, yet awed by power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.20#Seems half to yield, yet flies the bridal hour:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.21#Meantime their licence uncontroll'd I bear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.22#E'en now they envy me the vital air:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.11.23#But Heaven will sure revenge, and gods there are.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.12.1#"But go Eumaeus! to the queen impart
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.12.2#Our safe return, and ease a mother's heart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.12.3#Yet secret go; for numerous are my foes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.12.4#And here at least I may in peace repose."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.1#To whom the swain: "I hear and I obey:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.2#But old Laertes weeps his life away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.3#And deems thee lost: shall I speed employ
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.4#To bless his age: a messenger of joy?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.5#The mournful hour that tore his son away
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.6#Sent the sad sire in solitude to stray;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.7#Yet busied with his slaves, to ease his woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.8#He dress'd the vine, and bade the garden blow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.9#Nor food nor wine refused; but since the day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.10#That you to Pylos plough'd the watery way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.11#Nor wine nor food he tastes; but, sunk in woes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.12#Wild springs the vine, no more the garden blows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.13#Shut from the walks of men, to pleasure lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.13.14#Pensive and pale he wanders half a ghost."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.14.1#"Wretched old man! (with tears the prince returns)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.14.2#Yet cease to go--what man so blest but mourns?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.14.3#Were every wish indulged by favouring skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.14.4#This hour should give Ulysses to my eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.14.5#But to the queen with speed dispatchful bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.14.6#Our safe return, and back with speed repair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.14.7#And let some handmaid of her train resort
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.14.8#To good Laertes in his rural court."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.1#While yet he spoke, impatient of delay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.2#He braced his sandals on, and strode away:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.3#Then from the heavens the martial goddess flies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.4#Through the wild fields of air, and cleaves the skies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.5#In form, a virgin in soft beauty's bloom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.6#Skill'd in the illustrious labours of the loom.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.7#Alone to Ithaca she stood display'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.8#But unapparent as a viewless shade
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.9#Escaped Telemachus (the powers above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.10#Seen or unseen, o'er earth at pleasure move):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.11#The dogs intelligent confess'd the tread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.12#Of power divine, and howling, trembling, fled.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.13#The goddess, beckoning, waves her deathless hands:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.15.14#Dauntless the king before the goddess stands:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.16.1#"Then why (she said), O favour'd of the skies!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.16.2#Why to thy godlike son this long disguise?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.16.3#Stand forth reveal'd; with him thy cares employ
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.16.4#Against thy foes; be valiant and destroy!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.16.5#Lo! I descend in that avenging hour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.16.6#To combat by thy side, thy guardian power."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.17.1#She said, and o'er him waves her wand of gold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.17.2#Imperial robes his manly limbs infold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.17.3#At once with grace divine his frame improves;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.17.4#At once with majesty enlarged he moves:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.17.5#Youth flush'd his reddening cheek, and from his brows
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.17.6#A length of hair in sable ringlets flows;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.17.7#His blackening chin receives a deeper shade;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.17.8#Then from his eyes upsprung the warrior-maid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.18.1#The hero reascends: the prince o'erawed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.18.2#Scarce lifts his eyes, and bows as to a god,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.18.3#Then with surprise (surprise chastised by fears):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.18.4#"How art thou changed! (he cried)--a god appears!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.18.5#Far other vests thy limbs majestic grace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.18.6#Far other glories lighten from thy face!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.18.7#If heaven be thy abode, with pious care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.18.8#Lo! I the ready sacrifice prepare:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.18.9#Lo! gifts of labour'd gold adorn thy shrine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.18.10#To win thy grace: O save us, power divine!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.19.1#"Few are my days (Ulysses made reply),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.19.2#Nor I, alas! descendant of the sky.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.19.3#I am thy father. O my son! my son!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.19.4#That father, for whose sake thy days have run
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.19.5#One scene of woe! to endless cares consign'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.19.6#And outraged by the wrongs of base mankind."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.20.1#Then, rushing to his arms, he kiss'd his boy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.20.2#With the strong raptures of a parent's joy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.20.3#Tears bathe his cheek, and tears the ground bedew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.20.4#He strain'd him close, as to his breast he grew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.20.5#"Ah me! (exclaims the prince with fond desire)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.20.6#Thou art not--no, thou canst not be my sire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.20.7#Heaven such illusion only can impose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.20.8#By the false joy to aggravate my woes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.20.9#Who but a god can change the general doom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.20.10#And give to wither'd age a youthful bloom!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.20.11#Late, worn with years, in weeds obscene you trod;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.20.12#Now, clothed in majesty, you move a god!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.21.1#"Forbear (he cried,) for Heaven reserve that name;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.21.2#Give to thy father but a father's claim;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.21.3#Other Ulysses shalt thou never see,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.21.4#I am Ulysses, I, my son, am he.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.21.5#Twice ten sad years o'er earth and ocean toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.21.6#'Tis given at length to view my native coast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.21.7#Pallas, unconquer'd maid, my frame surrounds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.21.8#With grace divine: her power admits no bounds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.21.9#She o'er my limbs old age and wrinkles shed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.21.10#Now strong as youth, magnificent I tread.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.21.11#The gods with ease frail man depress or raise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.21.12#Exalt the lowly, or the proud debase."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.1#He spoke and sate. The prince with transport flew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.2#Hung round his neck, while tears his cheek bedew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.3#Nor less the father pour'd a social flood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.4#They wept abundant, and they wept aloud.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.5#As the bold eagle with fierce sorrow stung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.6#Or parent vulture, mourns her ravish'd young;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.7#They cry, they scream, their unfledged brood a prey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.8#To some rude churl, and borne by stealth away:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.9#So they aloud: and tears in tides had run,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.10#Their grief unfinish'd with the setting sun;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.11#But checking the full torrent in its flow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.12#The prince thus interrupts the solemn woe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.13#"What ship transported thee, O father, say;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.22.14#And what bless'd hands have oar'd thee on the way?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.1#"All, all (Ulysses instant made reply),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.2#I tell thee all, my child, my only joy!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.3#Phaeacians bore me to the port assign'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.4#A nation ever to the stranger kind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.5#Wrapp'd in the embrace of sleep, the faithful train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.6#O'er seas convey'd me to my native reign:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.7#Embroider'd vestures, gold, and brass, are laid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.8#Conceal'd in caverns in the sylvan shade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.9#Hither, intent the rival rout to slay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.10#And plan the scene of death, I bend my way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.11#So Pallas wills--but thou, my son, explain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.12#The names and numbers of the audacious train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.13#'Tis mine to judge if better to employ
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.23.14#Assistant force, or singly to destroy."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.1#"O'er earth (returns the prince) resounds thy name,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.2#Thy well-tried wisdom, and thy martial fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.3#Yet at thy words I start, in wonder lost;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.4#Can we engage, not decades but an host?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.5#Can we alone in furious battle stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.6#Against that numerous and determined band?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.7#Hear then their numbers; from Dulichium came
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.8#Twice twenty-six, all peers of mighty name.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.9#Six are their menial train: twice twelve the boast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.10#Of Samos; twenty from Zacynthus' coast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.11#And twelve our country's pride; to these belong
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.12#Medon and Phemius, skill'd in heavenly song.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.13#Two sewers from day to day the revels wait,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.14#Exact of taste, and serve the feast in state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.15#With such a foe the unequal fight to try,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.16#Were by false courage unrevenged to die.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.17#Then what assistant powers you boast relate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.24.18#Ere yet we mingle in the stern debate."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.25.1#"Mark well my voice, (Ulysses straight replies:)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.25.2#What need of aids, if favour'd by the skies?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.25.3#If shielded to the dreadful fight we move,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.25.4#By mighty Pallas, and by thundering Jove?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.26.1#"Sufficient they (Telemachus rejoin'd)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.26.2#Against the banded powers of all mankind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.26.3#They, high enthroned above the rolling clouds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.26.4#Wither the strength of man, and awe the gods."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.1#"Such aids expect (he cries,) when strong in might
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.2#We rise terrific to the task of fight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.3#But thou, when morn salutes the aerial plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.4#The court revisit and the lawless train:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.5#Me thither in disguise Eumaeus leads,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.6#An aged mendicant in tatter'd weeds.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.7#There, if base scorn insult my reverend age,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.8#Bear it, my son! repress thy rising rage.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.9#If outraged, cease that outrage to repel;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.10#Bear it, my son! howe'er thy heart rebel.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.11#Yet strive by prayer and counsel to restrain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.12#Their lawless insults, though thou strive in vain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.13#For wicked ears are deaf to wisdom's call,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.14#And vengeance strikes whom Heaven has doom'd to fall.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.15#Once more attend: when she whose power inspires
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.16#The thinking mind, my soul to vengeance fires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.17#I give the sign: that instant, from beneath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.18#Aloft convey the instruments of death,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.19#Armour and arms; and, if mistrust arise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.27.20#Thus veil the truth in plausible disguise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.28.1#"'These glittering weapons, ere he sail'd to Troy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.28.2#Ulysses view'd with stern heroic joy:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.28.3#Then, beaming o'er the illumined wall they shone;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.28.4#Now dust dishonours, all their lustre gone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.28.5#I bear them hence (so Jove my soul inspires),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.28.6#From the pollution of the fuming fires;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.28.7#Lest when the bowl inflames, in vengeful mood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.28.8#Ye rush to arms, and stain the feast with blood:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.28.9#Oft ready swords in luckless hour incite
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.28.10#The hand of wrath, and arm it for the fight.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.1#"Such be the plea, and by the plea deceive:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.2#For Jove infatuates all, and all believe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.3#Yet leave for each of us a sword to wield,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.4#A pointed javelin, and a fenceful shield.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.5#But by my blood that in thy bosom glows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.6#By that regard a son his father owes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.7#The secret, that thy father lives, retain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.8#Lock'd in thy bosom from the household train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.9#Hide it from all; e'en from Eumaeus hide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.10#From my dear father, and my dearer bride.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.11#One care remains, to note the loyal few
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.12#Whose faith yet lasts among the menial crew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.13#And noting, ere we rise in vengeance, prove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.29.14#Who love his prince; for sure you merit love."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.30.1#To whom the youth: "To emulate, I aim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.30.2#The brave and wise, and my great father's fame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.30.3#But reconsider, since the wisest err,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.30.4#Vengeance resolved, 'tis dangerous to defer.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.30.5#What length of time must we consume in vain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.30.6#Too curious to explore the menial train!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.30.7#While the proud foes, industrious to destroy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.30.8#Thy wealth, in riot the delay enjoy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.30.9#Suffice it in this exigence alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.30.10#To mark the damsels that attend the throne:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.30.11#Dispersed the youth reside; their faith to prove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.30.12#Jove grants henceforth, if thou hast spoke from Jove."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.1#While in debate they waste the hours away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.2#The associates of the prince repass'd the bay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.3#With speed they guide the vessel to the shores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.4#With speed debarking land the naval stores:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.5#Then, faithful to their charge, to Clytius bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.6#And trust the presents to his friendly care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.7#Swift to the queen a herald flies to impart
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.8#Her son's return, and ease a parent's heart:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.9#Lest a sad prey to ever-musing cares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.10#Pale grief destroy what time awhile forbears.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.11#The incautious herald with impatience burns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.12#And cries aloud, "Thy son, O queen, returns;"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.13#Eumaeus sage approach'd the imperial throne,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.14#And breathed his mandate to her ear alone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.15#Then measured back the way. The suitor band,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.16#Stung to the soul, abash'd, confounded, stand;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.17#And issuing from the dome, before the gate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.31.18#With clouded looks, a pale assembly sate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.32.1#At length Eurymachus: "Our hopes are vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.32.2#Telemachus in triumph sails the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.32.3#Haste, rear the mast, the swelling shroud display;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.32.4#Haste, to our ambush'd friends the news convey!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.33.1#Scarce had he spake, when, turning to the strand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.33.2#Amphinomos survey'd the associate band;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.33.3#Full to the bay within the winding shores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.33.4#With gather'd sails they stood, and lifted oars.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.33.5#"O friends!" he cried, elate with rising joy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.33.6#"See to the port secure the vessel fly!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.33.7#Some god has told them, or themselves survey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.33.8#The bark escaped; and measure back their way."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.34.1#Swift at the word descending to the shores,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.34.2#They moor the vessel and unlade the stores:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.34.3#Then, moving from the strand, apart they sate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.34.4#And full and frequent form'd a dire debate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.1#"Lives then the boy? he lives (Antinous cries),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.2#The care of gods and favourite of the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.3#All night we watch'd, till with her orient wheels
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.4#Aurora flamed above the eastern hills,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.5#And from the lofty brow of rocks by day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.6#Took in the ocean with a broad survey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.7#Yet safe he sails; the powers celestial give
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.8#To shun the hidden snares of death, and live.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.9#But die he shall, and thus condemn'd to bleed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.10#Be now the scene of instant death decreed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.11#Hope ye success? undaunted crush the foe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.12#Is he not wise? know this, and strike the blow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.13#Wait ye, till he to arms in council draws
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.14#The Greeks, averse too justly to our cause?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.15#Strike, ere, the states convened, the foe betray
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.16#Our murderous ambush on the watery way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.17#Or choose ye vagrant from their rage to fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.18#Outcasts of earth, to breathe an unknown sky?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.19#The brave prevent misfortune; then be brave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.20#And bury future danger in his grave.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.21#Returns he? ambush'd we'll his walk invade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.22#Or where he hides in solitude and shade;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.23#And give the palace to the queen a dower,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.24#Or him she blesses in the bridal hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.25#But if submissive you resign the sway,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.26#Slaves to a boy, go, flatter and obey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.27#Retire we instant to our native reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.28#Nor be the wealth of kings consumed in vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.29#Then wed whom choice approves: the queen be given
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.35.30#To some blest prince, the prince decreed by Heaven."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.36.1#Abash'd, the suitor train his voice attends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.36.2#Till from his throne Amphinomus ascends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.36.3#Who o'er Dulichium stretch'd his spacious reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.36.4#A land of plenty, bless'd with every grain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.36.5#Chief of the numbers who the queen address'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.36.6#And though displeasing, yet displeasing least.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.36.7#Soft were his words; his actions wisdom sway'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.36.8#Graceful awhile he paused, then mildly said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.37.1#"O friends, forbear! and be the thought withstood:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.37.2#'Tis horrible to shed imperial blood!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.37.3#Consult we first the all-seeing powers above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.37.4#And the sure oracles of righteous Jove.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.37.5#If they assent, e'en by this hand he dies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.37.6#If they forbid, I war not with the skies."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.38.1#He said: the rival train his voice approved,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.38.2#And rising instant to the palace moved.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.38.3#Arrived, with wild tumultuous noise they sate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.38.4#Recumbent on the shining thrones of state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.39.1#The Medon, conscious of their dire debates,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.39.2#The murderous counsel to the queen relates.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.39.3#Touch'd at the dreadful story, she descends:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.39.4#Her hasty steps a damsel train attends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.39.5#Full where the dome its shining valves expands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.39.6#Sudden before the rival powers she stands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.39.7#And, veiling, decent, with a modest shade
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.39.8#Her cheek, indignant to Antinous said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.1#"O void of faith! of all bad men the worst!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.2#Renown'd for wisdom, by the abuse accursed!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.3#Mistaking fame proclaims thy generous mind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.4#Thy deeds denote thee of the basest kind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.5#Wretch! to destroy a prince that friendship gives,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.6#While in his guest his murderer he receives;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.7#Nor dread superior Jove, to whom belong
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.8#The cause of suppliants, and revenge of wrong.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.9#Hast thou forgot, ungrateful as thou art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.10#Who saved thy father with a friendly part?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.11#Lawless he ravaged with his martial powers
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.12#The Taphian pirates on Thesprotia's shores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.13#Enraged, his life, his treasures they demand;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.14#Ulysses saved him from the avenger's hand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.15#And would'st thou evil for his good repay?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.16#His bed dishonour, and his house betray?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.17#Afflict his queen, and with a murderous hand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.40.18#Destroy his heir!--but cease, 'tis I command."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.41.1#"Far hence those fears (Eurymachus replied,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.41.2#O prudent princess! bid thy soul confide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.41.3#Breathes there a man who dares that hero slay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.41.4#While I behold the golden light of day?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.41.5#No: by the righteous powers of heaven I swear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.41.6#His blood in vengeance smokes upon my spear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.41.7#Ulysses, when my infant days I led,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.41.8#With wine sufficed me, and with dainties fed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.41.9#My generous soul abhors the ungrateful part,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.41.10#And my friend's son lives nearest to my heart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.41.11#Then fear no mortal arm; if Heaven destroy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.41.12#We must resign: for man is born to die."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.42.1#Thus smooth he ended, yet his death conspired:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.42.2#Then sorrowing, with sad step the queen retired,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.42.3#With streaming eyes, all comfortless deplored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.42.4#Touch'd with the dear remembrance of her lord:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.42.5#Nor ceased till Pallas bids her sorrows fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.42.6#And in soft slumber seal'd her flowing eye.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.1#And now Eumaeus, at the evening hour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.2#Came late, returning to his sylvan bower.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.3#Ulysses and his son had dress'd with art
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.4#A yearling boar, and gave the gods their part.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.5#Holy repast! That instant from the skies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.6#The martial goddess to Ulysses flies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.7#She waves her golden wand, and reassumes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.8#From every feature every grace that blooms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.9#At once his vestures change; at once she sheds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.10#Age o'er his limbs, that tremble as he treads:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.11#Lest to the queen the swain with transport fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.12#Unable to contain the unruly joy;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.13#When near he drew, the prince breaks forth: "Proclaim
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.14#What tidings, friend? what speaks the voice of fame?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.15#Say, if the suitors measure back the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.43.16#Or still in ambush thirst for blood in vain?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.44.1#"Whether (he cries) they measure back the flood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.44.2#Or still in ambush thirst in vain for blood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.44.3#Escaped my care: where lawless suitors sway,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.44.4#Thy mandate borne my soul disdain'd to stay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.44.5#But from the Hermaean height I cast a view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.44.6#Where to the port a bark high-bounding flew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.44.7#Her freight a shining band: with martial air
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.44.8#Each poised his shield, and each advanced his spear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.44.9#And, if aright these searching eyes survey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.44.10#The eluded suitors stem the watery way."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.45.1#The prince, well pleased to disappoint their wiles,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.45.2#Steals on his sire a glance, and secret smiles.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.45.3#And now, a short repast prepared, they fed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.45.4#Till the keen rage of craving hunger fled:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.45.5#Then to repose withdrawn, apart they lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:16.45.6#And in soft sleep forgot the cares of day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.1.1#Soon as Aurora, daughter of the dawn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.1.2#Sprinkled with roseate light the dewy lawn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.1.3#In haste the prince arose, prepared to part;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.1.4#His hand impatient grasps the pointed dart;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.1.5#Fair on his feet the polish'd sandals shine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.1.6#And thus he greets the master of the swine:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.2.1#"My friend, adieu! let this short stay suffice;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.2.2#I haste to meet my mother's longing eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.2.3#And end her tears, her sorrows and her sighs.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.2.4#But thou, attentive, what we order heed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.2.5#This hapless stranger to the city lead:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.2.6#By public bounty let him there be fed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.2.7#And bless the hand that stretches forth the bread.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.2.8#To wipe the tears from all afflicted eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.2.9#My will may covet, but my power denies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.2.10#If this raise anger in the stranger's thought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.2.11#The pain of anger punishes the fault:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.2.12#The very truth I undisguised declare;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.2.13#For what so easy as to be sincere?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.3.1#To this Ulysses: "What the prince requires
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.3.2#Of swift removal, seconds my desires.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.3.3#To want like mine the peopled town can yield
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.3.4#More hopes of comfort than the lonely field:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.3.5#Nor fits my age to till the labour'd lands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.3.6#Or stoop to tasks a rural lord demands.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.3.7#Adieu! but since this ragged garb can bear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.3.8#So ill the inclemencies of morning air,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.3.9#A few hours' space permit me here to stay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.3.10#My steps Eumaeus shall to town convey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.3.11#With riper beams when Phoebus warms the day."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.1#Thus he: nor aught Telemachus replied,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.2#But left the mansion with a lofty stride:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.3#Schemes of revenge his pondering breast elate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.4#Revolving deep the suitors' sudden fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.5#Arriving now before the imperial hall,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.6#He props his spear against the pillar'd wall;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.7#Then like a lion o'er the threshold bounds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.8#The marble pavement with his steps resounds:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.9#His eye first glanced where Euryclea spreads
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.10#With furry spoils of beasts the splendid beds:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.11#She saw, she wept, she ran with eager pace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.12#And reach'd her master with a long embrace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.13#All crowded round, the family appears
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.14#With wild entrancement, and ecstatic tears.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.15#Swift from above descends the royal fair
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.16#(Her beauteous cheeks the blush of Venus wear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.17#Chasten'd with coy Diana's pensive air);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.18#Hangs o'er her son, in his embraces dies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.19#Rains kisses on his neck, his face, his eyes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.20#Few words she spoke, though much she had to say;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.4.21#And scarce those few, for tears, could force their way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.5.1#"Light of my eyes: he comes! unhoped-for joy!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.5.2#Has Heaven from Pylos brought my lovely boy?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.5.3#So snatch'd from all our cares!--Tell, hast thou known
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.5.4#Thy father's fate, and tell me all thy own."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.6.1#"Oh dearest! most revered of womankind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.6.2#Cease with those tears to melt a manly mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.6.3#(Replied the prince); nor be our fates deplored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.6.4#From death and treason to thy arms restored.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.6.5#Go bathe, and robed in white ascend the towers;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.6.6#With all thy handmaids thank the immortal powers;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.6.7#To every god vow hecatombs to bleed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.6.8#And call Jove's vengeance on their guilty deed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.6.9#While to the assembled council I repair:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.6.10#A stranger sent by Heaven attends me there;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.6.11#My new accepted guest I haste to find,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.6.12#Now to Peiraeus' honour'd charge consign'd."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.1#The matron heard, nor was his word in vain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.2#She bathed; and, robed in white, with all her train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.3#To every god vow'd hecatombs to bleed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.4#And call'd Jove's vengeance on the guilty deed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.5#Arm'd with his lance, the prince then pass'd the gate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.6#Two dogs behind, a faithful guard, await;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.7#Pallas his form with grace divine improves:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.8#The gazing crowd admires him as he moves.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.9#Him, gathering round, the haughty suitors greet
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.10#With semblance fair, but inward deep deceit,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.11#Their false addresses, generous, he denied.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.12#Pass'd on, and sate by faithful Mentor's side;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.13#With Antiphus, and Halitherses sage
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.14#(His father's counsellors, revered for age).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.15#Of his own fortunes, and Ulysses' fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.16#Much ask'd the seniors; till Peiraeus came.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.17#The stranger-guest pursued him close behind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.18#Whom when Telemachus beheld, he join'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.19#He (when Peiraeus ask'd for slaves to bring
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.20#The gifts and treasures of the Spartan king)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.21#Thus thoughtful answer'd: "Those we shall not move,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.22#Dark and unconscious of the will of Jove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.23#We know not yet the full event of all:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.24#Stabb'd in his palace if your prince must fall,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.25#Us, and our house, if treason must o'erthrow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.26#Better a friend possess them than a foe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.27#If death to these, and vengeance Heaven decree,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.28#Riches are welcome then, not else, to me.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.29#Till then retain the gifts."--The hero said,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.30#And in his hand the willing stranger led.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.31#Then disarray'd, the shining bath they sought
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.32#(With unguents smooth) of polish'd marble wrought:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.33#Obedient handmaids with assistant toil
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.34#Supply the limpid wave, and fragrant oil:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.35#Then o'er their limbs refulgent robes they threw,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.36#And fresh from bathing to their seats withdrew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.37#The golden ewer a nymph attendant brings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.38#Replenish'd from the pure translucent springs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.39#With copious streams that golden ewer supplies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.40#A silver layer of capacious size.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.41#They wash: the table, in fair order spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.42#Is piled with viands and the strength of bread.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.43#Full opposite, before the folding gate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.44#The pensive mother sits in humble state;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.45#Lowly she sate, and with dejected view
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.46#The fleecy threads her ivory fingers drew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.47#The prince and stranger shared the genial feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.7.48#Till now the rage of thirst and hunger ceased.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.8.1#When thus the queen: "My son! my only friend!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.8.2#Say, to my mournful couch shall I ascend?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.8.3#(The couch deserted now a length of years;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.8.4#The couch for ever water'd with my tears;)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.8.5#Say, wilt thou not (ere yet the suitor crew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.8.6#Return, and riot shakes our walls anew),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.8.7#Say, wilt thou not the least account afford?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.8.8#The least glad tidings of my absent lord?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.1#To her the youth. "We reach'd the Pylian plains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.2#Where Nestor, shepherd of his people, reigns.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.3#All arts of tenderness to him are known,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.4#Kind to Ulysses' race as to his own;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.5#No father with a fonder grasp of joy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.6#Strains to his bosom his long-absent boy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.7#But all unknown, if yet Ulysses breathe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.8#Or glide a spectre in the realms beneath;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.9#For farther search, his rapid steeds transport
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.10#My lengthen'd journey to the Spartan court.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.11#There Argive Helen I beheld, whose charms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.12#(So Heaven decreed) engaged the great in arms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.13#My cause of coming told, he thus rejoin'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.9.14#And still his words live perfect in my mind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.1#"'Heavens! would a soft, inglorious, dastard train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.2#An absent hero's nuptial joys profane
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.3#So with her young, amid the woodland shades,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.4#A timorous hind the lion's court invades,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.5#Leaves in that fatal lair her tender fawns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.6#And climbs the cliffs, or feeds along the lawns;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.7#Meantime returning, with remorseless sway
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.8#The monarch savage rends the panting prey:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.9#With equal fury, and with equal fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.10#Shall great Ulysses reassert his claim.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.11#O Jove! supreme! whom men and gods revere;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.12#And thou whose lustre gilds the rolling sphere!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.13#With power congenial join'd, propitious aid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.14#The chief adopted by the martial maid!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.15#Such to our wish the warrior soon restore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.16#As when, contending on the Lesbian shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.17#His prowess Philomelides confess'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.18#And loud acclaiming Greeks the victor bless'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.19#Then soon the invaders of his bed, and throne,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.20#Their love presumptuous shall by death atone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.21#Now what you question of my ancient friend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.22#With truth I answer; thou the truth attend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.23#Learn what I heard the sea-born seer relate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.24#Whose eye can pierce the dark recess of fate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.25#Sole in an isle, imprison'd by the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.26#The sad survivor of his numerous train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.27#Ulysses lies; detain'd by magic charms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.28#And press'd unwilling in Calypso's arms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.29#No sailors there, no vessels to convey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.30#No oars to cut the immeasurable way.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.31#This told Atrides, and he told no more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.10.32#Then safe I voyaged to my native shore."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.1#He ceased; nor made the pensive queen reply,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.2#But droop'd her head, and drew a secret sigh.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.3#When Theoclymenus the seer began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.4#"O suffering consort of the suffering man!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.5#What human knowledge could, those kings might tell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.6#But I the secrets of high heaven reveal.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.7#Before the first of gods be this declared,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.8#Before the board whose blessings we have shared;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.9#Witness the genial rites, and witness all
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.10#This house holds sacred in her ample wall!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.11#E'en now, this instant, great Ulysses, laid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.12#At rest, or wandering in his country's shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.13#Their guilty deeds, in hearing, and in view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.14#Secret revolves; and plans the vengeance due.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.15#Of this sure auguries the gods bestow'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.16#When first our vessel anchor'd in your road."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.17#"Succeed those omens, Heaven! (the queen rejoin'd)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.18#So shall our bounties speak a grateful mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.19#And every envied happiness attend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.20#The man who calls Penelope his friend."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.21#Thus communed they: while in the marble court
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.22#(Scene of their insolence) the lords resort:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.23#Athwart the spacious square each tries his art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.24#To whirl the disk, or aim the missile dart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.25#Now did the hour of sweet repast arrive,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.26#And from the field the victim flocks they drive:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.27#Medon the herald (one who pleased them best,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.28#And honour'd with a portion of their feast),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.29#To bid the banquet, interrupts their play:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.30#Swift to the hall they haste; aside they lay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.31#Their garments, and succinct the victims slay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.32#Then sheep, and goats, and bristly porkers bled,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.33#And the proud steer was o'er the marble spread.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.34#While thus the copious banquet they provide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.35#Along the road, conversing side by side,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.36#Proceed Ulysses and the faithful swain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.37#When thus Eumaeus, generous and humane:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.38#"To town, observant of our lord's behest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.39#Now let us speed; my friend no more my guest!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.40#Yet like myself I wish thee here preferr'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.41#Guard of the flock, or keeper of the herd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.42#But much to raise my master's wrath I fear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.43#The wrath of princes ever is severe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.44#Then heed his will, and be our journey made
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.45#While the broad beams of Phoebus are display'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.46#Or ere brown evening spreads her chilly shade."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.47#"Just thy advice (the prudent chief rejoin'd),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.48#And such as suits the dictate of my mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.49#Lead on: but help me to some staff to stay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.50#My feeble step, since rugged is the way."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.51#Across his shoulders then the scrip he flung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.52#Wide-patch'd, and fasten'd by a twisted thong.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.53#A staff Eumaeus gave. Along the way
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.54#Cheerly they fare: behind, the keepers stay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.55#These with their watchful dogs (a constant guard)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.56#Supply his absence, and attend the herd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.57#And now his city strikes the monarch's eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.58#Alas! how changed! a man of miseries;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.59#Propp'd on a staff, a beggar old and bare
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.60#In rags dishonest fluttering with the air!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.61#Now pass'd the rugged road, they journey down
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.62#The cavern'd way descending to the town,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.63#Where, from the rock, with liquid drops distils
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.64#A limpid fount; that spread in parting rills
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.65#Its current thence to serve the city brings;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.66#An useful work, adorn'd by ancient kings.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.67#Neritus, Ithacus, Polyctor, there,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.68#In sculptured stone immortalized their care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.69#In marble urns received it from above,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.70#And shaded with a green surrounding grove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.71#Where silver alders, in high arches twined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.72#Drink the cool stream, and tremble to the wind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.73#Beneath, sequester'd to the nymphs, is seen
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.74#A mossy altar, deep embower'd in green;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.75#Where constant vows by travellers are paid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.11.76#And holy horrors solemnize the shade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.12.1#Here with his goats (not vow'd to sacred fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.12.2#But pamper'd luxury) Melanthias came:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.12.3#Two grooms attend him. With an envious look
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.12.4#He eyed the stranger, and imperious spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.1#"The good old proverb how this pair fulfil!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.2#One rogue is usher to another still.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.3#Heaven with a secret principle endued
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.4#Mankind, to seek their own similitude.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.5#Where goes the swineherd with that ill-look'd guest?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.6#That giant-glutton, dreadful at a feast!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.7#Full many a post have those broad shoulders worn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.8#From every great man's gate repulsed with scorn:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.9#To no brave prize aspired the worthless swain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.10#'Twas but for scraps he ask'd, and ask'd in vain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.11#To beg, than work, he better understands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.12#Or we perhaps might take him off thy hands.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.13#For any office could the slave be good,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.14#To cleanse the fold, or help the kids to food.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.15#If any labour those big joints could learn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.16#Some whey, to wash his bowels, he might earn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.17#To cringe, to whine, his idle hands to spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.18#Is all, by which that graceless maw is fed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.19#Yet hear me! if thy impudence but dare
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.20#Approach yon wall, I prophesy thy fare:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.21#Dearly, full dearly, shalt thou buy thy bread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.13.22#With many a footstool thundering at thy head."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.1#He thus: nor insolent of word alone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.2#Spurn'd with his rustic heel his king unknown;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.3#Spurn'd, but not moved: he like a pillar stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.4#Nor stirr'd an inch, contemptuous, from the road:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.5#Doubtful, or with his staff to strike him dead,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.6#Or greet the pavement with his worthless head.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.7#Short was that doubt; to quell his rage inured,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.8#The hero stood self-conquer'd, and endured.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.9#But hateful of the wretch, Eumaeus heaved
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.10#His hands obtesting, and this prayer conceived:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.11#"Daughters of Jove! who from the ethereal bowers
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.12#Descend to swell the springs, and feed the flowers!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.13#Nymphs of this fountain! to whose sacred names
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.14#Our rural victims mount in blazing flames!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.15#To whom Ulysses' piety preferr'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.16#The yearly firstlings of his flock and herd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.17#Succeed my wish, your votary restore:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.18#Oh, be some god his convoy to our shore!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.19#Due pains shall punish then this slave's offence,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.20#And humble all his airs of insolence,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.21#Who, proudly stalking, leaves the herds at large,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.14.22#Commences courtier, and neglects his charge."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.15.1#"What mutters he? (Melanthius sharp rejoins;)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.15.2#This crafty miscreant, big with dark designs?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.15.3#The day shall come--nay, 'tis already near--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.15.4#When, slave! to sell thee at a price too dear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.15.5#Must be my care; and hence transport thee o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.15.6#A load and scandal to this happy shore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.15.7#Oh! that as surely great Apollo's dart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.15.8#Or some brave suitor's sword, might pierce the heart
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.15.9#Of the proud son; as that we stand this hour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.15.10#In lasting safety from the father's power!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.16.1#So spoke the wretch, but, shunning farther fray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.16.2#Turn'd his proud step, and left them on their way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.16.3#Straight to the feastful palace he repair'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.16.4#Familiar enter'd, and the banquet shared;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.16.5#Beneath Eurymachus, his patron lord,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.16.6#He took his place, and plenty heap'd the board.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.17.1#Meantime they heard, soft circling in the sky
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.17.2#Sweet airs ascend, and heavenly minstrelsy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.17.3#(For Phemius to the lyre attuned the strain):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.17.4#Ulysses hearken'd, then address'd the swain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.18.1#"Well may this palace admiration claim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.18.2#Great and respondent to the master's fame!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.18.3#Stage above stage the imperial structure stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.18.4#Holds the chief honours, and the town commands:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.18.5#High walls and battlements the courts inclose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.18.6#And the strong gates defy a host of foes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.18.7#Far other cares its dwellers now employ;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.18.8#The throng'd assembly and the feast of joy:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.18.9#I see the smokes of sacrifice aspire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.18.10#And hear (what graces every feast) the lyre."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.19.1#Then thus Eumaeus: "Judge we which were best;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.19.2#Amidst yon revellers a sudden guest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.19.3#Choose you to mingle, while behind I stay?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.19.4#Or I first entering introduce the way?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.19.5#Wait for a space without, but wait not long;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.19.6#This is the house of violence and wrong:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.19.7#Some rude insult thy reverend age may bear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.19.8#For like their lawless lords the servants are."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.20.1#"Just is, O friend! thy caution, and address'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.20.2#(Replied the chief, to no unheedful breast:)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.20.3#The wrongs and injuries of base mankind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.20.4#Fresh to my sense, and always in my mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.20.5#The bravely-patient to no fortune yields:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.20.6#On rolling oceans, and in fighting fields,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.20.7#Storms have I pass'd, and many a stern debate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.20.8#And now in humbler scene submit to fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.20.9#What cannot want? The best she will expose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.20.10#And I am learn'd in all her train of woes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.20.11#She fills with navies, hosts, and loud alarms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.20.12#The sea, the land, and shakes the world with arms!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.1#Thus, near the gates conferring as they drew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.2#Argus, the dog, his ancient master knew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.3#He not unconscious of the voice and tread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.4#Lifts to the sound his ear, and rears his head;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.5#Bred by Ulysses, nourish'd at his board,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.6#But, ah! not fated long to please his lord;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.7#To him, his swiftness and his strength were vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.8#The voice of glory call'd him o'er the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.9#Till then in every sylvan chase renown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.10#With Argus, Argus, rung the woods around;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.11#With him the youth pursued the goat or fawn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.12#Or traced the mazy leveret o'er the lawn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.13#Now left to man's ingratitude he lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.14#Unhoused, neglected in the public way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.15#And where on heaps the rich manure was spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.21.16#Obscene with reptiles, took his sordid bed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.22.1#He knew his lord; he knew, and strove to meet;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.22.2#In vain he strove to crawl and kiss his feet;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.22.3#Yet (all he could) his tail, his tears, his eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.22.4#Salute his master, and confess his joys.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.22.5#Soft pity touch'd the mighty master's soul;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.22.6#Adown his cheek a tear unbidden stole,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.22.7#Stole unperceived: he turn'd his head and dried
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.22.8#The drop humane: then thus impassion'd cried:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.23.1#"What noble beast in this abandon'd state
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.23.2#Lies here all helpless at Ulysses' gate?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.23.3#His bulk and beauty speak no vulgar praise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.23.4#If, as he seems, he was in better days,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.23.5#Some care his age deserves; or was he prized
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.23.6#For worthless beauty? therefore now despised;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.23.7#Such dogs and men there are, mere things of state;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.23.8#And always cherish'd by their friends, the great."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.1#"Not Argus so, (Eumaeus thus rejoin'd,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.2#But served a master of a nobler kind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.3#Who, never, never shall behold him more!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.4#Long, long since perish'd on a distant shore!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.5#Oh had you seen him, vigorous, bold, and young,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.6#Swift as a stag, and as a lion strong:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.7#Him no fell savage on the plain withstood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.8#None 'scaped him bosom'd in the gloomy wood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.9#His eye how piercing, and his scent how true,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.10#To wind the vapour on the tainted dew!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.11#Such, when Ulysses left his natal coast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.12#Now years unnerve him, and his lord is lost!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.13#The women keep the generous creature bare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.14#A sleek and idle race is all their care:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.15#The master gone, the servants what restrains?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.16#Or dwells humanity where riot reigns?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.17#Jove fix'd it certain, that whatever day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.24.18#Makes man a slave, takes half his worth away."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.25.1#This said, the honest herdsman strode before;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.25.2#The musing monarch pauses at the door:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.25.3#The dog, whom Fate had granted to behold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.25.4#His lord, when twenty tedious years had roll'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.25.5#Takes a last look, and having seen him, dies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.25.6#So closed for ever faithful Argus' eyes!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.26.1#And now Telemachus, the first of all,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.26.2#Observed Eumaeus entering in the hall;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.26.3#Distant he saw, across the shady dome;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.26.4#Then gave a sign, and beckon'd him to come:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.26.5#There stood an empty seat, where late was placed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.26.6#In order due, the steward of the feast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.26.7#(Who now was busied carving round the board,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.26.8#Eumaeus took, and placed it near his lord.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.26.9#Before him instant was the banquet spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.26.10#And the bright basket piled with loaves of bread.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.27.1#Next came Ulysses lowly at the door,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.27.2#A figure despicable, old, and poor.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.27.3#In squalid vests, with many a gaping rent,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.27.4#Propp'd or a staff, and trembling as he went.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.27.5#Then, resting on the threshold of the gate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.27.6#Against a cypress pillar lean'd his weight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.27.7#Smooth'd by the workman to a polish'd plane);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.27.8#The thoughtful son beheld, and call'd his swain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.28.1#"These viands, and this bread, Eumaeus! bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.28.2#And let yon mendicant our plenty share:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.28.3#And let him circle round the suitors' board,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.28.4#And try the bounty of each gracious lord.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.28.5#Bold let him ask, encouraged thus by me:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.28.6#How ill, alas! do want and shame agree!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.1#His lord's command the faithful servant bears:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.2#The seeming beggar answers with his prayers:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.3#"Bless'd be Telemachus! in every deed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.4#Inspire him. Jove! in every wish succeed!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.5#This said, the portion from his son convey'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.6#With smiles receiving on his scrip he laid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.7#Long has the minstrel swept the sounding wire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.8#He fed, and ceased when silence held the lyre.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.9#Soon as the suitors from the banquet rose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.10#Minerva prompts the man of mighty woes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.11#To tempt their bounties with a suppliant's art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.12#And learn the generous from the ignoble heart
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.13#(Not but his soul, resentful as humane,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.14#Dooms to full vengeance all the offending train);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.15#With speaking eyes, and voice of plaintive sound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.16#Humble he moves, imploring all around.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.17#The proud feel pity, and relief bestow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.18#With such an image touch'd of human woe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.19#Inquiring all, their wonder they confess,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.29.20#And eye the man, majestic in distress.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.30.1#While thus they gaze and question with their eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.30.2#The bold Melanthius to their thought replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.30.3#"My lords! this stranger of gigantic port
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.30.4#The good Eumaeus usher'd to your court.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.30.5#Full well I mark'd the features of his face,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.30.6#Though all unknown his clime, or noble race."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.31.1#"And is this present, swineherd! of thy band?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.31.2#Bring'st thou these vagrants to infest the land?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.31.3#(Returns Antinous with retorted eye)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.31.4#Objects uncouth, to check the genial joy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.31.5#Enough of these our court already grace;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.31.6#Of giant stomach, and of famish'd face.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.31.7#Such guests Eumaeus to his country brings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.31.8#To share our feast, and lead the life of kings."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.1#To whom the hospitable swain rejoins:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.2#"Thy passion, prince, belies thy knowing mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.3#Who calls, from distant nations to his own,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.4#The poor, distinguish'd by their wants alone?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.5#Round the wide world are sought those men divine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.6#Who public structures raise, or who design;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.7#Those to whose eyes the gods their ways reveal,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.8#Or bless with salutary arts to heal;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.9#But chief to poets such respect belongs,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.10#By rival nations courted for their songs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.11#These states invite, and mighty kings admire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.12#Wide as the sun displays his vital fire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.13#It is not so with want! how few that feed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.14#A wretch unhappy, merely for his need!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.15#Unjust to me, and all that serve the state,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.16#To love Ulysses is to raise thy hate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.17#For me, suffice the approbation won
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.32.18#Of my great mistress, and her godlike son."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.33.1#To him Telemachus: "No more incense
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.33.2#The man by nature prone to insolence:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.33.3#Injurious minds just answers but provoke"--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.33.4#Then turning to Antinous, thus he spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.33.5#"Thanks to thy care! whose absolute command
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.33.6#Thus drives the stranger from our court and land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.33.7#Heaven bless its owner with a better mind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.33.8#From envy free, to charity inclined.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.33.9#This both Penelope and I afford:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.33.10#Then, prince! be bounteous of Ulysses' board.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.33.11#To give another's is thy hand so slow?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.33.12#So much more sweet to spoil than to bestow?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.34.1#"Whence, great Telemachus! this lofty strain?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.34.2#(Antinous cries with insolent disdain):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.34.3#Portions like mine if every suitor gave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.34.4#Our walls this twelvemonth should not see the slave."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.1#He spoke, and lifting high above the board
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.2#His ponderous footstool, shook it at his lord.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.3#The rest with equal hand conferr'd the bread:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.4#He fill'd his scrip, and to the threshold sped;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.5#But first before Antinous stopp'd, and said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.6#"Bestow, my friend! thou dost not seem the worst
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.7#Of all the Greeks, but prince-like and the first;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.8#Then, as in dignity, be first in worth,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.9#And I shall praise thee through the boundless earth.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.10#Once I enjoy'd in luxury of state
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.11#Whate'er gives man the envied name of great;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.12#Wealth, servants, friends, were mine in better days
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.13#And hospitality was then my praise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.14#In every sorrowing soul I pour'd delight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.15#And poverty stood smiling in my sight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.16#But Jove, all-governing, whose only will
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.17#Determines fate, and mingles good with ill,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.18#Sent me (to punish my pursuit of gain)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.19#With roving pirates o'er the Egyptian main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.20#By Egypt's silver flood our ships we moor;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.21#Our spies commission'd straight the coast explore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.22#But impotent of mind, the lawless will
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.23#The country ravage, and the natives kill.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.24#The spreading clamour to their city flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.25#And horse and foot in mingled tumults rise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.26#The reddening dawn reveals the hostile fields,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.27#Horrid with bristly spears, and gleaming shields:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.28#Jove thunder'd on their side: our guilty head
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.29#We turn'd to flight; the gathering vengeance spread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.30#On all parts round, and heaps on heaps lay dead.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.31#Some few the foe in servitude detain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.32#Death ill exchanged for bondage and for pain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.33#Unhappy me a Cyprian took aboard,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.34#And gave to Dmetor, Cyprus' haughty lord:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.35#Hither, to 'scape his chains, my course I steer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.35.36#Still cursed by Fortune, and insulted here!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.36.1#To whom Antinous thus his rage express'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.36.2#"What god has plagued us with this gourmand guest?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.36.3#Unless at distance, wretch! thou keep behind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.36.4#Another isle, than Cyprus more unkind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.36.5#Another Egypt shalt thou quickly find.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.36.6#From all thou begg'st, a bold audacious slave;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.36.7#Nor all can give so much as thou canst crave.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.36.8#Nor wonder I, at such profusion shown;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.36.9#Shameless they give, who give what's not their own."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.37.1#The chief, retiring: "Souls, like that in thee,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.37.2#Ill suits such forms of grace and dignity.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.37.3#Nor will that hand to utmost need afford
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.37.4#The smallest portion of a wasteful board,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.37.5#Whose luxury whole patrimonies sweeps,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.37.6#Yet starving want, amidst the riot, weeps."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.38.1#The haughty suitor with resentment burns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.38.2#And, sourly smiling, this reply returns:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.38.3#"Take that, ere yet thou quit this princely throng;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.38.4#And dumb for ever be thy slanderous tongue!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.38.5#He said, and high the whirling tripod flung.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.38.6#His shoulder-blade received the ungentle shock;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.38.7#He stood, and moved not, like a marble rock;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.38.8#But shook his thoughtful head, nor more complain'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.38.9#Sedate of soul, his character sustain'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.38.10#And inly form'd revenge; then back withdrew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.38.11#Before his feet the well fill'd scrip he threw,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.38.12#And thus with semblance mild address'd the crew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.39.1#"May what I speak your princely minds approve,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.39.2#Ye peers and rivals in this noble love!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.39.3#Not for the hurt I grieve, but for the cause.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.39.4#If, when the sword our country's quarrel draws,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.39.5#Or if, defending what is justly dear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.39.6#From Mars impartial some broad wound we bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.39.7#The generous motive dignifies the scar.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.39.8#But for mere want, how hard to suffer wrong!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.39.9#Want brings enough of other ills along!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.39.10#Yet, if injustice never be secure,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.39.11#If fiends revenge, and gods assert the poor,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.39.12#Death shall lay low the proud aggressor's head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.39.13#And make the dust Antinous' bridal bed."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.40.1#"Peace, wretch! and eat thy bread without offence
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.40.2#(The suitor cried), or force shall drag thee hence,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.40.3#Scourge through the public street, and cast thee there,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.40.4#A mangled carcase for the hounds to tear."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.41.1#His furious deed the general anger moved,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.41.2#All, even the worst, condemn'd; and some reproved.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.41.3#"Was ever chief for wars like these renown'd?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.41.4#Ill fits the stranger and the poor to wound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.41.5#Unbless'd thy hand! if in this low disguise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.41.6#Wander, perhaps, some inmate of the skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.41.7#They (curious oft of mortal actions) deign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.41.8#In forms like these to round the earth and main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.41.9#Just and unjust recording in their mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.41.10#And with sure eyes inspecting all mankind."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.42.1#Telemachus, absorb'd in thought severe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.42.2#Nourish'd deep anguish, though he shed no tear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.42.3#But the dark brow of silent sorrow shook:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.42.4#While thus his mother to her virgins spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.43.1#"On him and his may the bright god of day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.43.2#That base, inhospitable blow repay!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.43.3#The nurse replies: "If Jove receives my prayer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.43.4#Not one survives to breathe to-morrow's air."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.44.1#"All, all are foes, and mischief is their end;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.44.2#Antinous most to gloomy death a friend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.44.3#(Replies the queen): the stranger begg'd their grace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.44.4#And melting pity soften'd every face;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.44.5#From every other hand redress he found,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.44.6#But fell Antinous answer'd with a wound."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.44.7#Amidst her maids thus spoke the prudent queen,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.44.8#Then bade Eumaeus call the pilgrim in.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.44.9#"Much of the experienced man I long to hear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.44.10#If or his certain eye, or listening ear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.44.11#Have learn'd the fortunes of my wandering lord?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.44.12#Thus she, and good Eumaeus took the word:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.45.1#"A private audience if thy grace impart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.45.2#The stranger's words may ease the royal heart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.45.3#His sacred eloquence in balm distils,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.45.4#And the soothed heart with secret pleasure fills.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.45.5#Three days have spent their beams, three nights have run
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.45.6#Their silent journey, since his tale begun,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.45.7#Unfinish'd yet; and yet I thirst to hear!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.45.8#As when some heaven-taught poet charms the ear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.45.9#(Suspending sorrow with celestial strain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.45.10#Breathed from the gods to soften human pain)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.45.11#Time steals away with unregarded wing,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.45.12#And the soul hears him, though he cease to sing
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.46.1#"Ulysses late he saw, on Cretan ground
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.46.2#(His fathers guest), for Minos' birth renown'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.46.3#He now but waits the wind to waft him o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.46.4#With boundless treasure, from Thesprotia's shore."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.47.1#To this the queen: "The wanderer let me hear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.47.2#While yon luxurious race indulge their cheer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.47.3#Devour the grazing ox, and browsing goat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.47.4#And turn my generous vintage down their throat.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.47.5#For where's an arm, like thine, Ulysses! strong,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.47.6#To curb wild riot, and to punish wrong?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.48.1#She spoke. Telemachus then sneezed aloud;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.48.2#Constrain'd, his nostril echoed through the crowd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.48.3#The smiling queen the happy omen bless'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.49.1#"So may these impious fall, by Fate oppress'd!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.49.2#Then to Eumaeus: "Bring the stranger, fly!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.49.3#And if my questions meet a true reply,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.49.4#Graced with a decent robe he shall retire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.49.5#A gift in season which his wants require."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.50.1#Thus spoke Penelope. Eumaeus flies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.50.2#In duteous haste, and to Ulysses cries:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.50.3#"The queen invites thee, venerable guest!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.50.4#A secret instinct moves her troubled breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.50.5#Of her long absent lord from thee to gain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.50.6#Some light, and soothe her soul's eternal pain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.50.7#If true, if faithful thou, her grateful mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.50.8#Of decent robes a present has design'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.50.9#So finding favour in the royal eye,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.50.10#Thy other wants her subjects shall supply."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.1#"Fair truth alone (the patient man replied)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.2#My words shall dictate, and my lips shall guide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.3#To him, to me, one common lot was given,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.4#In equal woes, alas! involved by Heaven.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.5#Much of his fates I know; but check'd by fear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.6#I stand; the hand of violence is here:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.7#Here boundless wrongs the starry skies invade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.8#And injured suppliants seek in vain for aid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.9#Let for a space the pensive queen attend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.10#Nor claim my story till the sun descend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.11#Then in such robes as suppliants may require,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.12#Composed and cheerful by the genial fire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.13#When loud uproar and lawless riot cease,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.51.14#Shall her pleased ear receive my words in peace."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.52.1#Swift to the queen returns the gentle swain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.52.2#"And say (she cries), does fear or shame detain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.52.3#The cautious stranger? With the begging kind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.52.4#Shame suits but ill." Eumaeus thus rejoin'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.53.1#"He only asks a more propitious hour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.53.2#And shuns (who would not?) wicked men in power;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.53.3#At evening mild (meet season to confer)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.53.4#By turns to question, and by turns to hear."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.54.1#"Whoe'er this guest (the prudent queen replies)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.54.2#His every step and every thought is wise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.54.3#For men like these on earth he shall not find
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.54.4#In all the miscreant race of human kind."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.54.5#Thus she. Eumaeus all her words attends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.54.6#And, parting, to the suitor powers descends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.54.7#There seeks Telemachus, and thus apart
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.54.8#In whispers breathes the fondness of his heart:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.55.1#"The time, my lord, invites me to repair
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.55.2#Hence to the lodge; my charge demands my care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.55.3#These sons of murder thirst thy life to take;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.55.4#O guard it, guard it, for thy servant's sake!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.56.1#"Thanks to my friend (he cries): but now the hour
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.56.2#Of night draws on, go seek the rural bower:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.56.3#But first refresh: and at the dawn of day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.56.4#Hither a victim to the gods convey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.56.5#Our life to Heaven's immortal powers we trust,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.56.6#Safe in their care, for Heaven protects the just."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.57.1#Observant of his voice, Eumaeus sate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.57.2#And fed recumbent on a chair of state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.57.3#Then instant rose, and as he moved along,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.57.4#'Twas riot all amid the suitor throng,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.57.5#They feast, they dance, and raise the mirthful song
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.57.6#Till now, declining towards the close of day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:17.57.7#The sun obliquely shot his dewy ray.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.1.1#While fix'd in thought the pensive hero sate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.1.2#A mendicant approach'd the royal gate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.1.3#A surly vagrant of the giant kind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.1.4#The stain of manhood, of a coward mind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.1.5#From feast to feast, insatiate to devour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.1.6#He flew, attendant on the genial hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.1.7#Him on his mother's knees, when babe he lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.1.8#She named Arnaeus on his natal day:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.1.9#But Irus his associates call'd the boy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.1.10#Practised the common messenger to fly;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.1.11#Irus, a name expressive of the employ.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.2.1#From his own roof, with meditated blows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.2.2#He strove to drive the man of mighty woes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.1#"Hence, dotard! hence, and timely speed thy way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.2#Lest dragg'd in vengeance thou repent thy stay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.3#See how with nods assent yon princely train!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.4#But honouring age, in mercy I refrain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.5#In peace away! lest, if persuasions fail,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.6#This arm with blows more eloquent prevail."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.7#To whom, with stern regard: "O insolence,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.8#Indecently to rail without offence!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.9#What bounty gives without a rival share;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.10#I ask, what harms not thee, to breathe this air:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.11#Alike on alms we both precarious live:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.12#And canst thou envy when the great relieve?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.13#Know, from the bounteous heavens all riches flow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.14#And what man gives, the gods by man bestow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.15#Proud as thou art, henceforth no more be proud,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.16#Lest I imprint my vengeance in thy blood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.17#Old as I am, should once my fury burn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.3.18#How would'st thou fly, nor e'en in thought return!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.4.1#"Mere woman-glutton! (thus the churl replied;)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.4.2#A tongue so flippant, with a throat so wide!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.4.3#Why cease I gods! to dash those teeth away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.4.4#Like some wild boar's, that, greedy of his prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.4.5#Uproots the bearded corn? Rise, try the fight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.4.6#Gird well thy loins, approach, and feel my might:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.4.7#Sure of defeat, before the peers engage:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.4.8#Unequal fight, when youth contends with age!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.5.1#Thus in a wordy war their tongues display
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.5.2#More fierce intents, preluding to the fray;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.5.3#Antinous hears, and in a jovial vein,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.5.4#Thus with loud laughter to the suitor train:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.6.1#"This happy day in mirth, my friends, employ,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.6.2#And lo! the gods conspire to crown our joy;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.6.3#See ready for the fight, and hand to hand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.6.4#Yon surly mendicants contentious stand:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.6.5#Why urge we not to blows!" Well pleased they spring
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.6.6#Swift from their seats, and thickening form a ring.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.7.1#To whom Antinous: "Lo! enrich'd with blood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.7.2#A kid's well-fatted entrails (tasteful food)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.7.3#On glowing embers lie; on him bestow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.7.4#The choicest portion who subdues his foe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.7.5#Grant him unrivall'd in these walls to stay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.7.6#The sole attendant on the genial day."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.8.1#The lords applaud: Ulysses then with art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.8.2#And fears well-feign'd, disguised his dauntless heart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.9.1#"Worn as I am with age, decay'd with woe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.9.2#Say, is it baseness to decline the foe?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.9.3#Hard conflict! when calamity and age
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.9.4#With vigorous youth, unknown to cares, engage!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.9.5#Yet, fearful of disgrace, to try the day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.9.6#Imperious hunger bids, and I obey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.9.7#But swear, impartial arbiters of right,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.9.8#Swear to stand neutral, while we cope in fight."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.10.1#The peers assent: when straight his sacred head
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.10.2#Telemachus upraised, and sternly said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.10.3#"Stranger, if prompted to chastise the wrong
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.10.4#Of this bold insolent, confide, be strong!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.10.5#The injurious Greek that dares attempt a blow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.10.6#That instant makes Telemachus his foe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.10.7#And these my friends shall guard the sacred ties
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.10.8#Of hospitality, for they are wise."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.11.1#Then, girding his strong loins, the king prepares
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.11.2#To close in combat, and his body bares;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.11.3#Broad spread his shoulders, and his nervous thighs
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.11.4#By just degrees, like well-turn'd columns, rise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.11.5#Ample his chest, his arms are round and long,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.11.6#And each strong joint Minerva knits more strong
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.11.7#(Attendant on her chief): the suitor-crowd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.11.8#With wonder gaze, and gazing speak aloud:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.11.9#"Irus! alas! shall Irus be no more?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.11.10#Black fate impends, and this the avenging hour!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.11.11#Gods! how his nerves a matchless strength proclaim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.11.12#Swell o'er his well-strong limbs, and brace his frame!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.12.1#Then pale with fears, and sickening at the sight;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.12.2#They dragg'd the unwilling Irus to the fight;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.12.3#From his blank visage fled the coward blood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.12.4#And his flesh trembled as aghast he stood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.13.1#"O that such baseness should disgrace the light?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.13.2#O hide it, death, in everlasting night!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.13.3#(Exclaims Antinous;) can a vigorous foe
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.13.4#Meanly decline to combat age and woe?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.13.5#But hear me wretch! if recreant in the fray
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.13.6#That huge bulk yield this ill-contested day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.13.7#Instant thou sail'st, to Eschetus resign'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.13.8#A tyrant, fiercest of the tyrant kind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.13.9#Who casts thy mangled ears and nose a prey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.13.10#To hungry dogs, and lops the man away."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.1#While with indignant scorn he sternly spoke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.2#In every joint the trembling Irus shook.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.3#Now front to front each frowning champion stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.4#And poises high in air his adverse hands.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.5#The chief yet doubts, or to the shades below
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.6#To fell the giant at one vengeful blow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.7#Or save his life, and soon his life to save
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.8#The king resolves, for mercy sways the brave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.9#That instant Irus his huge arm extends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.10#Full on his shoulder the rude weight descends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.11#The sage Ulysses, fearful to disclose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.12#The hero latent in the man of woes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.13#Check'd half his might; yet rising to the stroke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.14#His jawbone dash'd, the crashing jawbone broke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.15#Down dropp'd he stupid from the stunning wound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.16#His feet extended quivering, beat the ground;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.17#His mouth and nostrils spout a purple flood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.14.18#His teeth, all shatter'd, rush inmix'd with blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.15.1#The peers transported, as outstretch'd he lies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.15.2#With bursts of laughter rend the vaulted skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.15.3#Then dragg'd along, all bleeding from the wound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.15.4#His length of carcase trailing prints the ground:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.15.5#Raised on his feet, again he reels, he falls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.15.6#Till propp'd, reclining on the palace walls:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.15.7#Then to his hand a staff the victor gave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.15.8#And thus with just reproach address'd the slave:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.15.9#"There terrible, affright with dogs, and reign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.15.10#A dreaded tyrant o'er the bestial train!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.15.11#But mercy to the poor and stranger show,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.15.12#Lest Heaven in vengeance send some mightier woe."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.16.1#Scornful he spoke, and o'er his shoulder flung
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.16.2#The broad-patch'd scrip in tatters hung
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.16.3#Ill join'd, and knotted to a twisted thong.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.16.4#Then, turning short, disdain'd a further stay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.16.5#But to the palace measured back the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.16.6#There, as he rested gathering in a ring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.16.7#The peers with smiles address'd their unknown king:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.16.8#"Stranger, may Jove and all the aerial powers
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.16.9#With every blessing crown thy happy hours!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.16.10#Our freedom to thy prowess'd arm we owe
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.16.11#From bold intrusion of thy coward foe:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.16.12#Instant the flying sail the slave shall wing
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.16.13#To Eschetus, the monster of a king."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.17.1#While pleased he hears, Antinous bears the food,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.17.2#A kid's well-fatted entrails, rich with blood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.17.3#The bread from canisters of shining mould
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.17.4#Amphinomus; and wines that laugh in gold:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.17.5#"And oh! (he mildly cries) may Heaven display
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.17.6#A beam of glory o'er thy future day!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.17.7#Alas, the brave too oft is doom'd to bear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.17.8#The gripes of poverty and stings of care."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.1#To whom with thought mature the king replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.2#"The tongue speaks wisely, when the soul is wise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.3#Such was thy father! in imperial state,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.4#Great without vice, that oft attends the great;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.5#Nor from the sire art thou, the son, declin'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.6#Then hear my words, and grace them in thy mind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.7#Of all that breathes, or grovelling creeps on earth,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.8#Most man in vain! calamitous by birth:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.9#To-day, with power elate, in strength he blooms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.10#The haughty creature on that power presumes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.11#Anon from Heaven a sad reverse he feels:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.12#Untaught to bear, 'gainst Heaven the wretch rebels.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.13#For man is changeful, as his bliss or woe!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.14#Too high when prosperous, when distress'd too low.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.15#There was a day, when with the scornful great
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.16#I swell'd in pomp and arrogance of state;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.17#Proud of the power that to high birth belongs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.18#And used that power to justify my wrongs.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.19#Then let not man be proud; but firm of mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.20#Bear the best humbly; and the worst resign'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.21#Be dumb when Heaven afflicts! unlike yon train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.22#Of haughty spoilers, insolently vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.23#Who make their queen and all her wealth a prey:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.24#But vengeance and Ulysses wing their way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.25#O may'st thou, favour'd by some guardian power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.26#Far, far be distant in that deathful hour!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.27#For sure I am, if stern Ulysses breathe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.18.28#These lawless riots end in blood and death."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.19.1#Then to the gods the rosy juice he pours,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.19.2#And the drain'd goblet to the chief restores.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.19.3#Stung to the soul, o'ercast with holy dread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.19.4#He shook the graceful honours of his head;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.19.5#His boding mind the future woe forestalls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.19.6#In vain! by great Telemachus he falls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.19.7#For Pallas seals his doom: all sad he turns
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.19.8#To join the peers; resumes his throne, and mourns.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.20.1#Meanwhile Minerva with instinctive fires
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.20.2#Thy soul, Penelope, from Heaven inspires;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.20.3#With flattering hopes the suitors to betray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.20.4#And seem to meet, yet fly, the bridal day:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.20.5#Thy husband's wonder, and thy son's to raise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.20.6#And crown the mother and the wife with praise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.20.7#Then, while the streaming sorrow dims her eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.20.8#Thus, with a transient smile, the matron cries:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.21.1#"Eurynome! to go where riot reigns
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.21.2#I feel an impulse, though my soul disdains;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.21.3#To my loved son the snares of death to show,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.21.4#And in the traitor friend, unmask the foe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.21.5#Who, smooth of tongue, in purpose insincere,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.21.6#Hides fraud in smiles, while death is ambush'd there."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.22.1#"Go, warn thy son, nor be the warning vain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.22.2#(Replied the sagest of the royal train);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.22.3#But bathed, anointed, and adorn'd, descend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.22.4#Powerful of charms, bid every grace attend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.22.5#The tide of flowing tears awhile suppress;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.22.6#Tears but indulge the sorrow, not repress.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.22.7#Some joy remains: to thee a son is given,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.22.8#Such as, in fondness, parents ask of Heaven."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.23.1#"Ah me! forbear!" returns the queen, "forbear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.23.2#Oh! talk not, talk not of vain beauty's care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.23.3#No more I bathe, since he no longer sees
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.23.4#Those charms, for whom alone I wish to please.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.23.5#The day that bore Ulysses from this coast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.23.6#Blasted the little bloom these cheeks could boast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.23.7#But instant bid Autonoe descend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.23.8#Instant Hippodame our steps attend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.23.9#Ill suits it female virtue, to be seen
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.23.10#Alone, indecent, in the walks of men."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.1#Then while Eurynome the mandate bears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.2#From heaven Minerva shoots with guardian cares;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.3#O'er all her senses, as the couch she press'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.4#She pours, a pleasing, deep and death-like rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.5#With every beauty every feature arms,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.6#Bids her cheeks glow, and lights up all her charms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.7#In her love-darting eyes awakes the fires
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.8#(Immortal gifts! to kindle soft desires);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.9#From limb to limb an air majestic sheds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.10#And the pure ivory o'er her bosom spreads.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.11#Such Venus shines, when with a measured bound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.12#She smoothly gliding swims the harmonious round,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.13#When with the Graces in the dance she moves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.24.14#And fires the gazing gods with ardent loves.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.25.1#Then to the skies her flight Minerva bends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.25.2#And to the queen the damsel train descends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.25.3#Waked at their steps, her flowing eyes unclose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.25.4#The tears she wipes, and thus renews her woes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.25.5#"Howe'er 'tis well that sleep awhile can free,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.25.6#With soft forgetfulness a wretch like me;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.25.7#Oh! were it given to yield this transient breath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.25.8#Send, O Diana! send the sleep of death!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.25.9#Why must I waste a tedious life in tears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.25.10#Nor bury in the silent grave my cares?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.25.11#O my Ulysses! ever honour'd name!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.25.12#For thee I mourn till death dissolves my frame."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.26.1#Thus wailing, slow and sadly she descends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.26.2#On either band a damsel train attends:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.26.3#Full where the dome its shining valves expands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.26.4#Radiant before the gazing peers she stands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.26.5#A veil translucent o'er her brow display'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.26.6#Her beauty seems, and only seems, to shade:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.26.7#Sudden she lightens in their dazzled eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.26.8#And sudden flames in every bosom rise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.26.9#They send their eager souls with every look.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.26.10#Till silence thus the imperial matron broke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.27.1#"O why! my son, why now no more appears
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.27.2#That warmth of soul that urged thy younger years?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.27.3#Thy riper days no growing worth impart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.27.4#A man in stature, still a boy in heart!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.27.5#Thy well-knit frame unprofitably strong,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.27.6#Speaks thee a hero, from a hero sprung:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.27.7#But the just gods in vain those gifts bestow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.27.8#O wise alone in form, and grave in show!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.27.9#Heavens! could a stranger feel oppression's hand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.27.10#Beneath thy roof, and couldst thou tamely stand!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.27.11#If thou the stranger's righteous cause decline
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.27.12#His is the sufferance, but the shame is thine."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.1#To whom, with filial awe, the prince returns:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.2#"That generous soul with just resentment burns;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.3#Yet, taught by time, my heart has learn'd to glow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.4#For others' good, and melt at others' woe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.5#But, impotent those riots to repel,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.6#I bear their outrage, though my soul rebel;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.7#Helpless amid the snares of death I tread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.8#And numbers leagued in impious union dread;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.9#But now no crime is theirs: this wrong proceeds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.10#From Irus, and the guilty Irus bleeds.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.11#Oh would to Jove! or her whose arms display
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.12#The shield of Jove, or him who rules the day!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.13#That yon proud suitors, who licentious tread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.14#These courts, within these courts like Irus bled:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.15#Whose loose head tottering, as with wine oppress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.16#Obliquely drops, and nodding knocks his breast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.17#Powerless to move, his staggering feet deny
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.28.18#The coward wretch the privilege to fly."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.29.1#Then to the queen Eurymachus replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.29.2#"O justly loved, and not more fair than wise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.29.3#Should Greece through all her hundred states survey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.29.4#Thy finish'd charms, all Greece would own thy sway
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.29.5#In rival crowds contest the glorious prize.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.29.6#Dispeopling realms to gaze upon thy eyes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.29.7#O woman! loveliest of the lovely kind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.29.8#In body perfect, and complete in mind."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.1#"Ah me! (returns the queen) when from this shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.2#Ulysses sail'd, then beauty was no more!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.3#The gods decreed these eyes no more should keep
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.4#Their wonted grace, but only serve to weep.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.5#Should he return, whate'er my beauties prove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.6#My virtues last; my brightest charm is love.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.7#Now, grief, thou all art mine! the gods o'ercast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.8#My soul with woes, that long, ah long must last!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.9#Too faithfully my heart retains the day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.10#That sadly tore my royal lord away:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.11#He grasp'd my hand, and, 'O, my spouse! I leave
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.12#Thy arms (he cried), perhaps to find a grave:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.13#Fame speaks the Trojans bold; they boast the skill
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.14#To give the feather'd arrow wings to kill,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.15#To dart the spear, and guide the rushing car
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.16#With dreadful inroad through the walks of war.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.17#My sentence is gone forth, and 'tis decreed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.18#Perhaps by righteous Heaven that I must bleed!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.19#My father, mother, all I trust to three;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.20#To them, to them, transfer the love of me:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.21#But, when my son grows man, the royal sway
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.22#Resign, and happy be thy bridal day!'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.23#Such were his words; and Hymen now prepares
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.24#To light his torch, and give me up to cares;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.25#The afflictive hand of wrathful Jove to bear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.26#A wretch the most complete that breathes the air!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.27#Fall'n e'en below the rights to woman due!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.28#Careless to please, with insolence ye woo!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.29#The generous lovers, studious to succeed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.30#Bid their whole herds and flocks in banquets bleed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.31#By precious gifts the vow sincere display:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.30.32#You, only you, make her ye love your prey."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.31.1#Well-pleased Ulysses hears his queen deceive
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.31.2#The suitor-train, and raise a thirst to give:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.31.3#False hopes she kindles, but those hopes betray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.31.4#And promise, yet elude, the bridal day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.32.1#While yet she speaks, the gay Antinous cries:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.32.2#"Offspring of kings, and more than woman wise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.32.3#'Tis right; 'tis man's prerogative to give,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.32.4#And custom bids thee without shame receive;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.32.5#Yet never, never, from thy dome we move,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.32.6#Till Hymen lights the torch of spousal love."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.1#The peers despatch'd their heralds to convey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.2#The gifts of love; with speed they take the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.3#A robe Antinous gives of shining dyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.4#The varying hues in gay confusion rise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.5#Rich from the artist's hand! Twelve clasps of gold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.6#Close to the lessening waist the vest infold!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.7#Down from the swelling loins the vest unbound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.8#Floats in bright waves redundant o'er the ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.9#A bracelet rich with gold, with amber gay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.10#That shot effulgence like the solar ray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.11#Eurymachus presents: and ear-rings bright,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.12#With triple stars, that casts a trembling light.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.13#Pisander bears a necklace wrought with art:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.14#And every peer, expressive of his heart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.15#A gift bestows: this done, the queen ascends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.33.16#And slow behind her damsel train attends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.34.1#Then to the dance they form the vocal strain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.34.2#Till Hesperus leads forth the starry train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.34.3#And now he raises, as the daylight fades,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.34.4#His golden circlet in the deepening shades:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.34.5#Three vases heap'd with copious fires display
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.34.6#O'er all the palace a fictitious day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.34.7#From space to space the torch wide-beaming burns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.34.8#And sprightly damsels trim the rays by turns.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.35.1#To whom the king: "Ill suits your sex to stay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.35.2#Alone with men! ye modest maids, away!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.35.3#Go, with the queen; the spindle guide; or cull
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.35.4#(The partners of her cares) the silver wool;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.35.5#Be it my task the torches to supply
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.35.6#E'en till the morning lamp adorns the sky;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.35.7#E'en till the morning, with unwearied care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.35.8#Sleepless I watch; for I have learn'd to bear."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.1#Scornful they heard: Melantho, fair and young,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.2#(Melantho, from the loins of Dolius sprung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.3#Who with the queen her years an infant led,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.4#With the soft fondness of a daughter bred,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.5#Chiefly derides: regardless of the cares
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.6#Her queen endures, polluted joys she shares
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.7#Nocturnal with Eurymachus: with eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.8#That speak disdain, the wanton thus replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.9#"Oh! whither wanders thy distemper'd brain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.10#Thou bold intruder on a princely train?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.11#Hence, to the vagrants' rendezvous repair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.12#Or shun in some black forge the midnight air.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.13#Proceeds this boldness from a turn of soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.14#Or flows licentious from the copious bowl?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.15#Is it that vanquish'd Irus swells thy mind?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.16#A foe may meet thee of a braver kind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.17#Who, shortening with a storm of blows thy stay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.36.18#Shall send thee howling all in blood away!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.37.1#To whom with frowns: "O impudent in wrong!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.37.2#Thy lord shall curb that insolence of tongue;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.37.3#Know, to Telemachus I tell the offence;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.37.4#The scourge, the scourge shall lash thee into sense."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.38.1#With conscious shame they hear the stern rebuke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.38.2#Nor longer durst sustain the sovereign look.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.39.1#Then to the servile task the monarch turns
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.39.2#His royal hands: each torch refulgent burns
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.39.3#With added day: meanwhile in museful mood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.39.4#Absorb'd in thought, on vengeance fix'd he stood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.39.5#And now the martial maid, by deeper wrongs
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.39.6#To rouse Ulysses, points the suitors' tongues:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.39.7#Scornful of age, to taunt the virtuous man,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.39.8#Thoughtless and gay, Eurymachus began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.40.1#"Hear me (he cries), confederates and friends!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.40.2#Some god, no doubt, this stranger kindly sends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.40.3#The shining baldness of his head survey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.40.4#It aids our torchlight, and reflects the ray."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.41.1#Then to the king that levell'd haughty Troy:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.41.2#"Say, if large hire can tempt thee to employ
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.41.3#Those hands in work; to tend the rural trade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.41.4#To dress the walk, and form the embowering shade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.41.5#So food and raiment constant will I give:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.41.6#But idly thus thy soul prefers to live,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.41.7#And starve by strolling, not by work to thrive."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.1#To whom incensed: "Should we, O prince, engage
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.2#In rival tasks beneath the burning rage
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.3#Of summer suns; were both constrain'd to wield
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.4#Foodless the scythe along the burden'd field;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.5#Or should we labour while the ploughshare wounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.6#With steers of equal strength, the allotted grounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.7#Beneath my labours, how thy wondering eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.8#Might see the sable field at once arise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.9#Should Jove dire war unloose, with spear and shield,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.10#And nodding helm, I tread the ensanguined field,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.11#Fierce in the van: then wouldst thou, wouldst thou,--say,--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.12#Misname me glutton, in that glorious day?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.13#No, thy ill-judging thoughts the brave disgrace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.14#'Tis thou injurious art, not I am base.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.15#Proud to seem brave among a coward train!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.16#But now, thou art not valorous, but vain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.17#God! should the stern Ulysses rise in might,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.42.18#These gates would seem too narrow for thy flight."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.43.1#While yet he speaks, Eurymachus replies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.43.2#With indignation flashing from his eyes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.44.1#"Slave, I with justice might deserve the wrong,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.44.2#Should I not punish that opprobrious tongue.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.44.3#Irreverent to the great, and uncontroll'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.44.4#Art thou from wine, or innate folly, bold?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.44.5#Perhaps these outrages from Irus flow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.44.6#A worthless triumph o'er a worthless foe!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.1#He said, and with full force a footstool threw;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.2#Whirl'd from his arm, with erring rage it flew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.3#Ulysses, cautious of the vengeful foe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.4#Stoops to the ground, and disappoints the blow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.5#Not so a youth, who deals the goblet round,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.6#Full on his shoulder it inflicts a wound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.7#Dash'd from his hand the sounding goblet flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.8#He shrieks, he reels, he falls, and breathless lies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.9#Then wild uproar and clamour mount the sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.10#Till mutual thus the peers indignant cry:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.11#"Oh had this stranger sunk to realms beneath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.12#To the black realms of darkness and of death,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.13#Ere yet he trod these shores! to strife he draws
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.14#Peer against peer; and what the weighty cause?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.15#A vagabond! for him the great destroy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.45.16#In vile ignoble jars, the feast of joy."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.46.1#To whom the stern Telemachus uprose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.46.2#"Gods! what wild folly from the goblet flows!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.46.3#Whence this unguarded openness of soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.46.4#But from the license of the copious bowl?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.46.5#Or Heaven delusion sends: but hence away!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.46.6#Force I forbear, and without force obey."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.47.1#Silent, abash'd, they hear the stern rebuke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.47.2#Till thus Amphinomus the silence broke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.48.1#"True are his words, and he whom truth offends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.48.2#Not with Telemachus, but truth contends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.48.3#Let not the hand of violence invade
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.48.4#The reverend stranger, or the spotless maid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.48.5#Retire we hence, but crown with rosy wine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.48.6#The flowing goblet to the powers divine!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.48.7#Guard he his guest beneath whose roof he stands:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.48.8#This justice, this the social rite demands."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.49.1#The peers assent: the goblet Mulius crown'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.49.2#With purple juice, and bore in order round:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.49.3#Each peer successive his libation pours
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.49.4#To the blest gods who fill'd the ethereal bowers:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.49.5#Then swill'd with wine, with noise the crowds obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:18.49.6#And rushing forth, tumultuous reel away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.1.1#Consulting secret with the blue-eyed maid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.1.2#Still in the dome divine Ulysses stay'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.1.3#Revenge mature for act inflamed his breast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.1.4#And thus the son the fervent sire address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.2.1#"Instant convey those steely stores of war
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.2.2#To distant rooms, disposed with secret care:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.2.3#The cause demanded by the suitor-train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.2.4#To soothe their fears, a specious reason feign:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.2.5#Say, since Ulysses left his natal coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.2.6#Obscene with smoke, their beamy lustre lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.2.7#His arms deform the roof they wont adorn:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.2.8#From the glad walls inglorious lumber torn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.2.9#Suggest, that Jove the peaceful thought inspired,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.2.10#Lest they, by sight of swords to fury fired,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.2.11#Dishonest wounds, or violence of soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.2.12#Defame the bridal feast and friendly bowl."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.3.1#The prince, obedient to the sage command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.3.2#To Euryclea thus: "The female band
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.3.3#In their apartments keep; secure the doors;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.3.4#These swarthy arms among the covert stores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.3.5#Are seemlier hid; my thoughtless youth they blame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.3.6#Imbrown'd with vapour of the smouldering flame."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.4.1#"In happier hour (pleased Euryclea cries),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.4.2#Tutour'd by early woes, grow early wise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.4.3#Inspect with sharpen'd sight, and frugal care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.4.4#Your patrimonial wealth, a prudent heir.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.4.5#But who the lighted taper will provide
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.4.6#(The female train retired) your toils to guide?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.5.1#"Without infringing hospitable right,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.5.2#This guest (he cried) shall bear the guiding light:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.5.3#I cheer no lazy vagrants with repast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.5.4#They share the meal that earn it ere they taste."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.6.1#He said: from female ken she straight secures
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.6.2#The purposed deed, and guards the bolted doors:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.6.3#Auxiliar to his son, Ulysses bears
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.6.4#The plumy-crested helms and pointed spears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.6.5#With shields indented deep in glorious wars.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.6.6#Minerva viewless on her charge attends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.6.7#And with her golden lamp his toil befriends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.6.8#Not such the sickly beams, which unsincere
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.6.9#Gild the gross vapour of this nether sphere!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.6.10#A present deity the prince confess'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.6.11#And wrapp'd with ecstasy the sire address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.7.1#"What miracle thus dazzles with surprise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.7.2#Distinct in rows the radiant columns rise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.7.3#The walls, where'er my wondering sight I turn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.7.4#And roofs, amidst a blaze of glory burn!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.7.5#Some visitant of pure ethereal race
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.7.6#With his bright presence deigns the dome to grace."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.8.1#"Be calm (replies the sire); to none impart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.8.2#But oft revolve the vision in thy heart:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.8.3#Celestials, mantled in excess of light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.8.4#Can visit unapproach'd by mortal sight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.8.5#Seek thou repose: whilst here I sole remain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.8.6#To explore the conduct of the female train:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.8.7#The pensive queen, perchance, desires to know
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.8.8#The series of my toils, to soothe her woe."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.9.1#With tapers flaming day his train attends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.9.2#His bright alcove the obsequious youth ascends:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.9.3#Soft slumberous shades his drooping eyelids close,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.9.4#Till on her eastern throne Aurora glows.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.1#Whilst, forming plans of death, Ulysses stay'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.2#In counsel secret with the martial maid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.3#Attendant nymphs in beauteous order wait
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.4#The queen, descending from her bower of state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.5#Her cheeks the warmer blush of Venus wear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.6#Chasten'd with coy Diana's pensive air.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.7#An ivory seat with silver ringlets graced,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.8#By famed Icmalius wrought, the menials placed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.9#With ivory silver'd thick the footstool shone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.10#O'er which the panther's various hide was thrown.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.11#The sovereign seat with graceful air she press'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.12#To different tasks their toil the nymphs address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.13#The golden goblets some, and some restored
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.14#From stains of luxury the polish'd board:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.15#These to remove the expiring embers came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.10.16#While those with unctuous fir foment the flame.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.11.1#'Twas then Melantho with imperious mien
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.11.2#Renew'd the attack, incontinent of spleen:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.11.3#"Avaunt (she cried), offensive to my sight!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.11.4#Deem not in ambush here to lurk by night,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.11.5#Into the woman-state asquint to pry;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.11.6#A day-devourer, and an evening spy!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.11.7#Vagrant, begone! before this blazing brand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.11.8#Shall urge"--and waved it hissing in her hand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.1#The insulted hero rolls his wrathful eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.2#And "Why so turbulent of soul? (he cries;)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.3#Can these lean shrivell'd limbs, unnerved with age,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.4#These poor but honest rags, enkindle rage?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.5#In crowds, we wear the badge of hungry fate:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.6#And beg, degraded from superior state!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.7#Constrain'd a rent-charge on the rich I live;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.8#Reduced to crave the good I once could give:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.9#A palace, wealth, and slaves, I late possess'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.10#And all that makes the great be call'd the bless'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.11#My gate, an emblem of my open soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.12#Embraced the poor, and dealt a bounteous dole.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.13#Scorn not the sad reverse, injurious maid!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.14#'Tis Jove's high will, and be his will obey'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.15#Nor think thyself exempt: that rosy prime
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.16#Must share the general doom of withering time:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.17#To some new channel soon the changeful tide
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.18#Of royal grace the offended queen may guide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.19#And her loved lord unplume thy towering pride.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.20#Or, were he dead, 'tis wisdom to beware:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.21#Sweet blooms the prince beneath Apollo's care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.22#Your deeds with quick impartial eye surveys,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.12.23#Potent to punish what he cannot praise."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.13.1#Her keen reproach had reach'd the sovereign's ear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.13.2#"Loquacious insolent! (she cries,) forbear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.13.3#To thee the purpose of my soul I told;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.13.4#Venial discourse, unblamed, with him to hold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.13.5#The storied labours of my wandering lord,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.13.6#To soothe my grief he haply may record:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.13.7#Yet him, my guest, thy venom'd rage hath stung;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.13.8#Thy head shall pay the forfeit of thy tongue!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.13.9#But thou on whom my palace cares depend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.13.10#Eurynome, regard the stranger-friend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.13.11#A seat, soft spread with furry spoils, prepare;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.13.12#Due-distant for us both to speak, and hear."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.14.1#The menial fair obeys with duteous haste:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.14.2#A seat adorn'd with furry spoils she placed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.14.3#Due-distant for discourse the hero sate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.14.4#When thus the sovereign from her chair of state:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.15.1#"Reveal, obsequious to my first demand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.15.2#Thy name, thy lineage, and thy natal land."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.1#He thus: "O queen! whose far-resounding fame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.2#Is bounded only by the starry frame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.3#Consummate pattern of imperial sway,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.4#Whose pious rule a warlike race obey!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.5#In wavy gold thy summer vales are dress'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.6#Thy autumns bind with copious fruit oppress'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.7#With flocks and herds each grassy plain is stored;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.8#And fish of every fin thy seas afford:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.9#Their affluent joys the grateful realms confess;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.10#And bless the power that still delights to bless,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.11#Gracious permit this prayer, imperial dame!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.12#Forbear to know my lineage, or my name:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.13#Urge not this breast to heave, these eyes to weep;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.14#In sweet oblivion let my sorrows sleep!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.15#My woes awaked, will violate your ear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.16#And to this gay censorious train appear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.16.17#A whiny vapour melting in a tear."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.1#"Their gifts the gods resumed (the queen rejoin'd),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.2#Exterior grace, and energy of mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.3#When the dear partner of my nuptial joy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.4#Auxiliar troops combined, to conquer Troy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.5#My lord's protecting hand alone would raise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.6#My drooping verdure, and extend my praise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.7#Peers from the distant Samian shore resort:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.8#Here with Dulichians join'd, besiege the court:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.9#Zacynthus, green with ever-shady groves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.10#And Ithaca, presumptuous, boast their loves:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.11#Obtruding on my choice a second lord,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.12#They press the Hymenaean rite abhorr'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.13#Misrule thus mingling with domestic cares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.14#I live regardless of my state affairs;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.15#Receive no stranger-guest, no poor relieve;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.16#But ever for my lord in secret grieve!--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.17#This art, instinct by some celestial power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.17.18#I tried, elusive of the bridal hour:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.1#"'Ye peers, (I cry,) who press to gain a heart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.2#Where dead Ulysses claims no future part;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.3#Rebate your loves, each rival suit suspend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.4#Till this funeral web my labours end:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.5#Cease, till to good Laertes I bequeath
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.6#A pall of state, the ornament of death.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.7#For when to fate he bows, each Grecian dame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.8#With just reproach were licensed to defame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.9#Should he, long honour'd in supreme command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.10#Want the last duties of a daughter's hand.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.11#The fiction pleased; their loves I long elude;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.12#The night still ravell'd what the day renew'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.13#Three years successful in my heart conceal'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.14#My ineffectual fraud the fourth reveal'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.15#Befriended by my own domestic spies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.16#The woof unwrought the suitor-train surprise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.17#From nuptial rites they now no more recede,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.18#And fear forbids to falsify the brede.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.19#My anxious parents urge a speedy choice,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.20#And to their suffrage gain the filial voice.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.21#For rule mature, Telemachus deplores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.22#His dome dishonour'd, and exhausted stores--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.23#But, stranger! as thy days seem full of fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.24#Divide discourse, in turn thy birth relate:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.25#Thy port asserts thee of distinguish'd race;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.18.26#No poor unfather'd product of disgrace."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.19.1#"Princess! (he cries,) renew'd by your command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.19.2#The dear remembrance of my native land
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.19.3#Of secret grief unseals the fruitful source;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.19.4#Fond tears repeat their long-forgotten course!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.19.5#So pays the wretch whom fate constrains to roam,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.19.6#The dues of nature to his natal home!--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.19.7#But inward on my soul let sorrow prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.19.8#Your sovereign will my duty bids obey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.1#"Crete awes the circling waves, a fruitful soil!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.2#And ninety cities crown the sea-born isle:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.3#Mix'd with her genuine sons, adopted names
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.4#In various tongues avow their various claims:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.5#Cydonians, dreadful with the bended yew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.6#And bold Pelasgi boast a native's due:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.7#The Dorians, plumed amid the files of war,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.8#Her foodful glebe with fierce Achaians share;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.9#Cnossus, her capital of high command;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.10#Where sceptred Minos with impartial hand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.11#Divided right: each ninth revolving year,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.12#By Jove received in council to confer.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.13#His son Deucalion bore successive sway:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.14#His son, who gave me first to view the day!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.15#The royal bed an elder issue bless'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.16#Idomeneus whom Ilion fields attest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.17#Of matchless deeds: untrain'd to martial toil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.18#I lived inglorious in my native isle.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.19#Studious of peace, and Aethon is my name.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.20#'Twas then to Crete the great Ulysses came.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.21#For elemental war, and wintry Jove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.22#From Malea's gusty cape his navy drove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.23#To bright Lucina's fane; the shelfy coast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.24#Where loud Amnisus in the deep is lost.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.25#His vessel's moor'd (an incommodious port!)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.26#The hero speeded to the Cnossian court:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.27#Ardent the partner of his arms to find,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.28#In leagues of long commutual friendship join'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.29#Vain hope! ten suns had warm'd the western strand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.30#Since my brave brother, with his Cretan band,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.31#Had sail'd for Troy: but to the genial feast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.32#My honour'd roof received the royal guest:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.33#Beeves for his train the Cnossian peers assign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.34#A public treat, with jars of generous wine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.35#Twelve days while Boreas vex'd the aerial space,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.36#My hospitable dome he deign'd to grace:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.37#And when the north had ceased the stormy roar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.20.38#He wing'd his voyage to the Phrygian shore."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.1#Thus the fam'd hero, perfected in wiles,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.2#With fair similitude of truth beguiles
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.3#The queen's attentive ear: dissolved in woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.4#From her bright eyes the tears unbounded flow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.5#As snows collected on the mountain freeze;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.6#When milder regions breathe a vernal breeze,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.7#The fleecy pile obeys the whispering gales,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.8#Ends in a stream, and murmurs through the vales:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.9#So, melting with the pleasing tale he told,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.10#Down her fair cheek the copious torrent roll'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.11#She to her present lord laments him lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.12#And views that object which she wants the most,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.13#Withering at heart to see the weeping fair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.14#His eyes look stern, and cast a gloomy stare;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.15#Of horn the stiff relentless balls appear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.16#Or globes of iron fix'd in either sphere;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.17#Firm wisdom interdicts the softening tear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.18#A speechless interval of grief ensues,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.21.19#Till thus the queen the tender theme renews.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.22.1#"Stranger! that e'er thy hospitable roof
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.22.2#Ulysses graced, confirm by faithful proof;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.22.3#Delineate to my view my warlike lord,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.22.4#His form, his habit, and his train record."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.1#"'Tis hard (he cries,) to bring to sudden sight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.2#Ideas that have wing'd their distant flight;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.3#Rare on the mind those images are traced,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.4#Whose footsteps twenty winters have defaced:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.5#But what I can, receive.--In ample mode,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.6#A robe of military purple flow'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.7#O'er all his frame: illustrious on his breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.8#The double-clasping gold the king confess'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.9#In the rich woof a hound, mosaic drawn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.10#Bore on full stretch, and seized a dappled fawn;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.11#Deep in the neck his fangs indent their hold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.12#They pant and struggle in the moving gold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.13#Fine as a filmy web beneath it shone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.14#A vest, that dazzled like a cloudless sun:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.15#The female train who round him throng'd to gaze,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.16#In silent wonder sigh'd unwilling praise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.17#A sabre, when the warrior press'd to part,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.18#I gave, enamell'd with Vulcanian art:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.19#A mantle purple-tinged, and radiant vest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.20#Dimension'd equal to his size, express'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.21#Affection grateful to my honour'd guest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.22#A favourite herald in his train I knew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.23#His visage solemn, sad of sable hue:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.24#Short woolly curls o'erfleeced his bending head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.25#O'er which a promontory shoulder spread;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.26#Eurybates; in whose large soul alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.23.27#Ulysses view'd an image of his own."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.1#His speech the tempest of her grief restored;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.2#In all he told she recognized her lord:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.3#But when the storm was spent in plenteous showers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.4#A pause inspiriting her languish'd powers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.5#"O thou, (she cried,) whom first inclement Fate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.6#Made welcome to my hospitable gate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.7#With all thy wants the name of poor shall end:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.8#Henceforth live honour'd, my domestic friend!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.9#The vest much envied on your native coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.10#And regal robe with figured gold emboss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.11#In happier hours my artful hand employ'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.12#When my loved lord this blissful bower enjoy'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.13#The fall of Troy erroneous and forlorn
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.24.14#Doom'd to survive, and never to return!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.1#Then he, with pity touch'd: "O royal dame!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.2#Your ever-anxious mind, and beauteous frame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.3#From the devouring rage of grief reclaim.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.4#I not the fondness of your soul reprove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.5#For such a lord! who crown'd your virgin love
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.6#With the dear blessing of a fair increase;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.7#Himself adorn'd with more than mortal grace:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.8#Yet while I speak the mighty woe suspend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.9#Truth forms my tale; to pleasing truth attend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.10#The royal object of your dearest care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.11#Breathes in no distant clime the vital air:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.12#In rich Thesprotia, and the nearer bound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.13#Of Thessaly, his name I heard renown'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.14#Without retinue, to that friendly shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.15#Welcomed with gifts of price, a sumless store!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.16#His sacrilegious train, who dared to prey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.17#On herds devoted to the god of day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.18#Were doom'd by Jove, and Phoebus' just decree,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.19#To perish in the rough Trinacrian sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.20#To better fate the blameless chief ordain'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.21#A floating fragment of the wreck regain'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.22#And rode the storm; till, by the billows toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.23#He landed on the fair Phaeacian coast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.24#That race who emulate the life of gods,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.25#Receive him joyous to their bless'd abodes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.26#Large gifts confer, a ready sail command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.27#To speed his voyage to the Grecian strand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.28#But your wise lord (in whose capacious soul
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.29#High schemes of power in just succession roll)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.30#His Ithaca refused from favouring Fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.31#Till copious wealth might guard his regal state.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.32#Phedon the fact affirm'd, whose sovereign sway
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.33#Thesprotian tribes, a duteous race, obey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.34#And bade the gods this added truth attest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.35#(While pure libations crown'd the genial feast),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.36#That anchor'd in his port the vessels stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.37#To waft the hero to his natal land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.38#I for Dulichium urge the watery way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.39#But first the Ulyssean wealth survey:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.40#So rich the value of a store so vast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.41#Demands the pomp of centuries to waste!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.42#The darling object of your royal love
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.43#Was journey'd thence to Dodonean Jove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.44#By the sure precept of the sylvan shrine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.45#To form the conduct of his great design;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.46#Irresolute of soul, his state to shroud
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.47#In dark disguise, or come, a king avow'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.48#Thus lives your lord; nor longer doom'd to roam;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.49#Soon will he grace this dear paternal dome.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.50#By Jove, the source of good, supreme in power!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.51#By the bless'd genius of this friendly bower!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.52#I ratify my speech, before the sun
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.53#His annual longitude of heaven shall run;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.54#When the pale empress of yon starry train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.55#In the next month renews her faded wane,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.25.56#Ulysses will assert his rightful reign."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.1#"What thanks! what boon! (replied the queen), are due,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.2#When time shall prove the storied blessing true!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.3#My lord's return should fate no more retard,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.4#Envy shall sicken at thy vast reward.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.5#But my prophetic fears, alas! presage
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.6#The wounds of Destiny's relentless rage.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.7#I long must weep, nor will Ulysses come,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.8#With royal gifts to send you honour'd home!--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.9#Your other task, ye menial train forbear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.10#Now wash the stranger, and the bed prepare:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.11#With splendid palls the downy fleece adorn:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.12#Uprising early with the purple morn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.13#His sinews, shrunk with age, and stiff with toil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.14#In the warm bath foment with fragrant oil.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.15#Then with Telemachus the social feast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.16#Partaking free, my soul invited guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.17#Whoe'er neglects to pay distinction due,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.18#The breach of hospitable right may rue.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.19#The vulgar of my sex I most exceed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.20#In real fame, when most humane my deed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.21#And vainly to the praise of queen aspire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.22#If, stranger! I permit that mean attire
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.23#Beneath the feastful bower. A narrow space
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.24#Confines the circle of our destin'd race;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.25#'Tis ours with good the scanty round to grace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.26#Those who to cruel wrong their state abuse,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.27#Dreaded in life the mutter'd curse pursues;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.28#By death disrobed of all their savage powers,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.29#Then, licensed rage her hateful prey devours.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.30#But he whose inborn worth his acts commend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.31#Of gentle soul, to human race a friend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.32#The wretched he relieves diffuse his fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.26.33#And distant tongues extol the patron-name."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.1#"Princess? (he cried) in vain your bounties flow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.2#On me, confirm'd and obstinate in woe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.3#When my loved Crete received my final view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.4#And from my weeping eyes her cliffs withdrew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.5#These tatter'd weeds (my decent robes resign'd)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.6#I chose, the livery of a woful mind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.7#Nor will my heart-corroding care abate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.8#With splendid palls, and canopies of state:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.9#Low-couch'd on earth, the gift of sleep I scorn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.10#And catch the glances of the waking morn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.11#The delicacy of your courtly train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.12#To wash a wretched wanderer would disdain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.13#But if, in tract of long experience tried,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.14#And sad similitude of woes allied,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.15#Some wretch reluctant views aerial light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.27.16#To her mean hand assign the friendly rite."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.1#Pleased with his wise reply, the queen rejoin'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.2#"Such gentle manners, and so sage a mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.3#In all who graced this hospitable bower
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.4#I ne'er discerned, before this social hour.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.5#Such servant as your humble choice requires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.6#To light received the lord of my desires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.7#New from the birth; and with a mother's hand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.8#His tender bloom to manly growth sustain'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.9#Of matchless prudence, and a duteous mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.10#Though now to life's extremest verge declined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.11#Of strength superior to the toil design'd--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.12#Rise, Euryclea! with officious care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.13#For the poor friend the cleansing bath prepare:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.14#This debt his correspondent fortunes claim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.15#Too like Ulysses, and perhaps the same!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.16#Thus old with woes my fancy paints him now!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.28.17#For age untimely marks the careful brow."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.29.1#Instant, obsequious to the mild command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.29.2#Sad Euryclea rose: with trembling hand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.29.3#She veils the torrent of her tearful eyes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.29.4#And thus impassion'd to herself replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.1#"Son of my love, and monarch of my cares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.2#What pangs for thee this wretched bosom bears!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.3#Are thus by Jove who constant beg his aid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.4#With pious deed, and pure devotion, paid?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.5#He never dared defraud the sacred fane
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.6#Of perfect hecatombs in order slain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.7#There oft implored his tutelary power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.8#Long to protract the sad sepulchral hour;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.9#That, form'd for empire with paternal care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.10#His realm might recognize an equal heir.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.11#O destined head! The pious vows are lost;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.12#His God forgets him on a foreign coast!--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.13#Perhaps, like thee, poor guest! in wanton pride
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.14#The rich insult him, and the young deride!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.15#Conscious of worth reviled, thy generous mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.16#The friendly rite of purity declined;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.17#My will concurring with my queen's command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.18#Accept the bath from this obsequious hand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.19#A strong emotion shakes my anguish'd breast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.20#In thy whole form Ulysses seems express'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.21#Of all the wretched harboured on our coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.30.22#None imaged e'er like thee my master lost."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.31.1#Thus half-discover'd through the dark disguise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.31.2#With cool composure feign'd, the chief replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.31.3#"You join your suffrage to the public vote;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.31.4#The same you think have all beholders thought."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.32.1#He said: replenish'd from the purest springs,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.32.2#The laver straight with busy care she brings:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.32.3#In the deep vase, that shone like burnish'd gold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.32.4#The boiling fluid temperates the cold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.32.5#Meantime revolving in his thoughtful mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.32.6#The scar, with which his manly knee was sign'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.32.7#His face averting from the crackling blaze,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.32.8#His shoulders intercept the unfriendly rays:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.32.9#Thus cautious in the obscure he hoped to fly
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.32.10#The curious search of Euryclea's eye.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.32.11#Cautious in vain! nor ceased the dame to find
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.32.12#This scar with which his manly knee was sign'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.1#This on Parnassus (combating the boar)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.2#With glancing rage the tusky savage tore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.3#Attended by his brave maternal race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.4#His grandsire sent him to the sylvan chase,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.5#Autolycus the bold (a mighty name
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.6#For spotless faith and deeds of martial fame:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.7#Hermes, his patron god, those gifts bestow'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.8#Whose shrine with weanling lambs he wont to load).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.9#His course to Ithaca this hero sped,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.10#When the first product of Laertes' bed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.11#Was now disclosed to birth: the banquet ends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.12#When Euryclea from the queen descends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.13#And to his fond embrace the babe commends:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.14#"Receive (she cries) your royal daughter's son;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.15#And name the blessing that your prayers have won."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.16#Then thus the hoary chief: "My victor arms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.17#Have awed the realms around with dire alarms:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.18#A sure memorial of my dreaded fame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.19#The boy shall bear; Ulysses be his name!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.20#And when with filial love the youth shall come
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.21#To view his mother's soil, my Delphic dome
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.22#With gifts of price shall send him joyous home."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.23#Lured with the promised boon, when youthful prime
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.24#Ended in man, his mother's natal clime
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.25#Ulysses sought; with fond affection dear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.26#Amphitea's arms received the royal heir:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.27#Her ancient lord an equal joy possess'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.28#Instant he bade prepare the genial feast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.29#A steer to form the sumptuous banquet bled,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.30#Whose stately growth five flowery summers fed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.31#His sons divide, and roast with artful care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.32#The limbs; then all the tasteful viands share.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.33#Nor ceased discourse (the banquet of the soul),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.34#Till Phoebus wheeling to the western goal
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.35#Resign'd the skies, and night involved the pole.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.36#Their drooping eyes the slumberous shade oppress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.33.37#Sated they rose, and all retired to rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.1#Soon as the morn, new-robed in purple light,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.2#Pierced with her golden shafts the rear of night,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.3#Ulysses, and his brave maternal race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.4#The young Autolyci, essay the chase.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.5#Parnassus, thick perplex'd with horrid shades,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.6#With deep-mouth'd hounds the hunter-troop invades;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.7#What time the sun, from ocean's peaceful stream,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.8#Darts o'er the lawn his horizontal beam.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.9#The pack impatient snuff the tainted gale;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.10#The thorny wilds the woodmen fierce assail:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.11#And, foremost of the train, his cornel spear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.12#Ulysses waved, to rouse the savage war.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.13#Deep in the rough recesses of the wood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.14#A lofty copse, the growth of ages, stood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.15#Nor winter's boreal blast, nor thunderous shower,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.16#Nor solar ray, could pierce the shady bower.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.17#With wither'd foliage strew'd, a heapy store!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.18#The warm pavilion of a dreadful boar.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.19#Roused by the hounds' and hunters' mingling cries,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.20#The savage from his leafy shelter flies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.21#With fiery glare his sanguine eye-balls shine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.22#And bristles high impale his horrid chine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.23#Young Ithacus advanced, defies the foe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.24#Poising his lifted lance in act to throw;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.25#The savage renders vain the wound decreed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.26#And springs impetuous with opponent speed!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.27#His tusks oblique he aim'd, the knee to gore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.28#Aslope they glanced, the sinewy fibres tore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.29#And bared the bone; Ulysses undismay'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.30#Soon with redoubled force the wound repaid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.31#To the right shoulder-joint the spear applied,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.32#His further flank with streaming purple dyed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.33#On earth he rushed with agonizing pain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.34#With joy and vast surprise, the applauding train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.35#View'd his enormous bulk extended on the plain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.36#With bandage firm Ulysses' knee they bound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.37#Then, chanting mystic lays, the closing wound
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.38#Of sacred melody confess'd the force;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.39#The tides of life regain'd their azure course.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.40#Then back they led the youth with loud acclaim;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.41#Autolycus, enamoured with his fame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.42#Confirm'd the cure; and from the Delphic dome
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.43#With added gifts return'd him glorious home.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.44#He safe at Ithaca with joy received,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.34.45#Relates the chase, and early praise achieved.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.1#Deep o'er his knee inseam'd remain'd the scar;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.2#Which noted token of the woodland war
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.3#When Euryclea found, the ablution ceased:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.4#Down dropp'd the leg, from her slack hand released;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.5#The mingled fluids from the base redound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.6#The vase reclining floats the floor around!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.7#Smiles dew'd with tears the pleasing strife express'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.8#Of grief and joy, alternate in her breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.9#Her fluttering words in melting murmurs died;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.10#At length abrupt--"My son!--my king!"--she cried.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.11#His neck with fond embrace infolding fast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.12#Full on the queen her raptured eye she cast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.13#Ardent to speak the monarch safe restored:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.14#But, studious to conceal her royal lord,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.15#Minerva fix'd her mind on views remote,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.16#And from the present bliss abstracts her thought.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.17#His hand to Euryclea's mouth applied,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.18#"Art thou foredoom'd my pest? (the hero cried:)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.19#Thy milky founts my infant lips have drain'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.20#And have the Fates thy babbling age ordain'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.21#To violate the life thy youth sustain'd?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.22#An exile have I told, with weeping eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.23#Full twenty annual suns in distant skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.24#At length return'd, some god inspires thy breast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.25#To know thy king, and here I stand confess'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.26#This heaven-discover'd truth to thee consign'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.27#Reserve the treasure of thy inmost mind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.28#Else, if the gods my vengeful arm sustain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.29#And prostrate to my sword the suitor-train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.30#With their lewd mates, thy undistinguish'd age
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.35.31#Shall bleed a victim to vindictive rage."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.36.1#Then thus rejoin'd the dame, devoid of fear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.36.2#"What words, my son, have passed thy lips severe?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.36.3#Deep in my soul the trust shall lodge secured;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.36.4#With ribs of steel, and marble heart, immured.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.36.5#When Heaven, auspicious to thy right avow'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.36.6#Shall prostrate to thy sword the suitor-crowd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.36.7#The deeds I'll blazon of the menial fair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.36.8#The lewd to death devote, the virtuous spare."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.37.1#"Thy aid avails me not (the chief replied);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.37.2#My own experience shall their doom decide:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.37.3#A witness-judge precludes a long appeal:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.37.4#Suffice it then thy monarch to conceal."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.38.1#He said: obsequious, with redoubled pace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.38.2#She to the fount conveys the exhausted vase:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.38.3#The bath renew'd, she ends the pleasing toil
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.38.4#With plenteous unction of ambrosial oil.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.38.5#Adjusting to his limbs the tatter'd vest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.38.6#His former seat received the stranger guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.38.7#Whom thus with pensive air the queen addressed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.1#"Though night, dissolving grief in grateful ease,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.2#Your drooping eyes with soft impression seize;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.3#Awhile, reluctant to her pleasing force,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.4#Suspend the restful hour with sweet discourse.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.5#The day (ne'er brighten'd with a beam of joy!)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.6#My menials, and domestic cares employ;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.7#And, unattended by sincere repose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.8#The night assists my ever-wakeful woes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.9#When nature's hush'd beneath her brooding shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.10#My echoing griefs the starry vault invade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.11#As when the months are clad in flowery green,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.12#Sad Philomel, in bowery shades unseen,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.13#To vernal airs attunes her varied strains;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.14#And Itylus sounds warbling o'er the plains;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.15#Young Itylus, his parents' darling joy!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.16#Whom chance misled the mother to destroy;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.17#Now doom'd a wakeful bird to wail the beauteous boy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.18#So in nocturnal solitude forlorn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.19#A sad variety of woes I mourn!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.20#My mind, reflective, in a thorny maze
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.21#Devious from care to care incessant strays.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.22#Now, wavering doubt succeeds to long despair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.23#Shall I my virgin nuptial vow revere;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.24#And, joining to my son's my menial train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.25#Partake his counsels, and assist his reign?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.26#Or, since, mature in manhood, he deplores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.27#His dome dishonour'd, and exhausted stores;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.28#Shall I, reluctant! to his will accord;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.29#And from the peers select the noblest lord;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.30#So by my choice avow'd, at length decide
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.31#These wasteful love-debates, a mourning bride!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.32#A visionary thought I'll now relate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.39.33#Illustrate, if you know, the shadow'd fate:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.1#"A team of twenty geese (a snow-white train!)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.2#Fed near the limpid lake with golden grain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.3#Amuse my pensive hours. The bird of Jove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.4#Fierce from his mountain-eyrie downward drove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.5#Each favourite fowl he pounced with deathful sway,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.6#And back triumphant wing'd his airy way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.7#My pitying eyes effused a plenteous stream,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.8#To view their death thus imaged in a dream;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.9#With tender sympathy to soothe my soul,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.10#A troop of matrons, fancy-form'd, condole.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.11#But whilst with grief and rage my bosom burn'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.12#Sudden the tyrant of the skies returned;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.13#Perch'd on the battlements he thus began
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.14#(In form an eagle, but in voice a man):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.15#`O queen! no vulgar vision of the sky
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.16#I come, prophetic of approaching joy;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.17#View in this plumy form thy victor-lord;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.18#The geese (a glutton race) by thee deplored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.19#Portend the suitors fated to my sword.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.20#This said, the pleasing feather'd omen ceased.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.21#When from the downy bands of sleep released,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.22#Fast by the limpid lake my swan-like train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.40.23#I found, insatiate of the golden grain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.41.1#"The vision self-explain'd (the chief replies)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.41.2#Sincere reveals the sanction of the skies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.41.3#Ulysses speaks his own return decreed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.41.4#And by his sword the suitors sure to bleed."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.1#"Hard is the task, and rare," (the queen rejoin'd,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.2#Impending destinies in dreams to find;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.3#Immured within the silent bower of sleep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.4#Two portals firm the various phantoms keep;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.5#Of ivory one; whence flit, to mock the brain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.6#Of winged lies a light fantastic train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.7#The gate opposed pellucid valves adorn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.8#And columns fair incased with polish'd horn;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.9#Where images of truth for passage wait,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.10#With visions manifest of future fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.11#Not to this troop, I fear, that phantom soar'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.12#Which spoke Ulysses to this realm restored;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.13#Delusive semblance!-but my remnant life
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.14#Heaven shall determine in a gameful strife;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.15#With that famed bow Ulysses taught to bend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.16#For me the rival archers shall contend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.17#As on the listed field he used to place
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.18#Six beams, opposed to six in equal space;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.19#Elanced afar by his unerring art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.20#Sure through six circlets flew the whizzing dart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.21#So, when the sun restores the purple day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.22#Their strength and skill the suitors shall assay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.23#To him the spousal honour is decreed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.24#Who through the rings directs the feather'd reed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.25#Torn from these walls (where long the kinder powers
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.26#With joy and pomp have wing'd my youthful hours!)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.27#On this poor breast no dawn of bliss shall beam;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.28#The pleasure past supplies a copious theme
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.42.29#For many a dreary thought, and many a doleful dream!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.43.1#"Propose the sportive lot (the chief replies),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.43.2#Nor dread to name yourself the bowyer's prize;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.43.3#Ulysses will surprise the unfinish'd game,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.43.4#Avow'd, and falsify the suitors' claim."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.44.1#To whom with grace serene the queen rejoin'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.44.2#"In all thy speech what pleasing force I find!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.44.3#O'er my suspended woe thy words prevail;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.44.4#I part reluctant from the pleasing tale,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.44.5#But Heaven, that knows what all terrestrials need,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.44.6#Repose to night, and toil to day decreed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.44.7#Grateful vicissitudes! yet me withdrawn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.44.8#Wakeful to weep and watch the tardy dawn
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.44.9#Establish'd use enjoins; to rest and joy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.44.10#Estranged, since dear Ulysses sail'd to Troy!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.44.11#Meantime instructed is the menial tribe
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.44.12#Your couch to fashion as yourself prescribe."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.45.1#Thus affable, her bower the queen ascends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.45.2#The sovereign step a beauteous train attends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.45.3#There imaged to her soul Ulysses rose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.45.4#Down her pale cheek new-streaming sorrow flows;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.45.5#Till soft oblivious shade Minerva spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:19.45.6#And o'er her eyes ambrosial slumber shed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.1.1#An ample hide devine Ulysses spread.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.1.2#And form'd of fleecy skins his humble bed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.1.3#(The remnants of the spoil the suitor-crowd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.1.4#In festival devour'd, and victims vow'd).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.1.5#Then o'er the chief, Eurynome the chaste
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.1.6#With duteous care a downy carpet cast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.1.7#With dire revenge his thoughtful bosom glows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.1.8#And, ruminating wrath, he scorns repose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.1#As thus pavilion'd in the porch he lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.2#Scenes of lewd loves his wakeful eyes survey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.3#Whilst to nocturnal joys impure repair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.4#With wanton glee, the prostituted fair.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.5#His heart with rage this new dishonour stung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.6#Wavering his thoughts in dubious balance hung:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.7#Or instant should he quench the guilty flame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.8#With their own blood, and intercept the shame:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.9#Or to their lust indulge a last embrace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.10#And let the peers consummate the disgrace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.11#Round his swoln heart the murmurous fury rolls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.12#As o'er her young the mother-mastiff growls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.13#And bays the stranger groom: so wrath compress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.14#Recoiling, mutter'd thunder in his breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.15#"Poor suffering heart! (he cried,) support the pain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.16#Of wounded honour, and thy rage restrain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.17#Not fiercer woes thy fortitude could foil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.18#When the brave partners of thy ten years' toil
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.19#Dire Polypheme devour'd; I then was freed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.2.20#By patient prudence from the death decreed."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.3.1#Thus anchor'd safe on reason's peaceful coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.3.2#Tempests of wrath his soul no longer toss'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.3.3#Restless his body rolls, to rage resign'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.3.4#As one who long with pale-eyed famine pined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.3.5#The savoury cates on glowing embers cast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.3.6#Incessant turns, impatient for repast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.3.7#Ulysses so, from side to side-devolved,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.3.8#In self-debate the suitor's doom resolved
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.3.9#When in the form of mortal nymph array'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.3.10#From heaven descends the Jove-born martial maid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.3.11#And'hovering o'er his head in view confess'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.3.12#The goddess thus her favourite care address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.4.1#"O thou, of mortals most inured to woes!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.4.2#Why roll those eyes unfriended of repose?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.4.3#Beneath thy palace-roof forget thy care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.4.4#Bless'd in thy queen! bless'd in thy blooming heir!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.4.5#Whom, to the gods when suppliant fathers bow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.4.6#They name the standard of their dearest vow."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.5.1#"Just is thy kind reproach (the chief rejoin'd),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.5.2#Deeds full of fate distract my various mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.5.3#In contemplation wrapp'd. This hostile crew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.5.4#What single arm hath prowess to subdue?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.5.5#Or if, by Jove's and thy auxiliar aid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.5.6#They're doom'd to bleed; O say, celestial maid!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.5.7#Where shall Ulysses shun, or how sustain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.5.8#Nations embattled to revenge the slain?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.6.1#"Oh impotence of faith! (Minerva cries,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.6.2#If man on frail unknowing man relies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.6.3#Doubt you the gods? Lo, Pallas' self descends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.6.4#Inspires thy counsels, and thy toils attends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.6.5#In me affianced, fortify thy breast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.6.6#Though myriads leagued thy rightful claim contest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.6.7#My sure divinity shall bear the shield,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.6.8#And edge thy sword to reap the glorious field.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.6.9#Now, pay the debt to craving nature due,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.6.10#Her faded powers with balmy rest renew."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.6.11#She ceased, ambrosial slumbers seal his eyes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.6.12#Her care dissolves in visionary joys
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.6.13#The goddess, pleased, regains her natal skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.7.1#Not so the queen; the downy bands of sleep
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.7.2#By grief relax'd she waked again to weep:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.7.3#A gloomy pause ensued of dumb despair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.7.4#Then thus her fate invoked, with fervent prayer
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.1#"Diana! speed thy deathful ebon dart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.2#And cure the pangs of this convulsive heart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.3#Snatch me, ye whirlwinds! far from human race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.4#Toss'd through the void illimitable space
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.5#Or if dismounted from the rapid cloud,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.6#Me with his whelming wave let Ocean shroud!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.7#So, Pandarus, thy hopes, three orphan fair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.8#Were doom'd to wander through the devious air;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.9#Thyself untimely, and thy consort died,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.10#But four celestials both your cares supplied.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.11#Venus in tender delicacy rears
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.12#With honey, milk, and wine their infant years;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.13#Imperial Juno to their youth assigned
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.14#A form majestic, and sagacious mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.15#With shapely growth Diana graced their bloom;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.16#And Pallas taught the texture of the loom.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.17#But whilst, to learn their lots in nuptial love,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.18#Bright Cytherea sought the bower of Jove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.19#(The God supreme, to whose eternal eye
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.20#The registers of fate expanded lie;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.21#Wing'd Harpies snatch the unguarded charge away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.22#And to the Furies bore a grateful prey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.23#Be such my lot! Or thou, Diana, speed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.24#Thy shaft, and send me joyful to the dead;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.25#To seek my lord among the warrior train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.26#Ere second vows my bridal faith profane.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.27#When woes the waking sense alone assail,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.28#Whilst Night extends her soft oblivious veil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.29#Of other wretches' care the torture ends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.30#No truce the warfare of my heart suspends!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.31#The night renews the day distracting theme,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.32#And airy terrors sable every dream.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.33#The last alone a kind illusion wrought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.34#And to my bed my loved Ulysses brought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.35#In manly bloom, and each majestic grace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.36#As when for Troy he left my fond embrace;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.37#Such raptures in my beating bosom rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.8.38#I deem it sure a vision of the skies."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.9.1#Thus, whilst Aurora mounts her purple throne,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.9.2#In audible laments she breathes her moan;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.9.3#The sounds assault Ulysses' wakeful ear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.9.4#Misjudging of the cause, a sudden fear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.9.5#Of his arrival known, the chief alarms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.9.6#He thinks the queen is rushing to his arms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.9.7#Upspringing from his couch, with active haste
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.9.8#The fleece and carpet in the dome he placed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.9.9#(The hide, without, imbibed the morning air);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.9.10#And thus the gods invoked with ardent prayer:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.10.1#"Jove, and eternal thrones! with heaven to friend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.10.2#If the long series of my woes shall end;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.10.3#Of human race now rising from repose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.10.4#Let one a blissful omen here disclose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.10.5#And, to confirm my faith, propitious Jove!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.10.6#Vouchsafe the sanction of a sign above."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.1#Whilst lowly thus the chief adoring bows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.2#The pitying god his guardian aid avows.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.3#Loud from a sapphire sky his thunder sounds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.4#With springing hope the hero's heart rebounds.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.5#Soon, with consummate joy to crown his prayer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.6#An omen'd voice invades his ravish'd ear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.7#Beneath a pile that close the dome adjoin'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.8#Twelve female slaves the gift of Ceres grind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.9#Task'd for the royal board to bolt the bran
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.10#From the pure flour (the growth and strength of man)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.11#Discharging to the day the labour due,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.12#Now early to repose the rest withdrew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.13#One maid unequal to the task assign'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.14#Still turn'd the toilsome mill with anxious mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.11.15#And thus in bitterness of soul divined:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.12.1#"Father of gods and men, whose thunders roll
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.12.2#O'er the cerulean vault, and shake the pole:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.12.3#Whoe'er from Heaven has gain'd this rare ostent
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.12.4#(Of granted vows a certain signal sent),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.12.5#In this blest moment of accepted prayer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.12.6#Piteous, regard a wretch consumed with care!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.12.7#Instant, O Jove! confound the suitor-train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.12.8#For whom o'ertoil'd I grind the golden grain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.12.9#Far from this dome the lewd devourers cast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.12.10#And be this festival decreed their last!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.13.1#Big with their doom denounced in earth and sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.13.2#Ulysses' heart dilates with secret joy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.13.3#Meantime the menial train with unctious wood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.13.4#Heap'd high the genial hearth, Vulcanian food:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.13.5#When, early dress'd, advanced the royal heir;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.13.6#With manly grasp he waved a martial spear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.13.7#A radiant sabre graced his purple zone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.13.8#And on his foot the golden sandal shone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.13.9#His steps impetuous to the portal press'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.13.10#And Euryclea thus he there address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.14.1#"Say thou to whom my youth its nurture owes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.14.2#Was care for due refection and repose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.14.3#Bestow'd the stranger-guest? Or waits he grieved,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.14.4#His age not honour'd, nor his wants relieved?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.14.5#Promiscuous grace on all the queen confers
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.14.6#(In woes bewilder'd, oft the wisest errs).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.14.7#The wordy vagrant to the dole aspires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.14.8#And modest worth with noble scorn retires."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.15.1#She thus: "O cease that ever-honour'd name
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.15.2#To blemish now: it ill deserves your blame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.15.3#A bowl of generous wine sufficed the guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.15.4#In vain the queen the night refection press'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.15.5#Nor would he court repose in downy state,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.15.6#Unbless'd, abandon'd to the rage of Fate!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.15.7#A hide beneath the portico was spread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.15.8#And fleecy skins composed an humble bed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.15.9#A downy carpet cast with duteous care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.15.10#Secured him from the keen nocturnal air."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.16.1#His cornel javelin poised with regal port,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.16.2#To the sage Greeks convened in Themis' court,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.16.3#Forth-issuing from the dome the prince repair'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.16.4#Two dogs of chase, a lion-hearted guard,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.16.5#Behind him sourly stalked. Without delay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.16.6#The dame divides the labour of the day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.16.7#Thus urging to the toil the menial train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.17.1#"What marks of luxury the marble stain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.17.2#Its wonted lustre let the floor regain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.17.3#The seats with purple clothe in order due;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.17.4#And let the abstersive sponge the board renew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.17.5#Let some refresh the vase's sullied mould;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.17.6#Some bid the goblets boast their native gold;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.17.7#Some to the spring, with each a jar, repair,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.17.8#And copious waters pure for bathing bear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.17.9#Dispatch! for soon the suitors will essay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.17.10#The lunar feast-rites to the god of day."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.1#She said: with duteous haste a bevy fair
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.2#Of twenty virgins to the spring repair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.3#With varied toils the rest adorn the dome.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.4#Magnificent, and blithe, the suitors come.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.5#Some wield the sounding axe; the dodder'd oaks
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.6#Divide, obedient to the forceful strokes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.7#Soon from the fount, with each a brimming urn
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.8#(Eumaeus in their train), the maids return.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.9#Three porkers for the feast, all brawny-chined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.10#He brought; the choicest of the tusky-kind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.11#In lodgments first secure his care he viewed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.12#Then to the king this friendly speech renew'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.13#"Now say sincere, my guest! the suitor-train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.14#Still treat thy worth with lordly dull disdain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.18.15#Or speaks their deed a bounteous mind humane?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.19.1#"Some pitying god (Ulysses sad replied)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.19.2#With vollied vengeance blast their towering pride!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.19.3#No conscious blush, no sense of right, restrains
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.19.4#The tides of lust that swell the boiling veins;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.19.5#From vice to vice their appetites are toss'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.19.6#All cheaply sated at another's cost!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.20.1#While thus the chief his woes indignant told,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.20.2#Melanthius, master of the bearded fold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.20.3#The goodliest goats of all the royal herd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.20.4#Spontaneous to the suitors' feast preferr'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.20.5#Two grooms assistant bore the victims bound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.20.6#With quavering cries the vaulted roofs resound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.20.7#And to the chief austere aloud began
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.20.8#The wretch unfriendly to the race of man:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.21.1#"Here vagrant, still? offensive to my lords!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.21.2#Blows have more energy than airy words;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.21.3#These arguments I'll use: nor conscious shame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.21.4#Nor threats, thy bold intrusion will reclaim.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.21.5#On this high feast the meanest vulgar boast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.21.6#A plenteous board! Hence! seek another host!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.22.1#Rejoinder to the churl the king disdain'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.22.2#But shook his head, and rising wrath restrain'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.23.1#From Cephanelia 'cross the surgy main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.23.2#Philaetius late arrived, a faithful swain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.23.3#A steer ungrateful to the bull's embrace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.23.4#And goats he brought, the pride of all their race;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.23.5#Imported in a shallop not his own;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.23.6#The dome re-echoed to the mingl'd moan.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.23.7#Straight to the guardian of the bristly kind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.23.8#He thus began, benevolent of mind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.24.1#"What guest is he, of such majestic air?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.24.2#His lineage and paternal clime declare:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.24.3#Dim through the eclipse of fate, the rays divine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.24.4#Of sovereign state with faded splendour shine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.24.5#If monarchs by the gods are plunged in woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.24.6#To what abyss are we foredoom'd to go!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.24.7#Then affable he thus the chief address'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.24.8#Whilst with pathetic warmth his hand he press'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.1#"Stranger, may fate a milder aspect show,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.2#And spin thy future with a whiter clue!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.3#O Jove! for ever death to human cries;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.4#The tyrant, not the father of the skies!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.5#Unpiteous of the race thy will began!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.6#The fool of fate, thy manufacture, man,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.7#With penury, contempt, repulse, and care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.8#The galling load of life is doom'd to bear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.9#Ulysses from his state a wanderer still,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.10#Upbraids thy power, thy wisdom, or thy will!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.11#O monarch ever dear!-O man of woe!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.12#Fresh flow my tears, and shall for ever flow!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.13#Like thee, poor stranger guest, denied his home,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.14#Like thee: in rags obscene decreed to roam!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.15#Or, haply perish'd on some distant coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.16#In stygian gloom he glides, a pensive ghost!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.17#Oh, grateful for the good his bounty gave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.18#I'll grieve, till sorrow sink me to the grave!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.19#His kind protecting hand my youth preferr'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.20#The regent of his Cephalenian herd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.21#With vast increase beneath my care it spreads:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.22#A stately breed! and blackens far the meads.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.23#Constrain'd, the choicest beeves I thence import,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.24#To cram these cormorants that crowd his court:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.25#Who in partition seek his realm to share;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.26#Nor human right nor wrath divine revere,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.27#Since here resolved oppressive these reside,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.28#Contending doubts my anxious heart divide:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.29#Now to some foreign clime inclined to fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.30#And with the royal herd protection buy;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.31#Then, happier thoughts return the nodding scale,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.32#Light mounts despair, alternate hopes prevail:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.33#In opening prospects of ideal joy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.25.34#My king returns; the proud usurpers die."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.26.1#To whom the chief: "In thy capacious mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.26.2#Since daring zeal with cool debate is join'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.26.3#Attend a deed already ripe in fate:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.26.4#Attest, O Jove! the truth I now relate!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.26.5#This sacred truth attest, each genial power,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.26.6#Who bless the board, and guard this friendly bower!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.26.7#Before thou quit the dome (nor long delay)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.26.8#Thy wish produced in act, with pleased survey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.26.9#Thy wondering eyes shall view: his rightful reign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.26.10#By arms avow'd Ulysses shall regain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.26.11#And to the shades devote the suitor-train."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.27.1#"O Jove supreme! (the raptured swain replies,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.27.2#With deeds consummate soon the promised joys!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.27.3#These aged nerves, with new-born vigour strung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.27.4#In that blest cause should emulate the young."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.27.5#Assents Eumaeus to the prayer address'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.27.6#And equal ardours fire his loyal breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.28.1#Meantime the suitors urge the prince's fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.28.2#And deathful arts employ the dire debate:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.28.3#When in his airy tour, the bird of Jove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.28.4#Truss'd with his sinewy pounce a trembling dove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.28.5#Sinister to their hope! This omen eyed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.28.6#Amphinomus, who thus presaging cried:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.29.1#"The gods from force and fraud the prince defend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.29.2#O peers! the sanguinary scheme suspend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.29.3#Your future thought let sable fate employ;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.29.4#And give the present hour to genial joy."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.1#From council straight the assenting peerage ceased,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.2#And in the dome prepared the genial feast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.3#Disrobed, their vests apart in order lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.4#Then all with speed succinct the victims slay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.5#With sheep and shaggy goats the porkers bled,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.6#And the proud steer was on the marble spread.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.7#With fire prepared, they deal the morsels round,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.8#Wine, rosy-bright, the brimming goblets crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.9#By sage Eumaeus borne; the purple tide
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.10#Melanthius from an ample jar supplied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.11#High canisters of bread Philaetius placed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.12#And eager all devour the rich repast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.13#Disposed apart, Ulysses shares the treat;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.14#A trivet table, and ignobler seat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.15#The prince appoints; but to his sire assigns
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.16#The tasteful inwards, and nectareous wines.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.17#"Partake, my guest (he cried), without control
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.18#The social feast, and drain the cheering bowl:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.19#Dread not the railer's laugh, nor ruffian's rage;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.20#No vulgar roof protects thy honour'd age;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.21#This dome a refuge to thy wrongs shall be,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.22#From my great sire too soon devolved to me!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.23#Your violence and scorn, ye suitors, cease,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.30.24#Lest arms avenge the violated peace."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.31.1#Awed by the prince, so haughty, brave, and young,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.31.2#Rage gnaw'd the lip, amazement chain'd the tongue.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.31.3#"Be patient, peers! (at length Antinous cries,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.31.4#The threats of vain imperious youth despise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.31.5#Would Jove permit the meditated blow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.31.6#That stream of eloquence should cease to flow."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.1#Without reply vouchsafed, Antinous ceased:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.2#Meanwhile the pomp of festival increased:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.3#By heralds rank'd; in marshall'd order move
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.4#The city tribes, to pleased Apollo's grove:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.5#Beneath the verdure of which awful shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.6#The lunar hecatomb they grateful laid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.7#Partook the sacred feast, and ritual honours paid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.8#But the rich banquet, in the dome prepared
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.9#(An humble sideboard set) Ulysses shared.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.10#Observant of the prince's high behest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.11#His menial train attend the stranger-guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.12#Whom Pallas with unpardoning fury fired,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.13#By lordly pride and keen reproach inspired.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.14#A Samian peer, more studious than the rest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.15#Of vice, who teem'd with many a dead-born jest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.16#And urged, for title to a consort queen,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.17#Unnumber'd acres arable and green
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.18#(Otesippus named); this lord Ulysses eyed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.32.19#And thus burst out the imposthumate with pride:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.33.1#"The sentence I propose, ye peers, attend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.33.2#Since due regard must wait the prince's friend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.33.3#Let each a token of esteem bestow:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.33.4#This gift acquits the dear respect I owe;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.33.5#With which he nobly may discharge his seat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.33.6#And pay the menials for a master's treat."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.1#He said: and of the steer before him placed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.2#That sinewy fragment at Ulysses cast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.3#Where to the pastern-bone, by nerves combined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.4#The well-horn'd foot indissolubly join'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.5#Which whizzing high, the wall unseemly sign'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.6#The chief indignant grins a ghastly smile;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.7#Revenge and scorn within his bosom boil:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.8#When thus the prince with pious rage inflamed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.9#"Had not the inglorious wound thy malice aim'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.10#Fall'n guiltless of the mark, my certain spear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.11#Had made thee buy the brutal triumph dear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.12#Nor should thy sire a queen his daughter boast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.13#The suitor, now, had vanish'd in a ghost:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.14#No more, ye lewd compeers, with lawless power
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.15#Invade my dome, my herds and flocks devour:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.16#For genuine worth, of age mature to know,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.17#My grape shall redden, and my harvest grow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.18#Or, if each other's wrongs ye still support,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.19#With rapes and riot to profane my court;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.20#What single arm with numbers can contend?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.21#On me let all your lifted swords descend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.34.22#And with my life such vile dishonours end."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.35.1#A long cessation of discourse ensued,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.35.2#By gentler Agelaus thus renew'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.1#"A just reproof, ye peers! your rage restrain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.2#From the protected guest, and menial train:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.3#And, prince! to stop the source of future ill,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.4#Assent yourself, and gain the royal will.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.5#Whilst hope prevail'd to see your sire restored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.6#Of right the queen refused a second lord:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.7#But who so vain of faith, so blind to fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.8#To think he still survives to claim the state?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.9#Now press the sovereign dame with warm desire
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.10#To wed, as wealth or worth her choice inspire:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.11#The lord selected to the nuptial joys
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.12#Far hence will lead the long-contested prize:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.13#Whilst in paternal pomp with plenty bless'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.36.14#You reign, of this imperial dome possess'd."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.37.1#Sage and serene Telemachus replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.37.2#"By him at whose behest the thunder flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.37.3#And by the name on earth I most revere,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.37.4#By great Ulysses and his woes I swear!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.37.5#(Who never must review his dear domain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.37.6#Enroll'd, perhaps, in Pluto's dreary train),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.37.7#Whene'er her choice the royal dame avows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.37.8#My bridal gifts shall load the future spouse:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.37.9#But from this dome my parent queen to chase!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.37.10#From me, ye gods! avert such dire disgrace."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.38.1#But Pallas clouds with intellectual gloom
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.38.2#The suitors' souls, insensate of their doom!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.38.3#A mirthful frenzy seized the fated crowd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.38.4#The roofs resound with causeless laughter loud;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.38.5#Floating in gore, portentous to survey!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.38.6#In each discolour'd vase the viands lay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.38.7#Then down each cheek the tears spontaneous flow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.38.8#And sudden sighs precede approaching woe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.38.9#In vision wrapp'd, the Hyperesian seer
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.38.10#Uprose, and thus divined the vengeance near:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.39.1#"O race to death devote! with Stygian shade
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.39.2#Each destin'd peer impending fates invade;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.39.3#With tears your wan distorted cheeks are drown'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.39.4#With sanguine drops the walls are rubied round:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.39.5#Thick swarms the spacious hall with howling ghosts,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.39.6#To people Orcus, and the burning coasts!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.39.7#Nor gives the sun his golden orb to roll,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.39.8#But universal night usurps the pole!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.40.1#Yet warn'd in vain, with laughter loud elate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.40.2#The peers reproach the sure divine of Fate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.40.3#And thus Eurymachus: "The dotard's mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.40.4#To every sense is lost, to reason blind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.40.5#Swift from the dome conduct the slave away;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.40.6#Let him in open air behold the day."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.41.1#"Tax not (the heaven-illumined seer rejoin'd)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.41.2#Of rage, or folly, my prophetic mind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.41.3#No clouds of error dim the ethereal rays,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.41.4#Her equal power each faithful sense obeys.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.41.5#Unguided hence my trembling steps I bend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.41.6#Far hence, before yon hovering deaths descend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.41.7#Lest the ripe harvest of revenge begun,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.41.8#I share the doom ye suitors cannot shun."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.1#This said, to sage Piraeus sped the seer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.2#His honour'd host, a welcome inmate there.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.3#O'er the protracted feast the suitors sit,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.4#And aim to wound the prince with pointless wit:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.5#Cries one, with scornful leer and mimic voice,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.6#"Thy charity we praise, but not thy choice;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.7#Why such profusion of indulgence shown
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.8#To this poor, timorous, toil-detesting drone?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.9#That others feeds on planetary schemes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.10#And pays his host with hideous noon-day dreams.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.11#But, prince! for once at least believe a friend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.12#To some Sicilian mart these courtiers send,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.13#Where, if they yield their freight across the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.42.14#Dear sell the slaves! demand no greater gain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.43.1#Thus jovial they; but nought the prince replies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.43.2#Full on his sire he roll'd his ardent eyes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.43.3#Impatient straight to flesh his virgin-sword;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.43.4#From the wise chief he waits the deathful word.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.43.5#Nigh in her bright alcove, the pensive queen
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.43.6#To see the circle sate, of all unseen.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.43.7#Sated at length they rise, and bid prepare
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.43.8#An eve-repast, with equal cost and care:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.43.9#But vengeful Pallas, with preventing speed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.43.10#A feast proportion'd to their crimes decreed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:20.43.11#A feast of death, the feasters doom'd to bleed!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.1.1#And Pallas now, to raise the rivals' fires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.1.2#With her own art Penelope inspires
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.1.3#Who now can bend Ulysses' bow, and wing
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.1.4#The well-aim'd arrow through the distant ring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.1.5#Shall end the strife, and win the imperial dame:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.1.6#But discord and black death await the game!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.2.1#The prudent queen the lofty stair ascends:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.2.2#At distance due a virgin-train attends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.2.3#A brazen key she held, the handle turn'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.2.4#With steel and polish'd elephant adorn'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.2.5#Swift to the inmost room she bent her way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.2.6#Where, safe reposed, the royal treasures lay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.2.7#There shone high heap'd the labour'd brass and ore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.2.8#And there the bow which great Ulysses bore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.2.9#And there the quiver, where now guiltless slept
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.2.10#Those winged deaths that many a matron wept.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.1#This gift, long since when Sparta's shore he trod,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.2#On young Ulysses Iphitus bestowed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.3#Beneath Orsilochus' roof they met;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.4#One loss was private, one a public debt;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.5#Messena's state from Ithaca detains
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.6#Three hundred sheep, and all the shepherd swains;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.7#And to the youthful prince to urge the laws,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.8#The king and elders trust their common cause.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.9#But Iphitus, employed on other cares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.10#Search'd the wide country for his wandering mares,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.11#And mules, the strongest of the labouring kind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.12#Hapless to search; more hapless still to find!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.13#For journeying on to Hercules, at length
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.14#That lawless wretch, that man of brutal strength,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.15#Deaf to Heaven's voice, the social rites transgress'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.16#And for the beauteous mares destroy'd his guest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.17#He gave the bow; and on Ulysses' part
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.18#Received a pointed sword, and missile dart:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.19#Of luckless friendship on a foreign shore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.20#Their first, last pledges! for they met no more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.21#The bow, bequeath'd by this unhappy hand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.22#Ulysses bore not from his native land;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.23#Nor in the front of battle taught to bend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.3.24#But kept in dear memorial of his friend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.1#Now gently winding up the fair ascent,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.2#By many an easy step the matron went;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.3#Then o'er the pavement glides with grace divine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.4#(With polish'd oak the level pavements shine);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.5#The folding gates a dazzling light display'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.6#With pomp of various architrave o'erlaid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.7#The bolt, obedient to the silken string,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.8#Forsakes the staple as she pulls the ring;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.9#The wards respondent to the key turn round;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.10#The bars fall back; the flying valves resound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.11#Loud as a bull makes hill and valley ring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.12#So roar'd the lock when it released the spring.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.13#She moves majestic through the wealthy room,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.14#Where treasured garments cast a rich perfume;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.15#There from the column where aloft it hung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.16#Reach'd in its splendid case, the bow unstrung;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.17#Across her knees she laid the well-known bow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.18#And pensive sate, and tears began to flow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.19#To full satiety of grief she mourns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.20#Then silent to the joyous hall returns,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.21#To the proud suitors bears in pensive state
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.4.22#The unbended bow, and arrows winged with fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.5.1#Behind, her train the polish'd coffer brings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.5.2#Which held the alternate brass and silver rings.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.5.3#Full in the portal the chaste queen appears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.5.4#And with her veil conceals the coming tears:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.5.5#On either side awaits a virgin fair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.5.6#While thus the matron, with majestic air:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.6.1#"Say you, when these forbidden walls inclose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.6.2#For whom my victims bleed, my vintage flows:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.6.3#If these neglected, faded charms can move?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.6.4#Or is it but a vain pretence, you love?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.6.5#If I the prize, if me you seek to wife,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.6.6#Hear the conditions, and commence the strife.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.6.7#Who first Ulysses' wondrous bow shall bend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.6.8#And through twelve ringlets the fleet arrow send;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.6.9#Him will I follow, and forsake my home,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.6.10#For him forsake this loved, this wealthy dome,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.6.11#Long, long the scene of all my past delight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.6.12#And still to last, the vision of my night!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.7.1#Graceful she said, and bade Eumaeus show
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.7.2#The rival peers the ringlets and the bow.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.7.3#From his full eyes the tears unbidden spring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.7.4#Touch'd at the dear memorials of his king.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.7.5#Philaetius too relents, but secret shed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.7.6#The tender drops. Antinous saw, and said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.8.1#"Hence to your fields, ye rustics! hence away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.8.2#Nor stain with grief the pleasures of the day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.8.3#Nor to the royal heart recall in vain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.8.4#The sad remembrance of a perish'd man.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.8.5#Enough her precious tears already flow--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.8.6#Or share the feast with due respect; or go
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.8.7#To weep abroad, and leave to us the bow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.8.8#No vulgar task! Ill suits this courtly crew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.8.9#That stubborn horn which brave Ulysses drew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.8.10#I well remember (for I gazed him o'er
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.8.11#While yet a child), what majesty he bore!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.8.12#And still (all infant as I was) retain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.8.13#The port, the strength, the grandeur of the man."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.9.1#He said, but in his soul fond joys arise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.9.2#And his proud hopes already win the prize.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.9.3#To speed the flying shaft through every ring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.9.4#Wretch! is not thine: the arrows of the king
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.9.5#Shall end those hopes, and fate is on the wing!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.10.1#Then thus Telemachus: "Some god I find
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.10.2#With pleasing frenzy has possess'd my mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.10.3#When a loved mother threatens to depart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.10.4#Why with this ill-timed gladness leaps my heart?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.10.5#Come then, ye suitors! and dispute a prize
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.10.6#Richer than all the Achaian state supplies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.10.7#Than all proud Argos, or Mycaena knows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.10.8#Than all our isles or continents inclose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.10.9#A woman matchless, and almost divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.10.10#Fit for the praise of every tongue but mine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.10.11#No more excuses then, no more delay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.10.12#Haste to the trial--Lo! I lead the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.11.1#"I too may try, and if this arm can wing
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.11.2#The feather'd arrow through the destined ring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.11.3#Then if no happier night the conquest boast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.11.4#I shall not sorrow for a mother lost;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.11.5#But, bless'd in her, possess those arms alone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.11.6#Heir of my father's strength, as well as throne."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.1#He spoke; then rising, his broad sword unbound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.2#And cast his purple garment on the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.3#A trench he open'd: in a line he placed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.4#The level axes, and the points made fast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.5#(His perfect skill the wondering gazers eyed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.6#The game as yet unseen, as yet untried).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.7#Then, with a manly pace, he took his stand:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.8#And grasp'd the bow, and twang'd it in his hand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.9#Three times, with beating heart, he made essay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.10#Three times, unequal to the task, gave way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.11#A modest boldness on his cheek appear'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.12#And thrice he hoped, and thrice again he fear'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.13#The fourth had drawn it. The great sire with joy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.14#Beheld, but with a sign forbade the boy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.15#His ardour straight the obedient prince suppress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.12.16#And, artful, thus the suitor-train address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.13.1#"O lay the cause on youth yet immature!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.13.2#(For heaven forbid such weakness should endure!)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.13.3#How shall this arm, unequal to the bow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.13.4#Retort an insult, or repel a foe?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.13.5#But you! whom Heaven with better nerves has bless'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.13.6#Accept the trial, and the prize contest."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.1#He cast the bow before him, and apart
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.2#Against the polish'd quiver propp'd the dart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.3#Resuming then his seat, Eupithes' son,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.4#The bold Antinous, to the rest begun:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.5#"From where the goblet first begins to flow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.6#From right to left in order take the bow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.7#And prove your several strengths." The princes heard
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.8#And first Leiodes, blameless priest'd, appear'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.9#The eldest born of Oenops' noble race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.10#Who next the goblet held his holy place:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.11#He, only he, of all the suitor throng,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.12#Their deeds detested, and abjured the wrong.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.13#With tender hands the stubborn horn he strains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.14#The stubborn horn resisted all his pains!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.15#Already in despair he gives it o'er:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.16#"Take it who will (he cries), I strive no more,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.17#What numerous deaths attend this fatal bow!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.18#What souls and spirits shall it send below!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.19#Better, indeed, to die, and fairly give
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.20#Nature her debt, than disappointed live,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.21#With each new sun to some new hope a prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.22#Yet still to-morrow falser than to-day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.23#How long in vain Penelope we sought!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.24#This bow shall ease us of that idle thought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.25#And send us with some humbler wife to live,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.14.26#Whom gold shall gain, or destiny shall give."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.15.1#Thus speaking, on the floor the bow he placed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.15.2#(With rich inlay the various floor was graced):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.15.3#At distance far the feather'd shaft he throws,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.15.4#And to the seat returns from whence he rose.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.1#To him Antinous thus with fury said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.2#"What words ill-omen'd from thy lips have fled?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.3#Thy coward-function ever is in fear!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.4#Those arms are dreadful which thou canst not bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.5#Why should this bow be fatal to the brave?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.6#Because the priest is born a peaceful slave.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.7#Mark then what others can." He ended there,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.8#And bade Melanthius a vast pile prepare;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.9#He gives it instant flame, then fast beside
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.10#Spreads o'er an ample board a bullock's hide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.11#With melted lard they soak the weapon o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.12#Chafe every knot, and supple every pore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.13#Vain all their art, and all their strength as vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.14#The bow inflexible resists their pain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.15#The force of great Eurymachus alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.16#And bold Antinous, yet untired, unknown:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.17#Those only now remain'd; but those confess'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.16.18#Of all the train the mightiest and the best.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.17.1#Then from the hall, and from the noisy crew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.17.2#The masters of the herd and flock withdrew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.17.3#The king observes them, he the hall forsakes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.17.4#And, past the limits of the court, o'ertakes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.17.5#Then thus with accent mild Ulysses spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.17.6#"Ye faithful guardians of the herd and flock!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.17.7#Shall I the secret of my breast conceal,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.17.8#Or (as my soul now dictates) shall I tell?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.17.9#Say, should some favouring god restore again
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.17.10#The lost Ulysses to his native reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.17.11#How beat your hearts? what aid would you afford
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.17.12#To the proud suitors, or your ancient lord?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.18.1#Philaetius thus: "O were thy word not vain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.18.2#Would mighty Jove restore that man again!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.18.3#These aged sinews, with new vigour strung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.18.4#In his blest cause should emulate the young."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.18.5#With equal vows Eumaeus too implored
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.18.6#Each power above, with wishes for his lord.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.1#He saw their secret souls, and thus began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.2#"Those vows the gods accord; behold the man!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.3#Your own Ulysses! twice ten years detain'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.4#By woes and wanderings from this hapless land:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.5#At length he comes; but comes despised, unknown,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.6#And finding faithful you, and you alone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.7#All else have cast him from their very thought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.8#E'en in their wishes and their prayers forgot!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.9#Hear then, my friends: If Jove this arm succeed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.10#And give yon impious revellers to bleed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.11#My care shall be to bless your future lives
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.12#With large possessions and with faithful wives;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.13#Fast by my palace shall your domes ascend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.14#And each on young Telemachus attend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.15#And each be call'd his brother and my friend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.16#To give you firmer faith, now trust your eye;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.17#Lo! the broad scar indented on my thigh,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.18#When with Autolycus' sons, of yore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.19#On Parnass' top I chased the tusky boar."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.20#His ragged vest then drawn aside disclosed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.21#The sign conspicuous, and the scar exposed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.22#Eager they view'd, with joy they stood amazed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.23#With tearful eyes o'er all their master gazed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.24#Around his neck their longing arms they cast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.25#His head, his shoulders, and his knees embraced;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.26#Tears followed tears; no word was in their power;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.27#In solemn silence fell the kindly shower.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.28#The king too weeps, the king too grasps their hands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.19.29#And moveless, as a marble fountain, stands.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.1#Thus had their joy wept down the setting sun,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.2#But first the wise man ceased, and thus begun:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.3#"Enough--on other cares your thought employ,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.4#For danger waits on all untimely joy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.5#Full many foes and fierce, observe us near;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.6#Some may betray, and yonder walls may hear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.7#Re-enter then, not all at once, but stay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.8#Some moments you, and let me lead the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.9#To me, neglected as I am I know
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.10#The haughty suitors will deny the bow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.11#But thou, Eumaeus, as 'tis borne away,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.12#Thy master's weapon to his hand convey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.13#At every portal let some matron wait,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.14#And each lock fast the well-compacted gate:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.15#Close let them keep, whate'er invades their ear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.16#Though arms, or shouts, or dying groans they hear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.17#To thy strict charge, Philaetius, we consign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.20.18#The court's main gate: to guard that pass be thine."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.21.1#This said, he first return'd; the faithful swains
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.21.2#At distance follow, as their king ordains.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.21.3#Before the flame Eurymachus now stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.21.4#And turns the bow, and chafes it with his hands
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.21.5#Still the tough bow unmoved. The lofty man
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.21.6#Sigh'd from his mighty soul, and thus began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.22.1#"I mourn the common cause: for, oh, my friends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.22.2#On me, on all, what grief, what shame attends!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.22.3#Not the lost nuptials can affect me more
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.22.4#(For Greece has beauteous dames on every shore),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.22.5#But baffled thus! confess'd so far below
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.22.6#Ulysses' strength, as not to bend his bow!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.22.7#How shall all ages our attempt deride!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.22.8#Our weakness scorn!" Antinous thus replied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.1#"Not so, Eurymachus: that no man draws
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.2#The wondrous bow, attend another cause.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.3#Sacred to Phoebus is the solemn day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.4#Which thoughtless we in games would waste away:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.5#Till the next dawn this ill-timed strife forego,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.6#And here leave fixed the ringlets in a row.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.7#Now bid the sewer approach, and let us join
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.8#In due libations, and in rites divine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.9#So end our night: before the day shall spring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.10#The choicest offerings let Melanthius bring:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.11#Let then to Phoebus' name the fatted thighs
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.12#Feed the rich smokes high curling to the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.13#So shall the patron of these arts bestow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.23.14#(For his the gift) the skill to bend the bow."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.24.1#They heard well pleased: the ready heralds bring
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.24.2#The cleansing waters from the limpid spring:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.24.3#The goblet high with rosy wine they crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.24.4#In order circling to the peers around.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.24.5#That rite complete, uprose the thoughtful man,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.24.6#And thus his meditated scheme began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.1#"If what I ask your noble minds approve,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.2#Ye peers and rivals in the royal love!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.3#Chief, if it hurt not great Antinous' ear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.4#(Whose sage decision I with wonder hear),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.5#And if Eurymachus the motion please:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.6#Give Heaven this day and rest the bow in peace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.7#To-morrow let your arms dispute the prize,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.8#And take it he, the favour'd of the skies!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.9#But, since till then this trial you delay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.10#Trust it one moment to my hands to-day:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.11#Fain would I prove, before your judging eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.12#What once I was, whom wretched you despise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.13#If yet this arm its ancient force retain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.14#Or if my woes (a long-continued train)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.25.15#And wants and insults, make me less than man."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.1#Rage flash'd in lightning from the suitors' eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.2#Yet mixed with terror at the bold emprise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.3#Antinous then: "O miserable guest!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.4#Is common sense quite banish'd from thy breast?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.5#Sufficed it not, within the palace placed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.6#To sit distinguish'd, with our presence graced,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.7#Admitted here with princes to confer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.8#A man unknown, a needy wanderer?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.9#To copious wine this insolence we owe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.10#And much thy betters wine can overthrow:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.11#The great Eurytian when this frenzy stung,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.12#Pirithous' roofs with frantic riot rung;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.13#Boundless the Centaur raged; till one and all
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.14#The heroes rose, and dragg'd him from the hall;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.15#His nose they shorten'd, and his ears they slit,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.16#And sent him sober'd home, with better wit.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.17#Hence with long war the double race was cursed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.18#Fatal to all, but to the aggressor first.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.19#Such fate I prophesy our guest attends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.20#If here this interdicted bow he bends:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.21#Nor shall these walls such insolence contain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.22#The first fair wind transports him o'er the main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.23#Where Echetus to death the guilty brings
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.24#(The worst of mortals, e'en the worst of kings).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.25#Better than that, if thou approve our cheer;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.26.26#Cease the mad strife and share our bounty here."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.27.1#To this the queen her just dislike express'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.28.1#"'Tis impious, prince, to harm the stranger-guest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.28.2#Base to insult who bears a suppliant's name,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.28.3#And some respect Telemachus may claim.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.28.4#What if the immortals on the man bestow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.28.5#Sufficient strength to draw the mighty bow?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.28.6#Shall I, a queen, by rival chiefs adored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.28.7#Accept a wandering stranger for my lord?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.28.8#A hope so idle never touch'd his brain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.28.9#Then ease your bosoms of a fear so vain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.28.10#Far be he banish'd from this stately scene
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.28.11#Who wrongs his princess with a thought so mean."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.29.1#"O fair! and wisest of so fair a kind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.29.2#(Respectful thus Eurymachus rejoin'd,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.29.3#Moved by no weak surmise, but sense of shame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.29.4#We dread the all-arraigning voice of Fame:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.29.5#We dread the censure of the meanest slave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.29.6#The weakest woman: all can wrong the brave.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.29.7#'Behold what wretches to the bed pretend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.29.8#Of that brave chief whose bow they could not bend!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.29.9#In came a beggar of the strolling crew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.29.10#And did what all those princes could not do.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.29.11#Thus will the common voice our deed defame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.29.12#And thus posterity upbraid our name."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.30.1#To whom the queen: "If fame engage your views,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.30.2#Forbear those acts which infamy pursues;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.30.3#Wrong and oppression no renown can raise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.30.4#Know, friend! that virtue is the path to praise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.30.5#The stature of our guest, his port, his face,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.30.6#Speak him descended from no vulgar race.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.30.7#To him the bow, as he desires, convey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.30.8#And to his hand if Phoebus give the day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.30.9#Hence, to reward his merit, be shall bear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.30.10#A two-edged falchion and a shining spear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.30.11#Embroider'd sandals, a rich cloak and vest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.30.12#A safe conveyance to his port of rest."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.31.1#"O royal mother! ever-honour'd name!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.31.2#Permit me (cries Telemachus) to claim
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.31.3#A son's just right. No Grecian prince but I
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.31.4#Has power this bow to grant or to deny.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.31.5#Of all that Ithaca's rough hills contain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.31.6#And all wide Elis' courser-breeding plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.31.7#To me alone my father's arms descend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.31.8#And mine alone they are, to give or lend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.31.9#Retire, O queen! thy household task resume,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.31.10#Tend, with thy maids, the labours of thy loom;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.31.11#The bow, the darts, and arms of chivalry,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.31.12#These cares to man belong, and most to me."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.32.1#Mature beyond his years, the queen admired
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.32.2#His sage reply, and with her train retired;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.32.3#There in her chamber as she sate apart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.32.4#Revolved his words, and placed them in her heart.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.32.5#On her Ulysses then she fix'd her soul;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.32.6#Down her fair cheek the tears abundant roll,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.32.7#Till gentle Pallas, piteous of her cries,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.32.8#In slumber closed her silver-streaming eyes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.1#Now through the press the bow Eumaeus bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.2#And all was riot, noise, and wild uproar.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.3#"Hold! lawless rustic! whither wilt thou go?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.4#To whom, insensate, dost thou bear the bow?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.5#Exiled for this to some sequester'd den,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.6#Far from the sweet society of men,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.7#To thy own dogs a prey thou shalt be made;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.8#If Heaven and Phoebus lend the suitors aid."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.9#Thus they. Aghast he laid the weapon down,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.10#But bold Telemachus thus urged him on:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.11#"Proceed, false slave, and slight their empty words:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.12#What! hopes the fool to please so many lords?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.13#Young as I am, thy prince's vengeful hand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.14#Stretch'd forth in wrath shall drive thee from the land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.15#Oh! could the vigour of this arm as well
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.16#The oppressive suitors from my walls expel!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.17#Then what a shoal of lawless men should go
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.33.18#To fill with tumult the dark courts below!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.34.1#The suitors with a scornful smile survey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.34.2#The youth, indulging in the genial day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.34.3#Eumaeus, thus encouraged, hastes to bring
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.34.4#The strifeful bow and gives it to the king.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.34.5#Old Euryclea calling them aside,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.34.6#"Hear what Telemachus enjoins (he cried):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.34.7#At every portal let some matron wait,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.34.8#And each lock fast the well-compacted gate;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.34.9#And if unusual sounds invade their ear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.34.10#If arms, or shouts, or dying groans they hear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.34.11#Let none to call or issue forth presume,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.34.12#But close attend the labours of the loom."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.35.1#Her prompt obedience on his order waits;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.35.2#Closed in an instant were the palace gates.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.35.3#In the same moment forth Philaetius flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.35.4#Secures the court, and with a cable ties
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.35.5#The utmost gate (the cable strongly wrought
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.35.6#Of Byblos' reed, a ship from Egypt brought);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.35.7#Then unperceived and silent at the board
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.35.8#His seat he takes, his eyes upon his lord.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.36.1#And now his well-known bow the master bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.36.2#Turn'd on all sides, and view'd it o'er and o'er;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.36.3#Lest time or worms had done the weapon wrong,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.36.4#Its owner absent, and untried so long.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.36.5#While some deriding--"How he turns the bow!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.36.6#Some other like it sure the man must know,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.36.7#Or else would copy; or in bows he deals;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.36.8#Perhaps he makes them, or perhaps he steals."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.36.9#"Heaven to this wretch (another cried) be kind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.36.10#And bless, in all to which he stands inclined.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.36.11#With such good fortune as he now shall find."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.1#Heedless he heard them: but disdain'd reply;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.2#The bow perusing with exactest eye.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.3#Then, as some heavenly minstrel, taught to sing
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.4#High notes responsive to the trembling string,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.5#To some new strain when he adapts the lyre,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.6#Or the dumb lute refits with vocal wire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.7#Relaxes, strains, and draws them to and fro;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.8#So the great master drew the mighty bow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.9#And drew with ease. One hand aloft display'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.10#The bending horns, and one the string essay'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.11#From his essaying hand the string, let fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.12#Twang'd short and sharp like the shrill swallow's cry.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.13#A general horror ran through all the race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.14#Sunk was each heart, and pale was every face,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.15#Signs from above ensued: the unfolding sky
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.16#In lightning burst; Jove thunder'd from on high.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.17#Fired at the call of heaven's almighty Lord,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.18#He snatch'd the shaft that glitter'd on the board
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.19#(Fast by, the rest lay sleeping in the sheath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.37.20#But soon to fly the messengers of death).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.1#Now sitting as he was, the cord he drew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.2#Through every ringlet levelling his view:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.3#Then notch'd the shaft, released, and gave it wing;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.4#The whizzing arrow vanished from the string,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.5#Sung on direct, and threaded every ring.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.6#The solid gate its fury scarcely bounds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.7#Pierced through and through the solid gate resounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.8#Then to the prince: "Nor have I wrought thee shame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.9#Nor err'd this hand unfaithful to its aim;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.10#Nor prov'd the toil too hard; nor have I lost
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.11#That ancient vigour, once my pride and boast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.12#Ill I deserved these haughty peers' disdain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.13#Now let them comfort their dejected train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.14#In sweet repast their present hour employ,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.15#Nor wait till evening for the genial joy:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.16#Then to the lute's soft voice prolong the night;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.38.17#Music, the banquet's most refined delight."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.39.1#He said, then gave a nod; and at the word
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.39.2#Telemachus girds on his shining sword.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.39.3#Fast by his father's side he takes his stand:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:21.39.4#The beamy javelin lightens in his hand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.1.1#Then fierce the hero o'er the threshold strode;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.1.2#Stripp'd of his rags, he blazed out like a god.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.1.3#Full in their face the lifted bow he bore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.1.4#And quiver'd deaths, a formidable store;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.1.5#Before his feet the rattling shower he threw,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.1.6#And thus, terrific, to the suitor-crew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.1#"One venturous game this hand hath won to-day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.2#Another, princes! yet remains to play;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.3#Another mark our arrow must attain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.4#Phoebus, assist! nor be the labour vain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.5#Swift as the word the parting arrow sings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.6#And bears thy fate, Antinous, on its wings:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.7#Wretch that he was, of unprophetic soul!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.8#High in his hands he rear'd the golden bowl!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.9#E'en then to drain it lengthen'd out his breath;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.10#Changed to the deep, the bitter draught of death:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.11#For fate who fear'd amidst a feastful band?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.12#And fate to numbers, by a single hand?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.13#Full through his throat Ulysses' weapon pass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.14#And pierced his neck. He falls, and breathes his last.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.15#The tumbling goblet the wide floor o'erflows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.16#A stream of gore burst spouting from his nose;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.17#Grim in convulsive agonies be sprawls:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.18#Before him spurn'd the loaded table falls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.19#And spreads the pavement with a mingled flood
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.20#Of floating meats, and wine, and human blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.21#Amazed, confounded, as they saw him fall,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.22#Up rose he throngs tumultuous round the hall:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.23#O'er all the dome they cast a haggard eye,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.24#Each look'd for arms--in vain; no arms were nigh:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.25#"Aim'st thou at princes? (all amazed they said;)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.26#Thy last of games unhappy hast thou play'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.27#Thy erring shaft has made our bravest bleed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.28#And death, unlucky guest, attends thy deed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.29#Vultures shall tear thee." Thus incensed they spoke,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.30#While each to chance ascribed the wondrous stroke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.31#Blind as they were: for death e'en now invades
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.32#His destined prey, and wraps them all in shades.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.33#Then, grimly frowning, with a dreadful look,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.2.34#That wither'd all their hearts, Ulysses spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.3.1#"Dogs, ye have had your day! ye fear'd no more
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.3.2#Ulysses vengeful from the Trojan shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.3.3#While, to your lust and spoil a guardless prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.3.4#Our house, our wealth, our helpless handmaids lay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.3.5#Not so content, with bolder frenzy fired,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.3.6#E'en to our bed presumptuous you aspired:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.3.7#Laws or divine or human fail'd to move,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.3.8#Or shame of men, or dread of gods above;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.3.9#Heedless alike of infamy or praise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.3.10#Or Fame's eternal voice in future days;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.3.11#The hour of vengeance, wretches, now is come;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.3.12#Impending fate is yours, and instant doom."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.4.1#Thus dreadful he. Confused the suitors stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.4.2#From their pale cheeks recedes the flying blood:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.4.3#Trembling they sought their guilty heads to hide.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.4.4#Alone the bold Eurymachus replied:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.1#"If, as thy words import (he thus began),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.2#Ulysses lives, and thou the mighty man,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.3#Great are thy wrongs, and much hast thou sustain'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.4#In thy spoil'd palace, and exhausted land;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.5#The cause and author of those guilty deeds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.6#Lo! at thy feet unjust Antinous bleeds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.7#Not love, but wild ambition was his guide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.8#To slay thy son, thy kingdom to divide,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.9#These were his aims; but juster Jove denied.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.10#Since cold in death the offender lies, oh spare
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.11#Thy suppliant people, and receive their prayer!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.12#Brass, gold, and treasures, shall the spoil defray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.13#Two hundred oxen every prince shall pay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.14#The waste of years refunded in a day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.15#Till then thy wrath is just." Ulysses burn'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.5.16#With high disdain, and sternly thus return'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.1#"All, all the treasure that enrich'd our throne
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.2#Before your rapines, join'd with all your own,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.3#If offer'd, vainly should for mercy call;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.4#'Tis you that offer, and I scorn them all;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.5#Your blood is my demand, your lives the prize,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.6#Till pale as yonder wretch each suitor lies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.7#Hence with those coward terms; or fight or fly;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.8#This choice is left you, to resist or die:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.9#And die I trust ye shall." He sternly spoke:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.10#With guilty fears the pale assembly shook.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.11#Alone Eurymachus exhorts the train:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.12#"Yon archer, comrades, will not shoot in vain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.13#But from the threshold shall his darts be sped,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.14#(Whoe'er he be), till every prince lie dead?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.15#Be mindful of yourselves, draw forth your swords,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.16#And to his shafts obtend these ample boards
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.17#(So need compels). Then, all united, strive
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.18#The bold invader from his post to drive:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.19#The city roused shall to our rescue haste,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.20#And this mad archer soon have shot his last."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.21#Swift as he spoke, he drew his traitor sword,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.22#And like a lion rush'd against his lord:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.23#The wary chief the rushing foe repress'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.24#Who met the point and forced it in his breast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.25#His falling hand deserts the lifted sword,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.26#And prone he falls extended o'er the board!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.27#Before him wide, in mix'd effusion roll
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.28#The untasted viands, and the jovial bowl.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.29#Full through his liver pass'd the mortal wound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.30#With dying rage his forehead beats the ground;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.31#He spurn'd the seat with fury as he fell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.32#And the fierce soul to darkness dived, and hell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.33#Next bold Amphinomus his arm extends
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.34#To force the pass; the godlike man defends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.35#Thy spear, Telemachus, prevents the attack,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.36#The brazen weapon driving through his back.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.37#Thence through his breast its bloody passage tore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.38#Flat falls he thundering on the marble floor,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.39#And his crush'd forehead marks the stone with gore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.40#He left his javelin in the dead, for fear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.41#The long encumbrance of the weighty spear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.42#To the fierce foe advantage might afford,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.43#To rash between and use the shorten'd sword.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.44#With speedy ardour to his sire he flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.45#And, "Arm, great father! arm (in haste he cries).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.46#Lo, hence I run for other arms to wield,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.47#For missive javelins, and for helm and shield;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.48#Fast by our side let either faithful swain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.6.49#In arms attend us, and their part sustain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.7.1#"Haste, and return (Ulysses made reply)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.7.2#While yet the auxiliar shafts this hand supply;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.7.3#Lest thus alone, encounter'd by an host,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.7.4#Driven from the gate, the important past be lost."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.1#With speed Telemachus obeys, and flies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.2#Where piled in heaps the royal armour lies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.3#Four brazen helmets, eight refulgent spears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.4#And four broad bucklers to his sire he bears:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.5#At once in brazen panoply they shone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.6#At once each servant braced his armour on;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.7#Around their king a faithful guard they stand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.8#While yet each shaft flew deathful from his hand:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.9#Chief after chief expired at every wound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.10#And swell'd the bleeding mountain on the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.11#Soon as his store of flying fates was spent.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.12#Against the wall he set the bow unbent;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.13#And now his shoulders bear the massy shield,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.14#And now his hands two beamy javelins wield:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.15#He frowns beneath his nodding plume, that play'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.8.16#O'er the high crest, and cast a dreadful shade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.1#There stood a window near, whence looking down
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.2#From o'er the porch appear'd the subject town.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.3#A double strength of valves secured the place,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.4#A high and narrow; but the only pass:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.5#The cautious king, with all-preventing care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.6#To guard that outlet, placed Eumaeus there;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.7#When Agelaus thus: "Has none the sense
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.8#To mount yon window, and alarm from thence
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.9#The neighbour-town? the town shall force the door,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.10#And this bold archer soon shall shoot no more."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.11#Melanthius then: "That outlet to the gate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.12#So near adjoins, that one may guard the strait.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.13#But other methods of defence remain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.14#Myself with arms can furnish all the train;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.15#Stores from the royal magazine I bring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.9.16#And their own darts shall pierce the prince and king."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.10.1#He said; and mounting up the lofty stairs,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.10.2#Twelve shields, twelve lances, and twelve helmets bears:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.10.3#All arm, and sudden round the hall appears
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.10.4#A blaze of bucklers, and a wood of spears.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.11.1#The hero stands oppress'd with mighty woe,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.11.2#On every side he sees the labour grow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.11.3#"Oh cursed event! and oh unlook'd for aid!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.11.4#Melanthius or the women have betray'd--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.11.5#Oh my dear son!"--The father with a sigh
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.11.6#Then ceased; the filial virtue made reply;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.12.1#"Falsehood is folly, and 'tis just to own
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.12.2#The fault committed: this was mine alone;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.12.3#My haste neglected yonder door to bar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.12.4#And hence the villain has supplied their war.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.12.5#Run, good Eumaeus, then, and (what before
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.12.6#I thoughtless err'd in) well secure that door:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.12.7#Learn, if by female fraud this deed were done,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.12.8#Or (as my thought misgives) by Dolius' son."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.13.1#While yet they spoke, in quest of arms again
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.13.2#To the high chamber stole the faithless swain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.13.3#Not unobserved. Eumaeus watchful eyed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.13.4#And thus address'd Ulysses near his side:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.14.1#"The miscreant we suspected takes that way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.14.2#Him, if this arm be powerful, shall I slay?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.14.3#Or drive him hither, to receive the meed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.14.4#From thy own hand, of this detested deed?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.15.1#"Not so (replied Ulysses); leave him there,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.15.2#For us sufficient is another care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.15.3#Within the structure of this palace wall
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.15.4#To keep enclosed his masters till they fall.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.15.5#Go you, and seize the felon; backward bind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.15.6#His arms and legs, and fix a plank behind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.15.7#On this his body by strong cords extend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.15.8#And on a column near the roof suspend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.15.9#So studied tortures his vile days shall end."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.1#The ready swains obey'd with joyful haste,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.2#Behind the felon unperceived they pass'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.3#As round the room in quest of arms he goes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.4#(The half-shut door conceal'd his lurking foes):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.5#One hand sustain'd a helm, and one the shield
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.6#Which old Laertes wont in youth to wield,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.7#Cover'd with dust, with dryness chapp'd and worn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.8#The brass corroded, and the leather torn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.9#Thus laden, o'er the threshold as he stepp'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.10#Fierce on the villain from each side they leap'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.11#Back by the hair the trembling dastard drew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.12#And down reluctant on the pavement threw.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.13#Active and pleased the zealous swains fulfil
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.14#At every point their master's rigid will;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.15#First, fast behind, his hands and feet they bound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.16#Then straighten'd cords involved his body round;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.17#So drawn aloft, athwart the column tied,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.16.18#The howling felon swung from side to side.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.17.1#Eumaeus scoffing then with keen disdain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.17.2#"There pass thy pleasing night, O gentle swain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.17.3#On that soft pillow, from that envied height,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.17.4#First may'st thou see the springing dawn of light;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.17.5#So timely rise, when morning streaks the east,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.17.6#To drive thy victims to the suitors' feast."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.18.1#This said, they, left him, tortured as he lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.18.2#Secured the door, and hasty strode away:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.18.3#Each, breathing death, resumed his dangerous post
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.18.4#Near great Ulysses; four against an host,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.18.5#When lo! descending to her hero's aid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.18.6#Jove's daughter, Pallas, War's triumphant maid:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.18.7#In Mentor's friendly form she join'd his side:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.18.8#Ulysses saw, and thus with transport cried:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.19.1#"Come, ever welcome, and thy succour lend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.19.2#O every sacred name in one, my friend!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.19.3#Early we loved, and long our loves have grown;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.19.4#Whate'er through life's whole series I have done,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.19.5#Or good, or grateful, now to mind recall,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.19.6#And, aiding this one hour, repay it all."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.20.1#Thus he; but pleasing hopes his bosom warm
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.20.2#Of Pallas latent in the friendly form.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.20.3#The adverse host the phantom-warrior eyed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.20.4#And first, loud-threatening, Agelaus cried:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.21.1#"Mentor, beware, nor let that tongue persuade
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.21.2#Thy frantic arm to lend Ulysses aid;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.21.3#Our force successful shall our threat make good,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.21.4#And with the sire and son commix thy blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.21.5#What hopest thou here? Thee first the sword shall slay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.21.6#Then lop thy whole posterity away;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.21.7#Far hence thy banish'd consort shall we send;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.21.8#With his thy forfeit lands and treasures blend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.21.9#Thus, and thus only, shalt thou join thy friend."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.22.1#His barbarous insult even the goddess fires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.22.2#Who thus the warrior to revenge inspires:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.23.1#"Art thou Ulysses? where then shall we find
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.23.2#The patient body and the constant mind?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.23.3#That courage, once the Trojans' daily dread,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.23.4#Known nine long years, and felt by heroes dead?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.23.5#And where that conduct, which revenged the lust
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.23.6#Of Priam's race, and laid proud Troy in dust?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.23.7#If this, when Helen was the cause, were done;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.23.8#What for thy country now, thy queen, thy son?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.23.9#Rise then in combat, at my side attend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.23.10#Observe what vigour gratitude can lend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.23.11#And foes how weak, opposed against a friend!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.24.1#She spoke; but willing longer to survey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.24.2#The sire and son's great acts withheld the day!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.24.3#By farther toils decreed the brave to try,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.24.4#And level poised the wings of victory;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.24.5#Then with a change of form eludes their sight,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.24.6#Perch'd like a swallow on a rafter's height,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.24.7#And unperceived enjoys the rising fight.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.25.1#Damastor's son, bold Agelaus, leads,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.25.2#The guilty war, Eurynomus succeeds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.25.3#With these, Pisander, great Polyctor's son,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.25.4#Sage Polybus, and stern Amphimedon,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.25.5#With Demoptolemus: these six survive:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.25.6#The best of all the shafts had left alive.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.25.7#Amidst the carnage, desperate as they stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.25.8#Thus Agelaus roused the lagging band:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.26.1#"The hour has come, when yon fierce man no more
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.26.2#With bleeding princes shall bestrew the floor;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.26.3#Lo! Mentor leaves him with an empty boast;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.26.4#The four remain, but four against an host.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.26.5#Let each at once discharge the deadly dart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.26.6#One sure of six shall reach Ulysses' heart:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.26.7#The rest must perish, their great leader slain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.26.8#Thus shall one stroke the glory lost regain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.27.1#Then all at once their mingled lances threw,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.27.2#And thirsty all of one man's blood they flew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.27.3#In vain! Minerva turned them with her breath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.27.4#And scattered short, or wide, the points of death!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.27.5#With deaden'd sound one on the threshold falls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.27.6#One strikes the gate, one rings against the walls:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.27.7#The storm passed innocent. The godlike man
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.27.8#Now loftier trod, and dreadful thus began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.27.9#"'Tis now (brave friends) our turn, at once to throw,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.27.10#(So speed them Heaven) our javelins at the foe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.27.11#That impious race to all their past misdeeds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.27.12#Would add our blood, injustice still proceeds."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.1#He spoke: at once their fiery lances flew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.2#Great Demoptolemus Ulysses slew;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.3#Euryades received the prince's dart;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.4#The goatherd's quiver'd in Pisander's heart;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.5#Fierce Elatus by thine, Eumaeus, falls;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.6#Their fall in thunder echoes round the walls.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.7#The rest retreat: the victors now advance,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.8#Each from the dead resumes his bloody lance.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.9#Again the foe discharge the steely shower;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.10#Again made frustrate by the virgin-power.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.11#Some, turn'd by Pallas, on the threshold fall,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.12#Some wound the gate, some ring against the wall;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.13#Some weak, or ponderous with the brazen head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.28.14#Drop harmless on the pavement, sounding dead.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.29.1#Then bold Amphimedon his javelin cast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.29.2#Thy hand, Telemachus, it lightly razed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.29.3#And from Ctesippus' arm the spear elanced:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.29.4#On good Eumaeus' shield and shoulder glanced;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.29.5#Not lessened of their force (so light the wound)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.29.6#Each sung along and dropped upon the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.29.7#Fate doom'd thee next, Eurydamus, to bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.29.8#Thy death ennobled by Ulysses' spear.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.29.9#By the bold son Amphimedon was slain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.29.10#And Polybus renown'd, the faithful swain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.29.11#Pierced through the breast the rude Ctesippus bled,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.29.12#And thus Philaetius gloried o'er the dead:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.30.1#"There end thy pompous vaunts and high disdain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.30.2#O sharp in scandal, voluble and vain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.30.3#How weak is mortal pride! To Heaven alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.30.4#The event of actions and our fates are known:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.30.5#Scoffer, behold what gratitude we bear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.30.6#The victim's heel is answered with this spear."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.31.1#Ulysses brandish'd high his vengeful steel,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.31.2#And Damastorides that instant fell:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.31.3#Fast by Leocritus expiring lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.31.4#The prince's javelin tore its bloody way
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.31.5#Through all his bowels: down he tumbled prone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.31.6#His batter'd front and brains besmear the stone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.1#Now Pallas shines confess'd; aloft she spreads
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.2#The arm of vengeance o'er their guilty heads:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.3#The dreadful aegis blazes in their eye:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.4#Amazed they see, they tremble, and they fly:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.5#Confused, distracted, through he rooms they fling:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.6#Like oxen madden'd by the breeze's sting,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.7#When sultry days, and long, succeed the gentle spring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.8#Not half so keen fierce vultures of the chase
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.9#Stoop from the mountains on the feather'd race,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.10#When, the wide field extended snares beset,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.11#With conscious dread they shun the quivering net:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.12#No help, no flight; but wounded every way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.13#Headlong they drop; the fowlers seize their prey.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.14#On all sides thus they double wound on wound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.15#In prostrate heaps the wretches beat the ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.16#Unmanly shrieks precede each dying groan,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.32.17#And a red deluge floats the reaking stone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.33.1#Leiodes first before the victor falls:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.33.2#The wretched augur thus for mercy calls:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.33.3#"Oh gracious hear, nor let thy suppliant bleed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.33.4#Still undishonoured, or by word or deed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.33.5#Thy house, for me remains; by me repress'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.33.6#Full oft was check'd the injustice of the rest:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.33.7#Averse they heard me when I counselled well,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.33.8#Their hearts were harden'd, and they justly fell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.33.9#O spare an augur's consecrated head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.33.10#Nor add the blameless to the guilty dead."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.34.1#"Priest as thou art! for that detested band
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.34.2#Thy lying prophecies deceived the land;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.34.3#Against Ulysses have thy vows been made,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.34.4#For them thy daily orisons were paid:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.34.5#Yet more, e'en to our bed thy pride aspires:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.34.6#One common crime one common fate requires."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.35.1#Thus speaking, from the ground the sword he took
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.35.2#Which Agelaus' dying hand forsook:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.35.3#Full through his neck the weighty falchion sped;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.35.4#Along the pavement roll'd the muttering head.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.36.1#Phemius alone the hand of vengeance spared,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.36.2#Phemius the sweet, the heaven-instructed bard.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.36.3#Beside the gate the reverend minstrel stands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.36.4#The lyre now silent trembling in his hands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.36.5#Dubious to supplicate the chief, or fly
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.36.6#To Jove's inviolable altar nigh,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.36.7#Where oft Laertes holy vows had paid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.36.8#And oft Ulysses smoking victims laid.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.36.9#His honour'd harp with care he first set down,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.36.10#Between the laver and the silver throne;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.36.11#Then prostrate stretch'd before the dreadful man,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.36.12#Persuasive thus, with accent soft began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.1#"O king! to mercy be thy soul inclined,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.2#And spare the poet's ever-gentle kind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.3#A deed like this thy future fame would wrong,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.4#For dear to gods and men is sacred song.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.5#Self-taught I sing; by Heaven, and Heaven alone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.6#The genuine seeds of poesy are sown:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.7#And (what the gods bestow) the lofty lay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.8#To gods alone and godlike worth we pay.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.9#Save then the poet, and thyself reward!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.10#'Tis thine to merit, mine is to record.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.11#That here I sung, was force, and not desire;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.12#This hand reluctant touch'd the warbling wire;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.13#And let thy son attest, nor sordid pay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.37.14#Nor servile flattery, stain'd the moral lay."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.38.1#The moving words Telemachus attends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.38.2#His sire approaches, and the bard defends.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.38.3#"O mix not, father, with those impious dead
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.38.4#The man divine! forbear that sacred head;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.38.5#Medon, the herald, too, our arms may spare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.38.6#Medon, who made my infancy his care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.38.7#If yet he breathes, permit thy son to give
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.38.8#Thus much to gratitude, and bid him live."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.39.1#Beneath a table, trembling with dismay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.39.2#Couch'd close to earth, unhappy Medon lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.39.3#Wrapp'd in a new-slain ox's ample hide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.39.4#Swift at the word he cast his screen aside,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.39.5#Sprung to the prince, embraced his knee with tears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.39.6#And thus with grateful voice address'd his ears
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.40.1#"O prince! O friend! lo, here thy Medon stands
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.40.2#Ah stop the hero's unresisted hands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.40.3#Incensed too justly by that impious brood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.40.4#Whose guilty glories now are set in blood."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.40.5#To whom Ulysses with a pleasing eye:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.41.1#"Be bold, on friendship and my son rely;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.41.2#Live, an example for the world to read,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.41.3#How much more safe the good than evil deed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.41.4#Thou, with the heaven-taught bard, in peace resort
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.41.5#From blood and carnage to yon open court:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.41.6#Me other work requires." With timorous awe
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.41.7#From the dire scene the exempted two withdraw,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.41.8#Scarce sure of life, look round, and trembling move
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.41.9#To the bright altars of Protector Jove.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.42.1#Meanwhile Ulysses search'd the dome, to find
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.42.2#If yet there live of all the offending kind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.42.3#Not one! complete the bloody tale he found,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.42.4#All steep'd in blood, all gasping on the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.42.5#So, when by hollow shores the fisher-train
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.42.6#Sweep with their arching nets the roaring main,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.42.7#And scarce the meshy toils the copious draught contain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.42.8#All naked of their element, and bare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.42.9#The fishes pant, and gasp in thinner air;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.42.10#Wide o'er the sands are spread the stiffening prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.42.11#Till the warm sun exhales their soul away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.43.1#And now the king commands his son to call
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.43.2#Old Euryclea to the deathful hall:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.43.3#The son observant not a moment stays;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.43.4#The aged governess with speed obeys;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.43.5#The sounding portals instant they display;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.43.6#The matron moves, the prince directs the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.43.7#On heaps of death the stern Ulysses stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.43.8#All black with dust, and cover'd thick with blood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.43.9#So the grim lion from the slaughter comes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.43.10#Dreadful lie glares, and terribly he foams,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.43.11#His breast with marks of carnage painted o'er,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.43.12#His jaws all dropping with the bull's black gore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.44.1#Soon as her eyes the welcome object met,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.44.2#The guilty fall'n, the mighty deed complete;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.44.3#A scream of joy her feeble voice essay'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.44.4#The hero check'd her, and composedly said.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.45.1#"Woman, experienced as thou art, control
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.45.2#Indecent joy, and feast thy secret soul.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.45.3#To insult the dead is cruel and unjust;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.45.4#Fate and their crime have sunk them to the dust.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.45.5#Nor heeded these the censure of mankind,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.45.6#The good and bad were equal in their mind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.45.7#Justly the price of worthlessness they paid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.45.8#And each now wails an unlamented shade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.45.9#But thou sincere! O Euryclea, say,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.45.10#What maids dishonour us, and what obey?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.1#Then she: "In these thy kingly walls remain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.2#(My son) full fifty of the handmaid train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.3#Taught by my care to cull the fleece or weave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.4#And servitude with pleasing tasks deceive;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.5#Of these, twice six pursue their wicked way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.6#Nor me, nor chaste Penelope obey;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.7#Nor fits it that Telemachus command
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.8#(Young as he is) his mother's female band.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.9#Hence to the upper chambers let me fly
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.10#Where slumbers soft now close the royal eye;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.11#There wake her with the news"--the matron cried
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.12#"Not so (Ulysses, more sedate, replied),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.13#Bring first the crew who wrought these guilty deeds."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.14#In haste the matron parts: the king proceeds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.15#"Now to dispose the dead, the care remains
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.16#To you, my son, and you, my faithfull swains;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.17#The offending females to that task we doom,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.18#To wash, to scent, and purify the room;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.19#These (every table cleansed, and every throne,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.20#And all the melancholy labour done)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.21#Drive to yon court, without the palace wall,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.22#There the revenging sword shall smite them all;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.23#So with the suitors let them mix in dust,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.24#Stretch'd in a long oblivion of their lust."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.25#He said: the lamentable train appear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.26#Each vents a groan, and drops a tender tear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.27#Each heaved her mournful burden, and beneath
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.28#The porch deposed the ghastly heap of death.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.29#The chief severe, compelling each to move,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.30#Urged the dire task imperious from above;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.31#With thirsty sponge they rub the tables o'er
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.32#(The swains unite their toil); the walls, the floor,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.33#Wash'd with the effusive wave, are purged of gore.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.34#Once more the palace set in fair array,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.35#To the base court the females take their way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.36#There compass'd close between the dome and wall
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.46.37#(Their life's last scene) they trembling wait their fall.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.47.1#Then thus the prince: "To these shall we afford
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.47.2#A fate so pure as by the martial sword?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.47.3#To these, the nightly prostitutes to shame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.47.4#And base revilers of our house and name?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.48.1#Thus speaking, on the circling wall he strung
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.48.2#A ship's tough cable from a column hung;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.48.3#Near the high top he strain'd it strongly round,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.48.4#Whence no contending foot could reach the ground.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.48.5#Their heads above connected in a row,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.48.6#They beat the air with quivering feet below:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.48.7#Thus on some tree hung struggling in the snare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.48.8#The doves or thrushes flap their wings in air.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.48.9#Soon fled the soul impure, and left behind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.48.10#The empty corse to waver with the wind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.49.1#Then forth they led Melanthius, and began
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.49.2#Their bloody work; they lopp'd away the man,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.49.3#Morsel for dogs! then trimm'd with brazen shears
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.49.4#The wretch, and shorten'd of his nose and ears;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.49.5#His hands and feet last felt the cruel steel:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.49.6#He roar'd, and torments gave his soul to hell.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.49.7#They wash, and to Ulysses take their way:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.49.8#So ends the bloody business of the day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.50.1#To Euryclea then address'd the king:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.50.2#("Bring hither fire, and hither sulphur bring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.50.3#To purge the palace: then the queen attend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.50.4#And let her with her matron-train descend;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.50.5#The matron-train, with all the virgin-band,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.50.6#Assemble here, to learn their lord's command."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.1#Then Euryclea: "Joyful I obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.2#But cast those mean dishonest rags away;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.3#Permit me first the royal robes to bring:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.4#Ill suits this garb the shoulders of a king."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.5#"Bring sulphur straight, and fire" (the monarch cries).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.6#She hears, and at the word obedient flies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.7#With fire and sulphur, cure of noxious fumes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.8#He purged the walls, and blood-polluted rooms.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.9#Again the matron springs with eager pace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.10#And spreads her lord's return from place to place.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.11#They hear, rush forth, and instant round him stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.12#A gazing throng, a torch in every hand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.13#They saw, they knew him, and with fond embrace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.14#Each humbly kiss'd his knee, or hand, or face;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.15#He knows them all, in all such truth appears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:22.51.16#E'en he indulges the sweet joy of tears.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.1.1#Then to the queen, as in repose she lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.1.2#The nurse with eager rapture speeds her way:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.1.3#The transports of her faithful heart supply
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.1.4#A sudden youth, and give her wings to fly.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.2.1#"And sleeps my child? (the reverend matron cries)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.2.2#Ulysses lives! arise, my child, arise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.2.3#At length appears the long-expected hour!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.2.4#Ulysses comes! the suitors are no more!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.2.5#No more they view the golden light of day!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.2.6#Arise, and bless thee with the glad survey?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.1#Touch'd at her words, the mournful queen rejoin'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.2#"Ah! whither wanders thy distemper'd mind?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.3#The righteous powers, who tread the starry skies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.4#The weak enlighten, and confound the wise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.5#And human thought, with unresisted sway,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.6#Depress or raise, enlarge or take away:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.7#Truth, by their high decree, thy voice forsakes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.8#And folly with the tongue of wisdom speaks.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.9#Unkind, the fond illusion to impose!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.10#Was it to flatter or deride my woes?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.11#Never did I sleep so sweet enjoy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.12#Since my dear lord left Ithaca for Troy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.13#Why must I wake to grieve, and curse thy shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.14#O Troy?--may never tongue pronounce thee more!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.15#Begone! another might have felt our rage,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.3.16#But age is sacred, and we spare thy age."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.4.1#To whom with warmth: "My soul a lie disdains;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.4.2#Ulysses lives, thy own Ulysses reigns:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.4.3#That stranger, patient of the suitors' wrongs,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.4.4#And the rude license of ungovern'd tongues!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.4.5#He, he is thine! Thy son his latent guest
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.4.6#Long knew, but lock'd the secret in his breast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.4.7#With well concerted art to end his woes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.4.8#And burst at once in vengeance on the foes."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.5.1#While yet she spoke, the queen in transport sprung
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.5.2#Swift from the couch, and round the matron hung;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.5.3#Fast from her eye descends the rolling tear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.5.4#"Say, once more say, is my Ulysses here?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.5.5#How could that numerous and outrageous band
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.5.6#By one be slain, though by a hero's hand?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.1#"I saw it not (she cries), but heard alone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.2#When death was busy, a loud dying groan;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.3#The damsel-train turn'd pale at every wound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.4#Immured we sate, and catch'd each passing sound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.5#When death had seized her prey, thy son attends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.6#And at his nod the damsel-train descends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.7#There terrible in arms Ulysses stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.8#And the dead suitors almost swam in blood:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.9#Thy heart had leap'd the hero to survey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.10#Stern as the surly lion o'er his prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.11#Glorious in gore, now with sulphereous fire
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.12#The dome he purges, now the flame aspires;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.13#Heap'd lie the dead without the palace walls--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.14#Haste, daughter, haste, thy own Ulysses calls!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.15#Thy every wish the bounteous gods bestow;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.16#Enjoy the present good, and former woe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.17#Ulysses lives, his vanquish'd foes to see;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.6.18#He lives to thy Telemachus and thee!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.7.1#"Ah, no! (with sighs Penelope rejoin'd,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.7.2#Excess of joy disturbs thy wandering mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.7.3#How blest this happy hour, should he appear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.7.4#Dear to us all, to me supremely dear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.7.5#Ah, no! some god the suitors death decreed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.7.6#Some god descends, and by his hand they bleed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.7.7#Blind! to contemn the stranger's righteous cause,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.7.8#And violate all hospitable laws!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.7.9#The good they hated, and the powers defied!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.7.10#But heaven is just, and by a god they died.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.7.11#For never must Ulysses view this shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.7.12#Never! the loved Ulysses is no more!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.1#"What words (the matron cries) have reach'd my ears?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.2#Doubt we his presence, when he now appears!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.3#Then hear conviction: Ere the fatal day
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.4#That forced Ulysses o'er the watery way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.5#A boar, fierce rushing in the sylvan war,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.6#Plough'd half his thigh; I saw, I saw the scar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.7#And wild with transport had reveal'd the wound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.8#But ere I spoke, he rose, and check'd the sound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.9#Then, daughter, haste away! and if a lie
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.10#Flow from this tongue, then let thy servant die!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.11#To whom with dubious joy the queen replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.12#"Wise is thy soul, but errors seize the wise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.13#The works of gods what mortal can survey?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.14#Who knows their motives, who shall trace their way?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.15#But learn we instant how the suitors trod
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.16#The paths of death, by man, or by a god."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.17#Thus speaks the queen, and no reply attends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.18#But with alternate joy and fear descends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.19#At every step debates her lord to prove;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.20#Or, rushing to his arms, confess her love!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.21#Then gliding through the marble valves, in state
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.22#Opposed, before the shining sire she sate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.23#The monarch, by a column high enthroned,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.24#His eye withdrew, and fix'd it on the ground;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.25#Curious to hear his queen the silence break:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.26#Amazed she sate, and impotent to speak;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.27#O'er all the man her eyes she rolls in vain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.28#Now hopes, now fears, now knows, then doubts again.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.29#At length Telemachus: "Oh, who can find
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.30#A woman like Penelope unkind?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.31#Why thus in silence? why with winning charms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.32#Thus slow to fly with rapture to his arms?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.33#Stubborn the breast that with no transport glows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.34#When twice ten years are pass'd of mighty woes;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.35#To softness lost, to spousal love unknown,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.36#The gods have formed that rigid heart of stone!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.37#"O my Telemachus! (the queen rejoin'd,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.38#Distracting fears confound my labouring mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.39#Powerless to speak. I scarce uplift my eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.40#Nor dare to question; doubts on doubts arise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.41#Oh deign he, if Ulysses, to remove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.42#These boding thoughts, and what he is, to prove!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.43#Pleased with her virtuous fears, the king replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.44#"Indulge, my son, the cautions of the wise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.45#Time shall the truth to sure remembrance bring:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.46#This garb of poverty belies the king:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.47#No more. This day our deepest care requires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.48#Cautious to act what thought mature inspires.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.49#If one man's blood, though mean, distain our hands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.50#The homicide retreats to foreign lands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.51#By us, in heaps the illustrious peerage falls,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.8.52#The important deed our whole attention calls."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.9.1#"Be that thy care (Telemachus replies)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.9.2#The world conspires to speak Ulysses wise;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.9.3#For wisdom all is thine! lo, I obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.9.4#And dauntless follow where you led the way;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.9.5#Nor shalt thou in the day of danger find
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.9.6#Thy coward son degenerate lag behind."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.10.1#"Then instant to the bath (the monarch cries),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.10.2#Bid the gay youth and sprightly virgins rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.10.3#Thence all descend in pomp and proud array,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.10.4#And bid the dome resound the mirthful lay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.10.5#While the sweet lyrist airs of rapture sings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.10.6#And forms the dance responsive to the strings,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.10.7#That hence the eluded passengers may say,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.10.8#'Lo! the queen weds! we hear the spousal lay!'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.10.9#The suitor's death, unknown, till we remove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.10.10#Far from the court, and act inspired by Jove."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.11.1#Thus spoke the king: the observant train obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.11.2#At once they bathe, and dress in proud array:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.11.3#The lyrist strikes the string; gay youths advance,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.11.4#And fair-zoned damsels form the sprightly dance.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.11.5#The voice, attuned to instrumental sounds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.11.6#Ascends the roof, the vaulted roof rebounds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.11.7#Not unobserved: the Greeks eluded say,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.11.8#"Lo! the queen weds, we hear the spousal lay!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.11.9#Inconstant! to admit the bridal hour."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.11.10#Thus they--but nobly chaste she weds no more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.1#Meanwhile the wearied king the bath ascends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.2#With faithful cares Eurynome attends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.3#O'er every limb a shower of fragrance sheds;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.4#Then, dress'd in pomp, magnificent he treads.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.5#The warrior-goddess gives his frame to shine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.6#With majesty enlarged, and grace divine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.7#Back from his brows in wavy ringlets fly
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.8#His thick large locks of hyacinthine dye.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.9#As by some artist to whom Vulcan gives
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.10#His heavenly skill, a breathing image lives;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.11#By Pallas taught, he frames the wondrous mould,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.12#And the pale silver glows with fusile gold:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.13#So Pallas his heroic form improves
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.14#With bloom divine, and like a god he moves!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.15#More high he treads, and issuing forth in state,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.16#Radiant before his gazing consort sate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.17#"And, O my queen! (he cries) what power above
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.18#Has steel'd that heart, averse to spousal love?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.19#Canst thou, Penelope, when heaven restores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.20#Thy lost Ulysses to his native shores,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.21#Canst thou, O cruel! unconcern'd survey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.22#Thy lost Ulysses, on this signal day?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.23#Haste, Euryclea, and despatchful spread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.24#For me, and me alone, the imperial bed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.25#My weary nature craves the balm of rest.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.12.26#But Heaven with adamant has arm'd her breast."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.13.1#"Ah no! (she cries) a tender heart I bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.13.2#A foe to pride: no adamant is there;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.13.3#And now, e'en now it melts! for sure I see
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.13.4#Once more Ulysses my beloved in thee!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.13.5#Fix'd in my soul, as when he sailed to Troy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.13.6#His image dwells: then haste the bed of joy,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.13.7#Haste, from the bridal bower the bed translate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.13.8#Fram'd by his hand, and be it dress'd in state!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.1#Thus speaks the queen, still dubious, with disguise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.2#Touch'd at her words, the king with warmth replies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.3#"Alas for this! what mortal strength can move
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.4#The enormous burden, who but Heaven above?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.5#It mocks the weak attempts of human hands!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.6#But the whole earth must move if Heaven commands
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.7#Then hear sure evidence, while we display
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.8#Words seal'd with sacred truth and truth obey:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.9#This hand the wonder framed; an olive spread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.10#Full in the court its ever verdant head.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.11#Vast as some mighty column's bulk, on high
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.12#The huge trunk rose, and heaved into the sky;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.13#Around the tree I raised a nuptial bower,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.14#And roof'd defensive of the storm and shower;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.15#The spacious valve, with art inwrought conjoins;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.16#And the fair dome with polished marble shines.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.17#I lopp'd the branchy head: aloft in twain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.18#Sever'd the bole, and smoothed the shining grain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.19#Then posts, capacious of the frame, I raise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.20#And bore it, regular, from space to space:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.21#Athwart the frame, at equal distance lie
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.22#Thongs of tough hides, that boast a purple dye;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.23#Then polishing the whole, the finished mould
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.24#With silver shone, with elephant, and gold.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.25#But if o'erturn'd by rude, ungovern'd hands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.26#Or still inviolate the olive stands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.27#'Tis thine, O queen, to say, and now impart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.14.28#If fears remain, or doubts distract thy heart."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.1#While yet he speaks, her powers of life decay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.2#She sickens, trembles, falls, and faints away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.3#At length recovering, to his arms she flew,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.4#And strain'd him close, as to his breast she grew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.5#The tears pour'd down amain, and "O (she cries)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.6#Let not against thy spouse thine anger rise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.7#O versed in every, turn of human art,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.8#Forgive the weakness of a woman's heart!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.9#The righteous powers, that mortal lot dispose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.10#Decree us to sustain a length of woes.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.11#And from the flower of life the bliss deny
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.12#To bloom together, fade away, and die.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.13#O let me, let me not thine anger move,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.14#That I forbore, thus, thus to speak my love:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.15#Thus in fond kisses, while the transport warms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.16#Pour out my soul and die within thine arms!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.17#I dreaded fraud! Men, faithless men, betray
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.18#Our easy faith, and make our sex their prey:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.19#Against the fondness of my heart I strove:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.20#'Twas caution, O my lord! not want of love.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.21#Like me had Helen fear'd, with wanton charms
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.22#Ere the fair mischief set two worlds in arms;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.23#Ere Greece rose dreadful in the avenging day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.24#Thus had she fear'd, she had not gone astray.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.25#But Heaven, averse to Greece, in wrath decreed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.26#That she should wander, and that Greece should bleed:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.27#Blind to the ills that from injustice flow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.28#She colour'd all our wretched lives with woe.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.29#But why these sorrows when my lord arrives?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.30#I yield, I yield! my own Ulysses lives!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.31#The secrets of the bridal bed are known
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.32#To thee, to me, to Actoris alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.33#(My father's present in the spousal hour,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.34#The sole attendant on our genial bower).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.35#Since what no eye hath seen thy tongue reveal'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.15.36#Hard and distrustful as I am, I yield."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.1#Touch'd to the soul, the king with rapture hears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.2#Hangs round her neck, and speaks his joy in tears.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.3#As to the shipwreck'd mariner, the shores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.4#Delightful rise, when angry Neptune roars:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.5#Then, when the surge in thunder mounts the sky,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.6#And gulf'd in crowds at once the sailors die;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.7#If one, more happy, while the tempest raves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.8#Outlives the tumult of conflicting waves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.9#All pale, with ooze deform'd, he views the strand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.10#And plunging forth with transport grasps the land:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.11#The ravish'd queen with equal rapture glows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.12#Clasps her loved lord, and to his bosom grows.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.13#Nor had they ended till the morning ray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.14#But Pallas backward held the rising day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.15#The wheels of night retarding, to detain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.16#The gay Aurora in the wavy main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.17#Whose flaming steeds, emerging through the night.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.16.18#Beam o'er the eastern hills with streaming light.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.17.1#At length Ulysses with a sigh replies:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.17.2#"Yet Fate, yet cruel Fate repose denies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.17.3#A labour long, and hard, remains behind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.17.4#By heaven above, by hell beneath enjoin'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.17.5#For to Tiresias through the eternal gates
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.17.6#Of hell I trode, to learn my future fates.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.17.7#But end we here--the night demands repose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.17.8#Be deck'd the couch! and peace awhile, my woes!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.18.1#To whom the queen: "Thy word we shall obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.18.2#And deck the couch; far hence be woes away:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.18.3#Since the just gods, who tread the starry plains,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.18.4#Restore thee safe, since my Ulysses reigns.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.18.5#But what those perils heaven decrees, impart;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.18.6#Knowledge may grieve, but fear distracts the heart."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.1#To this the king: "Ah, why must I disclose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.2#A dreadful story of approaching woes?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.3#Why in this hour of transport wound thy ears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.4#When thou must learn what I must speak with tears?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.5#Heaven, by the Theban ghost, thy spouse decrees,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.6#Torn from thy arms, to sail a length of seas;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.7#From realm to realm, a nation to explore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.8#Who ne'er knew salt, or heard the billows roar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.9#Nor saw gay vessel storm the surgy plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.10#A painted wonder, flying on the main:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.11#An oar my hand must bear; a shepherd eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.12#The unknown instrument with strange surprise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.13#And calls a corn-van; this upon the plain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.14#I fix, and hail the monarch of the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.15#Then bathe his altars with the mingled gore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.16#Of victims vow'd, a ram, a bull, a boar;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.17#Thence swift re-sailing to my native shores,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.18#Due victims slay to all the ethereal powers.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.19#Then Heaven decrees, in peace to end my days
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.20#And steal myself from life by slow decays!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.21#Unknown to pain, in age resign my breath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.22#When late stern Neptune points the shaft of death;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.23#To the dark grave retiring as to rest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.24#My people blessing, by my people bless'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.25#Such future scenes the all-righteous powers display
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.19.26#By their dread seer, and such my future day."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.20.1#To whom thus firm of soul: "If ripe for death,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.20.2#And full of days, thou gently yield thy breath;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.20.3#While Heaven a kind release from ills foreshows,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.20.4#Triumph, thou happy victor of thy woes?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.21.1#But Euryclea, with dispatchful care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.21.2#And sage Eurynome, the couch prepare;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.21.3#Instant they bid the blazing torch display
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.21.4#Around the dome and artificial day;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.21.5#Then to repose her steps the matron bends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.21.6#And to the queen Eurynome descends;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.21.7#A torch she bears, to light with guiding fires
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.21.8#The royal pair; she guides them, and retires
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.21.9#The instant his fair spouse Ulysses led
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.21.10#To the chaste love-rites of the nuptial bed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.1#And now the blooming youths and sprightly fair
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.2#Cease the gay dance, and to their rest repair;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.3#But in discourse the king and consort lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.4#While the soft hours stole unperceived away;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.5#Intent he hears Penelope disclose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.6#A mournful story of domestic woes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.7#His servants' insults, his invaded bed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.8#How his whole flocks and herds exhausted bled,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.9#His generous wines dishonour'd shed in vain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.10#And the wild riots of the suitor-train.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.11#The king alternate a dire tale relates,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.12#Of wars, of triumphs, and disastrous fates;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.13#All he unfolds; his listening spouse turns pale
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.14#With pleasing horror at the dreadful tale;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.15#Sleepless devours each word; and hears how slain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.16#Cicons on Cicons swell the ensanguined plain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.17#How to the land of Lote unbless'd he sails;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.18#And images the rills and flowery vales!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.19#How dash'd like dogs, his friends the Cyclops tore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.20#(Not unrevenged), and quaff'd the spouting gore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.21#How the loud storms in prison bound, he sails
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.22#From friendly Aeolus with prosperous gales:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.23#Yet fate withstands! a sudden tempest roars,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.24#And whirls him groaning from his native shores:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.25#How on the barbarous Laestrigonian coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.26#By savage hands his fleet and friends lie lost;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.27#How scarce himself survived: he paints the bower,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.28#The spells of Circe, and her magic power;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.29#His dreadful journey to the realms beneath,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.30#To seek Tiresias in the vales of death;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.31#How in the doleful mansions lie survey'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.32#His royal mother, pale Anticlea's shade;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.33#And friends in battle slain, heroic ghosts!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.34#Then how, unharm'd, he pass'd the Syren-coasts,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.35#The justling rocks where fierce Charybdis raves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.36#And howling Scylla whirls her thunderous waves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.37#The cave of death! How his companions slay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.38#The oxen sacred to the god of day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.39#Till Jove in wrath the rattling tempest guides,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.40#And whelms the offenders in the roaring tides:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.41#How struggling through the surge lie reach'd the shores
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.42#Of fair Ogygia and Calypso's bowers;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.43#Where the bay blooming nymph constrain'd his stay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.44#With sweet, reluctant, amorous delay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.45#And promised, vainly promised, to bestow
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.46#Immortal life, exempt from age and woe:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.47#How saved from storms Phaeacia's coast he trod,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.48#By great Alcinous honour'd as a god,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.49#Who gave him last his country to behold,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.22.50#With change of raiment, brass, and heaps of gold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.23.1#He ended, sinking into sleep, and shares
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.23.2#A sweet forgetfulness of all his cares.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.24.1#Soon as soft slumber eased the toils of day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.24.2#Minerva rushes through the aerial way,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.24.3#And bids Aurora with her golden wheels
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.24.4#Flame from the ocean o'er the eastern hills;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.24.5#Uprose Ulysses from the genial bed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.24.6#And thus with thought mature the monarch said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.1#"My queen, my consort! through a length of years
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.2#We drank the cup of sorrow mix'd with tears;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.3#Thou, for thy lord; while me the immortal powers
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.4#Detain'd reluctant from my native shores.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.5#Now, bless'd again by Heaven, the queen display,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.6#And rule our palace with an equal sway.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.7#Be it my care, by loans, or martial toils,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.8#To throng my empty folds with gifts or spoils.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.9#But now I haste to bless Laertes' eyes
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.10#With sight of his Ulysses ere he dies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.11#The good old man, to wasting woes a prey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.12#Weeps a sad life in solitude away.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.13#But hear, though wise! This morning shall unfold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.14#The deathful scene, on heroes heroes roll'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.15#Thou with thy maids within the palace stay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.25.16#From all the scene of tumult far away!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.26.1#He spoke, and sheathed in arms incessant flies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.26.2#To wake his son, and bid his friends arise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.26.3#"To arms!" aloud he cries; his friends obey,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.26.4#With glittering arms their manly limbs array,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.26.5#And pass the city gate; Ulysses leads the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.26.6#Now flames the rosy dawn, but Pallas shrouds
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:23.26.7#The latent warriors in a veil of clouds.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.1#Cylenius now to Pluto's dreary reign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.2#Conveys the dead, a lamentable train!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.3#The golden wand, that causes sleep to fly,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.4#Or in soft slumber seals the wakeful eye,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.5#That drives the ghosts to realms of night or day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.6#Points out the long uncomfortable way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.7#Trembling the spectres glide, and plaintive vent
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.8#Thin, hollow screams, along the deep descent.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.9#As in the cavern of some rifted den,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.10#Where flock nocturnal bats, and birds obscene;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.11#Cluster'd they hang, till at some sudden shock
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.12#They move, and murmurs run through all the rock!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.13#So cowering fled the sable heaps of ghosts,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.14#And such a scream fill'd all the dismal coasts.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.15#And now they reach'd the earth's remotest ends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.16#And now the gates where evening Sol descends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.17#And Leucas' rock, and Ocean's utmost streams,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.18#And now pervade the dusky land of dreams,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.19#And rest at last, where souls unbodied dwell
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.20#In ever-flowing meads of asphodel.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.21#The empty forms of men inhabit there,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.22#Impassive semblance, images of air!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.23#Naught else are all that shined on earth before:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.24#Ajax and great Achilles are no more!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.25#Yet still a master ghost, the rest he awed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.26#The rest adored him, towering as he trod;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.27#Still at his side is Nestor's son survey'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.1.28#And loved Patroclus still attends his shade.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.2.1#New as they were to that infernal shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.2.2#The suitors stopp'd, and gazed the hero o'er.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.2.3#When, moving slow, the regal form they view'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.2.4#Of great Atrides: him in pomp pursued
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.2.5#And solemn sadness through the gloom of hell,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.2.6#The train of those who by AEgysthus fell:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.1#"O mighty chief! (Pelides thus began)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.2#Honour'd by Jove above the lot of man!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.3#King of a hundred kings! to whom resign'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.4#The strongest, bravest, greatest of mankind
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.5#Comest thou the first, to view this dreary state?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.6#And was the noblest, the first mark of Fate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.7#Condemn'd to pay the great arrear so soon,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.8#The lot, which all lament, and none can shun!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.9#Oh! better hadst thou sunk in Trojan ground,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.10#With all thy full-blown honours cover'd round;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.11#Then grateful Greece with streaming eyes might raise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.12#Historic marbles to record thy praise:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.13#Thy praise eternal on the faithful stone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.14#Had with transmissive glories graced thy son.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.15#But heavier fates were destined to attend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.3.16#What man is happy, till he knows his end?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.1#"O son of Peleus! greater than mankind!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.2#(Thus Agamemnon's kingly shade rejoin'd)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.3#Thrice happy thou, to press the martial plain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.4#'Midst heaps of heroes in thy quarrel slain:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.5#In clouds of smoke raised by the noble fray,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.6#Great and terrific e'en in death you lay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.7#And deluges of blood flow'd round you every way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.8#Nor ceased the strife till Jove himself opposed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.9#And all in Tempests the dire evening closed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.10#Then to the fleet we bore thy honour'd load,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.11#And decent on the funeral bed bestow'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.12#Then unguents sweet and tepid streams we shed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.13#Tears flow'd from every eye, and o'er the dead
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.14#Each clipp'd the curling honours of his head.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.15#Struck at the news, thy azure mother came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.16#The sea-green sisters waited on the dame:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.17#A voice of loud lament through all the main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.18#Was heard; and terror seized the Grecian train:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.19#Back to their ships the frighted host had fled;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.20#But Nestor spoke, they listen'd and obey'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.21#(From old experience Nestor's counsel springs,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.22#And long vicissitudes of human things):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.23#'Forbear your flight: fair Thetis from the main
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.24#To mourn Achilles leads her azure train.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.25#Around thee stand the daughters of the deep,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.26#Robe thee in heavenly vests, and round thee weep:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.27#Round thee, the Muses, with alternate strain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.28#In ever-consecrating verse, complain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.29#Each warlike Greek the moving music hears,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.30#And iron-hearted heroes melt in tears.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.31#Till seventeen nights and seventeen days return'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.32#All that was mortal or immortal mourn'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.33#To flames we gave thee, the succeeding day,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.34#And fatted sheep and sable oxen slay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.35#With oils and honey blazed the augmented fires,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.36#And, like a god adorn'd, thy earthly part expires.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.37#Unnumber'd warriors round the burning pile
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.38#Urge the fleet coursers or the racer's toil;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.39#Thick clouds of dust o'er all the circle rise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.40#And the mix'd clamour thunders in the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.41#Soon as absorb'd in all-embracing flame
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.42#Sunk what was mortal of thy mighty name,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.43#We then collect thy snowy bones, and place
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.44#With wines and unguents in a golden vase
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.45#(The vase to Thetis Bacchus gave of old,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.46#And Vulcan's art enrich'd the sculptured gold).
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.47#There, we thy relics, great Achilles! blend
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.48#With dear Patroclus, thy departed friend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.49#In the same urn a separate space contains
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.50#Thy next beloved, Antilochus' remains.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.51#Now all the sons of warlike Greece surround
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.52#Thy destined tomb and cast a mighty mound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.53#High on the shore the growing hill we raise,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.54#That wide the extended Hellespont surveys;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.55#Where all, from age to age, who pass the coast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.56#May point Achilles' tomb, and hail the mighty ghost.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.57#Thetis herself to all our peers proclaims
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.58#Heroic prizes and exequial games;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.59#The gods assented; and around thee lay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.60#Rich spoils and gifts that blazed against the day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.61#Oft have I seen with solemn funeral games
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.62#Heroes and kings committed to the flames;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.63#But strength of youth, or valour of the brave,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.64#With nobler contest ne'er renown'd a grave.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.65#Such were the games by azure Thetis given,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.66#And such thy honours, O beloved of Heaven!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.67#Dear to mankind thy fame survives, nor fades
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.68#Its bloom eternal in the Stygian shades.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.69#But what to me avail my honours gone,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.70#Successful toils, and battles bravely won?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.71#Doom'd by stern Jove at home to end my life,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.72#By cursed Aegysthus, and a faithless wife!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.73#Thus they: while Hermes o'er the dreary plain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.74#Led the sad numbers by Ulysses slain.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.75#On each majestic form they cast a view,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.76#And timorous pass'd, and awfully withdrew.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.77#But Agamemnon, through the gloomy shade,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.78#His ancient host Amphimedon survey'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.79#"Son of Melanthius! (he began) O say!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.80#What cause compell'd so many, and so gay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.81#To tread the downward, melancholy way?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.82#Say, could one city yield a troop so fair?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.83#Were all these partners of one native air?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.84#Or did the rage of stormy Neptune sweep
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.85#Your lives at once, and whelm beneath the deep?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.86#Did nightly thieves, or pirates' cruel bands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.87#Drench with your blood your pillaged country's sands?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.88#Or well-defending some beleaguer'd wall,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.89#Say,--for the public did ye greatly fall?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.90#Inform thy guest: for such I was of yore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.91#When our triumphant navies touch'd your shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.92#Forced a long month the wintry seas to bear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.4.93#To move the great Ulysses to the war."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.1#"O king of men! I faithful shall relate
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.2#(Replied Amphimedon) our hapless fate.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.3#Ulysses absent, our ambitious aim
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.4#With rival loves pursued his royal dame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.5#Her coy reserve, and prudence mix'd with pride,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.6#Our common suit nor granted, nor denied;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.7#But close with inward hate our deaths design'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.8#Versed in all arts of wily womankind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.9#Her hand, laborious, in delusion spread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.10#A spacious loom, and mix'd the various thread.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.11#'Ye peers (she cried) who press to gain my heart,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.12#Where dead Ulysses claims no more a part,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.13#Yet a short space your rival suit suspend,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.14#Till this funereal web my labours end:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.15#Cease, till to good Laertes I bequeath
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.16#A task of grief, his ornaments of death:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.17#Lest when the Fates his royal ashes claim,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.18#The Grecian matrons taint my spotless fame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.19#Should he, long honour'd with supreme command,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.5.20#Want the last duties of a daughter's hand.'
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.6.1#"The fiction pleased, our generous train complies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.6.2#Nor fraud mistrusts in virtue's fair disguise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.6.3#The work she plied, but studious of delay,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.6.4#Each following night reversed the toils of day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.6.5#Unheard, unseen, three years her arts prevail;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.6.6#The fourth, her maid reveal'd the amazing tale,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.6.7#And show'd as unperceived we took our stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.6.8#The backward labours of her faithless hand.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.6.9#Forced she completes it; and before us lay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.6.10#The mingled web, whose gold and silver ray
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.6.11#Display'd the radiance of the night and day.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.1#"Just as she finished her illustrious toil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.2#Ill fortune led Ulysses to our isle.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.3#Far in a lonely nook, beside the sea,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.4#At an old swineherd's rural lodge he lay:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.5#Thither his son from sandy Pyle repairs,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.6#And speedy lands, and secretly confers.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.7#They plan our future ruin, and resort
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.8#Confederate to the city and the court.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.9#First came the son; the father nest succeeds,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.10#Clad like a beggar, whom Eumaeus leads;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.11#Propp'd on a staff, deform'd with age and care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.12#And hung with rags that flutter'd in the air.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.13#Who could Ulysses in that form behold?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.14#Scorn'd by the young, forgotten by the old,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.15#Ill-used by all! to every wrong resigned,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.16#Patient he suffered with a constant mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.17#But when, arising in his wrath to obey
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.18#The will of Jove, he gave the vengeance way:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.19#The scattered arms that hung around the dome
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.20#Careful he treasured in a private room;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.21#Then to her suitors bade his queen propose
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.22#The archer's strife, the source of future woes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.23#And omen of our death! In vain we drew
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.24#The twanging string, and tried the stubborn yew:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.25#To none it yields but great Ulysses' hands;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.26#In vain we threat; Telemachus commands:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.27#The bow he snatch'd, and in an instant bent;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.28#Through every ring the victor arrow went.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.29#Fierce on the threshold then in arms he stood;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.30#Poured forth the darts that thirsted for our blood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.31#And frown'd before us, dreadful as a god!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.32#First bleeds Antinous: thick the shafts resound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.33#And heaps on heaps the wretches strew the ground;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.34#This way, and that, we turn, we fly, we fall;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.35#Some god assisted, and unmann'd us all;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.36#Ignoble cries precede the dying groans;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.7.37#And battered brains and blood besmear the stones.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.8.1#"Thus, great Atrides, thus Ulysses drove
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.8.2#The shades thou seest from yon fair realms above;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.8.3#Our mangled bodies now deformed with gore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.8.4#Cold and neglected, spread the marble floor.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.8.5#No friend to bathe our wounds, or tears to shed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.8.6#O'er the pale corse! the honours of the dead."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.1#"Oh bless'd Ulysses! (thus the king express'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.2#His sudden rapture) in thy consort bless'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.3#Not more thy wisdom than her virtue shined;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.4#Not more thy patience than her constant mind.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.5#Icarius' daughter, glory of the past,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.6#And model to the future age, shall last:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.7#The gods, to honour her fair fame, shall rise
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.8#(Their great reward) a poet in her praise.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.9#Not such, O Tyndarus! thy daughter's deed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.10#By whose dire hand her king and husband bled;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.11#Her shall the Muse to infamy prolong,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.12#Example dread, and theme of tragic song!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.13#The general sex shall suffer in her shame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.9.14#And e'en the best that bears a woman's name."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.10.1#Thus in the regions of eternal shade
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.10.2#Conferr'd the mournful phantoms of the dead;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.10.3#While from the town, Ulysses and his band
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.10.4#Pass'd to Laertes' cultivated land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.10.5#The ground himself had purchased with his pain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.10.6#And labour made the rugged soil a plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.10.7#There stood his mansion of the rural sort,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.10.8#With useful buildings round the lowly court;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.10.9#Where the few servants that divide his care
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.10.10#Took their laborious rest, and homely fare;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.10.11#And one Sicilian matron, old and sage,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.10.12#With constant duty tends his drooping age.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.1#Here now arriving, to his rustic band
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.2#And martial son, Ulysses gave command:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.3#"Enter the house, and of the bristly swine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.4#Select the largest to the powers divine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.5#Alone, and unattended, let me try
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.6#If yet I share the old man's memory:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.7#If those dim eyes can yet Ulysses know
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.8#(Their light and dearest object long ago),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.9#Now changed with time, with absence and with woe."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.10#Then to his train he gives his spear and shield;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.11#The house they enter; and he seeks the field,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.12#Through rows of shade, with various fruitage crown'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.13#And labour'd scenes of richest verdure round.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.14#Nor aged Dolius; nor his sons, were there,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.15#Nor servants, absent on another care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.16#To search the woods for sets of flowery thorn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.11.17#Their orchard bounds to strengthen and adorn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.12.1#But all alone the hoary king he found;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.12.2#His habit course, but warmly wrapp'd around;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.12.3#His head, that bow'd with many a pensive care,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.12.4#Fenced with a double cap of goatskin hair:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.12.5#His buskins old, in former service torn,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.12.6#But swell repair'd; and gloves against the thorn.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.12.7#In this array the kingly gardener stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.12.8#And clear'd a plant, encumber'd with its wood.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.1#Beneath a neighbouring tree, the chief divine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.2#Gazed o'er his sire, retracing every line,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.3#The ruins of himself, now worn away
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.4#With age, yet still majestic in decay!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.5#Sudden his eyes released their watery store;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.6#The much-enduring man could bear no more.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.7#Doubtful he stood, if instant to embrace
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.8#His aged limbs, to kiss his reverend face,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.9#With eager transport to disclose the whole,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.10#And pour at once the torrent of his soul.--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.11#Not so: his judgment takes the winding way
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.12#Of question distant, and of soft essay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.13#More gentle methods on weak age employs:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.14#And moves the sorrows to enhance the joys.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.15#Then, to his sire with beating heart he moves,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.16#And with a tender pleasantry reproves;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.17#Who digging round the plant still hangs his bead,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.13.18#Nor aught remits the work, while thus he said:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.1#"Great is thy skill, O father! great thy toil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.2#Thy careful hand is stamp'd on all the soil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.3#Thy squadron'd vineyards well thy art declare,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.4#The olive green, blue fig, and pendent pear;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.5#And not one empty spot escapes thy care.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.6#On every plant and tree thy cares are shown,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.7#Nothing neglected, but thyself alone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.8#Forgive me, father, if this fault I blame;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.9#Age so advanced, may some indulgence claim.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.10#Not for thy sloth, I deem thy lord unkind:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.11#Nor speaks thy form a mean or servile mind;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.12#I read a monarch in that princely air,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.13#The same thy aspect, if the same thy care;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.14#Soft sleep, fair garments, and the joys of wine,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.15#These are the rights of age, and should be thine.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.16#Who then thy master, say? and whose the land
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.17#So dress'd and managed by thy skilful hand?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.18#But chief, oh tell me! (what I question most)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.19#Is this the far-famed Ithacensian coast?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.20#For so reported the first man I view'd
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.21#(Some surly islander, of manners rude),
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.22#Nor farther conference vouchsafed to stay;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.23#Heedless he whistled, and pursued his way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.24#But thou whom years have taught to understand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.25#Humanely hear, and answer my demand:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.26#A friend I seek, a wise one and a brave:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.27#Say, lives he yet, or moulders in the grave?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.28#Time was (my fortunes then were at the best)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.29#When at my house I lodged this foreign guest;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.30#He said, from Ithaca's fair isle he came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.31#And old Laertes was his father's name.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.32#To him, whatever to a guest is owed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.33#I paid, and hospitable gifts bestow'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.34#To him seven talents of pure ore I told,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.35#Twelve cloaks, twelve vests, twelve tunics stiff with gold:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.36#A bowl, that rich with polish'd silver flames,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.14.37#And skill'd in female works, four lovely dames."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.1#At this the father, with a father's fears
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.2#(His venerable eyes bedimm'd with tears):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.3#"This is the land; but ah! thy gifts are lost,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.4#For godless men, and rude possess the coast:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.5#Sunk is the glory of this once-famed shore!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.6#Thy ancient friend, O stranger, is no more!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.7#Full recompense thy bounty else had borne:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.8#For every good man yields a just return:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.9#So civil rights demand; and who begins
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.10#The track of friendship, not pursuing, sins.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.11#But tell me, stranger, be the truth confess'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.12#What years have circled since thou saw'st that guest?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.13#That hapless guest, alas! for ever gone!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.14#Wretch that he was! and that I am! my son!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.15#If ever man to misery was born,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.16#'Twas his to suffer, and 'tis mine to mourn!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.17#Far from his friends, and from his native reign,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.18#He lies a prey to monsters of the main;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.19#Or savage beasts his mangled relics tear,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.20#Or screaming vultures scatter through the air:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.21#Nor could his mother funeral unguents shed;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.22#Nor wail'd his father o'er the untimely dead:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.23#Nor his sad consort, on the mournful bier,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.15.24#Seal'd his cold eyes, or dropp'd a tender tear!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.16.1#"But, tell me who thou art? and what thy race?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.16.2#Thy town, thy parents, and thy native place?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.16.3#Or, if a merchant in pursuit of gain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.16.4#What port received thy vessel from the main?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.16.5#Or comest thou single, or attend thy train?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.1#Then thus the son: "From Alybas I came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.2#My palace there; Eperitus my name
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.3#Not vulgar born: from Aphidas, the king
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.4#Of Polyphemon's royal line, I spring.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.5#Some adverse demon from Sicania bore
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.6#Our wandering course, and drove us on your shore;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.7#Far from the town, an unfrequented bay
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.8#Relieved our wearied vessel from the sea.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.9#Five years have circled since these eyes pursued
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.10#Ulysses parting through the sable flood:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.11#Prosperous he sail'd, with dexter auguries,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.12#And all the wing'd good omens of the skies.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.13#Well hoped we then to meet on this fair shore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.17.14#Whom Heaven, alas! decreed to meet no more."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.1#Quick through the father's heart these accents ran;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.2#Grief seized at once, and wrapp'd up all the man:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.3#Deep from his soul lie sigh'd, and sorrowing spread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.4#A cloud of ashes on his hoary head.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.5#Trembling with agonies of strong delight
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.6#Stood the great son, heart-wounded with the sight:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.7#He ran, he seized him with a strict embrace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.8#With thousand kisses wander'd o'er his face:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.9#"I, I am he; O father, rise! behold
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.10#Thy son, with twenty winters now grown old;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.11#Thy son, so long desired, so long detain'd,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.12#Restored, and breathing in his native land:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.13#These floods of sorrow, O my sire, restrain!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.14#The vengeance is complete; the suitor train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.18.15#Stretch'd in our palace, by these hands lie slain."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.19.1#Amazed, Laertes: "Give some certain sign
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.19.2#(If such thou art) to manifest thee mine."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.1#"Lo here the wound (he cries) received of yore,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.2#The scar indented by the tusky boar,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.3#When, by thyself, and by Anticlea sent,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.4#To old Autolycus' realms I went.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.5#Yet by another sign thy offspring know;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.6#The several trees you gave me long ago,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.7#While yet a child, these fields I loved to trace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.8#And trod thy footsteps with unequal pace;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.9#To every plant in order as we came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.10#Well-pleased, you told its nature and its name,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.11#Whate'er my childish fancy ask'd, bestow'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.12#Twelve pear-trees, bowing with their pendent load,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.13#And ten, that red with blushing apples glow'd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.14#Full fifty purple figs; and many a row
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.15#Of various vines that then began to blow,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.16#A future vintage! when the Hours produce
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.20.17#Their latent buds, and Sol exalts the juice."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.1#Smit with the signs which all his doubts explain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.2#His heart within him melt; his knees sustain
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.3#Their feeble weight no more: his arms alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.4#Support him, round the loved Ulysses thrown;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.5#He faints, he sinks, with mighty joys oppress'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.6#Ulysses clasps him to his eager breast.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.7#Soon as returning life regains its seat,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.8#And his breath lengthens, and his pulses beat:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.9#"Yes, I believe (he cries) almighty Jove!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.10#Heaven rules us yet, and gods there are above.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.11#'Tis so--the suitors for their wrongs have paid--
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.12#But what shall guard us, if the town invade?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.13#If, while the news through every city flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.14#All Ithaca and Cephalenia rise?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.15#To this Ulysses: "As the gods shall please
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.16#Be all the rest: and set thy soul at ease.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.17#Haste to the cottage by this orchard's side,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.18#And take the banquet which our cares provide;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.19#There wait thy faithful band of rural friends,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.21.20#And there the young Telemachus attends."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.22.1#Thus, having said, they traced the garden o'er
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.22.2#And stooping entered at the lowly door.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.22.3#The swains and young Telemachus they found.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.22.4#The victim portion'd and the goblet crown'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.22.5#The hoary king, his old Sicilian maid
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.22.6#Perfum'd and wash'd, and gorgeously arrayed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.22.7#Pallas attending gives his frame to shine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.22.8#With awful port, and majesty divine;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.22.9#His gazing son admires the godlike grace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.22.10#And air celestial dawning o'er his face.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.22.11#"What god (he cried) my father's form improves!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.22.12#How high he treads and how enlarged he moves!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.23.1#"Oh! would to all the deathless powers on high,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.23.2#Pallas and Jove, and him who gilds the sky!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.23.3#(Replied the king elated with his praise)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.23.4#My strength were still, as once in better days:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.23.5#When the bold Cephalens the leaguer form'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.23.6#And proud Nericus trembled as I storm'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.23.7#Such were I now, not absent from your deed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.23.8#When the last sun beheld the suitors bleed,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.23.9#This arm had aided yours, this hand bestrown
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.23.10#Our shores with death, and push'd the slaughter on;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.23.11#Nor had the sire been separate from the son."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.1#They communed thus; while homeward bent their way
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.2#The swains, fatigued with labours of the day:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.3#Dolius, the first, the venerable man;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.4#And next his sons, a long succeeding train.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.5#For due refection to the bower they came,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.6#Call'd by the careful old Sicilian dame,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.7#Who nursed the children, and now tends the sire,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.8#They see their lord, they gaze, and they admire.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.9#On chairs and beds in order seated round,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.10#They share the gladsome board; the roofs resound,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.11#While thus Ulysses to his ancient friend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.12#"Forbear your wonder, and the feast attend:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.13#The rites have waited long." The chief commands
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.14#Their love in vain; old Dolius spreads his hands,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.15#Springs to his master with a warm embrace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.16#And fastens kisses on his hands and face;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.17#Then thus broke out: "O long, O daily mourn'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.18#Beyond our hopes, and to our wish return'd!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.19#Conducted sure by Heaven! for Heaven alone
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.20#Could work this wonder: welcome to thy own!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.21#And joys and happiness attend thy throne!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.22#Who knows thy bless'd, thy wish'd return? oh say,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.23#To the chaste queen shall we the news convey?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.24.24#Or hears she, and with blessings loads the day?"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.25.1#"Dismiss that care, for to the royal bride
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.25.2#Already is it known" (the king replied,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.25.3#And straight resumed his seat); while round him bows
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.25.4#Each faithful youth, and breathes out ardent vows:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.25.5#Then all beneath their father take their place,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.25.6#Rank'd by their ages, and the banquet grace.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.1#Now flying Fame the swift report had spread
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.2#Through all the city, of the suitors dead,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.3#In throngs they rise, and to the palace crowd;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.4#Their sighs were many and the tumult loud.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.5#Weeping they bear the mangled heaps of slain;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.6#Inhume the natives in their native plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.7#The rest in ships are wafted o'er the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.8#Then sad in council all the seniors sate,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.9#Frequent and full, assembled to debate:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.10#Amid the circle first Eupithes rose,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.11#Big was his eye with tears, his heart with woes:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.12#The bold Antinous was his age's pride,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.13#The first who by Ulysses' arrow died.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.14#Down his wan cheek the trickling torrent ran,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.26.15#As mixing words with sighs he thus began:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.1#"Great deeds, O friends! this wondrous man has wrought,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.2#And mighty blessings to his country brought!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.3#With ships he parted, and a numerous train,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.4#Those, and their ships, he buried in the main.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.5#Now he returns, and first essays his hand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.6#In the best blood of all his native land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.7#Haste, then, and ere to neighbouring Pyle he flies,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.8#Or sacred Elis, to procure supplies;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.9#Arise (or ye for ever fall), arise!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.10#Shame to this age, and all that shall succeed!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.11#If unrevenged your sons and brothers bleed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.12#Prove that we live, by vengeance on his head,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.13#Or sink at once forgotten with the dead."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.14#Here ceased he, but indignant tears let fall
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.15#Spoke when he ceased: dumb sorrow touch'd them all.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.16#When from the palace to the wondering throng
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.17#Sage Medon came, and Phemius came along
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.18#(Restless and early sleep's soft bands they broke);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.27.19#And Medon first the assembled chiefs bespoke;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.28.1#"Hear me, ye peers and elders of the land,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.28.2#Who deem this act the work of mortal hand;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.28.3#As o'er the heaps of death Ulysses strode,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.28.4#These eyes, these eyes beheld a present god,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.28.5#Who now before him, now beside him stood,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.28.6#Fought as he fought, and mark'd his way with blood:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.28.7#In vain old Mentor's form the god belied;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.28.8#'Twas Heaven that struck, and Heaven was on his side."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.1#A sudden horror all the assembly shook,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.2#When slowly rising, Halitherses spoke
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.3#(Reverend and wise, whose comprehensive view
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.4#At once the present and the future knew):
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.5#"Me too, ye fathers, hear! from you proceed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.6#The ills ye mourn; your own the guilty deed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.7#Ye gave your sons, your lawless sons, the rein
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.8#(Oft warn'd by Mentor and myself in vain);
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.9#An absent hero's bed they sought to soil,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.10#An absent hero's wealth they made their spoil;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.11#Immoderate riot, and intemperate lust!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.12#The offence was great, the punishment was just.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.13#Weigh then my counsels in an equal scale,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.29.14#Nor rush to ruin. Justice will prevail."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.30.1#His moderate words some better minds persuade:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.30.2#They part, and join him: but the number stay'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.30.3#They storm, they shout, with hasty frenzy fired,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.30.4#And second all Eupithes' rage inspired.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.30.5#They case their limbs in brass; to arms they run;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.30.6#The broad effulgence blazes in the sun.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.30.7#Before the city, and in ample plain,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.30.8#They meet: Eupithes heads the frantic train.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.30.9#Fierce for his son, he breathes his threats in air;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.30.10#Fate bears them not, and Death attends him there.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.31.1#This pass'd on earth, while in the realms above
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.31.2#Minerva thus to cloud-compelling Jove!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.31.3#"May I presume to search thy secret soul?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.31.4#O Power Supreme, O Ruler of the whole!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.31.5#Say, hast thou doom'd to this divided state
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.31.6#Or peaceful amity or stern debate?
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.31.7#Declare thy purpose, for thy will is fate."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.1#"Is not thy thought my own? (the god replies
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.2#Who rolls the thunder o'er the vaulted skies;)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.3#Hath not long since thy knowing soul decreed
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.4#The chief's return should make the guilty bleed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.5#'Tis done, and at thy will the Fates succeed.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.6#Yet hear the issue: Since Ulysses' hand
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.7#Has slain the suitors, Heaven shall bless the land.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.8#None now the kindred of the unjust shall own;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.9#Forgot the slaughter'd brother and the son:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.10#Each future day increase of wealth shall bring,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.11#And o'er the past Oblivion stretch her wing.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.12#Long shall Ulysses in his empire rest,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.13#His people blessing, by his people bless'd.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.14#Let all be peace."--He said, and gave the nod
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.15#That binds the Fates; the sanction of the god
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.16#And prompt to execute the eternal will,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.32.17#Descended Pallas from the Olympian hill.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.1#Now sat Ulysses at the rural feast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.2#The rage of hunger and of thirst repress'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.3#To watch the foe a trusty spy he sent:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.4#A son of Dolius on the message went,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.5#Stood in the way, and at a glance beheld
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.6#The foe approach, embattled on the field.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.7#With backward step he hastens to the bower,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.8#And tells the news. They arm with all their power.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.9#Four friends alone Ulysses' cause embrace,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.10#And six were all the sons of Dolius' race:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.11#Old Dolius too his rusted arms put on;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.12#And, still more old, in arms Laertes shone.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.13#Trembling with warmth, the hoary heroes stand,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.14#And brazen panoply invests the band.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.15#The opening gates at once their war display:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.16#Fierce they rush forth: Ulysses leads the way.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.17#That moment joins them with celestial aid,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.18#In Mentor's form, the Jove-descended maid:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.19#The suffering hero felt his patient breast
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.33.20#Swell with new joy, and thus his son address'd:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.34.1#"Behold, Telemachus! (nor fear the sight,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.34.2#The brave embattled, the grim front of fight!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.34.3#The valiant with the valiant must contend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.34.4#Shame not the line whence glorious you descend.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.34.5#Wide o'er the world their martial fame was spread;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.34.6#Regard thyself, the living and the dead."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.35.1#"Thy eyes, great father! on this battle cast,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.35.2#Shall learn from me Penelope was chaste."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.36.1#So spoke Telemachus: the gallant boy
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.36.2#Good old Laertes heard with panting joy.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.36.3#"And bless'd! thrice bless'd this happy day! (he cries,)
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.36.4#The day that shows me, ere I close my eyes,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.36.5#A son and grandson of the Arcesian name
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.36.6#Strive for fair virtue, and contest for fame!"
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.1#Then thus Minerva in Laertes' ear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.2#"Son of Arcesius, reverend warrior, hear!
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.3#Jove and Jove's daughter first implore in prayer,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.4#Then, whirling high, discharge thy lance in air."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.5#She said, infusing courage with the word.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.6#Jove and Jove's daughter then the chief implored,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.7#And, whirling high, dismiss'd the lance in air.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.8#Full at Eupithes drove the deathful spear:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.9#The brass-cheek'd helmet opens to the wound;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.10#He falls, earth thunders, and his arms resound.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.11#Before the father and the conquering son
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.12#Heaps rush on heaps, they fight, they drop, they run
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.13#Now by the sword, and now the javelin, fall
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.14#The rebel race, and death had swallow'd all;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.15#But from on high the blue-eyed virgin cried;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.16#Her awful voice detain'd the headlong tide:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.17#"Forbear, ye nations, your mad hands forbear
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.18#From mutual slaughter; Peace descends to spare."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.19#Fear shook the nations: at the voice divine
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.20#They drop their javelins, and their rage resign.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.21#All scatter'd round their glittering weapons lie;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.22#Some fall to earth, and some confusedly fly.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.23#With dreadful shouts Ulysses pour'd along,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.24#Swift as an eagle, as an eagle strong.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.25#But Jove's red arm the burning thunder aims:
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.26#Before Minerva shot the livid flames;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.27#Blazing they fell, and at her feet expired;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.37.28#Then stopped the goddess, trembled and retired.
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.38.1#"Descended from the gods! Ulysses, cease;
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.38.2#Offend not Jove: obey, and give the peace."
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.39.1#So Pallas spoke: the mandate from above
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.39.2#The king obey'd. The virgin-seed of Jove,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.39.3#In Mentor's form, confirm'd the full accord,
urn:cts:fufolio:pope.odyssey.fu2019:24.39.4#And willing nations knew their lawful lord.

